56 /// Handle the result of the special case name lookup for inheriting
57 /// constructor declarations. 'NS::X::X' and 'NS::X<...>::X' are treated as
58 /// constructor names in member using declarations, even if 'X' is not the
59 /// name of the corresponding type.
60 ParsedType Sema::getInheritingConstructorName(CXXScopeSpec &SS,
61  SourceLocation NameLoc,
62  const IdentifierInfo &Name) {
63  NestedNameSpecifier *NNS = SS.getScopeRep();
64 
65  // Convert the nested-name-specifier into a type.
66  QualType Type;
67  switch (NNS->getKind()) {
68  case NestedNameSpecifier::TypeSpec:
69  case NestedNameSpecifier::TypeSpecWithTemplate:
70  Type = QualType(NNS->getAsType(), 0);
71  break;
72 
73  case NestedNameSpecifier::Identifier:
74  // Strip off the last layer of the nested-name-specifier and build a
75  // typename type for it.
76  assert(NNS->getAsIdentifier() == &Name && "not a constructor name");
77  Type = Context.getDependentNameType(
78  ElaboratedTypeKeyword::None, NNS->getPrefix(), NNS->getAsIdentifier());
79  break;
80 
81  case NestedNameSpecifier::Global:
82  case NestedNameSpecifier::Super:
83  case NestedNameSpecifier::Namespace:
84  case NestedNameSpecifier::NamespaceAlias:
85  llvm_unreachable("Nested name specifier is not a type for inheriting ctor");
86  }
87 
88  // This reference to the type is located entirely at the location of the
89  // final identifier in the qualified-id.
90  return CreateParsedType(Type,
91  Context.getTrivialTypeSourceInfo(Type, NameLoc));
92 }
93 
94 ParsedType Sema::getConstructorName(const IdentifierInfo &II,
95  SourceLocation NameLoc, Scope *S,
96  CXXScopeSpec &SS, bool EnteringContext) {
97  CXXRecordDecl *CurClass = getCurrentClass(S, &SS);
98  assert(CurClass && &II == CurClass->getIdentifier() &&
99  "not a constructor name");
100 
101  // When naming a constructor as a member of a dependent context (eg, in a
102  // friend declaration or an inherited constructor declaration), form an
103  // unresolved "typename" type.
104  if (CurClass->isDependentContext() && !EnteringContext && SS.getScopeRep()) {
105  QualType T = Context.getDependentNameType(ElaboratedTypeKeyword::None,
106  SS.getScopeRep(), &II);
107  return ParsedType::make(T);
108  }
109 
110  if (SS.isNotEmpty() && RequireCompleteDeclContext(SS, CurClass))
111  return ParsedType();
112 
113  // Find the injected-class-name declaration. Note that we make no attempt to
114  // diagnose cases where the injected-class-name is shadowed: the only
115  // declaration that can validly shadow the injected-class-name is a
116  // non-static data member, and if the class contains both a non-static data
117  // member and a constructor then it is ill-formed (we check that in
118  // CheckCompletedCXXClass).
119  CXXRecordDecl *InjectedClassName = nullptr;
120  for (NamedDecl *ND : CurClass->lookup(&II)) {
121  auto *RD = dyn_cast<CXXRecordDecl>(ND);
122  if (RD && RD->isInjectedClassName()) {
123  InjectedClassName = RD;
124  break;
125  }
126  }
127  if (!InjectedClassName) {
128  if (!CurClass->isInvalidDecl()) {
129  // FIXME: RequireCompleteDeclContext doesn't check dependent contexts
130  // properly. Work around it here for now.
131  Diag(SS.getLastQualifierNameLoc(),
132  diag::err_incomplete_nested_name_spec) << CurClass << SS.getRange();
133  }
134  return ParsedType();
135  }
136 
137  QualType T = Context.getTypeDeclType(InjectedClassName);
138  DiagnoseUseOfDecl(InjectedClassName, NameLoc);
139  MarkAnyDeclReferenced(NameLoc, InjectedClassName, /*OdrUse=*/false);
140 
141  return ParsedType::make(T);
142 }

144 ParsedType Sema::getDestructorName(const IdentifierInfo &II,
145  SourceLocation NameLoc, Scope *S,
146  CXXScopeSpec &SS, ParsedType ObjectTypePtr,
147  bool EnteringContext) {
148  // Determine where to perform name lookup.
149 
150  // FIXME: This area of the standard is very messy, and the current
151  // wording is rather unclear about which scopes we search for the
152  // destructor name; see core issues 399 and 555. Issue 399 in
153  // particular shows where the current description of destructor name
154  // lookup is completely out of line with existing practice, e.g.,
155  // this appears to be ill-formed:
156  //
157  // namespace N {
158  // template <typename T> struct S {
159  // ~S();
160  // };
161  // }
162  //
163  // void f(N::S<int>* s) {
164  // s->N::S<int>::~S();
165  // }
166  //
167  // See also PR6358 and PR6359.
168  //
169  // For now, we accept all the cases in which the name given could plausibly
170  // be interpreted as a correct destructor name, issuing off-by-default
171  // extension diagnostics on the cases that don't strictly conform to the
172  // C++20 rules. This basically means we always consider looking in the
173  // nested-name-specifier prefix, the complete nested-name-specifier, and
174  // the scope, and accept if we find the expected type in any of the three
175  // places.
176 
177  if (SS.isInvalid())
178  return nullptr;
179 
180  // Whether we've failed with a diagnostic already.
181  bool Failed = false;
182 
183  llvm::SmallVector<NamedDecl*, 8> FoundDecls;
184  llvm::SmallPtrSet<CanonicalDeclPtr<Decl>, 8> FoundDeclSet;
185 
186  // If we have an object type, it's because we are in a
187  // pseudo-destructor-expression or a member access expression, and
188  // we know what type we're looking for.
189  QualType SearchType =
190  ObjectTypePtr ? GetTypeFromParser(ObjectTypePtr) : QualType();
191 
192  auto CheckLookupResult = [&](LookupResult &Found) -> ParsedType {
193  auto IsAcceptableResult = [&](NamedDecl *D) -> bool {
194  auto *Type = dyn_cast<TypeDecl>(D->getUnderlyingDecl());
195  if (!Type)
196  return false;
197 
198  if (SearchType.isNull() || SearchType->isDependentType())
199  return true;
200 
201  QualType T = Context.getTypeDeclType(Type);
202  return Context.hasSameUnqualifiedType(T, SearchType);
203  };
204 
205  unsigned NumAcceptableResults = 0;
206  for (NamedDecl *D : Found) {
207  if (IsAcceptableResult(D))
208  ++NumAcceptableResults;
209 
210  // Don't list a class twice in the lookup failure diagnostic if it's
211  // found by both its injected-class-name and by the name in the enclosing
212  // scope.
213  if (auto *RD = dyn_cast<CXXRecordDecl>(D))
214  if (RD->isInjectedClassName())
215  D = cast<NamedDecl>(RD->getParent());
216 
217  if (FoundDeclSet.insert(D).second)
218  FoundDecls.push_back(D);
219  }
220 
221  // As an extension, attempt to "fix" an ambiguity by erasing all non-type
222  // results, and all non-matching results if we have a search type. It's not
223  // clear what the right behavior is if destructor lookup hits an ambiguity,
224  // but other compilers do generally accept at least some kinds of
225  // ambiguity.
226  if (Found.isAmbiguous() && NumAcceptableResults == 1) {
227  Diag(NameLoc, diag::ext_dtor_name_ambiguous);
228  LookupResult::Filter F = Found.makeFilter();
229  while (F.hasNext()) {
230  NamedDecl *D = F.next();
231  if (auto *TD = dyn_cast<TypeDecl>(D->getUnderlyingDecl()))
232  Diag(D->getLocation(), diag::note_destructor_type_here)
233  << Context.getTypeDeclType(TD);
234  else
235  Diag(D->getLocation(), diag::note_destructor_nontype_here);
236 
237  if (!IsAcceptableResult(D))
238  F.erase();
239  }
240  F.done();
241  }
242 
243  if (Found.isAmbiguous())
244  Failed = true;
245 
246  if (TypeDecl *Type = Found.getAsSingle<TypeDecl>()) {
247  if (IsAcceptableResult(Type)) {
248  QualType T = Context.getTypeDeclType(Type);
249  MarkAnyDeclReferenced(Type->getLocation(), Type, /*OdrUse=*/false);
250  return CreateParsedType(
251  Context.getElaboratedType(ElaboratedTypeKeyword::None, nullptr, T),
252  Context.getTrivialTypeSourceInfo(T, NameLoc));
253  }
254  }
255 
256  return nullptr;
257  };
258 
259  bool IsDependent = false;
260 
261  auto LookupInObjectType = [&]() -> ParsedType {
262  if (Failed || SearchType.isNull())
263  return nullptr;
264 
265  IsDependent |= SearchType->isDependentType();
266 
267  LookupResult Found(*this, &II, NameLoc, LookupDestructorName);
268  DeclContext *LookupCtx = computeDeclContext(SearchType);
269  if (!LookupCtx)
270  return nullptr;
271  LookupQualifiedName(Found, LookupCtx);
272  return CheckLookupResult(Found);
273  };
274 
275  auto LookupInNestedNameSpec = [&](CXXScopeSpec &LookupSS) -> ParsedType {
276  if (Failed)
277  return nullptr;
278 
279  IsDependent |= isDependentScopeSpecifier(LookupSS);
280  DeclContext *LookupCtx = computeDeclContext(LookupSS, EnteringContext);
281  if (!LookupCtx)
282  return nullptr;
283 
284  LookupResult Found(*this, &II, NameLoc, LookupDestructorName);
285  if (RequireCompleteDeclContext(LookupSS, LookupCtx)) {
286  Failed = true;
287  return nullptr;
288  }
289  LookupQualifiedName(Found, LookupCtx);
290  return CheckLookupResult(Found);
291  };
292 
293  auto LookupInScope = [&]() -> ParsedType {
294  if (Failed || !S)
295  return nullptr;
296 
297  LookupResult Found(*this, &II, NameLoc, LookupDestructorName);
298  LookupName(Found, S);
299  return CheckLookupResult(Found);
300  };
301 
302  // C++2a [basic.lookup.qual]p6:
303  // In a qualified-id of the form
304  //
305  // nested-name-specifier[opt] type-name :: ~ type-name
306  //
307  // the second type-name is looked up in the same scope as the first.
308  //
309  // We interpret this as meaning that if you do a dual-scope lookup for the
310  // first name, you also do a dual-scope lookup for the second name, per
311  // C++ [basic.lookup.classref]p4:
312  //
313  // If the id-expression in a class member access is a qualified-id of the
314  // form
315  //
316  // class-name-or-namespace-name :: ...
317  //
318  // the class-name-or-namespace-name following the . or -> is first looked
319  // up in the class of the object expression and the name, if found, is used.
320  // Otherwise, it is looked up in the context of the entire
321  // postfix-expression.
322  //
323  // This looks in the same scopes as for an unqualified destructor name:
324  //
325  // C++ [basic.lookup.classref]p3:
326  // If the unqualified-id is ~ type-name, the type-name is looked up
327  // in the context of the entire postfix-expression. If the type T
328  // of the object expression is of a class type C, the type-name is
329  // also looked up in the scope of class C. At least one of the
330  // lookups shall find a name that refers to cv T.
331  //
332  // FIXME: The intent is unclear here. Should type-name::~type-name look in
333  // the scope anyway if it finds a non-matching name declared in the class?
334  // If both lookups succeed and find a dependent result, which result should
335  // we retain? (Same question for p->~type-name().)
336 
337  if (NestedNameSpecifier *Prefix =
338  SS.isSet() ? SS.getScopeRep()->getPrefix() : nullptr) {
339  // This is
340  //
341  // nested-name-specifier type-name :: ~ type-name
342  //
343  // Look for the second type-name in the nested-name-specifier.
344  CXXScopeSpec PrefixSS;
345  PrefixSS.Adopt(NestedNameSpecifierLoc(Prefix, SS.location_data()));
346  if (ParsedType T = LookupInNestedNameSpec(PrefixSS))
347  return T;
348  } else {
349  // This is one of
350  //
351  // type-name :: ~ type-name
352  // ~ type-name
353  //
354  // Look in the scope and (if any) the object type.
355  if (ParsedType T = LookupInScope())
356  return T;
357  if (ParsedType T = LookupInObjectType())
358  return T;
359  }
360 
361  if (Failed)
362  return nullptr;
363 
364  if (IsDependent) {
365  // We didn't find our type, but that's OK: it's dependent anyway.
366 
367  // FIXME: What if we have no nested-name-specifier?
368  QualType T =
369  CheckTypenameType(ElaboratedTypeKeyword::None, SourceLocation(),
370  SS.getWithLocInContext(Context), II, NameLoc);
371  return ParsedType::make(T);
372  }
373 
374  // The remaining cases are all non-standard extensions imitating the behavior
375  // of various other compilers.
376  unsigned NumNonExtensionDecls = FoundDecls.size();
377 
378  if (SS.isSet()) {
379  // For compatibility with older broken C++ rules and existing code,
380  //
381  // nested-name-specifier :: ~ type-name
382  //
383  // also looks for type-name within the nested-name-specifier.
384  if (ParsedType T = LookupInNestedNameSpec(SS)) {
385  Diag(SS.getEndLoc(), diag::ext_dtor_named_in_wrong_scope)
386  << SS.getRange()
387  << FixItHint::CreateInsertion(SS.getEndLoc(),
388  ("::" + II.getName()).str());
389  return T;
390  }
391 
392  // For compatibility with other compilers and older versions of Clang,
393  //
394  // nested-name-specifier type-name :: ~ type-name
395  //
396  // also looks for type-name in the scope. Unfortunately, we can't
397  // reasonably apply this fallback for dependent nested-name-specifiers.
398  if (SS.isValid() && SS.getScopeRep()->getPrefix()) {
399  if (ParsedType T = LookupInScope()) {
400  Diag(SS.getEndLoc(), diag::ext_qualified_dtor_named_in_lexical_scope)
401  << FixItHint::CreateRemoval(SS.getRange());
402  Diag(FoundDecls.back()->getLocation(), diag::note_destructor_type_here)
403  << GetTypeFromParser(T);
404  return T;
405  }
406  }
407  }
408 
409  // We didn't find anything matching; tell the user what we did find (if
410  // anything).
411 
412  // Don't tell the user about declarations we shouldn't have found.
413  FoundDecls.resize(NumNonExtensionDecls);
414 
415  // List types before non-types.
416  std::stable_sort(FoundDecls.begin(), FoundDecls.end(),
417  [](NamedDecl *A, NamedDecl *B) {
418  return isa<TypeDecl>(A->getUnderlyingDecl()) >
419  isa<TypeDecl>(B->getUnderlyingDecl());
420  });
421 
422  // Suggest a fixit to properly name the destroyed type.
423  auto MakeFixItHint = [&]{
424  const CXXRecordDecl *Destroyed = nullptr;
425  // FIXME: If we have a scope specifier, suggest its last component?
426  if (!SearchType.isNull())
427  Destroyed = SearchType->getAsCXXRecordDecl();
428  else if (S)
429  Destroyed = dyn_cast_or_null<CXXRecordDecl>(S->getEntity());
430  if (Destroyed)
431  return FixItHint::CreateReplacement(SourceRange(NameLoc),
432  Destroyed->getNameAsString());
433  return FixItHint();
434  };
435 
436  if (FoundDecls.empty()) {
437  // FIXME: Attempt typo-correction?
438  Diag(NameLoc, diag::err_undeclared_destructor_name)
439  << &II << MakeFixItHint();
440  } else if (!SearchType.isNull() && FoundDecls.size() == 1) {
441  if (auto *TD = dyn_cast<TypeDecl>(FoundDecls[0]->getUnderlyingDecl())) {
442  assert(!SearchType.isNull() &&
443  "should only reject a type result if we have a search type");
444  QualType T = Context.getTypeDeclType(TD);
445  Diag(NameLoc, diag::err_destructor_expr_type_mismatch)
446  << T << SearchType << MakeFixItHint();
447  } else {
448  Diag(NameLoc, diag::err_destructor_expr_nontype)
449  << &II << MakeFixItHint();
450  }
451  } else {
452  Diag(NameLoc, SearchType.isNull() ? diag::err_destructor_name_nontype
453  : diag::err_destructor_expr_mismatch)
454  << &II << SearchType << MakeFixItHint();
455  }
456 
457  for (NamedDecl *FoundD : FoundDecls) {
458  if (auto *TD = dyn_cast<TypeDecl>(FoundD->getUnderlyingDecl()))
459  Diag(FoundD->getLocation(), diag::note_destructor_type_here)
460  << Context.getTypeDeclType(TD);
461  else
462  Diag(FoundD->getLocation(), diag::note_destructor_nontype_here)
463  << FoundD;
464  }
465 
466  return nullptr;
467 }
468 
469 ParsedType Sema::getDestructorTypeForDecltype(const DeclSpec &DS,
470  ParsedType ObjectType) {
471  if (DS.getTypeSpecType() == DeclSpec::TST_error)
472  return nullptr;
473 
474  if (DS.getTypeSpecType() == DeclSpec::TST_decltype_auto) {
475  Diag(DS.getTypeSpecTypeLoc(), diag::err_decltype_auto_invalid);
476  return nullptr;
477  }
478 
479  assert(DS.getTypeSpecType() == DeclSpec::TST_decltype &&
480  "unexpected type in getDestructorType");
481  QualType T = BuildDecltypeType(DS.getRepAsExpr());
482 
483  // If we know the type of the object, check that the correct destructor
484  // type was named now; we can give better diagnostics this way.
485  QualType SearchType = GetTypeFromParser(ObjectType);
486  if (!SearchType.isNull() && !SearchType->isDependentType() &&
487  !Context.hasSameUnqualifiedType(T, SearchType)) {
488  Diag(DS.getTypeSpecTypeLoc(), diag::err_destructor_expr_type_mismatch)
489  << T << SearchType;
490  return nullptr;
491  }
492 
493  return ParsedType::make(T);
494 }
495 
496 bool Sema::checkLiteralOperatorId(const CXXScopeSpec &SS,
497  const UnqualifiedId &Name, bool IsUDSuffix) {
498  assert(Name.getKind() == UnqualifiedIdKind::IK_LiteralOperatorId);
499  if (!IsUDSuffix) {
500  // [over.literal] p8
501  //
502  // double operator""_Bq(long double); // OK: not a reserved identifier
503  // double operator"" _Bq(long double); // ill-formed, no diagnostic required
504  const IdentifierInfo *II = Name.Identifier;
505  ReservedIdentifierStatus Status = II->isReserved(PP.getLangOpts());
506  SourceLocation Loc = Name.getEndLoc();
507  if (!PP.getSourceManager().isInSystemHeader(Loc)) {
508  if (auto Hint = FixItHint::CreateReplacement(
509  Name.getSourceRange(),
510  (StringRef("operator\"\"") + II->getName()).str());
511  isReservedInAllContexts(Status)) {
512  Diag(Loc, diag::warn_reserved_extern_symbol)
513  << II << static_cast<int>(Status) << Hint;
514  } else {
515  Diag(Loc, diag::warn_deprecated_literal_operator_id) << II << Hint;
516  }
517  }
518  }
519 
520  if (!SS.isValid())
521  return false;
522 
523  switch (SS.getScopeRep()->getKind()) {
524  case NestedNameSpecifier::Identifier:
525  case NestedNameSpecifier::TypeSpec:
526  case NestedNameSpecifier::TypeSpecWithTemplate:
527  // Per C++11 [over.literal]p2, literal operators can only be declared at
528  // namespace scope. Therefore, this unqualified-id cannot name anything.
529  // Reject it early, because we have no AST representation for this in the
530  // case where the scope is dependent.
531  Diag(Name.getBeginLoc(), diag::err_literal_operator_id_outside_namespace)
532  << SS.getScopeRep();
533  return true;
534 
535  case NestedNameSpecifier::Global:
536  case NestedNameSpecifier::Super:
537  case NestedNameSpecifier::Namespace:
538  case NestedNameSpecifier::NamespaceAlias:
539  return false;
540  }
541 
542  llvm_unreachable("unknown nested name specifier kind");
543 }
544 
545 /// Build a C++ typeid expression with a type operand.
546 ExprResult Sema::BuildCXXTypeId(QualType TypeInfoType,
547  SourceLocation TypeidLoc,
548  TypeSourceInfo *Operand,
549  SourceLocation RParenLoc) {
550  // C++ [expr.typeid]p4:
551  // The top-level cv-qualifiers of the lvalue expression or the type-id
552  // that is the operand of typeid are always ignored.
553  // If the type of the type-id is a class type or a reference to a class
554  // type, the class shall be completely-defined.
555  Qualifiers Quals;
556  QualType T
557  = Context.getUnqualifiedArrayType(Operand->getType().getNonReferenceType(),
558  Quals);
559  if (T->getAs<RecordType>() &&
560  RequireCompleteType(TypeidLoc, T, diag::err_incomplete_typeid))
561  return ExprError();
562 
563  if (T->isVariablyModifiedType())
564  return ExprError(Diag(TypeidLoc, diag::err_variably_modified_typeid) << T);
565 
566  if (CheckQualifiedFunctionForTypeId(T, TypeidLoc))
567  return ExprError();
568 
569  return new (Context) CXXTypeidExpr(TypeInfoType.withConst(), Operand,
570  SourceRange(TypeidLoc, RParenLoc));
571 }
572 
573 /// Build a C++ typeid expression with an expression operand.
574 ExprResult Sema::BuildCXXTypeId(QualType TypeInfoType,
575  SourceLocation TypeidLoc,
576  Expr *E,
577  SourceLocation RParenLoc) {
578  bool WasEvaluated = false;
579  if (E && !E->isTypeDependent()) {
580  if (E->hasPlaceholderType()) {
581  ExprResult result = CheckPlaceholderExpr(E);
582  if (result.isInvalid()) return ExprError();
583  E = result.get();
584  }
585 
586  QualType T = E->getType();
587  if (const RecordType *RecordT = T->getAs<RecordType>()) {
588  CXXRecordDecl *RecordD = cast<CXXRecordDecl>(RecordT->getDecl());
589  // C++ [expr.typeid]p3:
590  // [...] If the type of the expression is a class type, the class
591  // shall be completely-defined.
592  if (RequireCompleteType(TypeidLoc, T, diag::err_incomplete_typeid))
593  return ExprError();
594 
595  // C++ [expr.typeid]p3:
596  // When typeid is applied to an expression other than an glvalue of a
597  // polymorphic class type [...] [the] expression is an unevaluated
598  // operand. [...]
599  if (RecordD->isPolymorphic() && E->isGLValue()) {
600  if (isUnevaluatedContext()) {
601  // The operand was processed in unevaluated context, switch the
602  // context and recheck the subexpression.
603  ExprResult Result = TransformToPotentiallyEvaluated(E);
604  if (Result.isInvalid())
605  return ExprError();
606  E = Result.get();
607  }
608 
609  // We require a vtable to query the type at run time.
610  MarkVTableUsed(TypeidLoc, RecordD);
611  WasEvaluated = true;
612  }
613  }
614 
615  ExprResult Result = CheckUnevaluatedOperand(E);
616  if (Result.isInvalid())
617  return ExprError();
618  E = Result.get();
619 
620  // C++ [expr.typeid]p4:
621  // [...] If the type of the type-id is a reference to a possibly
622  // cv-qualified type, the result of the typeid expression refers to a
623  // std::type_info object representing the cv-unqualified referenced
624  // type.
625  Qualifiers Quals;
626  QualType UnqualT = Context.getUnqualifiedArrayType(T, Quals);
627  if (!Context.hasSameType(T, UnqualT)) {
628  T = UnqualT;
629  E = ImpCastExprToType(E, UnqualT, CK_NoOp, E->getValueKind()).get();
630  }
631  }
632 
633  if (E->getType()->isVariablyModifiedType())
634  return ExprError(Diag(TypeidLoc, diag::err_variably_modified_typeid)
635  << E->getType());
636  else if (!inTemplateInstantiation() &&
637  E->HasSideEffects(Context, WasEvaluated)) {
638  // The expression operand for typeid is in an unevaluated expression
639  // context, so side effects could result in unintended consequences.
640  Diag(E->getExprLoc(), WasEvaluated
641  ? diag::warn_side_effects_typeid
642  : diag::warn_side_effects_unevaluated_context);
643  }
644 
645  return new (Context) CXXTypeidExpr(TypeInfoType.withConst(), E,
646  SourceRange(TypeidLoc, RParenLoc));
647 }
648 
649 /// ActOnCXXTypeidOfType - Parse typeid( type-id ) or typeid (expression);
650 ExprResult
651 Sema::ActOnCXXTypeid(SourceLocation OpLoc, SourceLocation LParenLoc,
652  bool isType, void *TyOrExpr, SourceLocation RParenLoc) {
653  // typeid is not supported in OpenCL.
654  if (getLangOpts().OpenCLCPlusPlus) {
655  return ExprError(Diag(OpLoc, diag::err_openclcxx_not_supported)
656  << "typeid");
657  }
658 
659  // Find the std::type_info type.
660  if (!getStdNamespace())
661  return ExprError(Diag(OpLoc, diag::err_need_header_before_typeid));
662 
663  if (!CXXTypeInfoDecl) {
664  IdentifierInfo *TypeInfoII = &PP.getIdentifierTable().get("type_info");
665  LookupResult R(*this, TypeInfoII, SourceLocation(), LookupTagName);
666  LookupQualifiedName(R, getStdNamespace());
667  CXXTypeInfoDecl = R.getAsSingle<RecordDecl>();
668  // Microsoft's typeinfo doesn't have type_info in std but in the global
669  // namespace if _HAS_EXCEPTIONS is defined to 0. See PR13153.
670  if (!CXXTypeInfoDecl && LangOpts.MSVCCompat) {
671  LookupQualifiedName(R, Context.getTranslationUnitDecl());
672  CXXTypeInfoDecl = R.getAsSingle<RecordDecl>();
673  }
674  if (!CXXTypeInfoDecl)
675  return ExprError(Diag(OpLoc, diag::err_need_header_before_typeid));
676  }
677 
678  if (!getLangOpts().RTTI) {
679  return ExprError(Diag(OpLoc, diag::err_no_typeid_with_fno_rtti));
680  }
681 
682  QualType TypeInfoType = Context.getTypeDeclType(CXXTypeInfoDecl);
683 
684  if (isType) {
685  // The operand is a type; handle it as such.
686  TypeSourceInfo *TInfo = nullptr;
687  QualType T = GetTypeFromParser(ParsedType::getFromOpaquePtr(TyOrExpr),
688  &TInfo);
689  if (T.isNull())
690  return ExprError();
691 
692  if (!TInfo)
693  TInfo = Context.getTrivialTypeSourceInfo(T, OpLoc);
694 
695  return BuildCXXTypeId(TypeInfoType, OpLoc, TInfo, RParenLoc);
696  }
697 
698  // The operand is an expression.
699  ExprResult Result =
700  BuildCXXTypeId(TypeInfoType, OpLoc, (Expr *)TyOrExpr, RParenLoc);
701 
702  if (!getLangOpts().RTTIData && !Result.isInvalid())
703  if (auto *CTE = dyn_cast<CXXTypeidExpr>(Result.get()))
704  if (CTE->isPotentiallyEvaluated() && !CTE->isMostDerived(Context))
705  Diag(OpLoc, diag::warn_no_typeid_with_rtti_disabled)
706  << (getDiagnostics().getDiagnosticOptions().getFormat() ==
707  DiagnosticOptions::MSVC);
708  return Result;
709 }
710 
711 /// Grabs __declspec(uuid()) off a type, or returns 0 if we cannot resolve to
712 /// a single GUID.
713 static void
714 getUuidAttrOfType(Sema &SemaRef, QualType QT,
715  llvm::SmallSetVector<const UuidAttr *, 1> &UuidAttrs) {
716  // Optionally remove one level of pointer, reference or array indirection.
717  const Type *Ty = QT.getTypePtr();
718  if (QT->isPointerType() || QT->isReferenceType())
719  Ty = QT->getPointeeType().getTypePtr();
720  else if (QT->isArrayType())
721  Ty = Ty->getBaseElementTypeUnsafe();
722 
723  const auto *TD = Ty->getAsTagDecl();
724  if (!TD)
725  return;
726 
727  if (const auto *Uuid = TD->getMostRecentDecl()->getAttr<UuidAttr>()) {
728  UuidAttrs.insert(Uuid);
729  return;
730  }
731 
732  // __uuidof can grab UUIDs from template arguments.
733  if (const auto *CTSD = dyn_cast<ClassTemplateSpecializationDecl>(TD)) {
734  const TemplateArgumentList &TAL = CTSD->getTemplateArgs();
735  for (const TemplateArgument &TA : TAL.asArray()) {
736  const UuidAttr *UuidForTA = nullptr;
737  if (TA.getKind() == TemplateArgument::Type)
738  getUuidAttrOfType(SemaRef, TA.getAsType(), UuidAttrs);
739  else if (TA.getKind() == TemplateArgument::Declaration)
740  getUuidAttrOfType(SemaRef, TA.getAsDecl()->getType(), UuidAttrs);
741 
742  if (UuidForTA)
743  UuidAttrs.insert(UuidForTA);
744  }
745  }
746 }
747 
748 /// Build a Microsoft __uuidof expression with a type operand.
749 ExprResult Sema::BuildCXXUuidof(QualType Type,
750  SourceLocation TypeidLoc,
751  TypeSourceInfo *Operand,
752  SourceLocation RParenLoc) {
753  MSGuidDecl *Guid = nullptr;
754  if (!Operand->getType()->isDependentType()) {
755  llvm::SmallSetVector<const UuidAttr *, 1> UuidAttrs;
756  getUuidAttrOfType(*this, Operand->getType(), UuidAttrs);
757  if (UuidAttrs.empty())
758  return ExprError(Diag(TypeidLoc, diag::err_uuidof_without_guid));
759  if (UuidAttrs.size() > 1)
760  return ExprError(Diag(TypeidLoc, diag::err_uuidof_with_multiple_guids));
761  Guid = UuidAttrs.back()->getGuidDecl();
762  }
763 
764  return new (Context)
765  CXXUuidofExpr(Type, Operand, Guid, SourceRange(TypeidLoc, RParenLoc));
766 }
767 
768 /// Build a Microsoft __uuidof expression with an expression operand.
769 ExprResult Sema::BuildCXXUuidof(QualType Type, SourceLocation TypeidLoc,
770  Expr *E, SourceLocation RParenLoc) {
771  MSGuidDecl *Guid = nullptr;
772  if (!E->getType()->isDependentType()) {
773  if (E->isNullPointerConstant(Context, Expr::NPC_ValueDependentIsNull)) {
774  // A null pointer results in {00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000}.
775  Guid = Context.getMSGuidDecl(MSGuidDecl::Parts{});
776  } else {
777  llvm::SmallSetVector<const UuidAttr *, 1> UuidAttrs;
778  getUuidAttrOfType(*this, E->getType(), UuidAttrs);
779  if (UuidAttrs.empty())
780  return ExprError(Diag(TypeidLoc, diag::err_uuidof_without_guid));
781  if (UuidAttrs.size() > 1)
782  return ExprError(Diag(TypeidLoc, diag::err_uuidof_with_multiple_guids));
783  Guid = UuidAttrs.back()->getGuidDecl();
784  }
785  }
786 
787  return new (Context)
788  CXXUuidofExpr(Type, E, Guid, SourceRange(TypeidLoc, RParenLoc));
789 }
790 
791 /// ActOnCXXUuidof - Parse __uuidof( type-id ) or __uuidof (expression);
792 ExprResult
793 Sema::ActOnCXXUuidof(SourceLocation OpLoc, SourceLocation LParenLoc,
794  bool isType, void *TyOrExpr, SourceLocation RParenLoc) {
795  QualType GuidType = Context.getMSGuidType();
796  GuidType.addConst();
797 
798  if (isType) {
799  // The operand is a type; handle it as such.
800  TypeSourceInfo *TInfo = nullptr;
801  QualType T = GetTypeFromParser(ParsedType::getFromOpaquePtr(TyOrExpr),
802  &TInfo);
803  if (T.isNull())
804  return ExprError();
805 
806  if (!TInfo)
807  TInfo = Context.getTrivialTypeSourceInfo(T, OpLoc);
808 
809  return BuildCXXUuidof(GuidType, OpLoc, TInfo, RParenLoc);
810  }
811 
812  // The operand is an expression.
813  return BuildCXXUuidof(GuidType, OpLoc, (Expr*)TyOrExpr, RParenLoc);
814 }

817 ExprResult
818 Sema::ActOnCXXBoolLiteral(SourceLocation OpLoc, tok::TokenKind Kind) {
819  assert((Kind == tok::kw_true || Kind == tok::kw_false) &&
820  "Unknown C++ Boolean value!");

822  CXXBoolLiteralExpr(Kind == tok::kw_true, Context.BoolTy, OpLoc);

831 /// ActOnCXXThrow - Parse throw expressions.
832 ExprResult
833 Sema::ActOnCXXThrow(Scope *S, SourceLocation OpLoc, Expr *Ex) {
834  bool IsThrownVarInScope = false;
835  if (Ex) {
836  // C++0x [class.copymove]p31:
837  // When certain criteria are met, an implementation is allowed to omit the
838  // copy/move construction of a class object [...]
839  //
840  // - in a throw-expression, when the operand is the name of a
841  // non-volatile automatic object (other than a function or catch-
842  // clause parameter) whose scope does not extend beyond the end of the
843  // innermost enclosing try-block (if there is one), the copy/move
844  // operation from the operand to the exception object (15.1) can be
845  // omitted by constructing the automatic object directly into the
846  // exception object
847  if (const auto *DRE = dyn_cast<DeclRefExpr>(Ex->IgnoreParens()))
848  if (const auto *Var = dyn_cast<VarDecl>(DRE->getDecl());
849  Var && Var->hasLocalStorage() &&
850  !Var->getType().isVolatileQualified()) {
851  for (; S; S = S->getParent()) {
852  if (S->isDeclScope(Var)) {
853  IsThrownVarInScope = true;
854  break;
855  }
856 
857  // FIXME: Many of the scope checks here seem incorrect.
858  if (S->getFlags() &
859  (Scope::FnScope | Scope::ClassScope | Scope::BlockScope |
860  Scope::ObjCMethodScope | Scope::TryScope))
861  break;
862  }
863  }
864  }
865 
866  return BuildCXXThrow(OpLoc, Ex, IsThrownVarInScope);
867 }
868 
869 ExprResult Sema::BuildCXXThrow(SourceLocation OpLoc, Expr *Ex,
870  bool IsThrownVarInScope) {
871  const llvm::Triple &T = Context.getTargetInfo().getTriple();
872  const bool IsOpenMPGPUTarget =
873  getLangOpts().OpenMPIsTargetDevice && (T.isNVPTX() || T.isAMDGCN());
874  // Don't report an error if 'throw' is used in system headers or in an OpenMP
875  // target region compiled for a GPU architecture.
876  if (!IsOpenMPGPUTarget && !getLangOpts().CXXExceptions &&
877  !getSourceManager().isInSystemHeader(OpLoc) && !getLangOpts().CUDA) {
878  // Delay error emission for the OpenMP device code.
879  targetDiag(OpLoc, diag::err_exceptions_disabled) << "throw";
880  }
881 
882  // In OpenMP target regions, we replace 'throw' with a trap on GPU targets.
883  if (IsOpenMPGPUTarget)
884  targetDiag(OpLoc, diag::warn_throw_not_valid_on_target) << T.str();
885 
886  // Exceptions aren't allowed in CUDA device code.
887  if (getLangOpts().CUDA)
888  CUDA().DiagIfDeviceCode(OpLoc, diag::err_cuda_device_exceptions)
889  << "throw" << llvm::to_underlying(CUDA().CurrentTarget());
890 
891  // Exceptions aren't allowed in SYCL device code.
892  if (getLangOpts().SYCLIsDevice)
893  SYCL().DiagIfDeviceCode(OpLoc, diag::err_sycl_restrict)
894  << SemaSYCL::KernelUseExceptions;
895 
896  if (getCurScope() && getCurScope()->isOpenMPSimdDirectiveScope())
897  Diag(OpLoc, diag::err_omp_simd_region_cannot_use_stmt) << "throw";
898 
899  // Exceptions that escape a compute construct are ill-formed.
900  if (getLangOpts().OpenACC && getCurScope() &&
901  getCurScope()->isInOpenACCComputeConstructScope(Scope::TryScope))
902  Diag(OpLoc, diag::err_acc_branch_in_out_compute_construct)
903  << /*throw*/ 2 << /*out of*/ 0;
904 
905  if (Ex && !Ex->isTypeDependent()) {
906  // Initialize the exception result. This implicitly weeds out
907  // abstract types or types with inaccessible copy constructors.
908 
909  // C++0x [class.copymove]p31:
910  // When certain criteria are met, an implementation is allowed to omit the
911  // copy/move construction of a class object [...]
912  //
913  // - in a throw-expression, when the operand is the name of a
914  // non-volatile automatic object (other than a function or
915  // catch-clause
916  // parameter) whose scope does not extend beyond the end of the
917  // innermost enclosing try-block (if there is one), the copy/move
918  // operation from the operand to the exception object (15.1) can be
919  // omitted by constructing the automatic object directly into the
920  // exception object
921  NamedReturnInfo NRInfo =
922  IsThrownVarInScope ? getNamedReturnInfo(Ex) : NamedReturnInfo();
923 
924  QualType ExceptionObjectTy = Context.getExceptionObjectType(Ex->getType());
925  if (CheckCXXThrowOperand(OpLoc, ExceptionObjectTy, Ex))
926  return ExprError();
927 
928  InitializedEntity Entity =
929  InitializedEntity::InitializeException(OpLoc, ExceptionObjectTy);
930  ExprResult Res = PerformMoveOrCopyInitialization(Entity, NRInfo, Ex);
931  if (Res.isInvalid())
932  return ExprError();
933  Ex = Res.get();
934  }
935 
936  // PPC MMA non-pointer types are not allowed as throw expr types.
937  if (Ex && Context.getTargetInfo().getTriple().isPPC64())
938  CheckPPCMMAType(Ex->getType(), Ex->getBeginLoc());
939 
940  return new (Context)
941  CXXThrowExpr(Ex, Context.VoidTy, OpLoc, IsThrownVarInScope);
942 }
943 
944 static void
945 collectPublicBases(CXXRecordDecl *RD,
946  llvm::DenseMap<CXXRecordDecl *, unsigned> &SubobjectsSeen,
947  llvm::SmallPtrSetImpl<CXXRecordDecl *> &VBases,
948  llvm::SetVector<CXXRecordDecl *> &PublicSubobjectsSeen,
949  bool ParentIsPublic) {
950  for (const CXXBaseSpecifier &BS : RD->bases()) {
951  CXXRecordDecl *BaseDecl = BS.getType()->getAsCXXRecordDecl();
952  bool NewSubobject;
953  // Virtual bases constitute the same subobject. Non-virtual bases are
954  // always distinct subobjects.
955  if (BS.isVirtual())
956  NewSubobject = VBases.insert(BaseDecl).second;
957  else
958  NewSubobject = true;
959 
960  if (NewSubobject)
961  ++SubobjectsSeen[BaseDecl];
962 
963  // Only add subobjects which have public access throughout the entire chain.
964  bool PublicPath = ParentIsPublic && BS.getAccessSpecifier() == AS_public;
965  if (PublicPath)
966  PublicSubobjectsSeen.insert(BaseDecl);
967 
968  // Recurse on to each base subobject.
969  collectPublicBases(BaseDecl, SubobjectsSeen, VBases, PublicSubobjectsSeen,
970  PublicPath);
971  }
972 }
973 
974 static void getUnambiguousPublicSubobjects(
975  CXXRecordDecl *RD, llvm::SmallVectorImpl<CXXRecordDecl *> &Objects) {
976  llvm::DenseMap<CXXRecordDecl *, unsigned> SubobjectsSeen;
977  llvm::SmallSet<CXXRecordDecl *, 2> VBases;
978  llvm::SetVector<CXXRecordDecl *> PublicSubobjectsSeen;
979  SubobjectsSeen[RD] = 1;
980  PublicSubobjectsSeen.insert(RD);
981  collectPublicBases(RD, SubobjectsSeen, VBases, PublicSubobjectsSeen,
982  /*ParentIsPublic=*/true);
983 
984  for (CXXRecordDecl *PublicSubobject : PublicSubobjectsSeen) {
985  // Skip ambiguous objects.
986  if (SubobjectsSeen[PublicSubobject] > 1)
987  continue;
988 
989  Objects.push_back(PublicSubobject);
990  }
991 }
992 
993 /// CheckCXXThrowOperand - Validate the operand of a throw.
994 bool Sema::CheckCXXThrowOperand(SourceLocation ThrowLoc,
995  QualType ExceptionObjectTy, Expr *E) {
996  // If the type of the exception would be an incomplete type or a pointer
997  // to an incomplete type other than (cv) void the program is ill-formed.
998  QualType Ty = ExceptionObjectTy;
999  bool isPointer = false;
1000  if (const PointerType* Ptr = Ty->getAs<PointerType>()) {
1001  Ty = Ptr->getPointeeType();
1002  isPointer = true;
1003  }
1004 
1005  // Cannot throw WebAssembly reference type.
1006  if (Ty.isWebAssemblyReferenceType()) {
1007  Diag(ThrowLoc, diag::err_wasm_reftype_tc) << 0 << E->getSourceRange();
1008  return true;
1009  }
1010 
1011  // Cannot throw WebAssembly table.
1012  if (isPointer && Ty.isWebAssemblyReferenceType()) {
1013  Diag(ThrowLoc, diag::err_wasm_table_art) << 2 << E->getSourceRange();
1014  return true;
1015  }
1016 
1017  if (!isPointer || !Ty->isVoidType()) {
1018  if (RequireCompleteType(ThrowLoc, Ty,
1019  isPointer ? diag::err_throw_incomplete_ptr
1020  : diag::err_throw_incomplete,
1021  E->getSourceRange()))
1022  return true;
1023 
1024  if (!isPointer && Ty->isSizelessType()) {
1025  Diag(ThrowLoc, diag::err_throw_sizeless) << Ty << E->getSourceRange();
1026  return true;
1027  }
1028 
1029  if (RequireNonAbstractType(ThrowLoc, ExceptionObjectTy,
1030  diag::err_throw_abstract_type, E))
1031  return true;
1032  }
1033 
1034  // If the exception has class type, we need additional handling.
1035  CXXRecordDecl *RD = Ty->getAsCXXRecordDecl();
1036  if (!RD)
1037  return false;
1038 
1039  // If we are throwing a polymorphic class type or pointer thereof,
1040  // exception handling will make use of the vtable.
1041  MarkVTableUsed(ThrowLoc, RD);
1042 
1043  // If a pointer is thrown, the referenced object will not be destroyed.
1044  if (isPointer)
1045  return false;
1046 
1047  // If the class has a destructor, we must be able to call it.
1048  if (!RD->hasIrrelevantDestructor()) {
1049  if (CXXDestructorDecl *Destructor = LookupDestructor(RD)) {
1050  MarkFunctionReferenced(E->getExprLoc(), Destructor);
1051  CheckDestructorAccess(E->getExprLoc(), Destructor,
1052  PDiag(diag::err_access_dtor_exception) << Ty);
1053  if (DiagnoseUseOfDecl(Destructor, E->getExprLoc()))
1054  return true;
1055  }
1056  }
1057 
1058  // The MSVC ABI creates a list of all types which can catch the exception
1059  // object. This list also references the appropriate copy constructor to call
1060  // if the object is caught by value and has a non-trivial copy constructor.
1061  if (Context.getTargetInfo().getCXXABI().isMicrosoft()) {
1062  // We are only interested in the public, unambiguous bases contained within
1063  // the exception object. Bases which are ambiguous or otherwise
1064  // inaccessible are not catchable types.
1065  llvm::SmallVector<CXXRecordDecl *, 2> UnambiguousPublicSubobjects;
1066  getUnambiguousPublicSubobjects(RD, UnambiguousPublicSubobjects);
1067 
1068  for (CXXRecordDecl *Subobject : UnambiguousPublicSubobjects) {
1069  // Attempt to lookup the copy constructor. Various pieces of machinery
1070  // will spring into action, like template instantiation, which means this
1071  // cannot be a simple walk of the class's decls. Instead, we must perform
1072  // lookup and overload resolution.
1073  CXXConstructorDecl *CD = LookupCopyingConstructor(Subobject, 0);
1074  if (!CD || CD->isDeleted())
1075  continue;
1076 
1077  // Mark the constructor referenced as it is used by this throw expression.
1078  MarkFunctionReferenced(E->getExprLoc(), CD);
1079 
1080  // Skip this copy constructor if it is trivial, we don't need to record it
1081  // in the catchable type data.
1082  if (CD->isTrivial())
1083  continue;
1084 
1085  // The copy constructor is non-trivial, create a mapping from this class
1086  // type to this constructor.
1087  // N.B. The selection of copy constructor is not sensitive to this
1088  // particular throw-site. Lookup will be performed at the catch-site to
1089  // ensure that the copy constructor is, in fact, accessible (via
1090  // friendship or any other means).
1091  Context.addCopyConstructorForExceptionObject(Subobject, CD);
1092 
1093  // We don't keep the instantiated default argument expressions around so
1094  // we must rebuild them here.
1095  for (unsigned I = 1, E = CD->getNumParams(); I != E; ++I) {
1096  if (CheckCXXDefaultArgExpr(ThrowLoc, CD, CD->getParamDecl(I)))
1097  return true;
1098  }
1099  }
1100  }
1101 
1102  // Under the Itanium C++ ABI, memory for the exception object is allocated by
1103  // the runtime with no ability for the compiler to request additional
1104  // alignment. Warn if the exception type requires alignment beyond the minimum
1105  // guaranteed by the target C++ runtime.
1106  if (Context.getTargetInfo().getCXXABI().isItaniumFamily()) {
1107  CharUnits TypeAlign = Context.getTypeAlignInChars(Ty);
1108  CharUnits ExnObjAlign = Context.getExnObjectAlignment();
1109  if (ExnObjAlign < TypeAlign) {
1110  Diag(ThrowLoc, diag::warn_throw_underaligned_obj);
1111  Diag(ThrowLoc, diag::note_throw_underaligned_obj)
1112  << Ty << (unsigned)TypeAlign.getQuantity()
1113  << (unsigned)ExnObjAlign.getQuantity();
1114  }
1115  }
1116  if (!isPointer && getLangOpts().AssumeNothrowExceptionDtor) {
1117  if (CXXDestructorDecl *Dtor = RD->getDestructor()) {
1118  auto Ty = Dtor->getType();
1119  if (auto *FT = Ty.getTypePtr()->getAs<FunctionProtoType>()) {
1120  if (!isUnresolvedExceptionSpec(FT->getExceptionSpecType()) &&
1121  !FT->isNothrow())
1122  Diag(ThrowLoc, diag::err_throw_object_throwing_dtor) << RD;
1123  }
1124  }
1125  }
1126 
1127  return false;
1128 }
1129 
1130 static QualType adjustCVQualifiersForCXXThisWithinLambda(
1131  ArrayRef<FunctionScopeInfo *> FunctionScopes, QualType ThisTy,
1132  DeclContext *CurSemaContext, ASTContext &ASTCtx) {
1133 
1134  QualType ClassType = ThisTy->getPointeeType();
1135  LambdaScopeInfo *CurLSI = nullptr;
1136  DeclContext *CurDC = CurSemaContext;
1137 
1138  // Iterate through the stack of lambdas starting from the innermost lambda to
1139  // the outermost lambda, checking if '*this' is ever captured by copy - since
1140  // that could change the cv-qualifiers of the '*this' object.
1141  // The object referred to by '*this' starts out with the cv-qualifiers of its
1142  // member function. We then start with the innermost lambda and iterate
1143  // outward checking to see if any lambda performs a by-copy capture of '*this'
1144  // - and if so, any nested lambda must respect the 'constness' of that
1145  // capturing lamdbda's call operator.
1146  //
1147 
1148  // Since the FunctionScopeInfo stack is representative of the lexical
1149  // nesting of the lambda expressions during initial parsing (and is the best
1150  // place for querying information about captures about lambdas that are
1151  // partially processed) and perhaps during instantiation of function templates
1152  // that contain lambda expressions that need to be transformed BUT not
1153  // necessarily during instantiation of a nested generic lambda's function call
1154  // operator (which might even be instantiated at the end of the TU) - at which
1155  // time the DeclContext tree is mature enough to query capture information
1156  // reliably - we use a two pronged approach to walk through all the lexically
1157  // enclosing lambda expressions:
1158  //
1159  // 1) Climb down the FunctionScopeInfo stack as long as each item represents
1160  // a Lambda (i.e. LambdaScopeInfo) AND each LSI's 'closure-type' is lexically
1161  // enclosed by the call-operator of the LSI below it on the stack (while
1162  // tracking the enclosing DC for step 2 if needed). Note the topmost LSI on
1163  // the stack represents the innermost lambda.
1164  //
1165  // 2) If we run out of enclosing LSI's, check if the enclosing DeclContext
1166  // represents a lambda's call operator. If it does, we must be instantiating
1167  // a generic lambda's call operator (represented by the Current LSI, and
1168  // should be the only scenario where an inconsistency between the LSI and the
1169  // DeclContext should occur), so climb out the DeclContexts if they
1170  // represent lambdas, while querying the corresponding closure types
1171  // regarding capture information.
1172 
1173  // 1) Climb down the function scope info stack.
1174  for (int I = FunctionScopes.size();
1175  I-- && isa<LambdaScopeInfo>(FunctionScopes[I]) &&
1176  (!CurLSI || !CurLSI->Lambda || CurLSI->Lambda->getDeclContext() ==
1177  cast<LambdaScopeInfo>(FunctionScopes[I])->CallOperator);
1178  CurDC = getLambdaAwareParentOfDeclContext(CurDC)) {
1179  CurLSI = cast<LambdaScopeInfo>(FunctionScopes[I]);
1180 
1181  if (!CurLSI->isCXXThisCaptured())
1182  continue;
1183 
1184  auto C = CurLSI->getCXXThisCapture();
1185 
1186  if (C.isCopyCapture()) {
1187  if (CurLSI->lambdaCaptureShouldBeConst())
1188  ClassType.addConst();
1189  return ASTCtx.getPointerType(ClassType);
1190  }
1191  }
1192 
1193  // 2) We've run out of ScopeInfos but check 1. if CurDC is a lambda (which
1194  // can happen during instantiation of its nested generic lambda call
1195  // operator); 2. if we're in a lambda scope (lambda body).
1196  if (CurLSI && isLambdaCallOperator(CurDC)) {
1197  assert(isGenericLambdaCallOperatorSpecialization(CurLSI->CallOperator) &&
1198  "While computing 'this' capture-type for a generic lambda, when we "
1199  "run out of enclosing LSI's, yet the enclosing DC is a "
1200  "lambda-call-operator we must be (i.e. Current LSI) in a generic "
1201  "lambda call oeprator");
1202  assert(CurDC == getLambdaAwareParentOfDeclContext(CurLSI->CallOperator));
1203 
1204  auto IsThisCaptured =
1205  [](CXXRecordDecl *Closure, bool &IsByCopy, bool &IsConst) {
1206  IsConst = false;
1207  IsByCopy = false;
1208  for (auto &&C : Closure->captures()) {
1209  if (C.capturesThis()) {
1210  if (C.getCaptureKind() == LCK_StarThis)
1211  IsByCopy = true;
1212  if (Closure->getLambdaCallOperator()->isConst())
1213  IsConst = true;
1214  return true;
1215  }
1216  }
1217  return false;
1218  };
1219 
1220  bool IsByCopyCapture = false;
1221  bool IsConstCapture = false;
1222  CXXRecordDecl *Closure = cast<CXXRecordDecl>(CurDC->getParent());
1223  while (Closure &&
1224  IsThisCaptured(Closure, IsByCopyCapture, IsConstCapture)) {
1225  if (IsByCopyCapture) {
1226  if (IsConstCapture)
1227  ClassType.addConst();
1228  return ASTCtx.getPointerType(ClassType);
1229  }
1230  Closure = isLambdaCallOperator(Closure->getParent())
1231  ? cast<CXXRecordDecl>(Closure->getParent()->getParent())
1232  : nullptr;
1233  }
1234  }
1235  return ThisTy;
1236 }
1237 
1238 QualType Sema::getCurrentThisType() {
1239  DeclContext *DC = getFunctionLevelDeclContext();
1240  QualType ThisTy = CXXThisTypeOverride;
1241 
1242  if (CXXMethodDecl *method = dyn_cast<CXXMethodDecl>(DC)) {
1243  if (method && method->isImplicitObjectMemberFunction())
1244  ThisTy = method->getThisType().getNonReferenceType();
1245  }
1246 
1247  if (ThisTy.isNull() && isLambdaCallWithImplicitObjectParameter(CurContext) &&
1248  inTemplateInstantiation() && isa<CXXRecordDecl>(DC)) {
1249 
1250  // This is a lambda call operator that is being instantiated as a default
1251  // initializer. DC must point to the enclosing class type, so we can recover
1252  // the 'this' type from it.
1253  QualType ClassTy = Context.getTypeDeclType(cast<CXXRecordDecl>(DC));
1254  // There are no cv-qualifiers for 'this' within default initializers,
1255  // per [expr.prim.general]p4.
1256  ThisTy = Context.getPointerType(ClassTy);
1257  }
1258 
1259  // If we are within a lambda's call operator, the cv-qualifiers of 'this'
1260  // might need to be adjusted if the lambda or any of its enclosing lambda's
1261  // captures '*this' by copy.
1262  if (!ThisTy.isNull() && isLambdaCallOperator(CurContext))
1263  return adjustCVQualifiersForCXXThisWithinLambda(FunctionScopes, ThisTy,
1264  CurContext, Context);
1265  return ThisTy;
1266 }
1267 
1268 Sema::CXXThisScopeRAII::CXXThisScopeRAII(Sema &S,
1269  Decl *ContextDecl,
1270  Qualifiers CXXThisTypeQuals,
1271  bool Enabled)
1272  : S(S), OldCXXThisTypeOverride(S.CXXThisTypeOverride), Enabled(false)
1273 {
1274  if (!Enabled || !ContextDecl)
1275  return;
1276 
1277  CXXRecordDecl *Record = nullptr;
1278  if (ClassTemplateDecl *Template = dyn_cast<ClassTemplateDecl>(ContextDecl))
1279  Record = Template->getTemplatedDecl();
1280  else
1281  Record = cast<CXXRecordDecl>(ContextDecl);
1282 
1283  QualType T = S.Context.getRecordType(Record);
1284  T = S.getASTContext().getQualifiedType(T, CXXThisTypeQuals);
1285 
1286  S.CXXThisTypeOverride =
1287  S.Context.getLangOpts().HLSL ? T : S.Context.getPointerType(T);
1288 
1289  this->Enabled = true;
1290 }
1291 
1292 
1293 Sema::CXXThisScopeRAII::~CXXThisScopeRAII() {
1294  if (Enabled) {
1295  S.CXXThisTypeOverride = OldCXXThisTypeOverride;
1296  }
1297 }
1298 
1299 static void buildLambdaThisCaptureFixit(Sema &Sema, LambdaScopeInfo *LSI) {
1300  SourceLocation DiagLoc = LSI->IntroducerRange.getEnd();
1301  assert(!LSI->isCXXThisCaptured());
1302  // [=, this] {}; // until C++20: Error: this when = is the default
1303  if (LSI->ImpCaptureStyle == CapturingScopeInfo::ImpCap_LambdaByval &&
1304  !Sema.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus20)
1305  return;
1306  Sema.Diag(DiagLoc, diag::note_lambda_this_capture_fixit)
1307  << FixItHint::CreateInsertion(
1308  DiagLoc, LSI->NumExplicitCaptures > 0 ? ", this" : "this");
1309 }
1310 
1311 bool Sema::CheckCXXThisCapture(SourceLocation Loc, const bool Explicit,
1312  bool BuildAndDiagnose, const unsigned *const FunctionScopeIndexToStopAt,
1313  const bool ByCopy) {
1314  // We don't need to capture this in an unevaluated context.
1315  if (isUnevaluatedContext() && !Explicit)
1316  return true;
1317 
1318  assert((!ByCopy || Explicit) && "cannot implicitly capture *this by value");
1319 
1320  const int MaxFunctionScopesIndex = FunctionScopeIndexToStopAt
1321  ? *FunctionScopeIndexToStopAt
1322  : FunctionScopes.size() - 1;
1323 
1324  // Check that we can capture the *enclosing object* (referred to by '*this')
1325  // by the capturing-entity/closure (lambda/block/etc) at
1326  // MaxFunctionScopesIndex-deep on the FunctionScopes stack.
1327 
1328  // Note: The *enclosing object* can only be captured by-value by a
1329  // closure that is a lambda, using the explicit notation:
1330  // [*this] { ... }.
1331  // Every other capture of the *enclosing object* results in its by-reference
1332  // capture.
1333 
1334  // For a closure 'L' (at MaxFunctionScopesIndex in the FunctionScopes
1335  // stack), we can capture the *enclosing object* only if:
1336  // - 'L' has an explicit byref or byval capture of the *enclosing object*
1337  // - or, 'L' has an implicit capture.
1338  // AND
1339  // -- there is no enclosing closure
1340  // -- or, there is some enclosing closure 'E' that has already captured the
1341  // *enclosing object*, and every intervening closure (if any) between 'E'
1342  // and 'L' can implicitly capture the *enclosing object*.
1343  // -- or, every enclosing closure can implicitly capture the
1344  // *enclosing object*
1345 
1346 
1347  unsigned NumCapturingClosures = 0;
1348  for (int idx = MaxFunctionScopesIndex; idx >= 0; idx--) {
1349  if (CapturingScopeInfo *CSI =
1350  dyn_cast<CapturingScopeInfo>(FunctionScopes[idx])) {
1351  if (CSI->CXXThisCaptureIndex != 0) {
1352  // 'this' is already being captured; there isn't anything more to do.
1353  CSI->Captures[CSI->CXXThisCaptureIndex - 1].markUsed(BuildAndDiagnose);
1354  break;
1355  }
1356  LambdaScopeInfo *LSI = dyn_cast<LambdaScopeInfo>(CSI);
1357  if (LSI && isGenericLambdaCallOperatorSpecialization(LSI->CallOperator)) {
1358  // This context can't implicitly capture 'this'; fail out.
1359  if (BuildAndDiagnose) {
1360  LSI->CallOperator->setInvalidDecl();
1361  Diag(Loc, diag::err_this_capture)
1362  << (Explicit && idx == MaxFunctionScopesIndex);
1363  if (!Explicit)
1364  buildLambdaThisCaptureFixit(*this, LSI);
1365  }
1366  return true;
1367  }
1368  if (CSI->ImpCaptureStyle == CapturingScopeInfo::ImpCap_LambdaByref ||
1369  CSI->ImpCaptureStyle == CapturingScopeInfo::ImpCap_LambdaByval ||
1370  CSI->ImpCaptureStyle == CapturingScopeInfo::ImpCap_Block ||
1371  CSI->ImpCaptureStyle == CapturingScopeInfo::ImpCap_CapturedRegion ||
1372  (Explicit && idx == MaxFunctionScopesIndex)) {
1373  // Regarding (Explicit && idx == MaxFunctionScopesIndex): only the first
1374  // iteration through can be an explicit capture, all enclosing closures,
1375  // if any, must perform implicit captures.
1376 
1377  // This closure can capture 'this'; continue looking upwards.
1378  NumCapturingClosures++;
1379  continue;
1380  }
1381  // This context can't implicitly capture 'this'; fail out.
1382  if (BuildAndDiagnose) {
1383  LSI->CallOperator->setInvalidDecl();
1384  Diag(Loc, diag::err_this_capture)
1385  << (Explicit && idx == MaxFunctionScopesIndex);
1386  }
1387  if (!Explicit)
1388  buildLambdaThisCaptureFixit(*this, LSI);
1389  return true;
1390  }
1391  break;
1392  }
1393  if (!BuildAndDiagnose) return false;
1394 
1395  // If we got here, then the closure at MaxFunctionScopesIndex on the
1396  // FunctionScopes stack, can capture the *enclosing object*, so capture it
1397  // (including implicit by-reference captures in any enclosing closures).
1398 
1399  // In the loop below, respect the ByCopy flag only for the closure requesting
1400  // the capture (i.e. first iteration through the loop below). Ignore it for
1401  // all enclosing closure's up to NumCapturingClosures (since they must be
1402  // implicitly capturing the *enclosing object* by reference (see loop
1403  // above)).
1404  assert((!ByCopy ||
1405  isa<LambdaScopeInfo>(FunctionScopes[MaxFunctionScopesIndex])) &&
1406  "Only a lambda can capture the enclosing object (referred to by "
1407  "*this) by copy");
1408  QualType ThisTy = getCurrentThisType();
1409  for (int idx = MaxFunctionScopesIndex; NumCapturingClosures;
1410  --idx, --NumCapturingClosures) {
1411  CapturingScopeInfo *CSI = cast<CapturingScopeInfo>(FunctionScopes[idx]);
1412 
1413  // The type of the corresponding data member (not a 'this' pointer if 'by
1414  // copy').
1415  QualType CaptureType = ByCopy ? ThisTy->getPointeeType() : ThisTy;
1416 
1417  bool isNested = NumCapturingClosures > 1;
1418  CSI->addThisCapture(isNested, Loc, CaptureType, ByCopy);
1419  }
1420  return false;
1421 }
1422 
1423 ExprResult Sema::ActOnCXXThis(SourceLocation Loc) {
1424  // C++20 [expr.prim.this]p1:
1425  // The keyword this names a pointer to the object for which an
1426  // implicit object member function is invoked or a non-static
1427  // data member's initializer is evaluated.
1428  QualType ThisTy = getCurrentThisType();
1429 
1430  if (CheckCXXThisType(Loc, ThisTy))
1431  return ExprError();
1432 
1433  return BuildCXXThisExpr(Loc, ThisTy, /*IsImplicit=*/false);
1434 }
1435 
1436 bool Sema::CheckCXXThisType(SourceLocation Loc, QualType Type) {
1437  if (!Type.isNull())
1438  return false;
1439 
1440  // C++20 [expr.prim.this]p3:
1441  // If a declaration declares a member function or member function template
1442  // of a class X, the expression this is a prvalue of type
1443  // "pointer to cv-qualifier-seq X" wherever X is the current class between
1444  // the optional cv-qualifier-seq and the end of the function-definition,
1445  // member-declarator, or declarator. It shall not appear within the
1446  // declaration of either a static member function or an explicit object
1447  // member function of the current class (although its type and value
1448  // category are defined within such member functions as they are within
1449  // an implicit object member function).
1450  DeclContext *DC = getFunctionLevelDeclContext();
1451  if (const auto *Method = dyn_cast<CXXMethodDecl>(DC);
1452  Method && Method->isExplicitObjectMemberFunction()) {
1453  Diag(Loc, diag::err_invalid_this_use) << 1;
1454  } else if (isLambdaCallWithExplicitObjectParameter(CurContext)) {
1455  Diag(Loc, diag::err_invalid_this_use) << 1;
1456  } else {
1457  Diag(Loc, diag::err_invalid_this_use) << 0;
1458  }
1459  return true;
1460 }
1461 
1462 Expr *Sema::BuildCXXThisExpr(SourceLocation Loc, QualType Type,
1463  bool IsImplicit) {
1464  auto *This = CXXThisExpr::Create(Context, Loc, Type, IsImplicit);
1465  MarkThisReferenced(This);
1466  return This;
1467 }
1468 
1469 void Sema::MarkThisReferenced(CXXThisExpr *This) {
1470  CheckCXXThisCapture(This->getExprLoc());
1471  if (This->isTypeDependent())
1472  return;
1473 
1474  // Check if 'this' is captured by value in a lambda with a dependent explicit
1475  // object parameter, and mark it as type-dependent as well if so.
1476  auto IsDependent = [&]() {
1477  for (auto *Scope : llvm::reverse(FunctionScopes)) {
1478  auto *LSI = dyn_cast<sema::LambdaScopeInfo>(Scope);
1479  if (!LSI)
1480  continue;
1481 
1482  if (LSI->Lambda && !LSI->Lambda->Encloses(CurContext) &&
1483  LSI->AfterParameterList)
1484  return false;
1485 
1486  // If this lambda captures 'this' by value, then 'this' is dependent iff
1487  // this lambda has a dependent explicit object parameter. If we can't
1488  // determine whether it does (e.g. because the CXXMethodDecl's type is
1489  // null), assume it doesn't.
1490  if (LSI->isCXXThisCaptured()) {
1491  if (!LSI->getCXXThisCapture().isCopyCapture())
1492  continue;
1493 
1494  const auto *MD = LSI->CallOperator;
1495  if (MD->getType().isNull())
1496  return false;
1497 
1498  const auto *Ty = MD->getType()->getAs<FunctionProtoType>();
1499  return Ty && MD->isExplicitObjectMemberFunction() &&
1500  Ty->getParamType(0)->isDependentType();
1501  }
1502  }
1503  return false;
1504  }();
1505 
1506  This->setCapturedByCopyInLambdaWithExplicitObjectParameter(IsDependent);
1507 }
1508 
1509 bool Sema::isThisOutsideMemberFunctionBody(QualType BaseType) {
1510  // If we're outside the body of a member function, then we'll have a specified
1511  // type for 'this'.
1512  if (CXXThisTypeOverride.isNull())
1513  return false;
1514 
1515  // Determine whether we're looking into a class that's currently being
1516  // defined.
1517  CXXRecordDecl *Class = BaseType->getAsCXXRecordDecl();
1518  return Class && Class->isBeingDefined();
1519 }
1520 
1521 /// Parse construction of a specified type.
1522 /// Can be interpreted either as function-style casting ("int(x)")
1523 /// or class type construction ("ClassType(x,y,z)")
1524 /// or creation of a value-initialized type ("int()").
1525 ExprResult
1526 Sema::ActOnCXXTypeConstructExpr(ParsedType TypeRep,
1527  SourceLocation LParenOrBraceLoc,
1528  MultiExprArg exprs,
1529  SourceLocation RParenOrBraceLoc,
1530  bool ListInitialization) {
1531  if (!TypeRep)
1532  return ExprError();
1533 
1534  TypeSourceInfo *TInfo;
1535  QualType Ty = GetTypeFromParser(TypeRep, &TInfo);
1536  if (!TInfo)
1537  TInfo = Context.getTrivialTypeSourceInfo(Ty, SourceLocation());
1538 
1539  auto Result = BuildCXXTypeConstructExpr(TInfo, LParenOrBraceLoc, exprs,
1540  RParenOrBraceLoc, ListInitialization);
1541  // Avoid creating a non-type-dependent expression that contains typos.
1542  // Non-type-dependent expressions are liable to be discarded without
1543  // checking for embedded typos.
1544  if (!Result.isInvalid() && Result.get()->isInstantiationDependent() &&
1545  !Result.get()->isTypeDependent())
1546  Result = CorrectDelayedTyposInExpr(Result.get());
1547  else if (Result.isInvalid())
1548  Result = CreateRecoveryExpr(TInfo->getTypeLoc().getBeginLoc(),
1549  RParenOrBraceLoc, exprs, Ty);
1550  return Result;
1551 }
1552 
1553 ExprResult
1554 Sema::BuildCXXTypeConstructExpr(TypeSourceInfo *TInfo,
1555  SourceLocation LParenOrBraceLoc,
1556  MultiExprArg Exprs,
1557  SourceLocation RParenOrBraceLoc,
1558  bool ListInitialization) {
1559  QualType Ty = TInfo->getType();
1560  SourceLocation TyBeginLoc = TInfo->getTypeLoc().getBeginLoc();
1561 
1562  assert((!ListInitialization || Exprs.size() == 1) &&
1563  "List initialization must have exactly one expression.");
1564  SourceRange FullRange = SourceRange(TyBeginLoc, RParenOrBraceLoc);
1565 
1566  InitializedEntity Entity =
1567  InitializedEntity::InitializeTemporary(Context, TInfo);
1568  InitializationKind Kind =
1569  Exprs.size()
1570  ? ListInitialization
1571  ? InitializationKind::CreateDirectList(
1572  TyBeginLoc, LParenOrBraceLoc, RParenOrBraceLoc)
1573  : InitializationKind::CreateDirect(TyBeginLoc, LParenOrBraceLoc,
1574  RParenOrBraceLoc)
1575  : InitializationKind::CreateValue(TyBeginLoc, LParenOrBraceLoc,
1576  RParenOrBraceLoc);
1577 
1578  // C++17 [expr.type.conv]p1:
1579  // If the type is a placeholder for a deduced class type, [...perform class
1580  // template argument deduction...]
1581  // C++23:
1582  // Otherwise, if the type contains a placeholder type, it is replaced by the
1583  // type determined by placeholder type deduction.
1584  DeducedType *Deduced = Ty->getContainedDeducedType();
1585  if (Deduced && !Deduced->isDeduced() &&
1586  isa<DeducedTemplateSpecializationType>(Deduced)) {
1587  Ty = DeduceTemplateSpecializationFromInitializer(TInfo, Entity,
1588  Kind, Exprs);
1589  if (Ty.isNull())
1590  return ExprError();
1591  Entity = InitializedEntity::InitializeTemporary(TInfo, Ty);
1592  } else if (Deduced && !Deduced->isDeduced()) {
1593  MultiExprArg Inits = Exprs;
1594  if (ListInitialization) {
1595  auto *ILE = cast<InitListExpr>(Exprs[0]);
1596  Inits = MultiExprArg(ILE->getInits(), ILE->getNumInits());
1597  }
1598 
1599  if (Inits.empty())
1600  return ExprError(Diag(TyBeginLoc, diag::err_auto_expr_init_no_expression)
1601  << Ty << FullRange);
1602  if (Inits.size() > 1) {
1603  Expr *FirstBad = Inits[1];
1604  return ExprError(Diag(FirstBad->getBeginLoc(),
1605  diag::err_auto_expr_init_multiple_expressions)
1606  << Ty << FullRange);
1607  }
1608  if (getLangOpts().CPlusPlus23) {
1609  if (Ty->getAs<AutoType>())
1610  Diag(TyBeginLoc, diag::warn_cxx20_compat_auto_expr) << FullRange;
1611  }
1612  Expr *Deduce = Inits[0];
1613  if (isa<InitListExpr>(Deduce))
1614  return ExprError(
1615  Diag(Deduce->getBeginLoc(), diag::err_auto_expr_init_paren_braces)
1616  << ListInitialization << Ty << FullRange);
1617  QualType DeducedType;
1618  TemplateDeductionInfo Info(Deduce->getExprLoc());
1619  TemplateDeductionResult Result =
1620  DeduceAutoType(TInfo->getTypeLoc(), Deduce, DeducedType, Info);
1621  if (Result != TemplateDeductionResult::Success &&
1622  Result != TemplateDeductionResult::AlreadyDiagnosed)
1623  return ExprError(Diag(TyBeginLoc, diag::err_auto_expr_deduction_failure)
1624  << Ty << Deduce->getType() << FullRange
1625  << Deduce->getSourceRange());
1626  if (DeducedType.isNull()) {
1627  assert(Result == TemplateDeductionResult::AlreadyDiagnosed);
1628  return ExprError();
1629  }
1630 
1631  Ty = DeducedType;
1632  Entity = InitializedEntity::InitializeTemporary(TInfo, Ty);
1633  }
1634 
1635  if (Ty->isDependentType() || CallExpr::hasAnyTypeDependentArguments(Exprs))
1636  return CXXUnresolvedConstructExpr::Create(
1637  Context, Ty.getNonReferenceType(), TInfo, LParenOrBraceLoc, Exprs,
1638  RParenOrBraceLoc, ListInitialization);
1639 
1640  // C++ [expr.type.conv]p1:
1641  // If the expression list is a parenthesized single expression, the type
1642  // conversion expression is equivalent (in definedness, and if defined in
1643  // meaning) to the corresponding cast expression.
1644  if (Exprs.size() == 1 && !ListInitialization &&
1645  !isa<InitListExpr>(Exprs[0])) {
1646  Expr *Arg = Exprs[0];
1647  return BuildCXXFunctionalCastExpr(TInfo, Ty, LParenOrBraceLoc, Arg,
1648  RParenOrBraceLoc);
1649  }
1650 
1651  // For an expression of the form T(), T shall not be an array type.
1652  QualType ElemTy = Ty;
1653  if (Ty->isArrayType()) {
1654  if (!ListInitialization)
1655  return ExprError(Diag(TyBeginLoc, diag::err_value_init_for_array_type)
1656  << FullRange);
1657  ElemTy = Context.getBaseElementType(Ty);
1658  }
1659 
1660  // Only construct objects with object types.
1661  // The standard doesn't explicitly forbid function types here, but that's an
1662  // obvious oversight, as there's no way to dynamically construct a function
1663  // in general.
1664  if (Ty->isFunctionType())
1665  return ExprError(Diag(TyBeginLoc, diag::err_init_for_function_type)
1666  << Ty << FullRange);
1667 
1668  // C++17 [expr.type.conv]p2:
1669  // If the type is cv void and the initializer is (), the expression is a
1670  // prvalue of the specified type that performs no initialization.
1671  if (!Ty->isVoidType() &&
1672  RequireCompleteType(TyBeginLoc, ElemTy,
1673  diag::err_invalid_incomplete_type_use, FullRange))
1674  return ExprError();
1675 
1676  // Otherwise, the expression is a prvalue of the specified type whose
1677  // result object is direct-initialized (11.6) with the initializer.
1678  InitializationSequence InitSeq(*this, Entity, Kind, Exprs);
1679  ExprResult Result = InitSeq.Perform(*this, Entity, Kind, Exprs);
1680 
1681  if (Result.isInvalid())
1682  return Result;
1683 
1684  Expr *Inner = Result.get();
1685  if (CXXBindTemporaryExpr *BTE = dyn_cast_or_null<CXXBindTemporaryExpr>(Inner))
1686  Inner = BTE->getSubExpr();
1687  if (auto *CE = dyn_cast<ConstantExpr>(Inner);
1688  CE && CE->isImmediateInvocation())
1689  Inner = CE->getSubExpr();
1690  if (!isa<CXXTemporaryObjectExpr>(Inner) &&
1691  !isa<CXXScalarValueInitExpr>(Inner)) {
1692  // If we created a CXXTemporaryObjectExpr, that node also represents the
1693  // functional cast. Otherwise, create an explicit cast to represent
1694  // the syntactic form of a functional-style cast that was used here.
1695  //
1696  // FIXME: Creating a CXXFunctionalCastExpr around a CXXConstructExpr
1697  // would give a more consistent AST representation than using a
1698  // CXXTemporaryObjectExpr. It's also weird that the functional cast
1699  // is sometimes handled by initialization and sometimes not.
1700  QualType ResultType = Result.get()->getType();
1701  SourceRange Locs = ListInitialization
1702  ? SourceRange()
1703  : SourceRange(LParenOrBraceLoc, RParenOrBraceLoc);
1704  Result = CXXFunctionalCastExpr::Create(
1705  Context, ResultType, Expr::getValueKindForType(Ty), TInfo, CK_NoOp,
1706  Result.get(), /*Path=*/nullptr, CurFPFeatureOverrides(),
1707  Locs.getBegin(), Locs.getEnd());
1708  }
1709 
1710  return Result;
1711 }
1712 
1713 bool Sema::isUsualDeallocationFunction(const CXXMethodDecl *Method) {
1714  // [CUDA] Ignore this function, if we can't call it.
1715  const FunctionDecl *Caller = getCurFunctionDecl(/*AllowLambda=*/true);
1716  if (getLangOpts().CUDA) {
1717  auto CallPreference = CUDA().IdentifyPreference(Caller, Method);
1718  // If it's not callable at all, it's not the right function.
1719  if (CallPreference < SemaCUDA::CFP_WrongSide)
1720  return false;
1721  if (CallPreference == SemaCUDA::CFP_WrongSide) {
1722  // Maybe. We have to check if there are better alternatives.
1723  DeclContext::lookup_result R =
1724  Method->getDeclContext()->lookup(Method->getDeclName());
1725  for (const auto *D : R) {
1726  if (const auto *FD = dyn_cast<FunctionDecl>(D)) {
1727  if (CUDA().IdentifyPreference(Caller, FD) > SemaCUDA::CFP_WrongSide)
1728  return false;
1729  }
1730  }
1731  // We've found no better variants.
1732  }
1733  }
1734 
1735  SmallVector<const FunctionDecl*, 4> PreventedBy;
1736  bool Result = Method->isUsualDeallocationFunction(PreventedBy);
1737 
1738  if (Result || !getLangOpts().CUDA || PreventedBy.empty())
1739  return Result;
1740 
1741  // In case of CUDA, return true if none of the 1-argument deallocator
1742  // functions are actually callable.
1743  return llvm::none_of(PreventedBy, [&](const FunctionDecl *FD) {
1744  assert(FD->getNumParams() == 1 &&
1745  "Only single-operand functions should be in PreventedBy");
1746  return CUDA().IdentifyPreference(Caller, FD) >= SemaCUDA::CFP_HostDevice;
1747  });
1748 }
1749 
1750 /// Determine whether the given function is a non-placement
1751 /// deallocation function.
1752 static bool isNonPlacementDeallocationFunction(Sema &S, FunctionDecl *FD) {
1753  if (CXXMethodDecl *Method = dyn_cast<CXXMethodDecl>(FD))
1754  return S.isUsualDeallocationFunction(Method);
1755 
1756  if (FD->getOverloadedOperator() != OO_Delete &&
1757  FD->getOverloadedOperator() != OO_Array_Delete)
1758  return false;
1759 
1760  unsigned UsualParams = 1;
1761 
1762  if (S.getLangOpts().SizedDeallocation && UsualParams < FD->getNumParams() &&
1763  S.Context.hasSameUnqualifiedType(
1764  FD->getParamDecl(UsualParams)->getType(),
1765  S.Context.getSizeType()))
1766  ++UsualParams;
1767 
1768  if (S.getLangOpts().AlignedAllocation && UsualParams < FD->getNumParams() &&
1769  S.Context.hasSameUnqualifiedType(
1770  FD->getParamDecl(UsualParams)->getType(),
1771  S.Context.getTypeDeclType(S.getStdAlignValT())))
1772  ++UsualParams;
1773 
1774  return UsualParams == FD->getNumParams();
1775 }
1776 
1777 namespace {
1778  struct UsualDeallocFnInfo {
1779  UsualDeallocFnInfo() : Found(), FD(nullptr) {}
1780  UsualDeallocFnInfo(Sema &S, DeclAccessPair Found)
1781  : Found(Found), FD(dyn_cast<FunctionDecl>(Found->getUnderlyingDecl())),
1782  Destroying(false), HasSizeT(false), HasAlignValT(false),
1783  CUDAPref(SemaCUDA::CFP_Native) {
1784  // A function template declaration is never a usual deallocation function.
1785  if (!FD)
1786  return;
1787  unsigned NumBaseParams = 1;
1788  if (FD->isDestroyingOperatorDelete()) {
1789  Destroying = true;
1790  ++NumBaseParams;
1791  }
1792 
1793  if (NumBaseParams < FD->getNumParams() &&
1794  S.Context.hasSameUnqualifiedType(
1795  FD->getParamDecl(NumBaseParams)->getType(),
1796  S.Context.getSizeType())) {
1797  ++NumBaseParams;
1798  HasSizeT = true;
1799  }
1800 
1801  if (NumBaseParams < FD->getNumParams() &&
1802  FD->getParamDecl(NumBaseParams)->getType()->isAlignValT()) {
1803  ++NumBaseParams;
1804  HasAlignValT = true;
1805  }
1806 
1807  // In CUDA, determine how much we'd like / dislike to call this.
1808  if (S.getLangOpts().CUDA)
1809  CUDAPref = S.CUDA().IdentifyPreference(
1810  S.getCurFunctionDecl(/*AllowLambda=*/true), FD);
1811  }
1812 
1813  explicit operator bool() const { return FD; }
1814 
1815  bool isBetterThan(const UsualDeallocFnInfo &Other, bool WantSize,
1816  bool WantAlign) const {
1817  // C++ P0722:
1818  // A destroying operator delete is preferred over a non-destroying
1819  // operator delete.
1820  if (Destroying != Other.Destroying)
1821  return Destroying;
1822 
1823  // C++17 [expr.delete]p10:
1824  // If the type has new-extended alignment, a function with a parameter
1825  // of type std::align_val_t is preferred; otherwise a function without
1826  // such a parameter is preferred
1827  if (HasAlignValT != Other.HasAlignValT)
1828  return HasAlignValT == WantAlign;
1829 
1830  if (HasSizeT != Other.HasSizeT)
1831  return HasSizeT == WantSize;
1832 
1833  // Use CUDA call preference as a tiebreaker.
1834  return CUDAPref > Other.CUDAPref;
1835  }
1836 
1837  DeclAccessPair Found;
1838  FunctionDecl *FD;
1839  bool Destroying, HasSizeT, HasAlignValT;
1840  SemaCUDA::CUDAFunctionPreference CUDAPref;
1841  };
1842 }
1843 
1844 /// Determine whether a type has new-extended alignment. This may be called when
1845 /// the type is incomplete (for a delete-expression with an incomplete pointee
1846 /// type), in which case it will conservatively return false if the alignment is
1847 /// not known.
1848 static bool hasNewExtendedAlignment(Sema &S, QualType AllocType) {
1849  return S.getLangOpts().AlignedAllocation &&
1850  S.getASTContext().getTypeAlignIfKnown(AllocType) >
1851  S.getASTContext().getTargetInfo().getNewAlign();
1852 }
1853 
1854 /// Select the correct "usual" deallocation function to use from a selection of
1855 /// deallocation functions (either global or class-scope).
1856 static UsualDeallocFnInfo resolveDeallocationOverload(
1857  Sema &S, LookupResult &R, bool WantSize, bool WantAlign,
1858  llvm::SmallVectorImpl<UsualDeallocFnInfo> *BestFns = nullptr) {
1859  UsualDeallocFnInfo Best;
1860 
1861  for (auto I = R.begin(), E = R.end(); I != E; ++I) {
1862  UsualDeallocFnInfo Info(S, I.getPair());
1863  if (!Info || !isNonPlacementDeallocationFunction(S, Info.FD) ||
1864  Info.CUDAPref == SemaCUDA::CFP_Never)
1865  continue;
1866 
1867  if (!Best) {
1868  Best = Info;
1869  if (BestFns)
1870  BestFns->push_back(Info);
1871  continue;
1872  }
1873 
1874  if (Best.isBetterThan(Info, WantSize, WantAlign))
1875  continue;
1876 
1877  // If more than one preferred function is found, all non-preferred
1878  // functions are eliminated from further consideration.
1879  if (BestFns && Info.isBetterThan(Best, WantSize, WantAlign))
1880  BestFns->clear();
1881 
1882  Best = Info;
1883  if (BestFns)
1884  BestFns->push_back(Info);
1885  }
1886 
1887  return Best;
1888 }
1889 
1890 /// Determine whether a given type is a class for which 'delete[]' would call
1891 /// a member 'operator delete[]' with a 'size_t' parameter. This implies that
1892 /// we need to store the array size (even if the type is
1893 /// trivially-destructible).
1894 static bool doesUsualArrayDeleteWantSize(Sema &S, SourceLocation loc,
1895  QualType allocType) {
1896  const RecordType *record =
1897  allocType->getBaseElementTypeUnsafe()->getAs<RecordType>();
1898  if (!record) return false;
1899 
1900  // Try to find an operator delete[] in class scope.
1901 
1902  DeclarationName deleteName =
1903  S.Context.DeclarationNames.getCXXOperatorName(OO_Array_Delete);
1904  LookupResult ops(S, deleteName, loc, Sema::LookupOrdinaryName);
1905  S.LookupQualifiedName(ops, record->getDecl());
1906 
1907  // We're just doing this for information.
1908  ops.suppressDiagnostics();
1909 
1910  // Very likely: there's no operator delete[].
1911  if (ops.empty()) return false;
1912 
1913  // If it's ambiguous, it should be illegal to call operator delete[]
1914  // on this thing, so it doesn't matter if we allocate extra space or not.
1915  if (ops.isAmbiguous()) return false;
1916 
1917  // C++17 [expr.delete]p10:
1918  // If the deallocation functions have class scope, the one without a
1919  // parameter of type std::size_t is selected.
1920  auto Best = resolveDeallocationOverload(
1921  S, ops, /*WantSize*/false,
1922  /*WantAlign*/hasNewExtendedAlignment(S, allocType));
1923  return Best && Best.HasSizeT;
1924 }
1925 
1926 /// Parsed a C++ 'new' expression (C++ 5.3.4).
1927 ///
1928 /// E.g.:
1929 /// @code new (memory) int[size][4] @endcode
1930 /// or
1931 /// @code ::new Foo(23, "hello") @endcode
1932 ///
1933 /// \param StartLoc The first location of the expression.
1934 /// \param UseGlobal True if 'new' was prefixed with '::'.
1935 /// \param PlacementLParen Opening paren of the placement arguments.
1936 /// \param PlacementArgs Placement new arguments.
1937 /// \param PlacementRParen Closing paren of the placement arguments.
1938 /// \param TypeIdParens If the type is in parens, the source range.
1939 /// \param D The type to be allocated, as well as array dimensions.
1940 /// \param Initializer The initializing expression or initializer-list, or null
1941 /// if there is none.
1942 ExprResult
1943 Sema::ActOnCXXNew(SourceLocation StartLoc, bool UseGlobal,
1944  SourceLocation PlacementLParen, MultiExprArg PlacementArgs,
1945  SourceLocation PlacementRParen, SourceRange TypeIdParens,
1946  Declarator &D, Expr *Initializer) {
1947  std::optional<Expr *> ArraySize;
1948  // If the specified type is an array, unwrap it and save the expression.
1949  if (D.getNumTypeObjects() > 0 &&
1950  D.getTypeObject(0).Kind == DeclaratorChunk::Array) {
1951  DeclaratorChunk &Chunk = D.getTypeObject(0);
1952  if (D.getDeclSpec().hasAutoTypeSpec())
1953  return ExprError(Diag(Chunk.Loc, diag::err_new_array_of_auto)
1954  << D.getSourceRange());
1955  if (Chunk.Arr.hasStatic)
1956  return ExprError(Diag(Chunk.Loc, diag::err_static_illegal_in_new)
1957  << D.getSourceRange());
1958  if (!Chunk.Arr.NumElts && !Initializer)
1959  return ExprError(Diag(Chunk.Loc, diag::err_array_new_needs_size)
1960  << D.getSourceRange());
1961 
1962  ArraySize = static_cast<Expr*>(Chunk.Arr.NumElts);
1963  D.DropFirstTypeObject();
1964  }
1965 
1966  // Every dimension shall be of constant size.
1967  if (ArraySize) {
1968  for (unsigned I = 0, N = D.getNumTypeObjects(); I < N; ++I) {
1969  if (D.getTypeObject(I).Kind != DeclaratorChunk::Array)
1970  break;
1971 
1972  DeclaratorChunk::ArrayTypeInfo &Array = D.getTypeObject(I).Arr;
1973  if (Expr *NumElts = (Expr *)Array.NumElts) {
1974  if (!NumElts->isTypeDependent() && !NumElts->isValueDependent()) {
1975  // FIXME: GCC permits constant folding here. We should either do so consistently
1976  // or not do so at all, rather than changing behavior in C++14 onwards.
1977  if (getLangOpts().CPlusPlus14) {
1978  // C++1y [expr.new]p6: Every constant-expression in a noptr-new-declarator
1979  // shall be a converted constant expression (5.19) of type std::size_t
1980  // and shall evaluate to a strictly positive value.
1981  llvm::APSInt Value(Context.getIntWidth(Context.getSizeType()));
1982  Array.NumElts
1983  = CheckConvertedConstantExpression(NumElts, Context.getSizeType(), Value,
1984  CCEK_ArrayBound)
1985  .get();
1986  } else {
1987  Array.NumElts =
1988  VerifyIntegerConstantExpression(
1989  NumElts, nullptr, diag::err_new_array_nonconst, AllowFold)
1990  .get();
1991  }
1992  if (!Array.NumElts)
1993  return ExprError();
1994  }
1995  }
1996  }
1997  }
1998 
1999  TypeSourceInfo *TInfo = GetTypeForDeclarator(D);
2000  QualType AllocType = TInfo->getType();
2001  if (D.isInvalidType())
2002  return ExprError();
2003 
2004  SourceRange DirectInitRange;
2005  if (ParenListExpr *List = dyn_cast_or_null<ParenListExpr>(Initializer))
2006  DirectInitRange = List->getSourceRange();
2007 
2008  return BuildCXXNew(SourceRange(StartLoc, D.getEndLoc()), UseGlobal,
2009  PlacementLParen, PlacementArgs, PlacementRParen,
2010  TypeIdParens, AllocType, TInfo, ArraySize, DirectInitRange,
2011  Initializer);
2012 }
2013 
2014 static bool isLegalArrayNewInitializer(CXXNewInitializationStyle Style,
2015  Expr *Init, bool IsCPlusPlus20) {
2016  if (!Init)
2017  return true;
2018  if (ParenListExpr *PLE = dyn_cast<ParenListExpr>(Init))
2019  return IsCPlusPlus20 || PLE->getNumExprs() == 0;
2020  if (isa<ImplicitValueInitExpr>(Init))
2021  return true;
2022  else if (CXXConstructExpr *CCE = dyn_cast<CXXConstructExpr>(Init))
2023  return !CCE->isListInitialization() &&
2024  CCE->getConstructor()->isDefaultConstructor();
2025  else if (Style == CXXNewInitializationStyle::Braces) {
2026  assert(isa<InitListExpr>(Init) &&
2027  "Shouldn't create list CXXConstructExprs for arrays.");
2028  return true;
2029  }
2030  return false;
2031 }
2032 
2033 bool
2034 Sema::isUnavailableAlignedAllocationFunction(const FunctionDecl &FD) const {
2035  if (!getLangOpts().AlignedAllocationUnavailable)
2036  return false;
2037  if (FD.isDefined())
2038  return false;
2039  std::optional<unsigned> AlignmentParam;
2040  if (FD.isReplaceableGlobalAllocationFunction(&AlignmentParam) &&
2041  AlignmentParam)
2042  return true;
2043  return false;
2044 }
2045 
2046 // Emit a diagnostic if an aligned allocation/deallocation function that is not
2047 // implemented in the standard library is selected.
2048 void Sema::diagnoseUnavailableAlignedAllocation(const FunctionDecl &FD,
2049  SourceLocation Loc) {
2050  if (isUnavailableAlignedAllocationFunction(FD)) {
2051  const llvm::Triple &T = getASTContext().getTargetInfo().getTriple();
2052  StringRef OSName = AvailabilityAttr::getPlatformNameSourceSpelling(
2053  getASTContext().getTargetInfo().getPlatformName());
2054  VersionTuple OSVersion = alignedAllocMinVersion(T.getOS());
2055 
2056  OverloadedOperatorKind Kind = FD.getDeclName().getCXXOverloadedOperator();
2057  bool IsDelete = Kind == OO_Delete || Kind == OO_Array_Delete;
2058  Diag(Loc, diag::err_aligned_allocation_unavailable)
2059  << IsDelete << FD.getType().getAsString() << OSName
2060  << OSVersion.getAsString() << OSVersion.empty();
2061  Diag(Loc, diag::note_silence_aligned_allocation_unavailable);
2062  }
2063 }
2064
