2065 ExprResult Sema::BuildCXXNew(SourceRange Range, bool UseGlobal,
2066  SourceLocation PlacementLParen,
2067  MultiExprArg PlacementArgs,
2068  SourceLocation PlacementRParen,
2069  SourceRange TypeIdParens, QualType AllocType,
2070  TypeSourceInfo *AllocTypeInfo,
2071  std::optional<Expr *> ArraySize,
2072  SourceRange DirectInitRange, Expr *Initializer) {
2073  SourceRange TypeRange = AllocTypeInfo->getTypeLoc().getSourceRange();
2074  SourceLocation StartLoc = Range.getBegin();
2075 
2076  CXXNewInitializationStyle InitStyle;
2077  if (DirectInitRange.isValid()) {
2078  assert(Initializer && "Have parens but no initializer.");
2079  InitStyle = CXXNewInitializationStyle::Parens;
2080  } else if (Initializer && isa<InitListExpr>(Initializer))
2081  InitStyle = CXXNewInitializationStyle::Braces;
2082  else {
2083  assert((!Initializer || isa<ImplicitValueInitExpr>(Initializer) ||
2084  isa<CXXConstructExpr>(Initializer)) &&
2085  "Initializer expression that cannot have been implicitly created.");
2086  InitStyle = CXXNewInitializationStyle::None;
2087  }
2088 
2089  MultiExprArg Exprs(&Initializer, Initializer ? 1 : 0);
2090  if (ParenListExpr *List = dyn_cast_or_null<ParenListExpr>(Initializer)) {
2091  assert(InitStyle == CXXNewInitializationStyle::Parens &&
2092  "paren init for non-call init");
2093  Exprs = MultiExprArg(List->getExprs(), List->getNumExprs());
2094  }
2095 
2096  // C++11 [expr.new]p15:
2097  // A new-expression that creates an object of type T initializes that
2098  // object as follows:
2099  InitializationKind Kind = [&] {
2100  switch (InitStyle) {
2101  // - If the new-initializer is omitted, the object is default-
2102  // initialized (8.5); if no initialization is performed,
2103  // the object has indeterminate value
2104  case CXXNewInitializationStyle::None:
2105  return InitializationKind::CreateDefault(TypeRange.getBegin());
2106  // - Otherwise, the new-initializer is interpreted according to the
2107  // initialization rules of 8.5 for direct-initialization.
2108  case CXXNewInitializationStyle::Parens:
2109  return InitializationKind::CreateDirect(TypeRange.getBegin(),
2110  DirectInitRange.getBegin(),
2111  DirectInitRange.getEnd());
2112  case CXXNewInitializationStyle::Braces:
2113  return InitializationKind::CreateDirectList(TypeRange.getBegin(),
2114  Initializer->getBeginLoc(),
2115  Initializer->getEndLoc());
2116  }
2117  llvm_unreachable("Unknown initialization kind");
2118  }();
2119 
2120  // C++11 [dcl.spec.auto]p6. Deduce the type which 'auto' stands in for.
2121  auto *Deduced = AllocType->getContainedDeducedType();
2122  if (Deduced && !Deduced->isDeduced() &&
2123  isa<DeducedTemplateSpecializationType>(Deduced)) {
2124  if (ArraySize)
2125  return ExprError(
2126  Diag(*ArraySize ? (*ArraySize)->getExprLoc() : TypeRange.getBegin(),
2127  diag::err_deduced_class_template_compound_type)
2128  << /*array*/ 2
2129  << (*ArraySize ? (*ArraySize)->getSourceRange() : TypeRange));
2130 
2131  InitializedEntity Entity
2132  = InitializedEntity::InitializeNew(StartLoc, AllocType);
2133  AllocType = DeduceTemplateSpecializationFromInitializer(
2134  AllocTypeInfo, Entity, Kind, Exprs);
2135  if (AllocType.isNull())
2136  return ExprError();
2137  } else if (Deduced && !Deduced->isDeduced()) {
2138  MultiExprArg Inits = Exprs;
2139  bool Braced = (InitStyle == CXXNewInitializationStyle::Braces);
2140  if (Braced) {
2141  auto *ILE = cast<InitListExpr>(Exprs[0]);
2142  Inits = MultiExprArg(ILE->getInits(), ILE->getNumInits());
2143  }
2144 
2145  if (InitStyle == CXXNewInitializationStyle::None || Inits.empty())
2146  return ExprError(Diag(StartLoc, diag::err_auto_new_requires_ctor_arg)
2147  << AllocType << TypeRange);
2148  if (Inits.size() > 1) {
2149  Expr *FirstBad = Inits[1];
2150  return ExprError(Diag(FirstBad->getBeginLoc(),
2151  diag::err_auto_new_ctor_multiple_expressions)
2152  << AllocType << TypeRange);
2153  }
2154  if (Braced && !getLangOpts().CPlusPlus17)
2155  Diag(Initializer->getBeginLoc(), diag::ext_auto_new_list_init)
2156  << AllocType << TypeRange;
2157  Expr *Deduce = Inits[0];
2158  if (isa<InitListExpr>(Deduce))
2159  return ExprError(
2160  Diag(Deduce->getBeginLoc(), diag::err_auto_expr_init_paren_braces)
2161  << Braced << AllocType << TypeRange);
2162  QualType DeducedType;
2163  TemplateDeductionInfo Info(Deduce->getExprLoc());
2164  TemplateDeductionResult Result =
2165  DeduceAutoType(AllocTypeInfo->getTypeLoc(), Deduce, DeducedType, Info);
2166  if (Result != TemplateDeductionResult::Success &&
2167  Result != TemplateDeductionResult::AlreadyDiagnosed)
2168  return ExprError(Diag(StartLoc, diag::err_auto_new_deduction_failure)
2169  << AllocType << Deduce->getType() << TypeRange
2170  << Deduce->getSourceRange());
2171  if (DeducedType.isNull()) {
2172  assert(Result == TemplateDeductionResult::AlreadyDiagnosed);
2173  return ExprError();
2174  }
2175  AllocType = DeducedType;
2176  }
2177 
2178  // Per C++0x [expr.new]p5, the type being constructed may be a
2179  // typedef of an array type.
2180  if (!ArraySize) {
2181  if (const ConstantArrayType *Array
2182  = Context.getAsConstantArrayType(AllocType)) {
2183  ArraySize = IntegerLiteral::Create(Context, Array->getSize(),
2184  Context.getSizeType(),
2185  TypeRange.getEnd());
2186  AllocType = Array->getElementType();
2187  }
2188  }
2189 
2190  if (CheckAllocatedType(AllocType, TypeRange.getBegin(), TypeRange))
2191  return ExprError();
2192 
2193  if (ArraySize && !checkArrayElementAlignment(AllocType, TypeRange.getBegin()))
2194  return ExprError();
2195 
2196  // In ARC, infer 'retaining' for the allocated
2197  if (getLangOpts().ObjCAutoRefCount &&
2198  AllocType.getObjCLifetime() == Qualifiers::OCL_None &&
2199  AllocType->isObjCLifetimeType()) {
2200  AllocType = Context.getLifetimeQualifiedType(AllocType,
2201  AllocType->getObjCARCImplicitLifetime());
2202  }
2203 
2204  QualType ResultType = Context.getPointerType(AllocType);
2205 
2206  if (ArraySize && *ArraySize &&
2207  (*ArraySize)->getType()->isNonOverloadPlaceholderType()) {
2208  ExprResult result = CheckPlaceholderExpr(*ArraySize);
2209  if (result.isInvalid()) return ExprError();
2210  ArraySize = result.get();
2211  }
2212  // C++98 5.3.4p6: "The expression in a direct-new-declarator shall have
2213  // integral or enumeration type with a non-negative value."
2214  // C++11 [expr.new]p6: The expression [...] shall be of integral or unscoped
2215  // enumeration type, or a class type for which a single non-explicit
2216  // conversion function to integral or unscoped enumeration type exists.
2217  // C++1y [expr.new]p6: The expression [...] is implicitly converted to
2218  // std::size_t.
2219  std::optional<uint64_t> KnownArraySize;
2220  if (ArraySize && *ArraySize && !(*ArraySize)->isTypeDependent()) {
2221  ExprResult ConvertedSize;
2222  if (getLangOpts().CPlusPlus14) {
2223  assert(Context.getTargetInfo().getIntWidth() && "Builtin type of size 0?");
2224 
2225  ConvertedSize = PerformImplicitConversion(*ArraySize, Context.getSizeType(),
2226  AA_Converting);
2227 
2228  if (!ConvertedSize.isInvalid() &&
2229  (*ArraySize)->getType()->getAs<RecordType>())
2230  // Diagnose the compatibility of this conversion.
2231  Diag(StartLoc, diag::warn_cxx98_compat_array_size_conversion)
2232  << (*ArraySize)->getType() << 0 << "'size_t'";
2233  } else {
2234  class SizeConvertDiagnoser : public ICEConvertDiagnoser {
2235  protected:
2236  Expr *ArraySize;
2237 
2238  public:
2239  SizeConvertDiagnoser(Expr *ArraySize)
2240  : ICEConvertDiagnoser(/*AllowScopedEnumerations*/false, false, false),
2241  ArraySize(ArraySize) {}
2242 
2243  SemaDiagnosticBuilder diagnoseNotInt(Sema &S, SourceLocation Loc,
2244  QualType T) override {
2245  return S.Diag(Loc, diag::err_array_size_not_integral)
2246  << S.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus11 << T;
2247  }
2248 
2249  SemaDiagnosticBuilder diagnoseIncomplete(
2250  Sema &S, SourceLocation Loc, QualType T) override {
2251  return S.Diag(Loc, diag::err_array_size_incomplete_type)
2252  << T << ArraySize->getSourceRange();
2253  }
2254 
2255  SemaDiagnosticBuilder diagnoseExplicitConv(
2256  Sema &S, SourceLocation Loc, QualType T, QualType ConvTy) override {
2257  return S.Diag(Loc, diag::err_array_size_explicit_conversion) << T << ConvTy;
2258  }
2259 
2260  SemaDiagnosticBuilder noteExplicitConv(
2261  Sema &S, CXXConversionDecl *Conv, QualType ConvTy) override {
2262  return S.Diag(Conv->getLocation(), diag::note_array_size_conversion)
2263  << ConvTy->isEnumeralType() << ConvTy;
2264  }
2265 
2266  SemaDiagnosticBuilder diagnoseAmbiguous(
2267  Sema &S, SourceLocation Loc, QualType T) override {
2268  return S.Diag(Loc, diag::err_array_size_ambiguous_conversion) << T;
2269  }
2270 
2271  SemaDiagnosticBuilder noteAmbiguous(
2272  Sema &S, CXXConversionDecl *Conv, QualType ConvTy) override {
2273  return S.Diag(Conv->getLocation(), diag::note_array_size_conversion)
2274  << ConvTy->isEnumeralType() << ConvTy;
2275  }
2276 
2277  SemaDiagnosticBuilder diagnoseConversion(Sema &S, SourceLocation Loc,
2278  QualType T,
2279  QualType ConvTy) override {
2280  return S.Diag(Loc,
2281  S.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus11
2282  ? diag::warn_cxx98_compat_array_size_conversion
2283  : diag::ext_array_size_conversion)
2284  << T << ConvTy->isEnumeralType() << ConvTy;
2285  }
2286  } SizeDiagnoser(*ArraySize);
2287 
2288  ConvertedSize = PerformContextualImplicitConversion(StartLoc, *ArraySize,
2289  SizeDiagnoser);
2290  }
2291  if (ConvertedSize.isInvalid())
2292  return ExprError();
2293 
2294  ArraySize = ConvertedSize.get();
2295  QualType SizeType = (*ArraySize)->getType();
2296 
2297  if (!SizeType->isIntegralOrUnscopedEnumerationType())
2298  return ExprError();
2299 
2300  // C++98 [expr.new]p7:
2301  // The expression in a direct-new-declarator shall have integral type
2302  // with a non-negative value.
2303  //
2304  // Let's see if this is a constant < 0. If so, we reject it out of hand,
2305  // per CWG1464. Otherwise, if it's not a constant, we must have an
2306  // unparenthesized array type.
2307 
2308  // We've already performed any required implicit conversion to integer or
2309  // unscoped enumeration type.
2310  // FIXME: Per CWG1464, we are required to check the value prior to
2311  // converting to size_t. This will never find a negative array size in
2312  // C++14 onwards, because Value is always unsigned here!
2313  if (std::optional<llvm::APSInt> Value =
2314  (*ArraySize)->getIntegerConstantExpr(Context)) {
2315  if (Value->isSigned() && Value->isNegative()) {
2316  return ExprError(Diag((*ArraySize)->getBeginLoc(),
2317  diag::err_typecheck_negative_array_size)
2318  << (*ArraySize)->getSourceRange());
2319  }
2320 
2321  if (!AllocType->isDependentType()) {
2322  unsigned ActiveSizeBits =
2323  ConstantArrayType::getNumAddressingBits(Context, AllocType, *Value);
2324  if (ActiveSizeBits > ConstantArrayType::getMaxSizeBits(Context))
2325  return ExprError(
2326  Diag((*ArraySize)->getBeginLoc(), diag::err_array_too_large)
2327  << toString(*Value, 10) << (*ArraySize)->getSourceRange());
2328  }
2329 
2330  KnownArraySize = Value->getZExtValue();
2331  } else if (TypeIdParens.isValid()) {
2332  // Can't have dynamic array size when the type-id is in parentheses.
2333  Diag((*ArraySize)->getBeginLoc(), diag::ext_new_paren_array_nonconst)
2334  << (*ArraySize)->getSourceRange()
2335  << FixItHint::CreateRemoval(TypeIdParens.getBegin())
2336  << FixItHint::CreateRemoval(TypeIdParens.getEnd());
2337 
2338  TypeIdParens = SourceRange();
2339  }
2340 
2341  // Note that we do *not* convert the argument in any way. It can
2342  // be signed, larger than size_t, whatever.
2343  }
2344 
2345  FunctionDecl *OperatorNew = nullptr;
2346  FunctionDecl *OperatorDelete = nullptr;
2347  unsigned Alignment =
2348  AllocType->isDependentType() ? 0 : Context.getTypeAlign(AllocType);
2349  unsigned NewAlignment = Context.getTargetInfo().getNewAlign();
2350  bool PassAlignment = getLangOpts().AlignedAllocation &&
2351  Alignment > NewAlignment;
2352 
2353  if (CheckArgsForPlaceholders(PlacementArgs))
2354  return ExprError();
2355 
2356  AllocationFunctionScope Scope = UseGlobal ? AFS_Global : AFS_Both;
2357  if (!AllocType->isDependentType() &&
2358  !Expr::hasAnyTypeDependentArguments(PlacementArgs) &&
2359  FindAllocationFunctions(
2360  StartLoc, SourceRange(PlacementLParen, PlacementRParen), Scope, Scope,
2361  AllocType, ArraySize.has_value(), PassAlignment, PlacementArgs,
2362  OperatorNew, OperatorDelete))
2363  return ExprError();
2364 
2365  // If this is an array allocation, compute whether the usual array
2366  // deallocation function for the type has a size_t parameter.
2367  bool UsualArrayDeleteWantsSize = false;
2368  if (ArraySize && !AllocType->isDependentType())
2369  UsualArrayDeleteWantsSize =
2370  doesUsualArrayDeleteWantSize(*this, StartLoc, AllocType);
2371 
2372  SmallVector<Expr *, 8> AllPlaceArgs;
2373  if (OperatorNew) {
2374  auto *Proto = OperatorNew->getType()->castAs<FunctionProtoType>();
2375  VariadicCallType CallType = Proto->isVariadic() ? VariadicFunction
2376  : VariadicDoesNotApply;
2377 
2378  // We've already converted the placement args, just fill in any default
2379  // arguments. Skip the first parameter because we don't have a corresponding
2380  // argument. Skip the second parameter too if we're passing in the
2381  // alignment; we've already filled it in.
2382  unsigned NumImplicitArgs = PassAlignment ? 2 : 1;
2383  if (GatherArgumentsForCall(PlacementLParen, OperatorNew, Proto,
2384  NumImplicitArgs, PlacementArgs, AllPlaceArgs,
2385  CallType))
2386  return ExprError();
2387 
2388  if (!AllPlaceArgs.empty())
2389  PlacementArgs = AllPlaceArgs;
2390 
2391  // We would like to perform some checking on the given `operator new` call,
2392  // but the PlacementArgs does not contain the implicit arguments,
2393  // namely allocation size and maybe allocation alignment,
2394  // so we need to conjure them.
2395 
2396  QualType SizeTy = Context.getSizeType();
2397  unsigned SizeTyWidth = Context.getTypeSize(SizeTy);
2398 
2399  llvm::APInt SingleEltSize(
2400  SizeTyWidth, Context.getTypeSizeInChars(AllocType).getQuantity());
2401 
2402  // How many bytes do we want to allocate here?
2403  std::optional<llvm::APInt> AllocationSize;
2404  if (!ArraySize && !AllocType->isDependentType()) {
2405  // For non-array operator new, we only want to allocate one element.
2406  AllocationSize = SingleEltSize;
2407  } else if (KnownArraySize && !AllocType->isDependentType()) {
2408  // For array operator new, only deal with static array size case.
2409  bool Overflow;
2410  AllocationSize = llvm::APInt(SizeTyWidth, *KnownArraySize)
2411  .umul_ov(SingleEltSize, Overflow);
2412  (void)Overflow;
2413  assert(
2414  !Overflow &&
2415  "Expected that all the overflows would have been handled already.");
2416  }
2417 
2418  IntegerLiteral AllocationSizeLiteral(
2419  Context, AllocationSize.value_or(llvm::APInt::getZero(SizeTyWidth)),
2420  SizeTy, SourceLocation());
2421  // Otherwise, if we failed to constant-fold the allocation size, we'll
2422  // just give up and pass-in something opaque, that isn't a null pointer.
2423  OpaqueValueExpr OpaqueAllocationSize(SourceLocation(), SizeTy, VK_PRValue,
2424  OK_Ordinary, /*SourceExpr=*/nullptr);
2425 
2426  // Let's synthesize the alignment argument in case we will need it.
2427  // Since we *really* want to allocate these on stack, this is slightly ugly
2428  // because there might not be a `std::align_val_t` type.
2429  EnumDecl *StdAlignValT = getStdAlignValT();
2430  QualType AlignValT =
2431  StdAlignValT ? Context.getTypeDeclType(StdAlignValT) : SizeTy;
2432  IntegerLiteral AlignmentLiteral(
2433  Context,
2434  llvm::APInt(Context.getTypeSize(SizeTy),
2435  Alignment / Context.getCharWidth()),
2436  SizeTy, SourceLocation());
2437  ImplicitCastExpr DesiredAlignment(ImplicitCastExpr::OnStack, AlignValT,
2438  CK_IntegralCast, &AlignmentLiteral,
2439  VK_PRValue, FPOptionsOverride());
2440 
2441  // Adjust placement args by prepending conjured size and alignment exprs.
2442  llvm::SmallVector<Expr *, 8> CallArgs;
2443  CallArgs.reserve(NumImplicitArgs + PlacementArgs.size());
2444  CallArgs.emplace_back(AllocationSize
2445  ? static_cast<Expr *>(&AllocationSizeLiteral)
2446  : &OpaqueAllocationSize);
2447  if (PassAlignment)
2448  CallArgs.emplace_back(&DesiredAlignment);
2449  CallArgs.insert(CallArgs.end(), PlacementArgs.begin(), PlacementArgs.end());
2450 
2451  DiagnoseSentinelCalls(OperatorNew, PlacementLParen, CallArgs);
2452 
2453  checkCall(OperatorNew, Proto, /*ThisArg=*/nullptr, CallArgs,
2454  /*IsMemberFunction=*/false, StartLoc, Range, CallType);
2455 
2456  // Warn if the type is over-aligned and is being allocated by (unaligned)
2457  // global operator new.
2458  if (PlacementArgs.empty() && !PassAlignment &&
2459  (OperatorNew->isImplicit() ||
2460  (OperatorNew->getBeginLoc().isValid() &&
2461  getSourceManager().isInSystemHeader(OperatorNew->getBeginLoc())))) {
2462  if (Alignment > NewAlignment)
2463  Diag(StartLoc, diag::warn_overaligned_type)
2464  << AllocType
2465  << unsigned(Alignment / Context.getCharWidth())
2466  << unsigned(NewAlignment / Context.getCharWidth());
2467  }
2468  }
2469 
2470  // Array 'new' can't have any initializers except empty parentheses.
2471  // Initializer lists are also allowed, in C++11. Rely on the parser for the
2472  // dialect distinction.
2473  if (ArraySize && !isLegalArrayNewInitializer(InitStyle, Initializer,
2474  getLangOpts().CPlusPlus20)) {
2475  SourceRange InitRange(Exprs.front()->getBeginLoc(),
2476  Exprs.back()->getEndLoc());
2477  Diag(StartLoc, diag::err_new_array_init_args) << InitRange;
2478  return ExprError();
2479  }
2480 
2481  // If we can perform the initialization, and we've not already done so,
2482  // do it now.
2483  if (!AllocType->isDependentType() &&
2484  !Expr::hasAnyTypeDependentArguments(Exprs)) {
2485  // The type we initialize is the complete type, including the array bound.
2486  QualType InitType;
2487  if (KnownArraySize)
2488  InitType = Context.getConstantArrayType(
2489  AllocType,
2490  llvm::APInt(Context.getTypeSize(Context.getSizeType()),
2491  *KnownArraySize),
2492  *ArraySize, ArraySizeModifier::Normal, 0);
2493  else if (ArraySize)
2494  InitType = Context.getIncompleteArrayType(AllocType,
2495  ArraySizeModifier::Normal, 0);
2496  else
2497  InitType = AllocType;
2498 
2499  InitializedEntity Entity
2500  = InitializedEntity::InitializeNew(StartLoc, InitType);
2501  InitializationSequence InitSeq(*this, Entity, Kind, Exprs);
2502  ExprResult FullInit = InitSeq.Perform(*this, Entity, Kind, Exprs);
2503  if (FullInit.isInvalid())
2504  return ExprError();
2505 
2506  // FullInit is our initializer; strip off CXXBindTemporaryExprs, because
2507  // we don't want the initialized object to be destructed.
2508  // FIXME: We should not create these in the first place.
2509  if (CXXBindTemporaryExpr *Binder =
2510  dyn_cast_or_null<CXXBindTemporaryExpr>(FullInit.get()))
2511  FullInit = Binder->getSubExpr();
2512 
2513  Initializer = FullInit.get();
2514 
2515  // FIXME: If we have a KnownArraySize, check that the array bound of the
2516  // initializer is no greater than that constant value.
2517 
2518  if (ArraySize && !*ArraySize) {
2519  auto *CAT = Context.getAsConstantArrayType(Initializer->getType());
2520  if (CAT) {
2521  // FIXME: Track that the array size was inferred rather than explicitly
2522  // specified.
2523  ArraySize = IntegerLiteral::Create(
2524  Context, CAT->getSize(), Context.getSizeType(), TypeRange.getEnd());
2525  } else {
2526  Diag(TypeRange.getEnd(), diag::err_new_array_size_unknown_from_init)
2527  << Initializer->getSourceRange();
2528  }
2529  }
2530  }
2531 
2532  // Mark the new and delete operators as referenced.
2533  if (OperatorNew) {
2534  if (DiagnoseUseOfDecl(OperatorNew, StartLoc))
2535  return ExprError();
2536  MarkFunctionReferenced(StartLoc, OperatorNew);
2537  if (getLangOpts().SYCLIsDevice &&
2538  OperatorNew->isReplaceableGlobalAllocationFunction())
2539  SYCL().DiagIfDeviceCode(StartLoc, diag::err_sycl_restrict)
2540  << SemaSYCL::KernelAllocateStorage;
2541  }
2542  if (OperatorDelete) {
2543  if (DiagnoseUseOfDecl(OperatorDelete, StartLoc))
2544  return ExprError();
2545  MarkFunctionReferenced(StartLoc, OperatorDelete);
2546  }
2547 
2548  return CXXNewExpr::Create(Context, UseGlobal, OperatorNew, OperatorDelete,
2549  PassAlignment, UsualArrayDeleteWantsSize,
2550  PlacementArgs, TypeIdParens, ArraySize, InitStyle,
2551  Initializer, ResultType, AllocTypeInfo, Range,
2552  DirectInitRange);
2553 }
2554 
2555 /// Checks that a type is suitable as the allocated type
2556 /// in a new-expression.
2557 bool Sema::CheckAllocatedType(QualType AllocType, SourceLocation Loc,
2558  SourceRange R) {
2559  // C++ 5.3.4p1: "[The] type shall be a complete object type, but not an
2560  // abstract class type or array thereof.
2561  if (AllocType->isFunctionType())
2562  return Diag(Loc, diag::err_bad_new_type)
2563  << AllocType << 0 << R;
2564  else if (AllocType->isReferenceType())
2565  return Diag(Loc, diag::err_bad_new_type)
2566  << AllocType << 1 << R;
2567  else if (!AllocType->isDependentType() &&
2568  RequireCompleteSizedType(
2569  Loc, AllocType, diag::err_new_incomplete_or_sizeless_type, R))
2570  return true;
2571  else if (RequireNonAbstractType(Loc, AllocType,
2572  diag::err_allocation_of_abstract_type))
2573  return true;
2574  else if (AllocType->isVariablyModifiedType())
2575  return Diag(Loc, diag::err_variably_modified_new_type)
2576  << AllocType;
2577  else if (AllocType.getAddressSpace() != LangAS::Default &&
2578  !getLangOpts().OpenCLCPlusPlus)
2579  return Diag(Loc, diag::err_address_space_qualified_new)
2580  << AllocType.getUnqualifiedType()
2581  << AllocType.getQualifiers().getAddressSpaceAttributePrintValue();
2582  else if (getLangOpts().ObjCAutoRefCount) {
2583  if (const ArrayType *AT = Context.getAsArrayType(AllocType)) {
2584  QualType BaseAllocType = Context.getBaseElementType(AT);
2585  if (BaseAllocType.getObjCLifetime() == Qualifiers::OCL_None &&
2586  BaseAllocType->isObjCLifetimeType())
2587  return Diag(Loc, diag::err_arc_new_array_without_ownership)
2588  << BaseAllocType;
2589  }
2590  }
2591 
2592  return false;
2593 }
2594 
2595 static bool resolveAllocationOverload(
2596  Sema &S, LookupResult &R, SourceRange Range, SmallVectorImpl<Expr *> &Args,
2597  bool &PassAlignment, FunctionDecl *&Operator,
2598  OverloadCandidateSet *AlignedCandidates, Expr *AlignArg, bool Diagnose) {
2599  OverloadCandidateSet Candidates(R.getNameLoc(),
2600  OverloadCandidateSet::CSK_Normal);
2601  for (LookupResult::iterator Alloc = R.begin(), AllocEnd = R.end();
2602  Alloc != AllocEnd; ++Alloc) {
2603  // Even member operator new/delete are implicitly treated as
2604  // static, so don't use AddMemberCandidate.
2605  NamedDecl *D = (*Alloc)->getUnderlyingDecl();
2606 
2607  if (FunctionTemplateDecl *FnTemplate = dyn_cast<FunctionTemplateDecl>(D)) {
2608  S.AddTemplateOverloadCandidate(FnTemplate, Alloc.getPair(),
2609  /*ExplicitTemplateArgs=*/nullptr, Args,
2610  Candidates,
2611  /*SuppressUserConversions=*/false);
2612  continue;
2613  }
2614 
2615  FunctionDecl *Fn = cast<FunctionDecl>(D);
2616  S.AddOverloadCandidate(Fn, Alloc.getPair(), Args, Candidates,
2617  /*SuppressUserConversions=*/false);
2618  }
2619 
2620  // Do the resolution.
2621  OverloadCandidateSet::iterator Best;
2622  switch (Candidates.BestViableFunction(S, R.getNameLoc(), Best)) {
2623  case OR_Success: {
2624  // Got one!
2625  FunctionDecl *FnDecl = Best->Function;
2626  if (S.CheckAllocationAccess(R.getNameLoc(), Range, R.getNamingClass(),
2627  Best->FoundDecl) == Sema::AR_inaccessible)
2628  return true;
2629 
2630  Operator = FnDecl;
2631  return false;
2632  }
2633 
2634  case OR_No_Viable_Function:
2635  // C++17 [expr.new]p13:
2636  // If no matching function is found and the allocated object type has
2637  // new-extended alignment, the alignment argument is removed from the
2638  // argument list, and overload resolution is performed again.
2639  if (PassAlignment) {
2640  PassAlignment = false;
2641  AlignArg = Args[1];
2642  Args.erase(Args.begin() + 1);
2643  return resolveAllocationOverload(S, R, Range, Args, PassAlignment,
2644  Operator, &Candidates, AlignArg,
2645  Diagnose);
2646  }
2647 
2648  // MSVC will fall back on trying to find a matching global operator new
2649  // if operator new[] cannot be found. Also, MSVC will leak by not
2650  // generating a call to operator delete or operator delete[], but we
2651  // will not replicate that bug.
2652  // FIXME: Find out how this interacts with the std::align_val_t fallback
2653  // once MSVC implements it.
2654  if (R.getLookupName().getCXXOverloadedOperator() == OO_Array_New &&
2655  S.Context.getLangOpts().MSVCCompat) {
2656  R.clear();
2657  R.setLookupName(S.Context.DeclarationNames.getCXXOperatorName(OO_New));
2658  S.LookupQualifiedName(R, S.Context.getTranslationUnitDecl());
2659  // FIXME: This will give bad diagnostics pointing at the wrong functions.
2660  return resolveAllocationOverload(S, R, Range, Args, PassAlignment,
2661  Operator, /*Candidates=*/nullptr,
2662  /*AlignArg=*/nullptr, Diagnose);
2663  }
2664 
2665  if (Diagnose) {
2666  // If this is an allocation of the form 'new (p) X' for some object
2667  // pointer p (or an expression that will decay to such a pointer),
2668  // diagnose the missing inclusion of <new>.
2669  if (!R.isClassLookup() && Args.size() == 2 &&
2670  (Args[1]->getType()->isObjectPointerType() ||
2671  Args[1]->getType()->isArrayType())) {
2672  S.Diag(R.getNameLoc(), diag::err_need_header_before_placement_new)
2673  << R.getLookupName() << Range;
2674  // Listing the candidates is unlikely to be useful; skip it.
2675  return true;
2676  }
2677 
2678  // Finish checking all candidates before we note any. This checking can
2679  // produce additional diagnostics so can't be interleaved with our
2680  // emission of notes.
2681  //
2682  // For an aligned allocation, separately check the aligned and unaligned
2683  // candidates with their respective argument lists.
2684  SmallVector<OverloadCandidate*, 32> Cands;
2685  SmallVector<OverloadCandidate*, 32> AlignedCands;
2686  llvm::SmallVector<Expr*, 4> AlignedArgs;
2687  if (AlignedCandidates) {
2688  auto IsAligned = [](OverloadCandidate &C) {
2689  return C.Function->getNumParams() > 1 &&
2690  C.Function->getParamDecl(1)->getType()->isAlignValT();
2691  };
2692  auto IsUnaligned = [&](OverloadCandidate &C) { return !IsAligned(C); };
2693 
2694  AlignedArgs.reserve(Args.size() + 1);
2695  AlignedArgs.push_back(Args[0]);
2696  AlignedArgs.push_back(AlignArg);
2697  AlignedArgs.append(Args.begin() + 1, Args.end());
2698  AlignedCands = AlignedCandidates->CompleteCandidates(
2699  S, OCD_AllCandidates, AlignedArgs, R.getNameLoc(), IsAligned);
2700 
2701  Cands = Candidates.CompleteCandidates(S, OCD_AllCandidates, Args,
2702  R.getNameLoc(), IsUnaligned);
2703  } else {
2704  Cands = Candidates.CompleteCandidates(S, OCD_AllCandidates, Args,
2705  R.getNameLoc());
2706  }
2707 
2708  S.Diag(R.getNameLoc(), diag::err_ovl_no_viable_function_in_call)
2709  << R.getLookupName() << Range;
2710  if (AlignedCandidates)
2711  AlignedCandidates->NoteCandidates(S, AlignedArgs, AlignedCands, "",
2712  R.getNameLoc());
2713  Candidates.NoteCandidates(S, Args, Cands, "", R.getNameLoc());
2714  }
2715  return true;
2716 
2717  case OR_Ambiguous:
2718  if (Diagnose) {
2719  Candidates.NoteCandidates(
2720  PartialDiagnosticAt(R.getNameLoc(),
2721  S.PDiag(diag::err_ovl_ambiguous_call)
2722  << R.getLookupName() << Range),
2723  S, OCD_AmbiguousCandidates, Args);
2724  }
2725  return true;
2726 
2727  case OR_Deleted: {
2728  if (Diagnose)
2729  S.DiagnoseUseOfDeletedFunction(R.getNameLoc(), Range, R.getLookupName(),
2730  Candidates, Best->Function, Args);
2731  return true;
2732  }
2733  }
2734  llvm_unreachable("Unreachable, bad result from BestViableFunction");
2735 }
2736 
2737 bool Sema::FindAllocationFunctions(SourceLocation StartLoc, SourceRange Range,
2738  AllocationFunctionScope NewScope,
2739  AllocationFunctionScope DeleteScope,
2740  QualType AllocType, bool IsArray,
2741  bool &PassAlignment, MultiExprArg PlaceArgs,
2742  FunctionDecl *&OperatorNew,
2743  FunctionDecl *&OperatorDelete,
2744  bool Diagnose) {
2745  // --- Choosing an allocation function ---
2746  // C++ 5.3.4p8 - 14 & 18
2747  // 1) If looking in AFS_Global scope for allocation functions, only look in
2748  // the global scope. Else, if AFS_Class, only look in the scope of the
2749  // allocated class. If AFS_Both, look in both.
2750  // 2) If an array size is given, look for operator new[], else look for
2751  // operator new.
2752  // 3) The first argument is always size_t. Append the arguments from the
2753  // placement form.
2754 
2755  SmallVector<Expr*, 8> AllocArgs;
2756  AllocArgs.reserve((PassAlignment ? 2 : 1) + PlaceArgs.size());
2757 
2758  // We don't care about the actual value of these arguments.
2759  // FIXME: Should the Sema create the expression and embed it in the syntax
2760  // tree? Or should the consumer just recalculate the value?
2761  // FIXME: Using a dummy value will interact poorly with attribute enable_if.
2762  QualType SizeTy = Context.getSizeType();
2763  unsigned SizeTyWidth = Context.getTypeSize(SizeTy);
2764  IntegerLiteral Size(Context, llvm::APInt::getZero(SizeTyWidth), SizeTy,
2765  SourceLocation());
2766  AllocArgs.push_back(&Size);
2767 
2768  QualType AlignValT = Context.VoidTy;
2769  if (PassAlignment) {
2770  DeclareGlobalNewDelete();
2771  AlignValT = Context.getTypeDeclType(getStdAlignValT());
2772  }
2773  CXXScalarValueInitExpr Align(AlignValT, nullptr, SourceLocation());
2774  if (PassAlignment)
2775  AllocArgs.push_back(&Align);
2776 
2777  AllocArgs.insert(AllocArgs.end(), PlaceArgs.begin(), PlaceArgs.end());
2778 
2779  // C++ [expr.new]p8:
2780  // If the allocated type is a non-array type, the allocation
2781  // function's name is operator new and the deallocation function's
2782  // name is operator delete. If the allocated type is an array
2783  // type, the allocation function's name is operator new[] and the
2784  // deallocation function's name is operator delete[].
2785  DeclarationName NewName = Context.DeclarationNames.getCXXOperatorName(
2786  IsArray ? OO_Array_New : OO_New);
2787 
2788  QualType AllocElemType = Context.getBaseElementType(AllocType);
2789 
2790  // Find the allocation function.
2791  {
2792  LookupResult R(*this, NewName, StartLoc, LookupOrdinaryName);
2793 
2794  // C++1z [expr.new]p9:
2795  // If the new-expression begins with a unary :: operator, the allocation
2796  // function's name is looked up in the global scope. Otherwise, if the
2797  // allocated type is a class type T or array thereof, the allocation
2798  // function's name is looked up in the scope of T.
2799  if (AllocElemType->isRecordType() && NewScope != AFS_Global)
2800  LookupQualifiedName(R, AllocElemType->getAsCXXRecordDecl());
2801 
2802  // We can see ambiguity here if the allocation function is found in
2803  // multiple base classes.
2804  if (R.isAmbiguous())
2805  return true;
2806 
2807  // If this lookup fails to find the name, or if the allocated type is not
2808  // a class type, the allocation function's name is looked up in the
2809  // global scope.
2810  if (R.empty()) {
2811  if (NewScope == AFS_Class)
2812  return true;
2813 
2814  LookupQualifiedName(R, Context.getTranslationUnitDecl());
2815  }
2816 
2817  if (getLangOpts().OpenCLCPlusPlus && R.empty()) {
2818  if (PlaceArgs.empty()) {
2819  Diag(StartLoc, diag::err_openclcxx_not_supported) << "default new";
2820  } else {
2821  Diag(StartLoc, diag::err_openclcxx_placement_new);
2822  }
2823  return true;
2824  }
2825 
2826  assert(!R.empty() && "implicitly declared allocation functions not found");
2827  assert(!R.isAmbiguous() && "global allocation functions are ambiguous");
2828 
2829  // We do our own custom access checks below.
2830  R.suppressDiagnostics();
2831 
2832  if (resolveAllocationOverload(*this, R, Range, AllocArgs, PassAlignment,
2833  OperatorNew, /*Candidates=*/nullptr,
2834  /*AlignArg=*/nullptr, Diagnose))
2835  return true;
2836  }
2837 
2838  // We don't need an operator delete if we're running under -fno-exceptions.
2839  if (!getLangOpts().Exceptions) {
2840  OperatorDelete = nullptr;
2841  return false;
2842  }
2843 
2844  // Note, the name of OperatorNew might have been changed from array to
2845  // non-array by resolveAllocationOverload.
2846  DeclarationName DeleteName = Context.DeclarationNames.getCXXOperatorName(
2847  OperatorNew->getDeclName().getCXXOverloadedOperator() == OO_Array_New
2848  ? OO_Array_Delete
2849  : OO_Delete);
2850 
2851  // C++ [expr.new]p19:
2852  //
2853  // If the new-expression begins with a unary :: operator, the
2854  // deallocation function's name is looked up in the global
2855  // scope. Otherwise, if the allocated type is a class type T or an
2856  // array thereof, the deallocation function's name is looked up in
2857  // the scope of T. If this lookup fails to find the name, or if
2858  // the allocated type is not a class type or array thereof, the
2859  // deallocation function's name is looked up in the global scope.
2860  LookupResult FoundDelete(*this, DeleteName, StartLoc, LookupOrdinaryName);
2861  if (AllocElemType->isRecordType() && DeleteScope != AFS_Global) {
2862  auto *RD =
2863  cast<CXXRecordDecl>(AllocElemType->castAs<RecordType>()->getDecl());
2864  LookupQualifiedName(FoundDelete, RD);
2865  }
2866  if (FoundDelete.isAmbiguous())
2867  return true; // FIXME: clean up expressions?
2868 
2869  // Filter out any destroying operator deletes. We can't possibly call such a
2870  // function in this context, because we're handling the case where the object
2871  // was not successfully constructed.
2872  // FIXME: This is not covered by the language rules yet.
2873  {
2874  LookupResult::Filter Filter = FoundDelete.makeFilter();
2875  while (Filter.hasNext()) {
2876  auto *FD = dyn_cast<FunctionDecl>(Filter.next()->getUnderlyingDecl());
2877  if (FD && FD->isDestroyingOperatorDelete())
2878  Filter.erase();
2879  }
2880  Filter.done();
2881  }
2882 
2883  bool FoundGlobalDelete = FoundDelete.empty();
2884  if (FoundDelete.empty()) {
2885  FoundDelete.clear(LookupOrdinaryName);
2886 
2887  if (DeleteScope == AFS_Class)
2888  return true;
2889 
2890  DeclareGlobalNewDelete();
2891  LookupQualifiedName(FoundDelete, Context.getTranslationUnitDecl());
2892  }
2893 
2894  FoundDelete.suppressDiagnostics();
2895 
2896  SmallVector<std::pair<DeclAccessPair,FunctionDecl*>, 2> Matches;
2897 
2898  // Whether we're looking for a placement operator delete is dictated
2899  // by whether we selected a placement operator new, not by whether
2900  // we had explicit placement arguments. This matters for things like
2901  // struct A { void *operator new(size_t, int = 0); ... };
2902  // A *a = new A()
2903  //
2904  // We don't have any definition for what a "placement allocation function"
2905  // is, but we assume it's any allocation function whose
2906  // parameter-declaration-clause is anything other than (size_t).
2907  //
2908  // FIXME: Should (size_t, std::align_val_t) also be considered non-placement?
2909  // This affects whether an exception from the constructor of an overaligned
2910  // type uses the sized or non-sized form of aligned operator delete.
2911  bool isPlacementNew = !PlaceArgs.empty() || OperatorNew->param_size() != 1 ||
2912  OperatorNew->isVariadic();
2913 
2914  if (isPlacementNew) {
2915  // C++ [expr.new]p20:
2916  // A declaration of a placement deallocation function matches the
2917  // declaration of a placement allocation function if it has the
2918  // same number of parameters and, after parameter transformations
2919  // (8.3.5), all parameter types except the first are
2920  // identical. [...]
2921  //
2922  // To perform this comparison, we compute the function type that
2923  // the deallocation function should have, and use that type both
2924  // for template argument deduction and for comparison purposes.
2925  QualType ExpectedFunctionType;
2926  {
2927  auto *Proto = OperatorNew->getType()->castAs<FunctionProtoType>();
2928 
2929  SmallVector<QualType, 4> ArgTypes;
2930  ArgTypes.push_back(Context.VoidPtrTy);
2931  for (unsigned I = 1, N = Proto->getNumParams(); I < N; ++I)
2932  ArgTypes.push_back(Proto->getParamType(I));
2933 
2934  FunctionProtoType::ExtProtoInfo EPI;
2935  // FIXME: This is not part of the standard's rule.
2936  EPI.Variadic = Proto->isVariadic();
2937 
2938  ExpectedFunctionType
2939  = Context.getFunctionType(Context.VoidTy, ArgTypes, EPI);
2940  }
2941 
2942  for (LookupResult::iterator D = FoundDelete.begin(),
2943  DEnd = FoundDelete.end();
2944  D != DEnd; ++D) {
2945  FunctionDecl *Fn = nullptr;
2946  if (FunctionTemplateDecl *FnTmpl =
2947  dyn_cast<FunctionTemplateDecl>((*D)->getUnderlyingDecl())) {
2948  // Perform template argument deduction to try to match the
2949  // expected function type.
2950  TemplateDeductionInfo Info(StartLoc);
2951  if (DeduceTemplateArguments(FnTmpl, nullptr, ExpectedFunctionType, Fn,
2952  Info) != TemplateDeductionResult::Success)
2953  continue;
2954  } else
2955  Fn = cast<FunctionDecl>((*D)->getUnderlyingDecl());
2956 
2957  if (Context.hasSameType(adjustCCAndNoReturn(Fn->getType(),
2958  ExpectedFunctionType,
2959  /*AdjustExcpetionSpec*/true),
2960  ExpectedFunctionType))
2961  Matches.push_back(std::make_pair(D.getPair(), Fn));
2962  }
2963 
2964  if (getLangOpts().CUDA)
2965  CUDA().EraseUnwantedMatches(getCurFunctionDecl(/*AllowLambda=*/true),
2966  Matches);
2967  } else {
2968  // C++1y [expr.new]p22:
2969  // For a non-placement allocation function, the normal deallocation
2970  // function lookup is used
2971  //
2972  // Per [expr.delete]p10, this lookup prefers a member operator delete
2973  // without a size_t argument, but prefers a non-member operator delete
2974  // with a size_t where possible (which it always is in this case).
2975  llvm::SmallVector<UsualDeallocFnInfo, 4> BestDeallocFns;
2976  UsualDeallocFnInfo Selected = resolveDeallocationOverload(
2977  *this, FoundDelete, /*WantSize*/ FoundGlobalDelete,
2978  /*WantAlign*/ hasNewExtendedAlignment(*this, AllocElemType),
2979  &BestDeallocFns);
2980  if (Selected)
2981  Matches.push_back(std::make_pair(Selected.Found, Selected.FD));
2982  else {
2983  // If we failed to select an operator, all remaining functions are viable
2984  // but ambiguous.
2985  for (auto Fn : BestDeallocFns)
2986  Matches.push_back(std::make_pair(Fn.Found, Fn.FD));
2987  }
2988  }
2989 
2990  // C++ [expr.new]p20:
2991  // [...] If the lookup finds a single matching deallocation
2992  // function, that function will be called; otherwise, no
2993  // deallocation function will be called.
2994  if (Matches.size() == 1) {
2995  OperatorDelete = Matches[0].second;
2996 
2997  // C++1z [expr.new]p23:
2998  // If the lookup finds a usual deallocation function (3.7.4.2)
2999  // with a parameter of type std::size_t and that function, considered
3000  // as a placement deallocation function, would have been
3001  // selected as a match for the allocation function, the program
3002  // is ill-formed.
3003  if (getLangOpts().CPlusPlus11 && isPlacementNew &&
3004  isNonPlacementDeallocationFunction(*this, OperatorDelete)) {
3005  UsualDeallocFnInfo Info(*this,
3006  DeclAccessPair::make(OperatorDelete, AS_public));
3007  // Core issue, per mail to core reflector, 2016-10-09:
3008  // If this is a member operator delete, and there is a corresponding
3009  // non-sized member operator delete, this isn't /really/ a sized
3010  // deallocation function, it just happens to have a size_t parameter.
3011  bool IsSizedDelete = Info.HasSizeT;
3012  if (IsSizedDelete && !FoundGlobalDelete) {
3013  auto NonSizedDelete =
3014  resolveDeallocationOverload(*this, FoundDelete, /*WantSize*/false,
3015  /*WantAlign*/Info.HasAlignValT);
3016  if (NonSizedDelete && !NonSizedDelete.HasSizeT &&
3017  NonSizedDelete.HasAlignValT == Info.HasAlignValT)
3018  IsSizedDelete = false;
3019  }
3020 
3021  if (IsSizedDelete) {
3022  SourceRange R = PlaceArgs.empty()
3023  ? SourceRange()
3024  : SourceRange(PlaceArgs.front()->getBeginLoc(),
3025  PlaceArgs.back()->getEndLoc());
3026  Diag(StartLoc, diag::err_placement_new_non_placement_delete) << R;
3027  if (!OperatorDelete->isImplicit())
3028  Diag(OperatorDelete->getLocation(), diag::note_previous_decl)
3029  << DeleteName;
3030  }
3031  }
3032 
3033  CheckAllocationAccess(StartLoc, Range, FoundDelete.getNamingClass(),
3034  Matches[0].first);
3035  } else if (!Matches.empty()) {
3036  // We found multiple suitable operators. Per [expr.new]p20, that means we
3037  // call no 'operator delete' function, but we should at least warn the user.
3038  // FIXME: Suppress this warning if the construction cannot throw.
3039  Diag(StartLoc, diag::warn_ambiguous_suitable_delete_function_found)
3040  << DeleteName << AllocElemType;
3041 
3042  for (auto &Match : Matches)
3043  Diag(Match.second->getLocation(),
3044  diag::note_member_declared_here) << DeleteName;
3045  }
3046 
3047  return false;
3048 }
3049 
3050 /// DeclareGlobalNewDelete - Declare the global forms of operator new and
3051 /// delete. These are:
3052 /// @code
3053 /// // C++03:
3054 /// void* operator new(std::size_t) throw(std::bad_alloc);
3055 /// void* operator new[](std::size_t) throw(std::bad_alloc);
3056 /// void operator delete(void *) throw();
3057 /// void operator delete[](void *) throw();
3058 /// // C++11:
3059 /// void* operator new(std::size_t);
3060 /// void* operator new[](std::size_t);
3061 /// void operator delete(void *) noexcept;
3062 /// void operator delete[](void *) noexcept;
3063 /// // C++1y:
3064 /// void* operator new(std::size_t);
3065 /// void* operator new[](std::size_t);
3066 /// void operator delete(void *) noexcept;
3067 /// void operator delete[](void *) noexcept;
3068 /// void operator delete(void *, std::size_t) noexcept;
3069 /// void operator delete[](void *, std::size_t) noexcept;
3070 /// @endcode
3071 /// Note that the placement and nothrow forms of new are *not* implicitly
3072 /// declared. Their use requires including <new>.
3073 void Sema::DeclareGlobalNewDelete() {
3074  if (GlobalNewDeleteDeclared)
3075  return;
3076 
3077  // The implicitly declared new and delete operators
3078  // are not supported in OpenCL.
3079  if (getLangOpts().OpenCLCPlusPlus)
3080  return;
3081 
3082  // C++ [basic.stc.dynamic.general]p2:
3083  // The library provides default definitions for the global allocation
3084  // and deallocation functions. Some global allocation and deallocation
3085  // functions are replaceable ([new.delete]); these are attached to the
3086  // global module ([module.unit]).
3087  if (getLangOpts().CPlusPlusModules && getCurrentModule())
3088  PushGlobalModuleFragment(SourceLocation());
3089 
3090  // C++ [basic.std.dynamic]p2:
3091  // [...] The following allocation and deallocation functions (18.4) are
3092  // implicitly declared in global scope in each translation unit of a
3093  // program
3094  //
3095  // C++03:
3096  // void* operator new(std::size_t) throw(std::bad_alloc);
3097  // void* operator new[](std::size_t) throw(std::bad_alloc);
3098  // void operator delete(void*) throw();
3099  // void operator delete[](void*) throw();
3100  // C++11:
3101  // void* operator new(std::size_t);
3102  // void* operator new[](std::size_t);
3103  // void operator delete(void*) noexcept;
3104  // void operator delete[](void*) noexcept;
3105  // C++1y:
3106  // void* operator new(std::size_t);
3107  // void* operator new[](std::size_t);
3108  // void operator delete(void*) noexcept;
3109  // void operator delete[](void*) noexcept;
3110  // void operator delete(void*, std::size_t) noexcept;
3111  // void operator delete[](void*, std::size_t) noexcept;
3112  //
3113  // These implicit declarations introduce only the function names operator
3114  // new, operator new[], operator delete, operator delete[].
3115  //
3116  // Here, we need to refer to std::bad_alloc, so we will implicitly declare
3117  // "std" or "bad_alloc" as necessary to form the exception specification.
3118  // However, we do not make these implicit declarations visible to name
3119  // lookup.
3120  if (!StdBadAlloc && !getLangOpts().CPlusPlus11) {
3121  // The "std::bad_alloc" class has not yet been declared, so build it
3122  // implicitly.
3123  StdBadAlloc = CXXRecordDecl::Create(
3124  Context, TagTypeKind::Class, getOrCreateStdNamespace(),
3125  SourceLocation(), SourceLocation(),
3126  &PP.getIdentifierTable().get("bad_alloc"), nullptr);
3127  getStdBadAlloc()->setImplicit(true);
3128 
3129  // The implicitly declared "std::bad_alloc" should live in global module
3130  // fragment.
3131  if (TheGlobalModuleFragment) {
3132  getStdBadAlloc()->setModuleOwnershipKind(
3133  Decl::ModuleOwnershipKind::ReachableWhenImported);
3134  getStdBadAlloc()->setLocalOwningModule(TheGlobalModuleFragment);
3135  }
3136  }
3137  if (!StdAlignValT && getLangOpts().AlignedAllocation) {
3138  // The "std::align_val_t" enum class has not yet been declared, so build it
3139  // implicitly.
3140  auto *AlignValT = EnumDecl::Create(
3141  Context, getOrCreateStdNamespace(), SourceLocation(), SourceLocation(),
3142  &PP.getIdentifierTable().get("align_val_t"), nullptr, true, true, true);
3143 
3144  // The implicitly declared "std::align_val_t" should live in global module
3145  // fragment.
3146  if (TheGlobalModuleFragment) {
3147  AlignValT->setModuleOwnershipKind(
3148  Decl::ModuleOwnershipKind::ReachableWhenImported);
3149  AlignValT->setLocalOwningModule(TheGlobalModuleFragment);
3150  }
3151 
3152  AlignValT->setIntegerType(Context.getSizeType());
3153  AlignValT->setPromotionType(Context.getSizeType());
3154  AlignValT->setImplicit(true);
3155 
3156  StdAlignValT = AlignValT;
3157  }
3158 
3159  GlobalNewDeleteDeclared = true;
3160 
3161  QualType VoidPtr = Context.getPointerType(Context.VoidTy);
3162  QualType SizeT = Context.getSizeType();
3163 
3164  auto DeclareGlobalAllocationFunctions = [&](OverloadedOperatorKind Kind,
3165  QualType Return, QualType Param) {
3166  llvm::SmallVector<QualType, 3> Params;
3167  Params.push_back(Param);
3168 
3169  // Create up to four variants of the function (sized/aligned).
3170  bool HasSizedVariant = getLangOpts().SizedDeallocation &&
3171  (Kind == OO_Delete || Kind == OO_Array_Delete);
3172  bool HasAlignedVariant = getLangOpts().AlignedAllocation;
3173 
3174  int NumSizeVariants = (HasSizedVariant ? 2 : 1);
3175  int NumAlignVariants = (HasAlignedVariant ? 2 : 1);
3176  for (int Sized = 0; Sized < NumSizeVariants; ++Sized) {
3177  if (Sized)
3178  Params.push_back(SizeT);
3179 
3180  for (int Aligned = 0; Aligned < NumAlignVariants; ++Aligned) {
3181  if (Aligned)
3182  Params.push_back(Context.getTypeDeclType(getStdAlignValT()));
3183 
3184  DeclareGlobalAllocationFunction(
3185  Context.DeclarationNames.getCXXOperatorName(Kind), Return, Params);
3186 
3187  if (Aligned)
3188  Params.pop_back();
3189  }
3190  }
3191  };
3192 
3193  DeclareGlobalAllocationFunctions(OO_New, VoidPtr, SizeT);
3194  DeclareGlobalAllocationFunctions(OO_Array_New, VoidPtr, SizeT);
3195  DeclareGlobalAllocationFunctions(OO_Delete, Context.VoidTy, VoidPtr);
3196  DeclareGlobalAllocationFunctions(OO_Array_Delete, Context.VoidTy, VoidPtr);
3197 
3198  if (getLangOpts().CPlusPlusModules && getCurrentModule())
3199  PopGlobalModuleFragment();
3200 }
3201 
3202 /// DeclareGlobalAllocationFunction - Declares a single implicit global
3203 /// allocation function if it doesn't already exist.
3204 void Sema::DeclareGlobalAllocationFunction(DeclarationName Name,
3205  QualType Return,
3206  ArrayRef<QualType> Params) {
3207  DeclContext *GlobalCtx = Context.getTranslationUnitDecl();
3208 
3209  // Check if this function is already declared.
3210  DeclContext::lookup_result R = GlobalCtx->lookup(Name);
3211  for (DeclContext::lookup_iterator Alloc = R.begin(), AllocEnd = R.end();
3212  Alloc != AllocEnd; ++Alloc) {
3213  // Only look at non-template functions, as it is the predefined,
3214  // non-templated allocation function we are trying to declare here.
3215  if (FunctionDecl *Func = dyn_cast<FunctionDecl>(*Alloc)) {
3216  if (Func->getNumParams() == Params.size()) {
3217  llvm::SmallVector<QualType, 3> FuncParams;
3218  for (auto *P : Func->parameters())
3219  FuncParams.push_back(
3220  Context.getCanonicalType(P->getType().getUnqualifiedType()));
3221  if (llvm::ArrayRef(FuncParams) == Params) {
3222  // Make the function visible to name lookup, even if we found it in
3223  // an unimported module. It either is an implicitly-declared global
3224  // allocation function, or is suppressing that function.
3225  Func->setVisibleDespiteOwningModule();
3226  return;
3227  }
3228  }
3229  }
3230  }
3231 
3232  FunctionProtoType::ExtProtoInfo EPI(Context.getDefaultCallingConvention(
3233  /*IsVariadic=*/false, /*IsCXXMethod=*/false, /*IsBuiltin=*/true));
3234 
3235  QualType BadAllocType;
3236  bool HasBadAllocExceptionSpec
3237  = (Name.getCXXOverloadedOperator() == OO_New ||
3238  Name.getCXXOverloadedOperator() == OO_Array_New);
3239  if (HasBadAllocExceptionSpec) {
3240  if (!getLangOpts().CPlusPlus11) {
3241  BadAllocType = Context.getTypeDeclType(getStdBadAlloc());
3242  assert(StdBadAlloc && "Must have std::bad_alloc declared");
3243  EPI.ExceptionSpec.Type = EST_Dynamic;
3244  EPI.ExceptionSpec.Exceptions = llvm::ArrayRef(BadAllocType);
3245  }
3246  if (getLangOpts().NewInfallible) {
3247  EPI.ExceptionSpec.Type = EST_DynamicNone;
3248  }
3249  } else {
3250  EPI.ExceptionSpec =
3251  getLangOpts().CPlusPlus11 ? EST_BasicNoexcept : EST_DynamicNone;
3252  }
3253 
3254  auto CreateAllocationFunctionDecl = [&](Attr *ExtraAttr) {
3255  QualType FnType = Context.getFunctionType(Return, Params, EPI);
3256  FunctionDecl *Alloc = FunctionDecl::Create(
3257  Context, GlobalCtx, SourceLocation(), SourceLocation(), Name, FnType,
3258  /*TInfo=*/nullptr, SC_None, getCurFPFeatures().isFPConstrained(), false,
3259  true);
3260  Alloc->setImplicit();
3261  // Global allocation functions should always be visible.
3262  Alloc->setVisibleDespiteOwningModule();
3263 
3264  if (HasBadAllocExceptionSpec && getLangOpts().NewInfallible &&
3265  !getLangOpts().CheckNew)
3266  Alloc->addAttr(
3267  ReturnsNonNullAttr::CreateImplicit(Context, Alloc->getLocation()));
3268 
3269  // C++ [basic.stc.dynamic.general]p2:
3270  // The library provides default definitions for the global allocation
3271  // and deallocation functions. Some global allocation and deallocation
3272  // functions are replaceable ([new.delete]); these are attached to the
3273  // global module ([module.unit]).
3274  //
3275  // In the language wording, these functions are attched to the global
3276  // module all the time. But in the implementation, the global module
3277  // is only meaningful when we're in a module unit. So here we attach
3278  // these allocation functions to global module conditionally.
3279  if (TheGlobalModuleFragment) {
3280  Alloc->setModuleOwnershipKind(
3281  Decl::ModuleOwnershipKind::ReachableWhenImported);
3282  Alloc->setLocalOwningModule(TheGlobalModuleFragment);
3283  }
3284 
3285  if (LangOpts.hasGlobalAllocationFunctionVisibility())
3286  Alloc->addAttr(VisibilityAttr::CreateImplicit(
3287  Context, LangOpts.hasHiddenGlobalAllocationFunctionVisibility()
3288  ? VisibilityAttr::Hidden
3289  : LangOpts.hasProtectedGlobalAllocationFunctionVisibility()
3290  ? VisibilityAttr::Protected
3291  : VisibilityAttr::Default));
3292 
3293  llvm::SmallVector<ParmVarDecl *, 3> ParamDecls;
3294  for (QualType T : Params) {
3295  ParamDecls.push_back(ParmVarDecl::Create(
3296  Context, Alloc, SourceLocation(), SourceLocation(), nullptr, T,
3297  /*TInfo=*/nullptr, SC_None, nullptr));
3298  ParamDecls.back()->setImplicit();
3299  }
3300  Alloc->setParams(ParamDecls);
3301  if (ExtraAttr)
3302  Alloc->addAttr(ExtraAttr);
3303  AddKnownFunctionAttributesForReplaceableGlobalAllocationFunction(Alloc);
3304  Context.getTranslationUnitDecl()->addDecl(Alloc);
3305  IdResolver.tryAddTopLevelDecl(Alloc, Name);
3306  };
3307 
3308  if (!LangOpts.CUDA)
3309  CreateAllocationFunctionDecl(nullptr);
3310  else {
3311  // Host and device get their own declaration so each can be
3312  // defined or re-declared independently.
3313  CreateAllocationFunctionDecl(CUDAHostAttr::CreateImplicit(Context));
3314  CreateAllocationFunctionDecl(CUDADeviceAttr::CreateImplicit(Context));
3315  }
3316 }
3317 
3318 FunctionDecl *Sema::FindUsualDeallocationFunction(SourceLocation StartLoc,
3319  bool CanProvideSize,
3320  bool Overaligned,
3321  DeclarationName Name) {
3322  DeclareGlobalNewDelete();
3323 
3324  LookupResult FoundDelete(*this, Name, StartLoc, LookupOrdinaryName);
3325  LookupQualifiedName(FoundDelete, Context.getTranslationUnitDecl());
3326 
3327  // FIXME: It's possible for this to result in ambiguity, through a
3328  // user-declared variadic operator delete or the enable_if attribute. We
3329  // should probably not consider those cases to be usual deallocation
3330  // functions. But for now we just make an arbitrary choice in that case.
3331  auto Result = resolveDeallocationOverload(*this, FoundDelete, CanProvideSize,
3332  Overaligned);
3333  assert(Result.FD && "operator delete missing from global scope?");
3334  return Result.FD;
3335 }
3336 
3337 FunctionDecl *Sema::FindDeallocationFunctionForDestructor(SourceLocation Loc,
3338  CXXRecordDecl *RD) {
3339  DeclarationName Name = Context.DeclarationNames.getCXXOperatorName(OO_Delete);
3340 
3341  FunctionDecl *OperatorDelete = nullptr;
3342  if (FindDeallocationFunction(Loc, RD, Name, OperatorDelete))
3343  return nullptr;
3344  if (OperatorDelete)
3345  return OperatorDelete;
3346 
3347  // If there's no class-specific operator delete, look up the global
3348  // non-array delete.
3349  return FindUsualDeallocationFunction(
3350  Loc, true, hasNewExtendedAlignment(*this, Context.getRecordType(RD)),
3351  Name);
3352 }
3353 
3354 bool Sema::FindDeallocationFunction(SourceLocation StartLoc, CXXRecordDecl *RD,
3355  DeclarationName Name,
3356  FunctionDecl *&Operator, bool Diagnose,
3357  bool WantSize, bool WantAligned) {
3358  LookupResult Found(*this, Name, StartLoc, LookupOrdinaryName);
3359  // Try to find operator delete/operator delete[] in class scope.
3360  LookupQualifiedName(Found, RD);
3361 
3362  if (Found.isAmbiguous())
3363  return true;
3364 
3365  Found.suppressDiagnostics();
3366 
3367  bool Overaligned =
3368  WantAligned || hasNewExtendedAlignment(*this, Context.getRecordType(RD));
3369 
3370  // C++17 [expr.delete]p10:
3371  // If the deallocation functions have class scope, the one without a
3372  // parameter of type std::size_t is selected.
3373  llvm::SmallVector<UsualDeallocFnInfo, 4> Matches;
3374  resolveDeallocationOverload(*this, Found, /*WantSize*/ WantSize,
3375  /*WantAlign*/ Overaligned, &Matches);
3376 
3377  // If we could find an overload, use it.
3378  if (Matches.size() == 1) {
3379  Operator = cast<CXXMethodDecl>(Matches[0].FD);
3380 
3381  // FIXME: DiagnoseUseOfDecl?
3382  if (Operator->isDeleted()) {
3383  if (Diagnose) {
3384  StringLiteral *Msg = Operator->getDeletedMessage();
3385  Diag(StartLoc, diag::err_deleted_function_use)
3386  << (Msg != nullptr) << (Msg ? Msg->getString() : StringRef());
3387  NoteDeletedFunction(Operator);
3388  }
3389  return true;
3390  }
3391 
3392  if (CheckAllocationAccess(StartLoc, SourceRange(), Found.getNamingClass(),
3393  Matches[0].Found, Diagnose) == AR_inaccessible)
3394  return true;
3395 
3396  return false;
3397  }
3398 
3399  // We found multiple suitable operators; complain about the ambiguity.
3400  // FIXME: The standard doesn't say to do this; it appears that the intent
3401  // is that this should never happen.
3402  if (!Matches.empty()) {
3403  if (Diagnose) {
3404  Diag(StartLoc, diag::err_ambiguous_suitable_delete_member_function_found)
3405  << Name << RD;
3406  for (auto &Match : Matches)
3407  Diag(Match.FD->getLocation(), diag::note_member_declared_here) << Name;
3408  }
3409  return true;
3410  }
3411 
3412  // We did find operator delete/operator delete[] declarations, but
3413  // none of them were suitable.
3414  if (!Found.empty()) {
3415  if (Diagnose) {
3416  Diag(StartLoc, diag::err_no_suitable_delete_member_function_found)
3417  << Name << RD;
3418 
3419  for (NamedDecl *D : Found)
3420  Diag(D->getUnderlyingDecl()->getLocation(),
3421  diag::note_member_declared_here) << Name;
3422  }
3423  return true;
3424  }
3425 
3426  Operator = nullptr;
3427  return false;
3428 }
3429 
3430 namespace {
3431 /// Checks whether delete-expression, and new-expression used for
3432 /// initializing deletee have the same array form.
3433 class MismatchingNewDeleteDetector {
3434 public:
3435  enum MismatchResult {
3436  /// Indicates that there is no mismatch or a mismatch cannot be proven.
3437  NoMismatch,
3438  /// Indicates that variable is initialized with mismatching form of \a new.
3439  VarInitMismatches,
3440  /// Indicates that member is initialized with mismatching form of \a new.
3441  MemberInitMismatches,
3442  /// Indicates that 1 or more constructors' definitions could not been
3443  /// analyzed, and they will be checked again at the end of translation unit.
3444  AnalyzeLater
3445  };
3446 
3447  /// \param EndOfTU True, if this is the final analysis at the end of
3448  /// translation unit. False, if this is the initial analysis at the point
3449  /// delete-expression was encountered.
3450  explicit MismatchingNewDeleteDetector(bool EndOfTU)
3451  : Field(nullptr), IsArrayForm(false), EndOfTU(EndOfTU),
3452  HasUndefinedConstructors(false) {}
3453 
3454  /// Checks whether pointee of a delete-expression is initialized with
3455  /// matching form of new-expression.
3456  ///
3457  /// If return value is \c VarInitMismatches or \c MemberInitMismatches at the
3458  /// point where delete-expression is encountered, then a warning will be
3459  /// issued immediately. If return value is \c AnalyzeLater at the point where
3460  /// delete-expression is seen, then member will be analyzed at the end of
3461  /// translation unit. \c AnalyzeLater is returned iff at least one constructor
3462  /// couldn't be analyzed. If at least one constructor initializes the member
3463  /// with matching type of new, the return value is \c NoMismatch.
3464  MismatchResult analyzeDeleteExpr(const CXXDeleteExpr *DE);
3465  /// Analyzes a class member.
3466  /// \param Field Class member to analyze.
3467  /// \param DeleteWasArrayForm Array form-ness of the delete-expression used
3468  /// for deleting the \p Field.
3469  MismatchResult analyzeField(FieldDecl *Field, bool DeleteWasArrayForm);
3470  FieldDecl *Field;
3471  /// List of mismatching new-expressions used for initialization of the pointee
3472  llvm::SmallVector<const CXXNewExpr *, 4> NewExprs;
3473  /// Indicates whether delete-expression was in array form.
3474  bool IsArrayForm;
3475 
3476 private:
3477  const bool EndOfTU;
3478  /// Indicates that there is at least one constructor without body.
3479  bool HasUndefinedConstructors;
3480  /// Returns \c CXXNewExpr from given initialization expression.
3481  /// \param E Expression used for initializing pointee in delete-expression.
3482  /// E can be a single-element \c InitListExpr consisting of new-expression.
3483  const CXXNewExpr *getNewExprFromInitListOrExpr(const Expr *E);
3484  /// Returns whether member is initialized with mismatching form of
3485  /// \c new either by the member initializer or in-class initialization.
3486  ///
3487  /// If bodies of all constructors are not visible at the end of translation
3488  /// unit or at least one constructor initializes member with the matching
3489  /// form of \c new, mismatch cannot be proven, and this function will return
3490  /// \c NoMismatch.
3491  MismatchResult analyzeMemberExpr(const MemberExpr *ME);
3492  /// Returns whether variable is initialized with mismatching form of
3493  /// \c new.
3494  ///
3495  /// If variable is initialized with matching form of \c new or variable is not
3496  /// initialized with a \c new expression, this function will return true.
3497  /// If variable is initialized with mismatching form of \c new, returns false.
3498  /// \param D Variable to analyze.
3499  bool hasMatchingVarInit(const DeclRefExpr *D);
3500  /// Checks whether the constructor initializes pointee with mismatching
3501  /// form of \c new.
3502  ///
3503  /// Returns true, if member is initialized with matching form of \c new in
3504  /// member initializer list. Returns false, if member is initialized with the
3505  /// matching form of \c new in this constructor's initializer or given
3506  /// constructor isn't defined at the point where delete-expression is seen, or
3507  /// member isn't initialized by the constructor.
3508  bool hasMatchingNewInCtor(const CXXConstructorDecl *CD);
3509  /// Checks whether member is initialized with matching form of
3510  /// \c new in member initializer list.
3511  bool hasMatchingNewInCtorInit(const CXXCtorInitializer *CI);
3512  /// Checks whether member is initialized with mismatching form of \c new by
3513  /// in-class initializer.
3514  MismatchResult analyzeInClassInitializer();
3515 };
3516 }
3517 
3518 MismatchingNewDeleteDetector::MismatchResult
3519 MismatchingNewDeleteDetector::analyzeDeleteExpr(const CXXDeleteExpr *DE) {
3520  NewExprs.clear();
3521  assert(DE && "Expected delete-expression");
3522  IsArrayForm = DE->isArrayForm();
3523  const Expr *E = DE->getArgument()->IgnoreParenImpCasts();
3524  if (const MemberExpr *ME = dyn_cast<const MemberExpr>(E)) {
3525  return analyzeMemberExpr(ME);
3526  } else if (const DeclRefExpr *D = dyn_cast<const DeclRefExpr>(E)) {
3527  if (!hasMatchingVarInit(D))
3528  return VarInitMismatches;
3529  }
3530  return NoMismatch;
3531 }
3532 
3533 const CXXNewExpr *
3534 MismatchingNewDeleteDetector::getNewExprFromInitListOrExpr(const Expr *E) {
3535  assert(E != nullptr && "Expected a valid initializer expression");
3536  E = E->IgnoreParenImpCasts();
3537  if (const InitListExpr *ILE = dyn_cast<const InitListExpr>(E)) {
3538  if (ILE->getNumInits() == 1)
3539  E = dyn_cast<const CXXNewExpr>(ILE->getInit(0)->IgnoreParenImpCasts());
3540  }
3541 
3542  return dyn_cast_or_null<const CXXNewExpr>(E);
3543 }
3544 
3545 bool MismatchingNewDeleteDetector::hasMatchingNewInCtorInit(
3546  const CXXCtorInitializer *CI) {
3547  const CXXNewExpr *NE = nullptr;
3548  if (Field == CI->getMember() &&
3549  (NE = getNewExprFromInitListOrExpr(CI->getInit()))) {
3550  if (NE->isArray() == IsArrayForm)
3551  return true;
3552  else
3553  NewExprs.push_back(NE);
3554  }
3555  return false;
3556 }
3557 
3558 bool MismatchingNewDeleteDetector::hasMatchingNewInCtor(
3559  const CXXConstructorDecl *CD) {
3560  if (CD->isImplicit())
3561  return false;
3562  const FunctionDecl *Definition = CD;
3563  if (!CD->isThisDeclarationADefinition() && !CD->isDefined(Definition)) {
3564  HasUndefinedConstructors = true;
3565  return EndOfTU;
3566  }
3567  for (const auto *CI : cast<const CXXConstructorDecl>(Definition)->inits()) {
3568  if (hasMatchingNewInCtorInit(CI))
3569  return true;
3570  }
3571  return false;
3572 }
3573 
3574 MismatchingNewDeleteDetector::MismatchResult
3575 MismatchingNewDeleteDetector::analyzeInClassInitializer() {
3576  assert(Field != nullptr && "This should be called only for members");
3577  const Expr *InitExpr = Field->getInClassInitializer();
3578  if (!InitExpr)
3579  return EndOfTU ? NoMismatch : AnalyzeLater;
3580  if (const CXXNewExpr *NE = getNewExprFromInitListOrExpr(InitExpr)) {
3581  if (NE->isArray() != IsArrayForm) {
3582  NewExprs.push_back(NE);
3583  return MemberInitMismatches;
3584  }
3585  }
3586  return NoMismatch;
3587 }
3588 
3589 MismatchingNewDeleteDetector::MismatchResult
3590 MismatchingNewDeleteDetector::analyzeField(FieldDecl *Field,
3591  bool DeleteWasArrayForm) {
3592  assert(Field != nullptr && "Analysis requires a valid class member.");
3593  this->Field = Field;
3594  IsArrayForm = DeleteWasArrayForm;
3595  const CXXRecordDecl *RD = cast<const CXXRecordDecl>(Field->getParent());
3596  for (const auto *CD : RD->ctors()) {
3597  if (hasMatchingNewInCtor(CD))
3598  return NoMismatch;
3599  }
3600  if (HasUndefinedConstructors)
3601  return EndOfTU ? NoMismatch : AnalyzeLater;
3602  if (!NewExprs.empty())
3603  return MemberInitMismatches;
3604  return Field->hasInClassInitializer() ? analyzeInClassInitializer()
3605  : NoMismatch;
3606 }
3607 
3608 MismatchingNewDeleteDetector::MismatchResult
3609 MismatchingNewDeleteDetector::analyzeMemberExpr(const MemberExpr *ME) {
3610  assert(ME != nullptr && "Expected a member expression");
3611  if (FieldDecl *F = dyn_cast<FieldDecl>(ME->getMemberDecl()))
3612  return analyzeField(F, IsArrayForm);
3613  return NoMismatch;
3614 }
3615 
3616 bool MismatchingNewDeleteDetector::hasMatchingVarInit(const DeclRefExpr *D) {
3617  const CXXNewExpr *NE = nullptr;
3618  if (const VarDecl *VD = dyn_cast<const VarDecl>(D->getDecl())) {
3619  if (VD->hasInit() && (NE = getNewExprFromInitListOrExpr(VD->getInit())) &&
3620  NE->isArray() != IsArrayForm) {
3621  NewExprs.push_back(NE);
3622  }
3623  }
3624  return NewExprs.empty();
3625 }
3626 
3627 static void
3628 DiagnoseMismatchedNewDelete(Sema &SemaRef, SourceLocation DeleteLoc,
3629  const MismatchingNewDeleteDetector &Detector) {
3630  SourceLocation EndOfDelete = SemaRef.getLocForEndOfToken(DeleteLoc);
3631  FixItHint H;
3632  if (!Detector.IsArrayForm)
3633  H = FixItHint::CreateInsertion(EndOfDelete, "[]");
3634  else {
3635  SourceLocation RSquare = Lexer::findLocationAfterToken(
3636  DeleteLoc, tok::l_square, SemaRef.getSourceManager(),
3637  SemaRef.getLangOpts(), true);
3638  if (RSquare.isValid())
3639  H = FixItHint::CreateRemoval(SourceRange(EndOfDelete, RSquare));
3640  }
3641  SemaRef.Diag(DeleteLoc, diag::warn_mismatched_delete_new)
3642  << Detector.IsArrayForm << H;
3643 
3644  for (const auto *NE : Detector.NewExprs)
3645  SemaRef.Diag(NE->getExprLoc(), diag::note_allocated_here)
3646  << Detector.IsArrayForm;
3647 }
3648 
3649 void Sema::AnalyzeDeleteExprMismatch(const CXXDeleteExpr *DE) {
3650  if (Diags.isIgnored(diag::warn_mismatched_delete_new, SourceLocation()))
3651  return;
3652  MismatchingNewDeleteDetector Detector(/*EndOfTU=*/false);
3653  switch (Detector.analyzeDeleteExpr(DE)) {
3654  case MismatchingNewDeleteDetector::VarInitMismatches:
3655  case MismatchingNewDeleteDetector::MemberInitMismatches: {
3656  DiagnoseMismatchedNewDelete(*this, DE->getBeginLoc(), Detector);
3657  break;
3658  }
3659  case MismatchingNewDeleteDetector::AnalyzeLater: {
3660  DeleteExprs[Detector.Field].push_back(
3661  std::make_pair(DE->getBeginLoc(), DE->isArrayForm()));
3662  break;
3663  }
3664  case MismatchingNewDeleteDetector::NoMismatch:
3665  break;
3666  }
3667 }
3668 
3669 void Sema::AnalyzeDeleteExprMismatch(FieldDecl *Field, SourceLocation DeleteLoc,
3670  bool DeleteWasArrayForm) {
3671  MismatchingNewDeleteDetector Detector(/*EndOfTU=*/true);
3672  switch (Detector.analyzeField(Field, DeleteWasArrayForm)) {
3673  case MismatchingNewDeleteDetector::VarInitMismatches:
3674  llvm_unreachable("This analysis should have been done for class members.");
3675  case MismatchingNewDeleteDetector::AnalyzeLater:
3676  llvm_unreachable("Analysis cannot be postponed any point beyond end of "
3677  "translation unit.");
3678  case MismatchingNewDeleteDetector::MemberInitMismatches:
3679  DiagnoseMismatchedNewDelete(*this, DeleteLoc, Detector);
3680  break;
3681  case MismatchingNewDeleteDetector::NoMismatch:
3682  break;
3683  }
3684 }
3685 
3686 /// ActOnCXXDelete - Parsed a C++ 'delete' expression (C++ 5.3.5), as in:
3687 /// @code ::delete ptr; @endcode
3688 /// or
3689 /// @code delete [] ptr; @endcode
3690 ExprResult
3691 Sema::ActOnCXXDelete(SourceLocation StartLoc, bool UseGlobal,
3692  bool ArrayForm, Expr *ExE) {
3693  // C++ [expr.delete]p1:
3694  // The operand shall have a pointer type, or a class type having a single
3695  // non-explicit conversion function to a pointer type. The result has type
3696  // void.
3697  //
3698  // DR599 amends "pointer type" to "pointer to object type" in both cases.
3699 
3700  ExprResult Ex = ExE;
3701  FunctionDecl *OperatorDelete = nullptr;
3702  bool ArrayFormAsWritten = ArrayForm;
3703  bool UsualArrayDeleteWantsSize = false;
3704 
3705  if (!Ex.get()->isTypeDependent()) {
3706  // Perform lvalue-to-rvalue cast, if needed.
3707  Ex = DefaultLvalueConversion(Ex.get());
3708  if (Ex.isInvalid())
3709  return ExprError();
3710 
3711  QualType Type = Ex.get()->getType();
3712 
3713  class DeleteConverter : public ContextualImplicitConverter {
3714  public:
3715  DeleteConverter() : ContextualImplicitConverter(false, true) {}
3716 
3717  bool match(QualType ConvType) override {
3718  // FIXME: If we have an operator T* and an operator void*, we must pick
3719  // the operator T*.
3720  if (const PointerType *ConvPtrType = ConvType->getAs<PointerType>())
3721  if (ConvPtrType->getPointeeType()->isIncompleteOrObjectType())
3722  return true;
3723  return false;
3724  }
3725 
3726  SemaDiagnosticBuilder diagnoseNoMatch(Sema &S, SourceLocation Loc,
3727  QualType T) override {
3728  return S.Diag(Loc, diag::err_delete_operand) << T;
3729  }
3730 
3731  SemaDiagnosticBuilder diagnoseIncomplete(Sema &S, SourceLocation Loc,
3732  QualType T) override {
3733  return S.Diag(Loc, diag::err_delete_incomplete_class_type) << T;
3734  }
3735 
3736  SemaDiagnosticBuilder diagnoseExplicitConv(Sema &S, SourceLocation Loc,
3737  QualType T,
3738  QualType ConvTy) override {
3739  return S.Diag(Loc, diag::err_delete_explicit_conversion) << T << ConvTy;
3740  }
3741 
3742  SemaDiagnosticBuilder noteExplicitConv(Sema &S, CXXConversionDecl *Conv,
3743  QualType ConvTy) override {
3744  return S.Diag(Conv->getLocation(), diag::note_delete_conversion)
3745  << ConvTy;
3746  }
3747 
3748  SemaDiagnosticBuilder diagnoseAmbiguous(Sema &S, SourceLocation Loc,
3749  QualType T) override {
3750  return S.Diag(Loc, diag::err_ambiguous_delete_operand) << T;
3751  }
3752 
3753  SemaDiagnosticBuilder noteAmbiguous(Sema &S, CXXConversionDecl *Conv,
3754  QualType ConvTy) override {
3755  return S.Diag(Conv->getLocation(), diag::note_delete_conversion)
3756  << ConvTy;
3757  }
3758 
3759  SemaDiagnosticBuilder diagnoseConversion(Sema &S, SourceLocation Loc,
3760  QualType T,
3761  QualType ConvTy) override {
3762  llvm_unreachable("conversion functions are permitted");
3763  }
3764  } Converter;
3765 
3766  Ex = PerformContextualImplicitConversion(StartLoc, Ex.get(), Converter);
3767  if (Ex.isInvalid())
3768  return ExprError();
3769  Type = Ex.get()->getType();
3770  if (!Converter.match(Type))
3771  // FIXME: PerformContextualImplicitConversion should return ExprError
3772  // itself in this case.
3773  return ExprError();
3774 
3775  QualType Pointee = Type->castAs<PointerType>()->getPointeeType();
3776  QualType PointeeElem = Context.getBaseElementType(Pointee);
3777 
3778  if (Pointee.getAddressSpace() != LangAS::Default &&
3779  !getLangOpts().OpenCLCPlusPlus)
3780  return Diag(Ex.get()->getBeginLoc(),
3781  diag::err_address_space_qualified_delete)
3782  << Pointee.getUnqualifiedType()
3783  << Pointee.getQualifiers().getAddressSpaceAttributePrintValue();
3784 
3785  CXXRecordDecl *PointeeRD = nullptr;
3786  if (Pointee->isVoidType() && !isSFINAEContext()) {
3787  // The C++ standard bans deleting a pointer to a non-object type, which
3788  // effectively bans deletion of "void*". However, most compilers support
3789  // this, so we treat it as a warning unless we're in a SFINAE context.
3790  Diag(StartLoc, diag::ext_delete_void_ptr_operand)
3791  << Type << Ex.get()->getSourceRange();
3792  } else if (Pointee->isFunctionType() || Pointee->isVoidType() ||
3793  Pointee->isSizelessType()) {
3794  return ExprError(Diag(StartLoc, diag::err_delete_operand)
3795  << Type << Ex.get()->getSourceRange());
3796  } else if (!Pointee->isDependentType()) {
3797  // FIXME: This can result in errors if the definition was imported from a
3798  // module but is hidden.
3799  if (!RequireCompleteType(StartLoc, Pointee,
3800  diag::warn_delete_incomplete, Ex.get())) {
3801  if (const RecordType *RT = PointeeElem->getAs<RecordType>())
3802  PointeeRD = cast<CXXRecordDecl>(RT->getDecl());
3803  }
3804  }
3805 
3806  if (Pointee->isArrayType() && !ArrayForm) {
3807  Diag(StartLoc, diag::warn_delete_array_type)
3808  << Type << Ex.get()->getSourceRange()
3809  << FixItHint::CreateInsertion(getLocForEndOfToken(StartLoc), "[]");
3810  ArrayForm = true;
3811  }
3812 
3813  DeclarationName DeleteName = Context.DeclarationNames.getCXXOperatorName(
3814  ArrayForm ? OO_Array_Delete : OO_Delete);
3815 
3816  if (PointeeRD) {
3817  if (!UseGlobal &&
3818  FindDeallocationFunction(StartLoc, PointeeRD, DeleteName,
3819  OperatorDelete))
3820  return ExprError();
3821 
3822  // If we're allocating an array of records, check whether the
3823  // usual operator delete[] has a size_t parameter.
3824  if (ArrayForm) {
3825  // If the user specifically asked to use the global allocator,
3826  // we'll need to do the lookup into the class.
3827  if (UseGlobal)
3828  UsualArrayDeleteWantsSize =
3829  doesUsualArrayDeleteWantSize(*this, StartLoc, PointeeElem);
3830 
3831  // Otherwise, the usual operator delete[] should be the
3832  // function we just found.
3833  else if (OperatorDelete && isa<CXXMethodDecl>(OperatorDelete))
3834  UsualArrayDeleteWantsSize =
3835  UsualDeallocFnInfo(*this,
3836  DeclAccessPair::make(OperatorDelete, AS_public))
3837  .HasSizeT;
3838  }
3839 
3840  if (!PointeeRD->hasIrrelevantDestructor())
3841  if (CXXDestructorDecl *Dtor = LookupDestructor(PointeeRD)) {
3842  MarkFunctionReferenced(StartLoc,
3843  const_cast<CXXDestructorDecl*>(Dtor));
3844  if (DiagnoseUseOfDecl(Dtor, StartLoc))
3845  return ExprError();
3846  }
3847 
3848  CheckVirtualDtorCall(PointeeRD->getDestructor(), StartLoc,
3849  /*IsDelete=*/true, /*CallCanBeVirtual=*/true,
3850  /*WarnOnNonAbstractTypes=*/!ArrayForm,
3851  SourceLocation());
3852  }
3853 
3854  if (!OperatorDelete) {
3855  if (getLangOpts().OpenCLCPlusPlus) {
3856  Diag(StartLoc, diag::err_openclcxx_not_supported) << "default delete";
3857  return ExprError();
3858  }
3859 
3860  bool IsComplete = isCompleteType(StartLoc, Pointee);
3861  bool CanProvideSize =
3862  IsComplete && (!ArrayForm || UsualArrayDeleteWantsSize ||
3863  Pointee.isDestructedType());
3864  bool Overaligned = hasNewExtendedAlignment(*this, Pointee);
3865 
3866  // Look for a global declaration.
3867  OperatorDelete = FindUsualDeallocationFunction(StartLoc, CanProvideSize,
3868  Overaligned, DeleteName);
3869  }
3870 
3871  MarkFunctionReferenced(StartLoc, OperatorDelete);
3872 
3873  // Check access and ambiguity of destructor if we're going to call it.
3874  // Note that this is required even for a virtual delete.
3875  bool IsVirtualDelete = false;
3876  if (PointeeRD) {
3877  if (CXXDestructorDecl *Dtor = LookupDestructor(PointeeRD)) {
3878  CheckDestructorAccess(Ex.get()->getExprLoc(), Dtor,
3879  PDiag(diag::err_access_dtor) << PointeeElem);
3880  IsVirtualDelete = Dtor->isVirtual();
3881  }
3882  }
3883 
3884  DiagnoseUseOfDecl(OperatorDelete, StartLoc);
3885 
3886  // Convert the operand to the type of the first parameter of operator
3887  // delete. This is only necessary if we selected a destroying operator
3888  // delete that we are going to call (non-virtually); converting to void*
3889  // is trivial and left to AST consumers to handle.
3890  QualType ParamType = OperatorDelete->getParamDecl(0)->getType();
3891  if (!IsVirtualDelete && !ParamType->getPointeeType()->isVoidType()) {
3892  Qualifiers Qs = Pointee.getQualifiers();
3893  if (Qs.hasCVRQualifiers()) {
3894  // Qualifiers are irrelevant to this conversion; we're only looking
3895  // for access and ambiguity.
3896  Qs.removeCVRQualifiers();
3897  QualType Unqual = Context.getPointerType(
3898  Context.getQualifiedType(Pointee.getUnqualifiedType(), Qs));
3899  Ex = ImpCastExprToType(Ex.get(), Unqual, CK_NoOp);
3900  }
3901  Ex = PerformImplicitConversion(Ex.get(), ParamType, AA_Passing);
3902  if (Ex.isInvalid())
3903  return ExprError();
3904  }
3905  }
3906 
3907  CXXDeleteExpr *Result = new (Context) CXXDeleteExpr(
3908  Context.VoidTy, UseGlobal, ArrayForm, ArrayFormAsWritten,
3909  UsualArrayDeleteWantsSize, OperatorDelete, Ex.get(), StartLoc);
3910  AnalyzeDeleteExprMismatch(Result);
3911  return Result;
3912 }
3913 
3914 static bool resolveBuiltinNewDeleteOverload(Sema &S, CallExpr *TheCall,
3915  bool IsDelete,
3916  FunctionDecl *&Operator) {
3917 
3918  DeclarationName NewName = S.Context.DeclarationNames.getCXXOperatorName(
3919  IsDelete ? OO_Delete : OO_New);
3920 
3921  LookupResult R(S, NewName, TheCall->getBeginLoc(), Sema::LookupOrdinaryName);
3922  S.LookupQualifiedName(R, S.Context.getTranslationUnitDecl());
3923  assert(!R.empty() && "implicitly declared allocation functions not found");
3924  assert(!R.isAmbiguous() && "global allocation functions are ambiguous");
3925 
3926  // We do our own custom access checks below.
3927  R.suppressDiagnostics();
3928 
3929  SmallVector<Expr *, 8> Args(TheCall->arguments());
3930  OverloadCandidateSet Candidates(R.getNameLoc(),
3931  OverloadCandidateSet::CSK_Normal);
3932  for (LookupResult::iterator FnOvl = R.begin(), FnOvlEnd = R.end();
3933  FnOvl != FnOvlEnd; ++FnOvl) {
3934  // Even member operator new/delete are implicitly treated as
3935  // static, so don't use AddMemberCandidate.
3936  NamedDecl *D = (*FnOvl)->getUnderlyingDecl();
3937 
3938  if (FunctionTemplateDecl *FnTemplate = dyn_cast<FunctionTemplateDecl>(D)) {
3939  S.AddTemplateOverloadCandidate(FnTemplate, FnOvl.getPair(),
3940  /*ExplicitTemplateArgs=*/nullptr, Args,
3941  Candidates,
3942  /*SuppressUserConversions=*/false);
3943  continue;
3944  }
3945 
3946  FunctionDecl *Fn = cast<FunctionDecl>(D);
3947  S.AddOverloadCandidate(Fn, FnOvl.getPair(), Args, Candidates,
3948  /*SuppressUserConversions=*/false);
3949  }
3950 
3951  SourceRange Range = TheCall->getSourceRange();
3952 
3953  // Do the resolution.
3954  OverloadCandidateSet::iterator Best;
3955  switch (Candidates.BestViableFunction(S, R.getNameLoc(), Best)) {
3956  case OR_Success: {
3957  // Got one!
3958  FunctionDecl *FnDecl = Best->Function;
3959  assert(R.getNamingClass() == nullptr &&
3960  "class members should not be considered");
3961 
3962  if (!FnDecl->isReplaceableGlobalAllocationFunction()) {
3963  S.Diag(R.getNameLoc(), diag::err_builtin_operator_new_delete_not_usual)
3964  << (IsDelete ? 1 : 0) << Range;
3965  S.Diag(FnDecl->getLocation(), diag::note_non_usual_function_declared_here)
3966  << R.getLookupName() << FnDecl->getSourceRange();
3967  return true;
3968  }
3969 
3970  Operator = FnDecl;
3971  return false;
3972  }
3973 
3974  case OR_No_Viable_Function:
3975  Candidates.NoteCandidates(
3976  PartialDiagnosticAt(R.getNameLoc(),
3977  S.PDiag(diag::err_ovl_no_viable_function_in_call)
3978  << R.getLookupName() << Range),
3979  S, OCD_AllCandidates, Args);
3980  return true;
3981 
3982  case OR_Ambiguous:
3983  Candidates.NoteCandidates(
3984  PartialDiagnosticAt(R.getNameLoc(),
3985  S.PDiag(diag::err_ovl_ambiguous_call)
3986  << R.getLookupName() << Range),
