3987  S, OCD_AmbiguousCandidates, Args);
3988  return true;
3989 
3990  case OR_Deleted:
3991  S.DiagnoseUseOfDeletedFunction(R.getNameLoc(), Range, R.getLookupName(),
3992  Candidates, Best->Function, Args);
3993  return true;
3994  }
3995  llvm_unreachable("Unreachable, bad result from BestViableFunction");
3996 }
3997 
3998 ExprResult Sema::BuiltinOperatorNewDeleteOverloaded(ExprResult TheCallResult,
3999  bool IsDelete) {
4000  CallExpr *TheCall = cast<CallExpr>(TheCallResult.get());
4001  if (!getLangOpts().CPlusPlus) {
4002  Diag(TheCall->getExprLoc(), diag::err_builtin_requires_language)
4003  << (IsDelete ? "__builtin_operator_delete" : "__builtin_operator_new")
4004  << "C++";
4005  return ExprError();
4006  }
4007  // CodeGen assumes it can find the global new and delete to call,
4008  // so ensure that they are declared.
4009  DeclareGlobalNewDelete();
4010 
4011  FunctionDecl *OperatorNewOrDelete = nullptr;
4012  if (resolveBuiltinNewDeleteOverload(*this, TheCall, IsDelete,
4013  OperatorNewOrDelete))
4014  return ExprError();
4015  assert(OperatorNewOrDelete && "should be found");
4016 
4017  DiagnoseUseOfDecl(OperatorNewOrDelete, TheCall->getExprLoc());
4018  MarkFunctionReferenced(TheCall->getExprLoc(), OperatorNewOrDelete);
4019 
4020  TheCall->setType(OperatorNewOrDelete->getReturnType());
4021  for (unsigned i = 0; i != TheCall->getNumArgs(); ++i) {
4022  QualType ParamTy = OperatorNewOrDelete->getParamDecl(i)->getType();
4023  InitializedEntity Entity =
4024  InitializedEntity::InitializeParameter(Context, ParamTy, false);
4025  ExprResult Arg = PerformCopyInitialization(
4026  Entity, TheCall->getArg(i)->getBeginLoc(), TheCall->getArg(i));
4027  if (Arg.isInvalid())
4028  return ExprError();
4029  TheCall->setArg(i, Arg.get());
4030  }
4031  auto Callee = dyn_cast<ImplicitCastExpr>(TheCall->getCallee());
4032  assert(Callee && Callee->getCastKind() == CK_BuiltinFnToFnPtr &&
4033  "Callee expected to be implicit cast to a builtin function pointer");
4034  Callee->setType(OperatorNewOrDelete->getType());
4035 
4036  return TheCallResult;
4037 }
4038 
4039 void Sema::CheckVirtualDtorCall(CXXDestructorDecl *dtor, SourceLocation Loc,
4040  bool IsDelete, bool CallCanBeVirtual,
4041  bool WarnOnNonAbstractTypes,
4042  SourceLocation DtorLoc) {
4043  if (!dtor || dtor->isVirtual() || !CallCanBeVirtual || isUnevaluatedContext())
4044  return;
4045 
4046  // C++ [expr.delete]p3:
4047  // In the first alternative (delete object), if the static type of the
4048  // object to be deleted is different from its dynamic type, the static
4049  // type shall be a base class of the dynamic type of the object to be
4050  // deleted and the static type shall have a virtual destructor or the
4051  // behavior is undefined.
4052  //
4053  const CXXRecordDecl *PointeeRD = dtor->getParent();
4054  // Note: a final class cannot be derived from, no issue there
4055  if (!PointeeRD->isPolymorphic() || PointeeRD->hasAttr<FinalAttr>())
4056  return;
4057 
4058  // If the superclass is in a system header, there's nothing that can be done.
4059  // The `delete` (where we emit the warning) can be in a system header,
4060  // what matters for this warning is where the deleted type is defined.
4061  if (getSourceManager().isInSystemHeader(PointeeRD->getLocation()))
4062  return;
4063 
4064  QualType ClassType = dtor->getFunctionObjectParameterType();
4065  if (PointeeRD->isAbstract()) {
4066  // If the class is abstract, we warn by default, because we're
4067  // sure the code has undefined behavior.
4068  Diag(Loc, diag::warn_delete_abstract_non_virtual_dtor) << (IsDelete ? 0 : 1)
4069  << ClassType;
4070  } else if (WarnOnNonAbstractTypes) {
4071  // Otherwise, if this is not an array delete, it's a bit suspect,
4072  // but not necessarily wrong.
4073  Diag(Loc, diag::warn_delete_non_virtual_dtor) << (IsDelete ? 0 : 1)
4074  << ClassType;
4075  }
4076  if (!IsDelete) {
4077  std::string TypeStr;
4078  ClassType.getAsStringInternal(TypeStr, getPrintingPolicy());
4079  Diag(DtorLoc, diag::note_delete_non_virtual)
4080  << FixItHint::CreateInsertion(DtorLoc, TypeStr + "::");
4081  }
4082 }

4084 Sema::ConditionResult Sema::ActOnConditionVariable(Decl *ConditionVar,
4085  SourceLocation StmtLoc,
4086  ConditionKind CK) {
4087  ExprResult E =
4088  CheckConditionVariable(cast<VarDecl>(ConditionVar), StmtLoc, CK);
4089  if (E.isInvalid())
4090  return ConditionError();
4091  return ConditionResult(*this, ConditionVar, MakeFullExpr(E.get(), StmtLoc),
4092  CK == ConditionKind::ConstexprIf);
4093 }
4094 
4095 /// Check the use of the given variable as a C++ condition in an if,
4096 /// while, do-while, or switch statement.
4097 ExprResult Sema::CheckConditionVariable(VarDecl *ConditionVar,
4098  SourceLocation StmtLoc,
4099  ConditionKind CK) {
4100  if (ConditionVar->isInvalidDecl())
4101  return ExprError();
4102 
4103  QualType T = ConditionVar->getType();
4104 
4105  // C++ [stmt.select]p2:
4106  // The declarator shall not specify a function or an array.
4107  if (T->isFunctionType())
4108  return ExprError(Diag(ConditionVar->getLocation(),
4109  diag::err_invalid_use_of_function_type)
4110  << ConditionVar->getSourceRange());
4111  else if (T->isArrayType())
4112  return ExprError(Diag(ConditionVar->getLocation(),
4113  diag::err_invalid_use_of_array_type)
4114  << ConditionVar->getSourceRange());
4115 
4116  ExprResult Condition = BuildDeclRefExpr(
4117  ConditionVar, ConditionVar->getType().getNonReferenceType(), VK_LValue,
4118  ConditionVar->getLocation());
4119 
4120  switch (CK) {
4121  case ConditionKind::Boolean:
4122  return CheckBooleanCondition(StmtLoc, Condition.get());
4123 
4124  case ConditionKind::ConstexprIf:
4125  return CheckBooleanCondition(StmtLoc, Condition.get(), true);
4126 
4127  case ConditionKind::Switch:
4128  return CheckSwitchCondition(StmtLoc, Condition.get());
4129  }
4130 
4131  llvm_unreachable("unexpected condition kind");
4132 }
4133 
4134 /// CheckCXXBooleanCondition - Returns true if a conversion to bool is invalid.
4135 ExprResult Sema::CheckCXXBooleanCondition(Expr *CondExpr, bool IsConstexpr) {
4136  // C++11 6.4p4:
4137  // The value of a condition that is an initialized declaration in a statement
4138  // other than a switch statement is the value of the declared variable
4139  // implicitly converted to type bool. If that conversion is ill-formed, the
4140  // program is ill-formed.
4141  // The value of a condition that is an expression is the value of the
4142  // expression, implicitly converted to bool.
4143  //
4144  // C++23 8.5.2p2
4145  // If the if statement is of the form if constexpr, the value of the condition
4146  // is contextually converted to bool and the converted expression shall be
4147  // a constant expression.
4148  //
4149 
4150  ExprResult E = PerformContextuallyConvertToBool(CondExpr);
4151  if (!IsConstexpr || E.isInvalid() || E.get()->isValueDependent())
4152  return E;
4153 
4154  // FIXME: Return this value to the caller so they don't need to recompute it.
4155  llvm::APSInt Cond;
4156  E = VerifyIntegerConstantExpression(
4157  E.get(), &Cond,
4158  diag::err_constexpr_if_condition_expression_is_not_constant);
4159  return E;
4160 }
4161 
4162 /// Helper function to determine whether this is the (deprecated) C++
4163 /// conversion from a string literal to a pointer to non-const char or
4164 /// non-const wchar_t (for narrow and wide string literals,
4165 /// respectively).
4166 bool
4167 Sema::IsStringLiteralToNonConstPointerConversion(Expr *From, QualType ToType) {
4168  // Look inside the implicit cast, if it exists.
4169  if (ImplicitCastExpr *Cast = dyn_cast<ImplicitCastExpr>(From))
4170  From = Cast->getSubExpr();
4171 
4172  // A string literal (2.13.4) that is not a wide string literal can
4173  // be converted to an rvalue of type "pointer to char"; a wide
4174  // string literal can be converted to an rvalue of type "pointer
4175  // to wchar_t" (C++ 4.2p2).
4176  if (StringLiteral *StrLit = dyn_cast<StringLiteral>(From->IgnoreParens()))
4177  if (const PointerType *ToPtrType = ToType->getAs<PointerType>())
4178  if (const BuiltinType *ToPointeeType
4179  = ToPtrType->getPointeeType()->getAs<BuiltinType>()) {
4180  // This conversion is considered only when there is an
4181  // explicit appropriate pointer target type (C++ 4.2p2).
4182  if (!ToPtrType->getPointeeType().hasQualifiers()) {
4183  switch (StrLit->getKind()) {
4184  case StringLiteralKind::UTF8:
4185  case StringLiteralKind::UTF16:
4186  case StringLiteralKind::UTF32:
4187  // We don't allow UTF literals to be implicitly converted
4188  break;
4189  case StringLiteralKind::Ordinary:
4190  return (ToPointeeType->getKind() == BuiltinType::Char_U ||
4191  ToPointeeType->getKind() == BuiltinType::Char_S);
4192  case StringLiteralKind::Wide:
4193  return Context.typesAreCompatible(Context.getWideCharType(),
4194  QualType(ToPointeeType, 0));
4195  case StringLiteralKind::Unevaluated:
4196  assert(false && "Unevaluated string literal in expression");
4197  break;
4198  }
4199  }
4200  }
4201 
4202  return false;
4203 }
4204 
4205 static ExprResult BuildCXXCastArgument(Sema &S,
4206  SourceLocation CastLoc,
4207  QualType Ty,
4208  CastKind Kind,
4209  CXXMethodDecl *Method,
4210  DeclAccessPair FoundDecl,
4211  bool HadMultipleCandidates,
4212  Expr *From) {
4213  switch (Kind) {
4214  default: llvm_unreachable("Unhandled cast kind!");
4215  case CK_ConstructorConversion: {
4216  CXXConstructorDecl *Constructor = cast<CXXConstructorDecl>(Method);
4217  SmallVector<Expr*, 8> ConstructorArgs;
4218 
4219  if (S.RequireNonAbstractType(CastLoc, Ty,
4220  diag::err_allocation_of_abstract_type))
4221  return ExprError();
4222 
4223  if (S.CompleteConstructorCall(Constructor, Ty, From, CastLoc,
4224  ConstructorArgs))
4225  return ExprError();
4226 
4227  S.CheckConstructorAccess(CastLoc, Constructor, FoundDecl,
4228  InitializedEntity::InitializeTemporary(Ty));
4229  if (S.DiagnoseUseOfDecl(Method, CastLoc))
4230  return ExprError();
4231 
4232  ExprResult Result = S.BuildCXXConstructExpr(
4233  CastLoc, Ty, FoundDecl, cast<CXXConstructorDecl>(Method),
4234  ConstructorArgs, HadMultipleCandidates,
4235  /*ListInit*/ false, /*StdInitListInit*/ false, /*ZeroInit*/ false,
4236  CXXConstructionKind::Complete, SourceRange());
4237  if (Result.isInvalid())
4238  return ExprError();
4239 
4240  return S.MaybeBindToTemporary(Result.getAs<Expr>());
4241  }
4242 
4243  case CK_UserDefinedConversion: {
4244  assert(!From->getType()->isPointerType() && "Arg can't have pointer type!");
4245 
4246  S.CheckMemberOperatorAccess(CastLoc, From, /*arg*/ nullptr, FoundDecl);
4247  if (S.DiagnoseUseOfDecl(Method, CastLoc))
4248  return ExprError();
4249 
4250  // Create an implicit call expr that calls it.
4251  CXXConversionDecl *Conv = cast<CXXConversionDecl>(Method);
4252  ExprResult Result = S.BuildCXXMemberCallExpr(From, FoundDecl, Conv,
4253  HadMultipleCandidates);
4254  if (Result.isInvalid())
4255  return ExprError();
4256  // Record usage of conversion in an implicit cast.
4257  Result = ImplicitCastExpr::Create(S.Context, Result.get()->getType(),
4258  CK_UserDefinedConversion, Result.get(),
4259  nullptr, Result.get()->getValueKind(),
4260  S.CurFPFeatureOverrides());
4261 
4262  return S.MaybeBindToTemporary(Result.get());
4263  }
4264  }
4265 }
4266 
4267 /// PerformImplicitConversion - Perform an implicit conversion of the
4268 /// expression From to the type ToType using the pre-computed implicit
4269 /// conversion sequence ICS. Returns the converted
4270 /// expression. Action is the kind of conversion we're performing,
4271 /// used in the error message.
4272 ExprResult
4273 Sema::PerformImplicitConversion(Expr *From, QualType ToType,
4274  const ImplicitConversionSequence &ICS,
4275  AssignmentAction Action,
4276  CheckedConversionKind CCK) {
4277  // C++ [over.match.oper]p7: [...] operands of class type are converted [...]
4278  if (CCK == CheckedConversionKind::ForBuiltinOverloadedOp &&
4279  !From->getType()->isRecordType())
4280  return From;
4281 
4282  switch (ICS.getKind()) {
4283  case ImplicitConversionSequence::StandardConversion: {
4284  ExprResult Res = PerformImplicitConversion(From, ToType, ICS.Standard,
4285  Action, CCK);
4286  if (Res.isInvalid())
4287  return ExprError();
4288  From = Res.get();
4289  break;
4290  }
4291 
4292  case ImplicitConversionSequence::UserDefinedConversion: {
4293 
4294  FunctionDecl *FD = ICS.UserDefined.ConversionFunction;
4295  CastKind CastKind;
4296  QualType BeforeToType;
4297  assert(FD && "no conversion function for user-defined conversion seq");
4298  if (const CXXConversionDecl *Conv = dyn_cast<CXXConversionDecl>(FD)) {
4299  CastKind = CK_UserDefinedConversion;
4300 
4301  // If the user-defined conversion is specified by a conversion function,
4302  // the initial standard conversion sequence converts the source type to
4303  // the implicit object parameter of the conversion function.
4304  BeforeToType = Context.getTagDeclType(Conv->getParent());
4305  } else {
4306  const CXXConstructorDecl *Ctor = cast<CXXConstructorDecl>(FD);
4307  CastKind = CK_ConstructorConversion;
4308  // Do no conversion if dealing with ... for the first conversion.
4309  if (!ICS.UserDefined.EllipsisConversion) {
4310  // If the user-defined conversion is specified by a constructor, the
4311  // initial standard conversion sequence converts the source type to
4312  // the type required by the argument of the constructor
4313  BeforeToType = Ctor->getParamDecl(0)->getType().getNonReferenceType();
4314  }
4315  }
4316  // Watch out for ellipsis conversion.
4317  if (!ICS.UserDefined.EllipsisConversion) {
4318  ExprResult Res =
4319  PerformImplicitConversion(From, BeforeToType,
4320  ICS.UserDefined.Before, AA_Converting,
4321  CCK);
4322  if (Res.isInvalid())
4323  return ExprError();
4324  From = Res.get();
4325  }
4326 
4327  ExprResult CastArg = BuildCXXCastArgument(
4328  *this, From->getBeginLoc(), ToType.getNonReferenceType(), CastKind,
4329  cast<CXXMethodDecl>(FD), ICS.UserDefined.FoundConversionFunction,
4330  ICS.UserDefined.HadMultipleCandidates, From);
4331 
4332  if (CastArg.isInvalid())
4333  return ExprError();
4334 
4335  From = CastArg.get();
4336 
4337  // C++ [over.match.oper]p7:
4338  // [...] the second standard conversion sequence of a user-defined
4339  // conversion sequence is not applied.
4340  if (CCK == CheckedConversionKind::ForBuiltinOverloadedOp)
4341  return From;
4342 
4343  return PerformImplicitConversion(From, ToType, ICS.UserDefined.After,
4344  AA_Converting, CCK);
4345  }
4346 
4347  case ImplicitConversionSequence::AmbiguousConversion:
4348  ICS.DiagnoseAmbiguousConversion(*this, From->getExprLoc(),
4349  PDiag(diag::err_typecheck_ambiguous_condition)
4350  << From->getSourceRange());
4351  return ExprError();
4352 
4353  case ImplicitConversionSequence::EllipsisConversion:
4354  case ImplicitConversionSequence::StaticObjectArgumentConversion:
4355  llvm_unreachable("bad conversion");
4356 
4357  case ImplicitConversionSequence::BadConversion:
4358  Sema::AssignConvertType ConvTy =
4359  CheckAssignmentConstraints(From->getExprLoc(), ToType, From->getType());
4360  bool Diagnosed = DiagnoseAssignmentResult(
4361  ConvTy == Compatible ? Incompatible : ConvTy, From->getExprLoc(),
4362  ToType, From->getType(), From, Action);
4363  assert(Diagnosed && "failed to diagnose bad conversion"); (void)Diagnosed;
4364  return ExprError();
4365  }
4366 
4367  // Everything went well.
4368  return From;
4369 }
4370 
4371 /// PerformImplicitConversion - Perform an implicit conversion of the
4372 /// expression From to the type ToType by following the standard
4373 /// conversion sequence SCS. Returns the converted
4374 /// expression. Flavor is the context in which we're performing this
4375 /// conversion, for use in error messages.
4376 ExprResult
4377 Sema::PerformImplicitConversion(Expr *From, QualType ToType,
4378  const StandardConversionSequence& SCS,
4379  AssignmentAction Action,
4380  CheckedConversionKind CCK) {
4381  bool CStyle = (CCK == CheckedConversionKind::CStyleCast ||
4382  CCK == CheckedConversionKind::FunctionalCast);
4383 
4384  // Overall FIXME: we are recomputing too many types here and doing far too
4385  // much extra work. What this means is that we need to keep track of more
4386  // information that is computed when we try the implicit conversion initially,
4387  // so that we don't need to recompute anything here.
4388  QualType FromType = From->getType();
4389 
4390  if (SCS.CopyConstructor) {
4391  // FIXME: When can ToType be a reference type?
4392  assert(!ToType->isReferenceType());
4393  if (SCS.Second == ICK_Derived_To_Base) {
4394  SmallVector<Expr*, 8> ConstructorArgs;
4395  if (CompleteConstructorCall(
4396  cast<CXXConstructorDecl>(SCS.CopyConstructor), ToType, From,
4397  /*FIXME:ConstructLoc*/ SourceLocation(), ConstructorArgs))
4398  return ExprError();
4399  return BuildCXXConstructExpr(
4400  /*FIXME:ConstructLoc*/ SourceLocation(), ToType,
4401  SCS.FoundCopyConstructor, SCS.CopyConstructor, ConstructorArgs,
4402  /*HadMultipleCandidates*/ false,
4403  /*ListInit*/ false, /*StdInitListInit*/ false, /*ZeroInit*/ false,
4404  CXXConstructionKind::Complete, SourceRange());
4405  }
4406  return BuildCXXConstructExpr(
4407  /*FIXME:ConstructLoc*/ SourceLocation(), ToType,
4408  SCS.FoundCopyConstructor, SCS.CopyConstructor, From,
4409  /*HadMultipleCandidates*/ false,
4410  /*ListInit*/ false, /*StdInitListInit*/ false, /*ZeroInit*/ false,
4411  CXXConstructionKind::Complete, SourceRange());
4412  }
4413 
4414  // Resolve overloaded function references.
4415  if (Context.hasSameType(FromType, Context.OverloadTy)) {
4416  DeclAccessPair Found;
4417  FunctionDecl *Fn = ResolveAddressOfOverloadedFunction(From, ToType,
4418  true, Found);
4419  if (!Fn)
4420  return ExprError();
4421 
4422  if (DiagnoseUseOfDecl(Fn, From->getBeginLoc()))
4423  return ExprError();
4424 
4425  ExprResult Res = FixOverloadedFunctionReference(From, Found, Fn);
4426  if (Res.isInvalid())
4427  return ExprError();
4428 
4429  // We might get back another placeholder expression if we resolved to a
4430  // builtin.
4431  Res = CheckPlaceholderExpr(Res.get());
4432  if (Res.isInvalid())
4433  return ExprError();
4434 
4435  From = Res.get();
4436  FromType = From->getType();
4437  }
4438 
4439  // If we're converting to an atomic type, first convert to the corresponding
4440  // non-atomic type.
4441  QualType ToAtomicType;
4442  if (const AtomicType *ToAtomic = ToType->getAs<AtomicType>()) {
4443  ToAtomicType = ToType;
4444  ToType = ToAtomic->getValueType();
4445  }
4446 
4447  QualType InitialFromType = FromType;
4448  // Perform the first implicit conversion.
4449  switch (SCS.First) {
4450  case ICK_Identity:
4451  if (const AtomicType *FromAtomic = FromType->getAs<AtomicType>()) {
4452  FromType = FromAtomic->getValueType().getUnqualifiedType();
4453  From = ImplicitCastExpr::Create(Context, FromType, CK_AtomicToNonAtomic,
4454  From, /*BasePath=*/nullptr, VK_PRValue,
4455  FPOptionsOverride());
4456  }
4457  break;
4458 
4459  case ICK_Lvalue_To_Rvalue: {
4460  assert(From->getObjectKind() != OK_ObjCProperty);
4461  ExprResult FromRes = DefaultLvalueConversion(From);
4462  if (FromRes.isInvalid())
4463  return ExprError();
4464 
4465  From = FromRes.get();
4466  FromType = From->getType();
4467  break;
4468  }
4469 
4470  case ICK_Array_To_Pointer:
4471  FromType = Context.getArrayDecayedType(FromType);
4472  From = ImpCastExprToType(From, FromType, CK_ArrayToPointerDecay, VK_PRValue,
4473  /*BasePath=*/nullptr, CCK)
4474  .get();
4475  break;
4476 
4477  case ICK_HLSL_Array_RValue:
4478  FromType = Context.getArrayParameterType(FromType);
4479  From = ImpCastExprToType(From, FromType, CK_HLSLArrayRValue, VK_PRValue,
4480  /*BasePath=*/nullptr, CCK)
4481  .get();
4482  break;
4483 
4484  case ICK_Function_To_Pointer:
4485  FromType = Context.getPointerType(FromType);
4486  From = ImpCastExprToType(From, FromType, CK_FunctionToPointerDecay,
4487  VK_PRValue, /*BasePath=*/nullptr, CCK)
4488  .get();
4489  break;
4490 
4491  default:
4492  llvm_unreachable("Improper first standard conversion");
4493  }
4494 
4495  // Perform the second implicit conversion
4496  switch (SCS.Second) {
4497  case ICK_Identity:
4498  // C++ [except.spec]p5:
4499  // [For] assignment to and initialization of pointers to functions,
4500  // pointers to member functions, and references to functions: the
4501  // target entity shall allow at least the exceptions allowed by the
4502  // source value in the assignment or initialization.
4503  switch (Action) {
4504  case AA_Assigning:
4505  case AA_Initializing:
4506  // Note, function argument passing and returning are initialization.
4507  case AA_Passing:
4508  case AA_Returning:
4509  case AA_Sending:
4510  case AA_Passing_CFAudited:
4511  if (CheckExceptionSpecCompatibility(From, ToType))
4512  return ExprError();
4513  break;
4514 
4515  case AA_Casting:
4516  case AA_Converting:
4517  // Casts and implicit conversions are not initialization, so are not
4518  // checked for exception specification mismatches.
4519  break;
4520  }
4521  // Nothing else to do.
4522  break;
4523 
4524  case ICK_Integral_Promotion:
4525  case ICK_Integral_Conversion:
4526  if (ToType->isBooleanType()) {
4527  assert(FromType->castAs<EnumType>()->getDecl()->isFixed() &&
4528  SCS.Second == ICK_Integral_Promotion &&
4529  "only enums with fixed underlying type can promote to bool");
4530  From = ImpCastExprToType(From, ToType, CK_IntegralToBoolean, VK_PRValue,
4531  /*BasePath=*/nullptr, CCK)
4532  .get();
4533  } else {
4534  From = ImpCastExprToType(From, ToType, CK_IntegralCast, VK_PRValue,
4535  /*BasePath=*/nullptr, CCK)
4536  .get();
4537  }
4538  break;
4539 
4540  case ICK_Floating_Promotion:
4541  case ICK_Floating_Conversion:
4542  From = ImpCastExprToType(From, ToType, CK_FloatingCast, VK_PRValue,
4543  /*BasePath=*/nullptr, CCK)
4544  .get();
4545  break;
4546 
4547  case ICK_Complex_Promotion:
4548  case ICK_Complex_Conversion: {
4549  QualType FromEl = From->getType()->castAs<ComplexType>()->getElementType();
4550  QualType ToEl = ToType->castAs<ComplexType>()->getElementType();
4551  CastKind CK;
4552  if (FromEl->isRealFloatingType()) {
4553  if (ToEl->isRealFloatingType())
4554  CK = CK_FloatingComplexCast;
4555  else
4556  CK = CK_FloatingComplexToIntegralComplex;
4557  } else if (ToEl->isRealFloatingType()) {
4558  CK = CK_IntegralComplexToFloatingComplex;
4559  } else {
4560  CK = CK_IntegralComplexCast;
4561  }
4562  From = ImpCastExprToType(From, ToType, CK, VK_PRValue, /*BasePath=*/nullptr,
4563  CCK)
4564  .get();
4565  break;
4566  }
4567 
4568  case ICK_Floating_Integral:
4569  if (ToType->isRealFloatingType())
4570  From = ImpCastExprToType(From, ToType, CK_IntegralToFloating, VK_PRValue,
4571  /*BasePath=*/nullptr, CCK)
4572  .get();
4573  else
4574  From = ImpCastExprToType(From, ToType, CK_FloatingToIntegral, VK_PRValue,
4575  /*BasePath=*/nullptr, CCK)
4576  .get();
4577  break;
4578 
4579  case ICK_Fixed_Point_Conversion:
4580  assert((FromType->isFixedPointType() || ToType->isFixedPointType()) &&
4581  "Attempting implicit fixed point conversion without a fixed "
4582  "point operand");
4583  if (FromType->isFloatingType())
4584  From = ImpCastExprToType(From, ToType, CK_FloatingToFixedPoint,
4585  VK_PRValue,
4586  /*BasePath=*/nullptr, CCK).get();
4587  else if (ToType->isFloatingType())
4588  From = ImpCastExprToType(From, ToType, CK_FixedPointToFloating,
4589  VK_PRValue,
4590  /*BasePath=*/nullptr, CCK).get();
4591  else if (FromType->isIntegralType(Context))
4592  From = ImpCastExprToType(From, ToType, CK_IntegralToFixedPoint,
4593  VK_PRValue,
4594  /*BasePath=*/nullptr, CCK).get();
4595  else if (ToType->isIntegralType(Context))
4596  From = ImpCastExprToType(From, ToType, CK_FixedPointToIntegral,
4597  VK_PRValue,
4598  /*BasePath=*/nullptr, CCK).get();
4599  else if (ToType->isBooleanType())
4600  From = ImpCastExprToType(From, ToType, CK_FixedPointToBoolean,
4601  VK_PRValue,
4602  /*BasePath=*/nullptr, CCK).get();
4603  else
4604  From = ImpCastExprToType(From, ToType, CK_FixedPointCast,
4605  VK_PRValue,
4606  /*BasePath=*/nullptr, CCK).get();
4607  break;
4608 
4609  case ICK_Compatible_Conversion:
4610  From = ImpCastExprToType(From, ToType, CK_NoOp, From->getValueKind(),
4611  /*BasePath=*/nullptr, CCK).get();
4612  break;
4613 
4614  case ICK_Writeback_Conversion:
4615  case ICK_Pointer_Conversion: {
4616  if (SCS.IncompatibleObjC && Action != AA_Casting) {
4617  // Diagnose incompatible Objective-C conversions
4618  if (Action == AA_Initializing || Action == AA_Assigning)
4619  Diag(From->getBeginLoc(),
4620  diag::ext_typecheck_convert_incompatible_pointer)
4621  << ToType << From->getType() << Action << From->getSourceRange()
4622  << 0;
4623  else
4624  Diag(From->getBeginLoc(),
4625  diag::ext_typecheck_convert_incompatible_pointer)
4626  << From->getType() << ToType << Action << From->getSourceRange()
4627  << 0;
4628 
4629  if (From->getType()->isObjCObjectPointerType() &&
4630  ToType->isObjCObjectPointerType())
4631  EmitRelatedResultTypeNote(From);
4632  } else if (getLangOpts().allowsNonTrivialObjCLifetimeQualifiers() &&
4633  !CheckObjCARCUnavailableWeakConversion(ToType,
4634  From->getType())) {
4635  if (Action == AA_Initializing)
4636  Diag(From->getBeginLoc(), diag::err_arc_weak_unavailable_assign);
4637  else
4638  Diag(From->getBeginLoc(), diag::err_arc_convesion_of_weak_unavailable)
4639  << (Action == AA_Casting) << From->getType() << ToType
4640  << From->getSourceRange();
4641  }
4642 
4643  // Defer address space conversion to the third conversion.
4644  QualType FromPteeType = From->getType()->getPointeeType();
4645  QualType ToPteeType = ToType->getPointeeType();
4646  QualType NewToType = ToType;
4647  if (!FromPteeType.isNull() && !ToPteeType.isNull() &&
4648  FromPteeType.getAddressSpace() != ToPteeType.getAddressSpace()) {
4649  NewToType = Context.removeAddrSpaceQualType(ToPteeType);
4650  NewToType = Context.getAddrSpaceQualType(NewToType,
4651  FromPteeType.getAddressSpace());
4652  if (ToType->isObjCObjectPointerType())
4653  NewToType = Context.getObjCObjectPointerType(NewToType);
4654  else if (ToType->isBlockPointerType())
4655  NewToType = Context.getBlockPointerType(NewToType);
4656  else
4657  NewToType = Context.getPointerType(NewToType);
4658  }
4659 
4660  CastKind Kind;
4661  CXXCastPath BasePath;
4662  if (CheckPointerConversion(From, NewToType, Kind, BasePath, CStyle))
4663  return ExprError();
4664 
4665  // Make sure we extend blocks if necessary.
4666  // FIXME: doing this here is really ugly.
4667  if (Kind == CK_BlockPointerToObjCPointerCast) {
4668  ExprResult E = From;
4669  (void) PrepareCastToObjCObjectPointer(E);
4670  From = E.get();
4671  }
4672  if (getLangOpts().allowsNonTrivialObjCLifetimeQualifiers())
4673  CheckObjCConversion(SourceRange(), NewToType, From, CCK);
4674  From = ImpCastExprToType(From, NewToType, Kind, VK_PRValue, &BasePath, CCK)
4675  .get();
4676  break;
4677  }
4678 
4679  case ICK_Pointer_Member: {
4680  CastKind Kind;
4681  CXXCastPath BasePath;
4682  if (CheckMemberPointerConversion(From, ToType, Kind, BasePath, CStyle))
4683  return ExprError();
4684  if (CheckExceptionSpecCompatibility(From, ToType))
4685  return ExprError();
4686 
4687  // We may not have been able to figure out what this member pointer resolved
4688  // to up until this exact point. Attempt to lock-in it's inheritance model.
4689  if (Context.getTargetInfo().getCXXABI().isMicrosoft()) {
4690  (void)isCompleteType(From->getExprLoc(), From->getType());
4691  (void)isCompleteType(From->getExprLoc(), ToType);
4692  }
4693 
4694  From =
4695  ImpCastExprToType(From, ToType, Kind, VK_PRValue, &BasePath, CCK).get();
4696  break;
4697  }
4698 
4699  case ICK_Boolean_Conversion:
4700  // Perform half-to-boolean conversion via float.
4701  if (From->getType()->isHalfType()) {
4702  From = ImpCastExprToType(From, Context.FloatTy, CK_FloatingCast).get();
4703  FromType = Context.FloatTy;
4704  }
4705 
4706  From = ImpCastExprToType(From, Context.BoolTy,
4707  ScalarTypeToBooleanCastKind(FromType), VK_PRValue,
4708  /*BasePath=*/nullptr, CCK)
4709  .get();
4710  break;
4711 
4712  case ICK_Derived_To_Base: {
4713  CXXCastPath BasePath;
4714  if (CheckDerivedToBaseConversion(
4715  From->getType(), ToType.getNonReferenceType(), From->getBeginLoc(),
4716  From->getSourceRange(), &BasePath, CStyle))
4717  return ExprError();
4718 
4719  From = ImpCastExprToType(From, ToType.getNonReferenceType(),
4720  CK_DerivedToBase, From->getValueKind(),
4721  &BasePath, CCK).get();
4722  break;
4723  }
4724 
4725  case ICK_Vector_Conversion:
4726  From = ImpCastExprToType(From, ToType, CK_BitCast, VK_PRValue,
4727  /*BasePath=*/nullptr, CCK)
4728  .get();
4729  break;
4730 
4731  case ICK_SVE_Vector_Conversion:
4732  case ICK_RVV_Vector_Conversion:
4733  From = ImpCastExprToType(From, ToType, CK_BitCast, VK_PRValue,
4734  /*BasePath=*/nullptr, CCK)
4735  .get();
4736  break;
4737 
4738  case ICK_Vector_Splat: {
4739  // Vector splat from any arithmetic type to a vector.
4740  Expr *Elem = prepareVectorSplat(ToType, From).get();
4741  From = ImpCastExprToType(Elem, ToType, CK_VectorSplat, VK_PRValue,
4742  /*BasePath=*/nullptr, CCK)
4743  .get();
4744  break;
4745  }
4746 
4747  case ICK_Complex_Real:
4748  // Case 1. x -> _Complex y
4749  if (const ComplexType *ToComplex = ToType->getAs<ComplexType>()) {
4750  QualType ElType = ToComplex->getElementType();
4751  bool isFloatingComplex = ElType->isRealFloatingType();
4752 
4753  // x -> y
4754  if (Context.hasSameUnqualifiedType(ElType, From->getType())) {
4755  // do nothing
4756  } else if (From->getType()->isRealFloatingType()) {
4757  From = ImpCastExprToType(From, ElType,
4758  isFloatingComplex ? CK_FloatingCast : CK_FloatingToIntegral).get();
4759  } else {
4760  assert(From->getType()->isIntegerType());
4761  From = ImpCastExprToType(From, ElType,
4762  isFloatingComplex ? CK_IntegralToFloating : CK_IntegralCast).get();
4763  }
4764  // y -> _Complex y
4765  From = ImpCastExprToType(From, ToType,
4766  isFloatingComplex ? CK_FloatingRealToComplex
4767  : CK_IntegralRealToComplex).get();
4768 
4769  // Case 2. _Complex x -> y
4770  } else {
4771  auto *FromComplex = From->getType()->castAs<ComplexType>();
4772  QualType ElType = FromComplex->getElementType();
4773  bool isFloatingComplex = ElType->isRealFloatingType();
4774 
4775  // _Complex x -> x
4776  From = ImpCastExprToType(From, ElType,
4777  isFloatingComplex ? CK_FloatingComplexToReal
4778  : CK_IntegralComplexToReal,
4779  VK_PRValue, /*BasePath=*/nullptr, CCK)
4780  .get();
4781 
4782  // x -> y
4783  if (Context.hasSameUnqualifiedType(ElType, ToType)) {
4784  // do nothing
4785  } else if (ToType->isRealFloatingType()) {
4786  From = ImpCastExprToType(From, ToType,
4787  isFloatingComplex ? CK_FloatingCast
4788  : CK_IntegralToFloating,
4789  VK_PRValue, /*BasePath=*/nullptr, CCK)
4790  .get();
4791  } else {
4792  assert(ToType->isIntegerType());
4793  From = ImpCastExprToType(From, ToType,
4794  isFloatingComplex ? CK_FloatingToIntegral
4795  : CK_IntegralCast,
4796  VK_PRValue, /*BasePath=*/nullptr, CCK)
4797  .get();
4798  }
4799  }
4800  break;
4801 
4802  case ICK_Block_Pointer_Conversion: {
4803  LangAS AddrSpaceL =
4804  ToType->castAs<BlockPointerType>()->getPointeeType().getAddressSpace();
4805  LangAS AddrSpaceR =
4806  FromType->castAs<BlockPointerType>()->getPointeeType().getAddressSpace();
4807  assert(Qualifiers::isAddressSpaceSupersetOf(AddrSpaceL, AddrSpaceR) &&
4808  "Invalid cast");
4809  CastKind Kind =
4810  AddrSpaceL != AddrSpaceR ? CK_AddressSpaceConversion : CK_BitCast;
4811  From = ImpCastExprToType(From, ToType.getUnqualifiedType(), Kind,
4812  VK_PRValue, /*BasePath=*/nullptr, CCK)
4813  .get();
4814  break;
4815  }
4816 
4817  case ICK_TransparentUnionConversion: {
4818  ExprResult FromRes = From;
4819  Sema::AssignConvertType ConvTy =
4820  CheckTransparentUnionArgumentConstraints(ToType, FromRes);
4821  if (FromRes.isInvalid())
4822  return ExprError();
4823  From = FromRes.get();
4824  assert ((ConvTy == Sema::Compatible) &&
4825  "Improper transparent union conversion");
4826  (void)ConvTy;
4827  break;
4828  }
4829 
4830  case ICK_Zero_Event_Conversion:
4831  case ICK_Zero_Queue_Conversion:
4832  From = ImpCastExprToType(From, ToType,
4833  CK_ZeroToOCLOpaqueType,
4834  From->getValueKind()).get();
4835  break;
4836  case ICK_HLSL_Vector_Truncation: {
4837  // Note: HLSL built-in vectors are ExtVectors. Since this truncates a vector
4838  // to a smaller vector, this can only operate on arguments where the source
4839  // and destination types are ExtVectors.
4840  assert(From->getType()->isExtVectorType() && ToType->isExtVectorType() &&
4841  "HLSL vector truncation should only apply to ExtVectors");
4842  auto *FromVec = From->getType()->castAs<VectorType>();
4843  auto *ToVec = ToType->castAs<VectorType>();
4844  QualType ElType = FromVec->getElementType();
4845  QualType TruncTy =
4846  Context.getExtVectorType(ElType, ToVec->getNumElements());
4847  From = ImpCastExprToType(From, TruncTy, CK_HLSLVectorTruncation,
4848  From->getValueKind())
4849  .get();
4850  break;
4851  }
4852 
4853  case ICK_Lvalue_To_Rvalue:
4854  case ICK_Array_To_Pointer:
4855  case ICK_Function_To_Pointer:
4856  case ICK_Function_Conversion:
4857  case ICK_Qualification:
4858  case ICK_Num_Conversion_Kinds:
4859  case ICK_C_Only_Conversion:
4860  case ICK_Incompatible_Pointer_Conversion:
4861  case ICK_HLSL_Array_RValue:
4862  llvm_unreachable("Improper second standard conversion");
4863  }
4864 
4865  if (SCS.Element != ICK_Identity) {
4866  // If SCS.Element is not ICK_Identity the To and From types must be HLSL
4867  // vectors or matrices.
4868 
4869  // TODO: Support HLSL matrices.
4870  assert((!From->getType()->isMatrixType() && !ToType->isMatrixType()) &&
4871  "Element conversion for matrix types is not implemented yet.");
4872  assert(From->getType()->isVectorType() && ToType->isVectorType() &&
4873  "Element conversion is only supported for vector types.");
4874  assert(From->getType()->getAs<VectorType>()->getNumElements() ==
4875  ToType->getAs<VectorType>()->getNumElements() &&
4876  "Element conversion is only supported for vectors with the same "
4877  "element counts.");
4878  QualType FromElTy = From->getType()->getAs<VectorType>()->getElementType();
4879  unsigned NumElts = ToType->getAs<VectorType>()->getNumElements();
4880  switch (SCS.Element) {
4881  case ICK_Boolean_Conversion:
4882  // Perform half-to-boolean conversion via float.
4883  if (FromElTy->isHalfType()) {
4884  QualType FPExtType = Context.getExtVectorType(FromElTy, NumElts);
4885  From = ImpCastExprToType(From, FPExtType, CK_FloatingCast).get();
4886  FromType = FPExtType;
4887  }
4888 
4889  From =
4890  ImpCastExprToType(From, ToType, ScalarTypeToBooleanCastKind(FromElTy),
4891  VK_PRValue,
4892  /*BasePath=*/nullptr, CCK)
4893  .get();
4894  break;
4895  case ICK_Integral_Promotion:
4896  case ICK_Integral_Conversion:
4897  if (ToType->isBooleanType()) {
4898  assert(FromType->castAs<EnumType>()->getDecl()->isFixed() &&
4899  SCS.Second == ICK_Integral_Promotion &&
4900  "only enums with fixed underlying type can promote to bool");
4901  From = ImpCastExprToType(From, ToType, CK_IntegralToBoolean, VK_PRValue,
4902  /*BasePath=*/nullptr, CCK)
4903  .get();
4904  } else {
4905  From = ImpCastExprToType(From, ToType, CK_IntegralCast, VK_PRValue,
4906  /*BasePath=*/nullptr, CCK)
4907  .get();
4908  }
4909  break;
4910 
4911  case ICK_Floating_Promotion:
4912  case ICK_Floating_Conversion:
4913  From = ImpCastExprToType(From, ToType, CK_FloatingCast, VK_PRValue,
4914  /*BasePath=*/nullptr, CCK)
4915  .get();
4916  break;
4917  case ICK_Floating_Integral:
4918  if (ToType->hasFloatingRepresentation())
4919  From =
4920  ImpCastExprToType(From, ToType, CK_IntegralToFloating, VK_PRValue,
4921  /*BasePath=*/nullptr, CCK)
4922  .get();
4923  else
4924  From =
4925  ImpCastExprToType(From, ToType, CK_FloatingToIntegral, VK_PRValue,
4926  /*BasePath=*/nullptr, CCK)
4927  .get();
4928  break;
4929  case ICK_Identity:
4930  default:
4931  llvm_unreachable("Improper element standard conversion");
4932  }
4933  }
4934 
4935  switch (SCS.Third) {
4936  case ICK_Identity:
4937  // Nothing to do.
4938  break;
4939 
4940  case ICK_Function_Conversion:
4941  // If both sides are functions (or pointers/references to them), there could
4942  // be incompatible exception declarations.
4943  if (CheckExceptionSpecCompatibility(From, ToType))
4944  return ExprError();
4945 
4946  From = ImpCastExprToType(From, ToType, CK_NoOp, VK_PRValue,
4947  /*BasePath=*/nullptr, CCK)
4948  .get();
4949  break;
4950 
4951  case ICK_Qualification: {
4952  ExprValueKind VK = From->getValueKind();
4953  CastKind CK = CK_NoOp;
4954 
4955  if (ToType->isReferenceType() &&
4956  ToType->getPointeeType().getAddressSpace() !=
4957  From->getType().getAddressSpace())
4958  CK = CK_AddressSpaceConversion;
4959 
4960  if (ToType->isPointerType() &&
4961  ToType->getPointeeType().getAddressSpace() !=
4962  From->getType()->getPointeeType().getAddressSpace())
4963  CK = CK_AddressSpaceConversion;
4964 
4965  if (!isCast(CCK) &&
4966  !ToType->getPointeeType().getQualifiers().hasUnaligned() &&
4967  From->getType()->getPointeeType().getQualifiers().hasUnaligned()) {
4968  Diag(From->getBeginLoc(), diag::warn_imp_cast_drops_unaligned)
4969  << InitialFromType << ToType;
4970  }
4971 
4972  From = ImpCastExprToType(From, ToType.getNonLValueExprType(Context), CK, VK,
4973  /*BasePath=*/nullptr, CCK)
4974  .get();
4975 
4976  if (SCS.DeprecatedStringLiteralToCharPtr &&
4977  !getLangOpts().WritableStrings) {
4978  Diag(From->getBeginLoc(),
4979  getLangOpts().CPlusPlus11
4980  ? diag::ext_deprecated_string_literal_conversion
4981  : diag::warn_deprecated_string_literal_conversion)
4982  << ToType.getNonReferenceType();
4983  }
4984 
4985  break;
4986  }
4987 
4988  default:
4989  llvm_unreachable("Improper third standard conversion");
4990  }
4991 
4992  // If this conversion sequence involved a scalar -> atomic conversion, perform
4993  // that conversion now.
4994  if (!ToAtomicType.isNull()) {
4995  assert(Context.hasSameType(
4996  ToAtomicType->castAs<AtomicType>()->getValueType(), From->getType()));
4997  From = ImpCastExprToType(From, ToAtomicType, CK_NonAtomicToAtomic,
4998  VK_PRValue, nullptr, CCK)
4999  .get();
5000  }
5001 
5002  // Materialize a temporary if we're implicitly converting to a reference
5003  // type. This is not required by the C++ rules but is necessary to maintain
5004  // AST invariants.
5005  if (ToType->isReferenceType() && From->isPRValue()) {
5006  ExprResult Res = TemporaryMaterializationConversion(From);
5007  if (Res.isInvalid())
5008  return ExprError();
5009  From = Res.get();
5010  }
5011 
5012  // If this conversion sequence succeeded and involved implicitly converting a
5013  // _Nullable type to a _Nonnull one, complain.
5014  if (!isCast(CCK))
5015  diagnoseNullableToNonnullConversion(ToType, InitialFromType,
5016  From->getBeginLoc());
5017 
5018  return From;
5019 }
5020 
5021 /// Checks that type T is not a VLA.
5022 ///
5023 /// @returns @c true if @p T is VLA and a diagnostic was emitted,
5024 /// @c false otherwise.
5025 static bool DiagnoseVLAInCXXTypeTrait(Sema &S, const TypeSourceInfo *T,
5026  clang::tok::TokenKind TypeTraitID) {
5027  if (!T->getType()->isVariableArrayType())
5028  return false;
5029 
5030  S.Diag(T->getTypeLoc().getBeginLoc(), diag::err_vla_unsupported)
5031  << 1 << TypeTraitID;
5032  return true;
5033 }
5034 
5035 /// Check the completeness of a type in a unary type trait.
5036 ///
5037 /// If the particular type trait requires a complete type, tries to complete
5038 /// it. If completing the type fails, a diagnostic is emitted and false
5039 /// returned. If completing the type succeeds or no completion was required,
5040 /// returns true.
5041 static bool CheckUnaryTypeTraitTypeCompleteness(Sema &S, TypeTrait UTT,
5042  SourceLocation Loc,
5043  QualType ArgTy) {
5044  // C++0x [meta.unary.prop]p3:
5045  // For all of the class templates X declared in this Clause, instantiating
5046  // that template with a template argument that is a class template
5047  // specialization may result in the implicit instantiation of the template
5048  // argument if and only if the semantics of X require that the argument
5049  // must be a complete type.
5050  // We apply this rule to all the type trait expressions used to implement
5051  // these class templates. We also try to follow any GCC documented behavior
5052  // in these expressions to ensure portability of standard libraries.
5053  switch (UTT) {
5054  default: llvm_unreachable("not a UTT");
5055  // is_complete_type somewhat obviously cannot require a complete type.
5056  case UTT_IsCompleteType:
5057  // Fall-through
5058 
5059  // These traits are modeled on the type predicates in C++0x
5060  // [meta.unary.cat] and [meta.unary.comp]. They are not specified as
5061  // requiring a complete type, as whether or not they return true cannot be
5062  // impacted by the completeness of the type.
5063  case UTT_IsVoid:
5064  case UTT_IsIntegral:
5065  case UTT_IsFloatingPoint:
5066  case UTT_IsArray:
5067  case UTT_IsBoundedArray:
5068  case UTT_IsPointer:
5069  case UTT_IsNullPointer:
5070  case UTT_IsReferenceable:
5071  case UTT_IsLvalueReference:
5072  case UTT_IsRvalueReference:
5073  case UTT_IsMemberFunctionPointer:
5074  case UTT_IsMemberObjectPointer:
5075  case UTT_IsEnum:
5076  case UTT_IsScopedEnum:
5077  case UTT_IsUnion:
5078  case UTT_IsClass:
5079  case UTT_IsFunction:
5080  case UTT_IsReference:
5081  case UTT_IsArithmetic:
5082  case UTT_IsFundamental:
5083  case UTT_IsObject:
5084  case UTT_IsScalar:
5085  case UTT_IsCompound:
5086  case UTT_IsMemberPointer:
5087  // Fall-through
5088 
5089  // These traits are modeled on type predicates in C++0x [meta.unary.prop]
5090  // which requires some of its traits to have the complete type. However,
5091  // the completeness of the type cannot impact these traits' semantics, and
5092  // so they don't require it. This matches the comments on these traits in
5093  // Table 49.
5094  case UTT_IsConst:
5095  case UTT_IsVolatile:
5096  case UTT_IsSigned:
5097  case UTT_IsUnboundedArray:
5098  case UTT_IsUnsigned:
5099 
5100  // This type trait always returns false, checking the type is moot.
5101  case UTT_IsInterfaceClass:
5102  return true;
5103 
5104  // C++14 [meta.unary.prop]:
5105  // If T is a non-union class type, T shall be a complete type.
5106  case UTT_IsEmpty:
5107  case UTT_IsPolymorphic:
5108  case UTT_IsAbstract:
5109  if (const auto *RD = ArgTy->getAsCXXRecordDecl())
5110  if (!RD->isUnion())
5111  return !S.RequireCompleteType(
5112  Loc, ArgTy, diag::err_incomplete_type_used_in_type_trait_expr);
5113  return true;
5114 
5115  // C++14 [meta.unary.prop]:
5116  // If T is a class type, T shall be a complete type.
5117  case UTT_IsFinal:
5118  case UTT_IsSealed:
5119  if (ArgTy->getAsCXXRecordDecl())
5120  return !S.RequireCompleteType(
5121  Loc, ArgTy, diag::err_incomplete_type_used_in_type_trait_expr);
5122  return true;
5123 
5124  // LWG3823: T shall be an array type, a complete type, or cv void.
5125  case UTT_IsAggregate:
5126  if (ArgTy->isArrayType() || ArgTy->isVoidType())
5127  return true;
5128 
5129  return !S.RequireCompleteType(
5130  Loc, ArgTy, diag::err_incomplete_type_used_in_type_trait_expr);
5131 
5132  // C++1z [meta.unary.prop]:
5133  // remove_all_extents_t<T> shall be a complete type or cv void.
5134  case UTT_IsTrivial:
5135  case UTT_IsTriviallyCopyable:
5136  case UTT_IsStandardLayout:
5137  case UTT_IsPOD:
5138  case UTT_IsLiteral:
5139  // By analogy, is_trivially_relocatable and is_trivially_equality_comparable
5140  // impose the same constraints.
5141  case UTT_IsTriviallyRelocatable:
5142  case UTT_IsTriviallyEqualityComparable:
5143  case UTT_CanPassInRegs:
5144  // Per the GCC type traits documentation, T shall be a complete type, cv void,
5145  // or an array of unknown bound. But GCC actually imposes the same constraints
5146  // as above.
5147  case UTT_HasNothrowAssign:
5148  case UTT_HasNothrowMoveAssign:
5149  case UTT_HasNothrowConstructor:
5150  case UTT_HasNothrowCopy:
5151  case UTT_HasTrivialAssign:
5152  case UTT_HasTrivialMoveAssign:
5153  case UTT_HasTrivialDefaultConstructor:
5154  case UTT_HasTrivialMoveConstructor:
5155  case UTT_HasTrivialCopy:
5156  case UTT_HasTrivialDestructor:
5157  case UTT_HasVirtualDestructor:
5158  ArgTy = QualType(ArgTy->getBaseElementTypeUnsafe(), 0);
5159  [[fallthrough]];
5160 
5161  // C++1z [meta.unary.prop]:
5162  // T shall be a complete type, cv void, or an array of unknown bound.
5163  case UTT_IsDestructible:
5164  case UTT_IsNothrowDestructible:
5165  case UTT_IsTriviallyDestructible:
5166  case UTT_HasUniqueObjectRepresentations:
5167  if (ArgTy->isIncompleteArrayType() || ArgTy->isVoidType())
5168  return true;
5169 
5170  return !S.RequireCompleteType(
5171  Loc, ArgTy, diag::err_incomplete_type_used_in_type_trait_expr);
5172  }
5173 }
5174 
5175 static bool HasNoThrowOperator(const RecordType *RT, OverloadedOperatorKind Op,
5176  Sema &Self, SourceLocation KeyLoc, ASTContext &C,
5177  bool (CXXRecordDecl::*HasTrivial)() const,
5178  bool (CXXRecordDecl::*HasNonTrivial)() const,
5179  bool (CXXMethodDecl::*IsDesiredOp)() const)
5180 {
5181  CXXRecordDecl *RD = cast<CXXRecordDecl>(RT->getDecl());
5182  if ((RD->*HasTrivial)() && !(RD->*HasNonTrivial)())
5183  return true;
5184 
5185  DeclarationName Name = C.DeclarationNames.getCXXOperatorName(Op);
5186  DeclarationNameInfo NameInfo(Name, KeyLoc);
5187  LookupResult Res(Self, NameInfo, Sema::LookupOrdinaryName);
5188  if (Self.LookupQualifiedName(Res, RD)) {
5189  bool FoundOperator = false;
5190  Res.suppressDiagnostics();
5191  for (LookupResult::iterator Op = Res.begin(), OpEnd = Res.end();
5192  Op != OpEnd; ++Op) {
5193  if (isa<FunctionTemplateDecl>(*Op))
5194  continue;
5195 
5196  CXXMethodDecl *Operator = cast<CXXMethodDecl>(*Op);
5197  if((Operator->*IsDesiredOp)()) {
5198  FoundOperator = true;
5199  auto *CPT = Operator->getType()->castAs<FunctionProtoType>();
5200  CPT = Self.ResolveExceptionSpec(KeyLoc, CPT);
5201  if (!CPT || !CPT->isNothrow())
5202  return false;
5203  }
5204  }
5205  return FoundOperator;
5206  }
5207  return false;
5208 }
5209 
5210 static bool EvaluateUnaryTypeTrait(Sema &Self, TypeTrait UTT,
5211  SourceLocation KeyLoc,
5212  TypeSourceInfo *TInfo) {
5213  QualType T = TInfo->getType();
5214  assert(!T->isDependentType() && "Cannot evaluate traits of dependent type");
5215 
5216  ASTContext &C = Self.Context;
5217  switch(UTT) {
5218  default: llvm_unreachable("not a UTT");
5219  // Type trait expressions corresponding to the primary type category
5220  // predicates in C++0x [meta.unary.cat].
5221  case UTT_IsVoid:
5222  return T->isVoidType();
5223  case UTT_IsIntegral:
5224  return T->isIntegralType(C);
5225  case UTT_IsFloatingPoint:
5226  return T->isFloatingType();
5227  case UTT_IsArray:
5228  return T->isArrayType();
5229  case UTT_IsBoundedArray:
5230  if (DiagnoseVLAInCXXTypeTrait(Self, TInfo, tok::kw___is_bounded_array))
5231  return false;
5232  return T->isArrayType() && !T->isIncompleteArrayType();
5233  case UTT_IsUnboundedArray:
5234  if (DiagnoseVLAInCXXTypeTrait(Self, TInfo, tok::kw___is_unbounded_array))
5235  return false;
5236  return T->isIncompleteArrayType();
5237  case UTT_IsPointer:
5238  return T->isAnyPointerType();
5239  case UTT_IsNullPointer:
5240  return T->isNullPtrType();
5241  case UTT_IsLvalueReference:
5242  return T->isLValueReferenceType();
5243  case UTT_IsRvalueReference:
5244  return T->isRValueReferenceType();
5245  case UTT_IsMemberFunctionPointer:
5246  return T->isMemberFunctionPointerType();
5247  case UTT_IsMemberObjectPointer:
5248  return T->isMemberDataPointerType();
5249  case UTT_IsEnum:
5250  return T->isEnumeralType();
5251  case UTT_IsScopedEnum:
5252  return T->isScopedEnumeralType();
5253  case UTT_IsUnion:
5254  return T->isUnionType();
5255  case UTT_IsClass:
5256  return T->isClassType() || T->isStructureType() || T->isInterfaceType();
5257  case UTT_IsFunction:
5258  return T->isFunctionType();
5259 
5260  // Type trait expressions which correspond to the convenient composition
5261  // predicates in C++0x [meta.unary.comp].
5262  case UTT_IsReference:
5263  return T->isReferenceType();
5264  case UTT_IsArithmetic:
5265  return T->isArithmeticType() && !T->isEnumeralType();
5266  case UTT_IsFundamental:
5267  return T->isFundamentalType();
5268  case UTT_IsObject:
5269  return T->isObjectType();
5270  case UTT_IsScalar:
5271  // Note: semantic analysis depends on Objective-C lifetime types to be
5272  // considered scalar types. However, such types do not actually behave
5273  // like scalar types at run time (since they may require retain/release
5274  // operations), so we report them as non-scalar.
5275  if (T->isObjCLifetimeType()) {
5276  switch (T.getObjCLifetime()) {
5277  case Qualifiers::OCL_None:
5278  case Qualifiers::OCL_ExplicitNone:
5279  return true;
5280 
5281  case Qualifiers::OCL_Strong:
5282  case Qualifiers::OCL_Weak:
5283  case Qualifiers::OCL_Autoreleasing:
5284  return false;
5285  }
5286  }
5287 
5288  return T->isScalarType();
5289  case UTT_IsCompound:
5290  return T->isCompoundType();
5291  case UTT_IsMemberPointer:
5292  return T->isMemberPointerType();
5293 
5294  // Type trait expressions which correspond to the type property predicates
5295  // in C++0x [meta.unary.prop].
5296  case UTT_IsConst:
5297  return T.isConstQualified();
5298  case UTT_IsVolatile:
5299  return T.isVolatileQualified();
5300  case UTT_IsTrivial:
5301  return T.isTrivialType(C);
5302  case UTT_IsTriviallyCopyable:
5303  return T.isTriviallyCopyableType(C);
5304  case UTT_IsStandardLayout:
5305  return T->isStandardLayoutType();
5306  case UTT_IsPOD:
5307  return T.isPODType(C);
5308  case UTT_IsLiteral:
5309  return T->isLiteralType(C);
5310  case UTT_IsEmpty:
5311  if (const CXXRecordDecl *RD = T->getAsCXXRecordDecl())
5312  return !RD->isUnion() && RD->isEmpty();
5313  return false;
5314  case UTT_IsPolymorphic:
5315  if (const CXXRecordDecl *RD = T->getAsCXXRecordDecl())
5316  return !RD->isUnion() && RD->isPolymorphic();
5317  return false;
5318  case UTT_IsAbstract:
5319  if (const CXXRecordDecl *RD = T->getAsCXXRecordDecl())
5320  return !RD->isUnion() && RD->isAbstract();
5321  return false;
5322  case UTT_IsAggregate:
5323  // Report vector extensions and complex types as aggregates because they
5324  // support aggregate initialization. GCC mirrors this behavior for vectors
5325  // but not _Complex.
5326  return T->isAggregateType() || T->isVectorType() || T->isExtVectorType() ||
5327  T->isAnyComplexType();
5328  // __is_interface_class only returns true when CL is invoked in /CLR mode and
5329  // even then only when it is used with the 'interface struct ...' syntax
5330  // Clang doesn't support /CLR which makes this type trait moot.
5331  case UTT_IsInterfaceClass:
5332  return false;
5333  case UTT_IsFinal:
5334  case UTT_IsSealed:
5335  if (const CXXRecordDecl *RD = T->getAsCXXRecordDecl())
5336  return RD->hasAttr<FinalAttr>();
5337  return false;
5338  case UTT_IsSigned:
5339  // Enum types should always return false.
5340  // Floating points should always return true.
5341  return T->isFloatingType() ||
5342  (T->isSignedIntegerType() && !T->isEnumeralType());
5343  case UTT_IsUnsigned:
5344  // Enum types should always return false.
5345  return T->isUnsignedIntegerType() && !T->isEnumeralType();
5346 
5347  // Type trait expressions which query classes regarding their construction,
5348  // destruction, and copying. Rather than being based directly on the
5349  // related type predicates in the standard, they are specified by both
5350  // GCC[1] and the Embarcadero C++ compiler[2], and Clang implements those
5351  // specifications.
5352  //
5353  // 1: http://gcc.gnu/.org/onlinedocs/gcc/Type-Traits.html
5354  // 2: http://docwiki.embarcadero.com/RADStudio/XE/en/Type_Trait_Functions_(C%2B%2B0x)_Index
5355  //
5356  // Note that these builtins do not behave as documented in g++: if a class
5357  // has both a trivial and a non-trivial special member of a particular kind,
5358  // they return false! For now, we emulate this behavior.
5359  // FIXME: This appears to be a g++ bug: more complex cases reveal that it
5360  // does not correctly compute triviality in the presence of multiple special
5361  // members of the same kind. Revisit this once the g++ bug is fixed.
5362  case UTT_HasTrivialDefaultConstructor:
5363  // http://gcc.gnu.org/onlinedocs/gcc/Type-Traits.html:
5364  // If __is_pod (type) is true then the trait is true, else if type is
5365  // a cv class or union type (or array thereof) with a trivial default
5366  // constructor ([class.ctor]) then the trait is true, else it is false.
5367  if (T.isPODType(C))
5368  return true;
5369  if (CXXRecordDecl *RD = C.getBaseElementType(T)->getAsCXXRecordDecl())
5370  return RD->hasTrivialDefaultConstructor() &&
5371  !RD->hasNonTrivialDefaultConstructor();
5372  return false;
5373  case UTT_HasTrivialMoveConstructor:
5374  // This trait is implemented by MSVC 2012 and needed to parse the
5375  // standard library headers. Specifically this is used as the logic
5376  // behind std::is_trivially_move_constructible (20.9.4.3).
5377  if (T.isPODType(C))
5378  return true;
5379  if (CXXRecordDecl *RD = C.getBaseElementType(T)->getAsCXXRecordDecl())
5380  return RD->hasTrivialMoveConstructor() && !RD->hasNonTrivialMoveConstructor();
5381  return false;
5382  case UTT_HasTrivialCopy:
5383  // http://gcc.gnu.org/onlinedocs/gcc/Type-Traits.html:
5384  // If __is_pod (type) is true or type is a reference type then
5385  // the trait is true, else if type is a cv class or union type
5386  // with a trivial copy constructor ([class.copy]) then the trait
5387  // is true, else it is false.
5388  if (T.isPODType(C) || T->isReferenceType())
5389  return true;
5390  if (CXXRecordDecl *RD = T->getAsCXXRecordDecl())
5391  return RD->hasTrivialCopyConstructor() &&
5392  !RD->hasNonTrivialCopyConstructor();
5393  return false;
5394  case UTT_HasTrivialMoveAssign:
5395  // This trait is implemented by MSVC 2012 and needed to parse the
5396  // standard library headers. Specifically it is used as the logic
5397  // behind std::is_trivially_move_assignable (20.9.4.3)
5398  if (T.isPODType(C))
5399  return true;
5400  if (CXXRecordDecl *RD = C.getBaseElementType(T)->getAsCXXRecordDecl())
5401  return RD->hasTrivialMoveAssignment() && !RD->hasNonTrivialMoveAssignment();
5402  return false;
5403  case UTT_HasTrivialAssign:
5404  // http://gcc.gnu.org/onlinedocs/gcc/Type-Traits.html:
5405  // If type is const qualified or is a reference type then the
5406  // trait is false. Otherwise if __is_pod (type) is true then the
5407  // trait is true, else if type is a cv class or union type with
5408  // a trivial copy assignment ([class.copy]) then the trait is
5409  // true, else it is false.
5410  // Note: the const and reference restrictions are interesting,
5411  // given that const and reference members don't prevent a class
5412  // from having a trivial copy assignment operator (but do cause
5413  // errors if the copy assignment operator is actually used, q.v.
5414  // [class.copy]p12).
5415 
5416  if (T.isConstQualified())
5417  return false;
5418  if (T.isPODType(C))
5419  return true;
5420  if (CXXRecordDecl *RD = T->getAsCXXRecordDecl())
5421  return RD->hasTrivialCopyAssignment() &&
5422  !RD->hasNonTrivialCopyAssignment();
5423  return false;
5424  case UTT_IsDestructible:
5425  case UTT_IsTriviallyDestructible:
5426  case UTT_IsNothrowDestructible:
5427  // C++14 [meta.unary.prop]:
5428  // For reference types, is_destructible<T>::value is true.
5429  if (T->isReferenceType())
5430  return true;
5431 
5432  // Objective-C++ ARC: autorelease types don't require destruction.
5433  if (T->isObjCLifetimeType() &&
5434  T.getObjCLifetime() == Qualifiers::OCL_Autoreleasing)
5435  return true;
5436 
5437  // C++14 [meta.unary.prop]:
5438  // For incomplete types and function types, is_destructible<T>::value is
5439  // false.
5440  if (T->isIncompleteType() || T->isFunctionType())
5441  return false;
5442 
5443  // A type that requires destruction (via a non-trivial destructor or ARC
5444  // lifetime semantics) is not trivially-destructible.
5445  if (UTT == UTT_IsTriviallyDestructible && T.isDestructedType())
5446  return false;
5447 
5448  // C++14 [meta.unary.prop]:
5449  // For object types and given U equal to remove_all_extents_t<T>, if the
5450  // expression std::declval<U&>().~U() is well-formed when treated as an
5451  // unevaluated operand (Clause 5), then is_destructible<T>::value is true
5452  if (auto *RD = C.getBaseElementType(T)->getAsCXXRecordDecl()) {
5453  CXXDestructorDecl *Destructor = Self.LookupDestructor(RD);
5454  if (!Destructor)
5455  return false;
5456  // C++14 [dcl.fct.def.delete]p2:
5457  // A program that refers to a deleted function implicitly or
5458  // explicitly, other than to declare it, is ill-formed.
5459  if (Destructor->isDeleted())
5460  return false;
5461  if (C.getLangOpts().AccessControl && Destructor->getAccess() != AS_public)
5462  return false;
5463  if (UTT == UTT_IsNothrowDestructible) {
5464  auto *CPT = Destructor->getType()->castAs<FunctionProtoType>();
5465  CPT = Self.ResolveExceptionSpec(KeyLoc, CPT);
5466  if (!CPT || !CPT->isNothrow())
5467  return false;
5468  }
5469  }
5470  return true;
5471 
5472  case UTT_HasTrivialDestructor:
5473  // http://gcc.gnu.org/onlinedocs/gcc/Type-Traits.html
5474  // If __is_pod (type) is true or type is a reference type
5475  // then the trait is true, else if type is a cv class or union
5476  // type (or array thereof) with a trivial destructor
5477  // ([class.dtor]) then the trait is true, else it is
5478  // false.
5479  if (T.isPODType(C) || T->isReferenceType())
5480  return true;
5481 
5482  // Objective-C++ ARC: autorelease types don't require destruction.
5483  if (T->isObjCLifetimeType() &&
5484  T.getObjCLifetime() == Qualifiers::OCL_Autoreleasing)
5485  return true;
5486 
5487  if (CXXRecordDecl *RD = C.getBaseElementType(T)->getAsCXXRecordDecl())
5488  return RD->hasTrivialDestructor();
5489  return false;
5490  // TODO: Propagate nothrowness for implicitly declared special members.
5491  case UTT_HasNothrowAssign:
5492  // http://gcc.gnu.org/onlinedocs/gcc/Type-Traits.html:
5493  // If type is const qualified or is a reference type then the
5494  // trait is false. Otherwise if __has_trivial_assign (type)
5495  // is true then the trait is true, else if type is a cv class
5496  // or union type with copy assignment operators that are known
5497  // not to throw an exception then the trait is true, else it is
5498  // false.
5499  if (C.getBaseElementType(T).isConstQualified())
5500  return false;
5501  if (T->isReferenceType())
5502  return false;
5503  if (T.isPODType(C) || T->isObjCLifetimeType())
5504  return true;
5505 
5506  if (const RecordType *RT = T->getAs<RecordType>())
5507  return HasNoThrowOperator(RT, OO_Equal, Self, KeyLoc, C,
5508  &CXXRecordDecl::hasTrivialCopyAssignment,
5509  &CXXRecordDecl::hasNonTrivialCopyAssignment,
5510  &CXXMethodDecl::isCopyAssignmentOperator);
5511  return false;
5512  case UTT_HasNothrowMoveAssign:
5513  // This trait is implemented by MSVC 2012 and needed to parse the
5514  // standard library headers. Specifically this is used as the logic
5515  // behind std::is_nothrow_move_assignable (20.9.4.3).
5516  if (T.isPODType(C))
5517  return true;
5518 
5519  if (const RecordType *RT = C.getBaseElementType(T)->getAs<RecordType>())
5520  return HasNoThrowOperator(RT, OO_Equal, Self, KeyLoc, C,
5521  &CXXRecordDecl::hasTrivialMoveAssignment,
5522  &CXXRecordDecl::hasNonTrivialMoveAssignment,
5523  &CXXMethodDecl::isMoveAssignmentOperator);
5524  return false;
5525  case UTT_HasNothrowCopy:
5526  // http://gcc.gnu.org/onlinedocs/gcc/Type-Traits.html:
5527  // If __has_trivial_copy (type) is true then the trait is true, else
5528  // if type is a cv class or union type with copy constructors that are
5529  // known not to throw an exception then the trait is true, else it is
5530  // false.
5531  if (T.isPODType(C) || T->isReferenceType() || T->isObjCLifetimeType())
5532  return true;
5533  if (CXXRecordDecl *RD = T->getAsCXXRecordDecl()) {
5534  if (RD->hasTrivialCopyConstructor() &&
5535  !RD->hasNonTrivialCopyConstructor())
5536  return true;
5537 
5538  bool FoundConstructor = false;
5539  unsigned FoundTQs;
5540  for (const auto *ND : Self.LookupConstructors(RD)) {
5541  // A template constructor is never a copy constructor.
5542  // FIXME: However, it may actually be selected at the actual overload
5543  // resolution point.
5544  if (isa<FunctionTemplateDecl>(ND->getUnderlyingDecl()))
5545  continue;
5546  // UsingDecl itself is not a constructor
5547  if (isa<UsingDecl>(ND))
5548  continue;
5549  auto *Constructor = cast<CXXConstructorDecl>(ND->getUnderlyingDecl());
5550  if (Constructor->isCopyConstructor(FoundTQs)) {
5551  FoundConstructor = true;
5552  auto *CPT = Constructor->getType()->castAs<FunctionProtoType>();
5553  CPT = Self.ResolveExceptionSpec(KeyLoc, CPT);
5554  if (!CPT)
5555  return false;
5556  // TODO: check whether evaluating default arguments can throw.
5557  // For now, we'll be conservative and assume that they can throw.
5558  if (!CPT->isNothrow() || CPT->getNumParams() > 1)
5559  return false;
5560  }
5561  }
5562 
5563  return FoundConstructor;
5564  }
5565  return false;
5566  case UTT_HasNothrowConstructor:
5567  // http://gcc.gnu.org/onlinedocs/gcc/Type-Traits.html
5568  // If __has_trivial_constructor (type) is true then the trait is
5569  // true, else if type is a cv class or union type (or array
5570  // thereof) with a default constructor that is known not to
5571  // throw an exception then the trait is true, else it is false.
5572  if (T.isPODType(C) || T->isObjCLifetimeType())
5573  return true;
5574  if (CXXRecordDecl *RD = C.getBaseElementType(T)->getAsCXXRecordDecl()) {
5575  if (RD->hasTrivialDefaultConstructor() &&
5576  !RD->hasNonTrivialDefaultConstructor())
5577  return true;
5578 
5579  bool FoundConstructor = false;
5580  for (const auto *ND : Self.LookupConstructors(RD)) {
5581  // FIXME: In C++0x, a constructor template can be a default constructor.
5582  if (isa<FunctionTemplateDecl>(ND->getUnderlyingDecl()))
5583  continue;
5584  // UsingDecl itself is not a constructor
5585  if (isa<UsingDecl>(ND))
5586  continue;
5587  auto *Constructor = cast<CXXConstructorDecl>(ND->getUnderlyingDecl());
5588  if (Constructor->isDefaultConstructor()) {
5589  FoundConstructor = true;
5590  auto *CPT = Constructor->getType()->castAs<FunctionProtoType>();
5591  CPT = Self.ResolveExceptionSpec(KeyLoc, CPT);
5592  if (!CPT)
5593  return false;
5594  // FIXME: check whether evaluating default arguments can throw.
5595  // For now, we'll be conservative and assume that they can throw.
5596  if (!CPT->isNothrow() || CPT->getNumParams() > 0)
5597  return false;
5598  }
5599  }
5600  return FoundConstructor;
5601  }
5602  return false;
5603  case UTT_HasVirtualDestructor:
5604  // http://gcc.gnu.org/onlinedocs/gcc/Type-Traits.html:
5605  // If type is a class type with a virtual destructor ([class.dtor])
5606  // then the trait is true, else it is false.
5607  if (CXXRecordDecl *RD = T->getAsCXXRecordDecl())
5608  if (CXXDestructorDecl *Destructor = Self.LookupDestructor(RD))
5609  return Destructor->isVirtual();
5610  return false;
5611 
5612  // These type trait expressions are modeled on the specifications for the
5613  // Embarcadero C++0x type trait functions:
5614  // http://docwiki.embarcadero.com/RADStudio/XE/en/Type_Trait_Functions_(C%2B%2B0x)_Index
5615  case UTT_IsCompleteType:
5616  // http://docwiki.embarcadero.com/RADStudio/XE/en/Is_complete_type_(typename_T_):
5617  // Returns True if and only if T is a complete type at the point of the
5618  // function call.
5619  return !T->isIncompleteType();
5620  case UTT_HasUniqueObjectRepresentations:
5621  return C.hasUniqueObjectRepresentations(T);
5622  case UTT_IsTriviallyRelocatable:
5623  return T.isTriviallyRelocatableType(C);
5624  case UTT_IsReferenceable:
5625  return T.isReferenceable();
5626  case UTT_CanPassInRegs:
5627  if (CXXRecordDecl *RD = T->getAsCXXRecordDecl(); RD && !T.hasQualifiers())
5628  return RD->canPassInRegisters();
5629  Self.Diag(KeyLoc, diag::err_builtin_pass_in_regs_non_class) << T;
5630  return false;
5631  case UTT_IsTriviallyEqualityComparable:
5632  return T.isTriviallyEqualityComparableType(C);
5633  }
5634 }
5635 
5636 static bool EvaluateBinaryTypeTrait(Sema &Self, TypeTrait BTT, const TypeSourceInfo *Lhs,
5637  const TypeSourceInfo *Rhs, SourceLocation KeyLoc);
5638 
5639 static bool EvaluateBooleanTypeTrait(Sema &S, TypeTrait Kind,
5640  SourceLocation KWLoc,
5641  ArrayRef<TypeSourceInfo *> Args,
5642  SourceLocation RParenLoc,
5643  bool IsDependent) {
5644  if (IsDependent)
5645  return false;
5646 
5647  if (Kind <= UTT_Last)
5648  return EvaluateUnaryTypeTrait(S, Kind, KWLoc, Args[0]);
5649 
5650  // Evaluate ReferenceBindsToTemporary and ReferenceConstructsFromTemporary
5651  // alongside the IsConstructible traits to avoid duplication.
5652  if (Kind <= BTT_Last && Kind != BTT_ReferenceBindsToTemporary && Kind != BTT_ReferenceConstructsFromTemporary)
5653  return EvaluateBinaryTypeTrait(S, Kind, Args[0],
5654  Args[1], RParenLoc);
5655 
5656  switch (Kind) {
5657  case clang::BTT_ReferenceBindsToTemporary:
5658  case clang::BTT_ReferenceConstructsFromTemporary:
5659  case clang::TT_IsConstructible:
5660  case clang::TT_IsNothrowConstructible:
5661  case clang::TT_IsTriviallyConstructible: {
5662  // C++11 [meta.unary.prop]:
5663  // is_trivially_constructible is defined as:
5664  //
5665  // is_constructible<T, Args...>::value is true and the variable
5666  // definition for is_constructible, as defined below, is known to call
5667  // no operation that is not trivial.
5668  //
5669  // The predicate condition for a template specialization
5670  // is_constructible<T, Args...> shall be satisfied if and only if the
5671  // following variable definition would be well-formed for some invented
5672  // variable t:
5673  //
5674  // T t(create<Args>()...);
5675  assert(!Args.empty());
5676 
5677  // Precondition: T and all types in the parameter pack Args shall be
5678  // complete types, (possibly cv-qualified) void, or arrays of
5679  // unknown bound.
5680  for (const auto *TSI : Args) {
5681  QualType ArgTy = TSI->getType();
5682  if (ArgTy->isVoidType() || ArgTy->isIncompleteArrayType())
5683  continue;
5684 
5685  if (S.RequireCompleteType(KWLoc, ArgTy,
5686  diag::err_incomplete_type_used_in_type_trait_expr))
5687  return false;
5688  }
5689 
5690  // Make sure the first argument is not incomplete nor a function type.
5691  QualType T = Args[0]->getType();
5692  if (T->isIncompleteType() || T->isFunctionType())
5693  return false;
5694 
5695  // Make sure the first argument is not an abstract type.
5696  CXXRecordDecl *RD = T->getAsCXXRecordDecl();
5697  if (RD && RD->isAbstract())
5698  return false;
5699 
5700  llvm::BumpPtrAllocator OpaqueExprAllocator;
5701  SmallVector<Expr *, 2> ArgExprs;
5702  ArgExprs.reserve(Args.size() - 1);
5703  for (unsigned I = 1, N = Args.size(); I != N; ++I) {
5704  QualType ArgTy = Args[I]->getType();
5705  if (ArgTy->isObjectType() || ArgTy->isFunctionType())
5706  ArgTy = S.Context.getRValueReferenceType(ArgTy);
5707  ArgExprs.push_back(
5708  new (OpaqueExprAllocator.Allocate<OpaqueValueExpr>())
5709  OpaqueValueExpr(Args[I]->getTypeLoc().getBeginLoc(),
5710  ArgTy.getNonLValueExprType(S.Context),
5711  Expr::getValueKindForType(ArgTy)));
5712  }
5713 
5714  // Perform the initialization in an unevaluated context within a SFINAE
5715  // trap at translation unit scope.
5716  EnterExpressionEvaluationContext Unevaluated(
5717  S, Sema::ExpressionEvaluationContext::Unevaluated);
5718  Sema::SFINAETrap SFINAE(S, /*AccessCheckingSFINAE=*/true);
5719  Sema::ContextRAII TUContext(S, S.Context.getTranslationUnitDecl());
5720  InitializedEntity To(
5721  InitializedEntity::InitializeTemporary(S.Context, Args[0]));
5722  InitializationKind InitKind(InitializationKind::CreateDirect(KWLoc, KWLoc,
5723  RParenLoc));
5724  InitializationSequence Init(S, To, InitKind, ArgExprs);
5725  if (Init.Failed())
5726  return false;
5727 
5728  ExprResult Result = Init.Perform(S, To, InitKind, ArgExprs);
5729  if (Result.isInvalid() || SFINAE.hasErrorOccurred())
5730  return false;
5731 
5732  if (Kind == clang::TT_IsConstructible)
5733  return true;
5734 
5735  if (Kind == clang::BTT_ReferenceBindsToTemporary || Kind == clang::BTT_ReferenceConstructsFromTemporary) {
5736  if (!T->isReferenceType())
5737  return false;
5738 
5739  if (!Init.isDirectReferenceBinding())
5740  return true;
5741 
5742  if (Kind == clang::BTT_ReferenceBindsToTemporary)
5743  return false;
5744 
5745  QualType U = Args[1]->getType();
5746  if (U->isReferenceType())
5747  return false;
5748 
5749  TypeSourceInfo *TPtr = S.Context.CreateTypeSourceInfo(S.Context.getPointerType(S.BuiltinRemoveReference(T, UnaryTransformType::RemoveCVRef, {})));
5750  TypeSourceInfo *UPtr = S.Context.CreateTypeSourceInfo(S.Context.getPointerType(S.BuiltinRemoveReference(U, UnaryTransformType::RemoveCVRef, {})));
5751  return EvaluateBinaryTypeTrait(S, TypeTrait::BTT_IsConvertibleTo, UPtr, TPtr, RParenLoc);
5752  }
5753 
5754  if (Kind == clang::TT_IsNothrowConstructible)
5755  return S.canThrow(Result.get()) == CT_Cannot;
5756 
5757  if (Kind == clang::TT_IsTriviallyConstructible) {
5758  // Under Objective-C ARC and Weak, if the destination has non-trivial
5759  // Objective-C lifetime, this is a non-trivial construction.
5760  if (T.getNonReferenceType().hasNonTrivialObjCLifetime())
5761  return false;
5762 
5763  // The initialization succeeded; now make sure there are no non-trivial
5764  // calls.
5765  return !Result.get()->hasNonTrivialCall(S.Context);
5766  }
5767 
5768  llvm_unreachable("unhandled type trait");
5769  return false;
5770  }
5771  default: llvm_unreachable("not a TT");
5772  }
5773 
5774  return false;
5775 }
5776 
5777 namespace {
5778 void DiagnoseBuiltinDeprecation(Sema& S, TypeTrait Kind,
5779  SourceLocation KWLoc) {
5780  TypeTrait Replacement;
5781  switch (Kind) {
5782  case UTT_HasNothrowAssign:
5783  case UTT_HasNothrowMoveAssign:
5784  Replacement = BTT_IsNothrowAssignable;
5785  break;
5786  case UTT_HasNothrowCopy:
5787  case UTT_HasNothrowConstructor:
5788  Replacement = TT_IsNothrowConstructible;
5789  break;
5790  case UTT_HasTrivialAssign:
5791  case UTT_HasTrivialMoveAssign:
5792  Replacement = BTT_IsTriviallyAssignable;
5793  break;
5794  case UTT_HasTrivialCopy:
5795  Replacement = UTT_IsTriviallyCopyable;
5796  break;
5797  case UTT_HasTrivialDefaultConstructor:
5798  case UTT_HasTrivialMoveConstructor:
5799  Replacement = TT_IsTriviallyConstructible;
5800  break;
5801  case UTT_HasTrivialDestructor:
5802  Replacement = UTT_IsTriviallyDestructible;
5803  break;
5804  default:
5805  return;
5806  }
5807  S.Diag(KWLoc, diag::warn_deprecated_builtin)
5808  << getTraitSpelling(Kind) << getTraitSpelling(Replacement);
5809 }
5810 }
5811 
5812 bool Sema::CheckTypeTraitArity(unsigned Arity, SourceLocation Loc, size_t N) {
5813  if (Arity && N != Arity) {
5814  Diag(Loc, diag::err_type_trait_arity)
5815  << Arity << 0 << (Arity > 1) << (int)N << SourceRange(Loc);
5816  return false;
5817  }
5818 
5819  if (!Arity && N == 0) {
5820  Diag(Loc, diag::err_type_trait_arity)
5821  << 1 << 1 << 1 << (int)N << SourceRange(Loc);
5822  return false;
5823  }
5824  return true;
5825 }
5826 
5827 enum class TypeTraitReturnType {
5828  Bool,
5829 };
5830 
5831 static TypeTraitReturnType GetReturnType(TypeTrait Kind) {
5832  return TypeTraitReturnType::Bool;
5833 }
5834 
5835 ExprResult Sema::BuildTypeTrait(TypeTrait Kind, SourceLocation KWLoc,
5836  ArrayRef<TypeSourceInfo *> Args,
5837  SourceLocation RParenLoc) {
5838  if (!CheckTypeTraitArity(getTypeTraitArity(Kind), KWLoc, Args.size()))
5839  return ExprError();
5840 
5841  if (Kind <= UTT_Last && !CheckUnaryTypeTraitTypeCompleteness(
5842  *this, Kind, KWLoc, Args[0]->getType()))
5843  return ExprError();
5844 
5845  DiagnoseBuiltinDeprecation(*this, Kind, KWLoc);
5846 
5847  bool Dependent = false;
5848  for (unsigned I = 0, N = Args.size(); I != N; ++I) {
5849  if (Args[I]->getType()->isDependentType()) {
5850  Dependent = true;
5851  break;
5852  }
5853  }
5854 
5855  switch (GetReturnType(Kind)) {
5856  case TypeTraitReturnType::Bool: {
5857  bool Result = EvaluateBooleanTypeTrait(*this, Kind, KWLoc, Args, RParenLoc,
5858  Dependent);
5859  return TypeTraitExpr::Create(Context, Context.getLogicalOperationType(),
5860  KWLoc, Kind, Args, RParenLoc, Result);
5861  }
5862  }
5863  llvm_unreachable("unhandled type trait return type");
5864 }
5865 
5866 ExprResult Sema::ActOnTypeTrait(TypeTrait Kind, SourceLocation KWLoc,
5867  ArrayRef<ParsedType> Args,
5868  SourceLocation RParenLoc) {
5869  SmallVector<TypeSourceInfo *, 4> ConvertedArgs;
5870  ConvertedArgs.reserve(Args.size());
5871 
5872  for (unsigned I = 0, N = Args.size(); I != N; ++I) {
5873  TypeSourceInfo *TInfo;
5874  QualType T = GetTypeFromParser(Args[I], &TInfo);
5875  if (!TInfo)
5876  TInfo = Context.getTrivialTypeSourceInfo(T, KWLoc);
5877 
5878  ConvertedArgs.push_back(TInfo);
5879  }
5880 
5881  return BuildTypeTrait(Kind, KWLoc, ConvertedArgs, RParenLoc);
5882 }
5883 
5884 static bool EvaluateBinaryTypeTrait(Sema &Self, TypeTrait BTT, const TypeSourceInfo *Lhs,
5885  const TypeSourceInfo *Rhs, SourceLocation KeyLoc) {
5886  QualType LhsT = Lhs->getType();
5887  QualType RhsT = Rhs->getType();
5888 
5889  assert(!LhsT->isDependentType() && !RhsT->isDependentType() &&
5890  "Cannot evaluate traits of dependent types");
5891 
5892  switch(BTT) {
5893  case BTT_IsBaseOf: {
5894  // C++0x [meta.rel]p2
5895  // Base is a base class of Derived without regard to cv-qualifiers or
5896  // Base and Derived are not unions and name the same class type without
5897  // regard to cv-qualifiers.
5898 
5899  const RecordType *lhsRecord = LhsT->getAs<RecordType>();
5900  const RecordType *rhsRecord = RhsT->getAs<RecordType>();
5901  if (!rhsRecord || !lhsRecord) {
5902  const ObjCObjectType *LHSObjTy = LhsT->getAs<ObjCObjectType>();
5903  const ObjCObjectType *RHSObjTy = RhsT->getAs<ObjCObjectType>();
5904  if (!LHSObjTy || !RHSObjTy)
5905  return false;
5906 
5907  ObjCInterfaceDecl *BaseInterface = LHSObjTy->getInterface();
5908  ObjCInterfaceDecl *DerivedInterface = RHSObjTy->getInterface();
5909  if (!BaseInterface || !DerivedInterface)
5910  return false;
5911 
5912  if (Self.RequireCompleteType(
5913  Rhs->getTypeLoc().getBeginLoc(), RhsT,
5914  diag::err_incomplete_type_used_in_type_trait_expr))
5915  return false;
5916 
5917  return BaseInterface->isSuperClassOf(DerivedInterface);
5918  }
5919 
5920  assert(Self.Context.hasSameUnqualifiedType(LhsT, RhsT)
5921  == (lhsRecord == rhsRecord));
5922 
5923  // Unions are never base classes, and never have base classes.
5924  // It doesn't matter if they are complete or not. See PR#41843
5925  if (lhsRecord && lhsRecord->getDecl()->isUnion())
5926  return false;
5927  if (rhsRecord && rhsRecord->getDecl()->isUnion())
5928  return false;
5929 
5930  if (lhsRecord == rhsRecord)
5931  return true;
5932 
5933  // C++0x [meta.rel]p2:
5934  // If Base and Derived are class types and are different types
5935  // (ignoring possible cv-qualifiers) then Derived shall be a
5936  // complete type.
5937  if (Self.RequireCompleteType(
5938  Rhs->getTypeLoc().getBeginLoc(), RhsT,
5939  diag::err_incomplete_type_used_in_type_trait_expr))
5940  return false;
5941 
5942  return cast<CXXRecordDecl>(rhsRecord->getDecl())
5943  ->isDerivedFrom(cast<CXXRecordDecl>(lhsRecord->getDecl()));
5944  }
5945  case BTT_IsSame:
5946  return Self.Context.hasSameType(LhsT, RhsT);
5947  case BTT_TypeCompatible: {
5948  // GCC ignores cv-qualifiers on arrays for this builtin.
5949  Qualifiers LhsQuals, RhsQuals;
5950  QualType Lhs = Self.getASTContext().getUnqualifiedArrayType(LhsT, LhsQuals);
5951  QualType Rhs = Self.getASTContext().getUnqualifiedArrayType(RhsT, RhsQuals);
5952  return Self.Context.typesAreCompatible(Lhs, Rhs);
5953  }
5954  case BTT_IsConvertible:
5955  case BTT_IsConvertibleTo:
5956  case BTT_IsNothrowConvertible: {
5957  // C++0x [meta.rel]p4:
5958  // Given the following function prototype:
5959  //
5960  // template <class T>
5961  // typename add_rvalue_reference<T>::type create();
5962  //
5963  // the predicate condition for a template specialization
5964  // is_convertible<From, To> shall be satisfied if and only if
5965  // the return expression in the following code would be
5966  // well-formed, including any implicit conversions to the return
5967  // type of the function:
5968  //
5969  // To test() {
5970  // return create<From>();
5971  // }
5972  //
5973  // Access checking is performed as if in a context unrelated to To and
5974  // From. Only the validity of the immediate context of the expression
5975  // of the return-statement (including conversions to the return type)
5976  // is considered.
5977  //
5978  // We model the initialization as a copy-initialization of a temporary
5979  // of the appropriate type, which for this expression is identical to the
5980  // return statement (since NRVO doesn't apply).
5981 
5982  // Functions aren't allowed to return function or array types.
5983  if (RhsT->isFunctionType() || RhsT->isArrayType())
5984  return false;
5985 
5986  // A return statement in a void function must have void type.
5987  if (RhsT->isVoidType())
5988  return LhsT->isVoidType();
5989 
5990  // A function definition requires a complete, non-abstract return type.
5991  if (!Self.isCompleteType(Rhs->getTypeLoc().getBeginLoc(), RhsT) ||
5992  Self.isAbstractType(Rhs->getTypeLoc().getBeginLoc(), RhsT))
5993  return false;
5994 
5995  // Compute the result of add_rvalue_reference.
5996  if (LhsT->isObjectType() || LhsT->isFunctionType())
5997  LhsT = Self.Context.getRValueReferenceType(LhsT);
5998 
5999  // Build a fake source and destination for initialization.
6000  InitializedEntity To(InitializedEntity::InitializeTemporary(RhsT));
6001  OpaqueValueExpr From(KeyLoc, LhsT.getNonLValueExprType(Self.Context),
6002  Expr::getValueKindForType(LhsT));
6003  Expr *FromPtr = &From;
6004  InitializationKind Kind(InitializationKind::CreateCopy(KeyLoc,
6005  SourceLocation()));
6006 
6007  // Perform the initialization in an unevaluated context within a SFINAE
6008  // trap at translation unit scope.
6009  EnterExpressionEvaluationContext Unevaluated(
6010  Self, Sema::ExpressionEvaluationContext::Unevaluated);
6011  Sema::SFINAETrap SFINAE(Self, /*AccessCheckingSFINAE=*/true);
6012  Sema::ContextRAII TUContext(Self, Self.Context.getTranslationUnitDecl());
6013  InitializationSequence Init(Self, To, Kind, FromPtr);
6014  if (Init.Failed())
6015  return false;
6016 
6017  ExprResult Result = Init.Perform(Self, To, Kind, FromPtr);
6018  if (Result.isInvalid() || SFINAE.hasErrorOccurred())
6019  return false;
6020 
6021  if (BTT != BTT_IsNothrowConvertible)
6022  return true;
6023 
6024  return Self.canThrow(Result.get()) == CT_Cannot;
6025  }
6026 
6027  case BTT_IsAssignable:
