6028  case BTT_IsNothrowAssignable:
6029  case BTT_IsTriviallyAssignable: {
6030  // C++11 [meta.unary.prop]p3:
6031  // is_trivially_assignable is defined as:
6032  // is_assignable<T, U>::value is true and the assignment, as defined by
6033  // is_assignable, is known to call no operation that is not trivial
6034  //
6035  // is_assignable is defined as:
6036  // The expression declval<T>() = declval<U>() is well-formed when
6037  // treated as an unevaluated operand (Clause 5).
6038  //
6039  // For both, T and U shall be complete types, (possibly cv-qualified)
6040  // void, or arrays of unknown bound.
6041  if (!LhsT->isVoidType() && !LhsT->isIncompleteArrayType() &&
6042  Self.RequireCompleteType(
6043  Lhs->getTypeLoc().getBeginLoc(), LhsT,
6044  diag::err_incomplete_type_used_in_type_trait_expr))
6045  return false;
6046  if (!RhsT->isVoidType() && !RhsT->isIncompleteArrayType() &&
6047  Self.RequireCompleteType(
6048  Rhs->getTypeLoc().getBeginLoc(), RhsT,
6049  diag::err_incomplete_type_used_in_type_trait_expr))
6050  return false;
6051 
6052  // cv void is never assignable.
6053  if (LhsT->isVoidType() || RhsT->isVoidType())
6054  return false;
6055 
6056  // Build expressions that emulate the effect of declval<T>() and
6057  // declval<U>().
6058  if (LhsT->isObjectType() || LhsT->isFunctionType())
6059  LhsT = Self.Context.getRValueReferenceType(LhsT);
6060  if (RhsT->isObjectType() || RhsT->isFunctionType())
6061  RhsT = Self.Context.getRValueReferenceType(RhsT);
6062  OpaqueValueExpr Lhs(KeyLoc, LhsT.getNonLValueExprType(Self.Context),
6063  Expr::getValueKindForType(LhsT));
6064  OpaqueValueExpr Rhs(KeyLoc, RhsT.getNonLValueExprType(Self.Context),
6065  Expr::getValueKindForType(RhsT));
6066 
6067  // Attempt the assignment in an unevaluated context within a SFINAE
6068  // trap at translation unit scope.
6069  EnterExpressionEvaluationContext Unevaluated(
6070  Self, Sema::ExpressionEvaluationContext::Unevaluated);
6071  Sema::SFINAETrap SFINAE(Self, /*AccessCheckingSFINAE=*/true);
6072  Sema::ContextRAII TUContext(Self, Self.Context.getTranslationUnitDecl());
6073  ExprResult Result = Self.BuildBinOp(/*S=*/nullptr, KeyLoc, BO_Assign, &Lhs,
6074  &Rhs);
6075  if (Result.isInvalid())
6076  return false;
6077 
6078  // Treat the assignment as unused for the purpose of -Wdeprecated-volatile.
6079  Self.CheckUnusedVolatileAssignment(Result.get());
6080 
6081  if (SFINAE.hasErrorOccurred())
6082  return false;
6083 
6084  if (BTT == BTT_IsAssignable)
6085  return true;
6086 
6087  if (BTT == BTT_IsNothrowAssignable)
6088  return Self.canThrow(Result.get()) == CT_Cannot;
6089 
6090  if (BTT == BTT_IsTriviallyAssignable) {
6091  // Under Objective-C ARC and Weak, if the destination has non-trivial
6092  // Objective-C lifetime, this is a non-trivial assignment.
6093  if (LhsT.getNonReferenceType().hasNonTrivialObjCLifetime())
6094  return false;
6095 
6096  return !Result.get()->hasNonTrivialCall(Self.Context);
6097  }
6098 
6099  llvm_unreachable("unhandled type trait");
6100  return false;
6101  }
6102  case BTT_IsLayoutCompatible: {
6103  if (!LhsT->isVoidType() && !LhsT->isIncompleteArrayType())
6104  Self.RequireCompleteType(Lhs->getTypeLoc().getBeginLoc(), LhsT,
6105  diag::err_incomplete_type);
6106  if (!RhsT->isVoidType() && !RhsT->isIncompleteArrayType())
6107  Self.RequireCompleteType(Rhs->getTypeLoc().getBeginLoc(), RhsT,
6108  diag::err_incomplete_type);
6109 
6110  DiagnoseVLAInCXXTypeTrait(Self, Lhs, tok::kw___is_layout_compatible);
6111  DiagnoseVLAInCXXTypeTrait(Self, Rhs, tok::kw___is_layout_compatible);
6112 
6113  return Self.IsLayoutCompatible(LhsT, RhsT);
6114  }
6115  case BTT_IsPointerInterconvertibleBaseOf: {
6116  if (LhsT->isStructureOrClassType() && RhsT->isStructureOrClassType() &&
6117  !Self.getASTContext().hasSameUnqualifiedType(LhsT, RhsT)) {
6118  Self.RequireCompleteType(Rhs->getTypeLoc().getBeginLoc(), RhsT,
6119  diag::err_incomplete_type);
6120  }
6121 
6122  DiagnoseVLAInCXXTypeTrait(Self, Lhs,
6123  tok::kw___is_pointer_interconvertible_base_of);
6124  DiagnoseVLAInCXXTypeTrait(Self, Rhs,
6125  tok::kw___is_pointer_interconvertible_base_of);
6126 
6127  return Self.IsPointerInterconvertibleBaseOf(Lhs, Rhs);
6128  }
6129  default: llvm_unreachable("not a BTT");
6130  }
6131  llvm_unreachable("Unknown type trait or not implemented");
6132 }
6133 
6134 ExprResult Sema::ActOnArrayTypeTrait(ArrayTypeTrait ATT,
6135  SourceLocation KWLoc,
6136  ParsedType Ty,
6137  Expr* DimExpr,
6138  SourceLocation RParen) {
6139  TypeSourceInfo *TSInfo;
6140  QualType T = GetTypeFromParser(Ty, &TSInfo);
6141  if (!TSInfo)
6142  TSInfo = Context.getTrivialTypeSourceInfo(T);
6143 
6144  return BuildArrayTypeTrait(ATT, KWLoc, TSInfo, DimExpr, RParen);
6145 }
6146 
6147 static uint64_t EvaluateArrayTypeTrait(Sema &Self, ArrayTypeTrait ATT,
6148  QualType T, Expr *DimExpr,
6149  SourceLocation KeyLoc) {
6150  assert(!T->isDependentType() && "Cannot evaluate traits of dependent type");
6151 
6152  switch(ATT) {
6153  case ATT_ArrayRank:
6154  if (T->isArrayType()) {
6155  unsigned Dim = 0;
6156  while (const ArrayType *AT = Self.Context.getAsArrayType(T)) {
6157  ++Dim;
6158  T = AT->getElementType();
6159  }
6160  return Dim;
6161  }
6162  return 0;
6163 
6164  case ATT_ArrayExtent: {
6165  llvm::APSInt Value;
6166  uint64_t Dim;
6167  if (Self.VerifyIntegerConstantExpression(
6168  DimExpr, &Value, diag::err_dimension_expr_not_constant_integer)
6169  .isInvalid())
6170  return 0;
6171  if (Value.isSigned() && Value.isNegative()) {
6172  Self.Diag(KeyLoc, diag::err_dimension_expr_not_constant_integer)
6173  << DimExpr->getSourceRange();
6174  return 0;
6175  }
6176  Dim = Value.getLimitedValue();
6177 
6178  if (T->isArrayType()) {
6179  unsigned D = 0;
6180  bool Matched = false;
6181  while (const ArrayType *AT = Self.Context.getAsArrayType(T)) {
6182  if (Dim == D) {
6183  Matched = true;
6184  break;
6185  }
6186  ++D;
6187  T = AT->getElementType();
6188  }
6189 
6190  if (Matched && T->isArrayType()) {
6191  if (const ConstantArrayType *CAT = Self.Context.getAsConstantArrayType(T))
6192  return CAT->getLimitedSize();
6193  }
6194  }
6195  return 0;
6196  }
6197  }
6198  llvm_unreachable("Unknown type trait or not implemented");
6199 }
6200 
6201 ExprResult Sema::BuildArrayTypeTrait(ArrayTypeTrait ATT,
6202  SourceLocation KWLoc,
6203  TypeSourceInfo *TSInfo,
6204  Expr* DimExpr,
6205  SourceLocation RParen) {
6206  QualType T = TSInfo->getType();
6207 
6208  // FIXME: This should likely be tracked as an APInt to remove any host
6209  // assumptions about the width of size_t on the target.
6210  uint64_t Value = 0;
6211  if (!T->isDependentType())
6212  Value = EvaluateArrayTypeTrait(*this, ATT, T, DimExpr, KWLoc);
6213 
6214  // While the specification for these traits from the Embarcadero C++
6215  // compiler's documentation says the return type is 'unsigned int', Clang
6216  // returns 'size_t'. On Windows, the primary platform for the Embarcadero
6217  // compiler, there is no difference. On several other platforms this is an
6218  // important distinction.
6219  return new (Context) ArrayTypeTraitExpr(KWLoc, ATT, TSInfo, Value, DimExpr,
6220  RParen, Context.getSizeType());
6221 }

6223 ExprResult Sema::ActOnExpressionTrait(ExpressionTrait ET,
6224  SourceLocation KWLoc,
6225  Expr *Queried,
6226  SourceLocation RParen) {
6227  // If error parsing the expression, ignore.
6228  if (!Queried)
6229  return ExprError();
6230 
6231  ExprResult Result = BuildExpressionTrait(ET, KWLoc, Queried, RParen);
6232 
6233  return Result;
6234 }
6235 
6236 static bool EvaluateExpressionTrait(ExpressionTrait ET, Expr *E) {
6237  switch (ET) {
6238  case ET_IsLValueExpr: return E->isLValue();
6239  case ET_IsRValueExpr:
6240  return E->isPRValue();
6241  }
6242  llvm_unreachable("Expression trait not covered by switch");
6243 }
6244 
6245 ExprResult Sema::BuildExpressionTrait(ExpressionTrait ET,
6246  SourceLocation KWLoc,
6247  Expr *Queried,
6248  SourceLocation RParen) {
6249  if (Queried->isTypeDependent()) {
6250  // Delay type-checking for type-dependent expressions.
6251  } else if (Queried->hasPlaceholderType()) {
6252  ExprResult PE = CheckPlaceholderExpr(Queried);
6253  if (PE.isInvalid()) return ExprError();
6254  return BuildExpressionTrait(ET, KWLoc, PE.get(), RParen);
6255  }
6256 
6257  bool Value = EvaluateExpressionTrait(ET, Queried);
6258 
6259  return new (Context)
6260  ExpressionTraitExpr(KWLoc, ET, Queried, Value, RParen, Context.BoolTy);
6261 }
6262 
6263 QualType Sema::CheckPointerToMemberOperands(ExprResult &LHS, ExprResult &RHS,
6264  ExprValueKind &VK,
6265  SourceLocation Loc,
6266  bool isIndirect) {
6267  assert(!LHS.get()->hasPlaceholderType() && !RHS.get()->hasPlaceholderType() &&
6268  "placeholders should have been weeded out by now");
6269 
6270  // The LHS undergoes lvalue conversions if this is ->*, and undergoes the
6271  // temporary materialization conversion otherwise.
6272  if (isIndirect)
6273  LHS = DefaultLvalueConversion(LHS.get());
6274  else if (LHS.get()->isPRValue())
6275  LHS = TemporaryMaterializationConversion(LHS.get());
6276  if (LHS.isInvalid())
6277  return QualType();
6278 
6279  // The RHS always undergoes lvalue conversions.
6280  RHS = DefaultLvalueConversion(RHS.get());
6281  if (RHS.isInvalid()) return QualType();
6282 
6283  const char *OpSpelling = isIndirect ? "->*" : ".*";
6284  // C++ 5.5p2
6285  // The binary operator .* [p3: ->*] binds its second operand, which shall
6286  // be of type "pointer to member of T" (where T is a completely-defined
6287  // class type) [...]
6288  QualType RHSType = RHS.get()->getType();
6289  const MemberPointerType *MemPtr = RHSType->getAs<MemberPointerType>();
6290  if (!MemPtr) {
6291  Diag(Loc, diag::err_bad_memptr_rhs)
6292  << OpSpelling << RHSType << RHS.get()->getSourceRange();
6293  return QualType();
6294  }
6295 
6296  QualType Class(MemPtr->getClass(), 0);
6297 
6298  // Note: C++ [expr.mptr.oper]p2-3 says that the class type into which the
6299  // member pointer points must be completely-defined. However, there is no
6300  // reason for this semantic distinction, and the rule is not enforced by
6301  // other compilers. Therefore, we do not check this property, as it is
6302  // likely to be considered a defect.
6303 
6304  // C++ 5.5p2
6305  // [...] to its first operand, which shall be of class T or of a class of
6306  // which T is an unambiguous and accessible base class. [p3: a pointer to
6307  // such a class]
6308  QualType LHSType = LHS.get()->getType();
6309  if (isIndirect) {
6310  if (const PointerType *Ptr = LHSType->getAs<PointerType>())
6311  LHSType = Ptr->getPointeeType();
6312  else {
6313  Diag(Loc, diag::err_bad_memptr_lhs)
6314  << OpSpelling << 1 << LHSType
6315  << FixItHint::CreateReplacement(SourceRange(Loc), ".*");
6316  return QualType();
6317  }
6318  }
6319 
6320  if (!Context.hasSameUnqualifiedType(Class, LHSType)) {
6321  // If we want to check the hierarchy, we need a complete type.
6322  if (RequireCompleteType(Loc, LHSType, diag::err_bad_memptr_lhs,
6323  OpSpelling, (int)isIndirect)) {
6324  return QualType();
6325  }
6326 
6327  if (!IsDerivedFrom(Loc, LHSType, Class)) {
6328  Diag(Loc, diag::err_bad_memptr_lhs) << OpSpelling
6329  << (int)isIndirect << LHS.get()->getType();
6330  return QualType();
6331  }
6332 
6333  CXXCastPath BasePath;
6334  if (CheckDerivedToBaseConversion(
6335  LHSType, Class, Loc,
6336  SourceRange(LHS.get()->getBeginLoc(), RHS.get()->getEndLoc()),
6337  &BasePath))
6338  return QualType();
6339 
6340  // Cast LHS to type of use.
6341  QualType UseType = Context.getQualifiedType(Class, LHSType.getQualifiers());
6342  if (isIndirect)
6343  UseType = Context.getPointerType(UseType);
6344  ExprValueKind VK = isIndirect ? VK_PRValue : LHS.get()->getValueKind();
6345  LHS = ImpCastExprToType(LHS.get(), UseType, CK_DerivedToBase, VK,
6346  &BasePath);
6347  }
6348 
6349  if (isa<CXXScalarValueInitExpr>(RHS.get()->IgnoreParens())) {
6350  // Diagnose use of pointer-to-member type which when used as
6351  // the functional cast in a pointer-to-member expression.
6352  Diag(Loc, diag::err_pointer_to_member_type) << isIndirect;
6353  return QualType();
6354  }
6355 
6356  // C++ 5.5p2
6357  // The result is an object or a function of the type specified by the
6358  // second operand.
6359  // The cv qualifiers are the union of those in the pointer and the left side,
6360  // in accordance with 5.5p5 and 5.2.5.
6361  QualType Result = MemPtr->getPointeeType();
6362  Result = Context.getCVRQualifiedType(Result, LHSType.getCVRQualifiers());
6363 
6364  // C++0x [expr.mptr.oper]p6:
6365  // In a .* expression whose object expression is an rvalue, the program is
6366  // ill-formed if the second operand is a pointer to member function with
6367  // ref-qualifier &. In a ->* expression or in a .* expression whose object
6368  // expression is an lvalue, the program is ill-formed if the second operand
6369  // is a pointer to member function with ref-qualifier &&.
6370  if (const FunctionProtoType *Proto = Result->getAs<FunctionProtoType>()) {
6371  switch (Proto->getRefQualifier()) {
6372  case RQ_None:
6373  // Do nothing
6374  break;
6375 
6376  case RQ_LValue:
6377  if (!isIndirect && !LHS.get()->Classify(Context).isLValue()) {
6378  // C++2a allows functions with ref-qualifier & if their cv-qualifier-seq
6379  // is (exactly) 'const'.
6380  if (Proto->isConst() && !Proto->isVolatile())
6381  Diag(Loc, getLangOpts().CPlusPlus20
6382  ? diag::warn_cxx17_compat_pointer_to_const_ref_member_on_rvalue
6383  : diag::ext_pointer_to_const_ref_member_on_rvalue);
6384  else
6385  Diag(Loc, diag::err_pointer_to_member_oper_value_classify)
6386  << RHSType << 1 << LHS.get()->getSourceRange();
6387  }
6388  break;
6389 
6390  case RQ_RValue:
6391  if (isIndirect || !LHS.get()->Classify(Context).isRValue())
6392  Diag(Loc, diag::err_pointer_to_member_oper_value_classify)
6393  << RHSType << 0 << LHS.get()->getSourceRange();
6394  break;
6395  }
6396  }
6397 
6398  // C++ [expr.mptr.oper]p6:
6399  // The result of a .* expression whose second operand is a pointer
6400  // to a data member is of the same value category as its
6401  // first operand. The result of a .* expression whose second
6402  // operand is a pointer to a member function is a prvalue. The
6403  // result of an ->* expression is an lvalue if its second operand
6404  // is a pointer to data member and a prvalue otherwise.
6405  if (Result->isFunctionType()) {
6406  VK = VK_PRValue;
6407  return Context.BoundMemberTy;
6408  } else if (isIndirect) {
6409  VK = VK_LValue;
6410  } else {
6411  VK = LHS.get()->getValueKind();
6412  }
6413 
6414  return Result;
6415 }
6416 
6417 /// Try to convert a type to another according to C++11 5.16p3.
6418 ///
6419 /// This is part of the parameter validation for the ? operator. If either
6420 /// value operand is a class type, the two operands are attempted to be
6421 /// converted to each other. This function does the conversion in one direction.
6422 /// It returns true if the program is ill-formed and has already been diagnosed
6423 /// as such.
6424 static bool TryClassUnification(Sema &Self, Expr *From, Expr *To,
6425  SourceLocation QuestionLoc,
6426  bool &HaveConversion,
6427  QualType &ToType) {
6428  HaveConversion = false;
6429  ToType = To->getType();
6430 
6431  InitializationKind Kind =
6432  InitializationKind::CreateCopy(To->getBeginLoc(), SourceLocation());
6433  // C++11 5.16p3
6434  // The process for determining whether an operand expression E1 of type T1
6435  // can be converted to match an operand expression E2 of type T2 is defined
6436  // as follows:
6437  // -- If E2 is an lvalue: E1 can be converted to match E2 if E1 can be
6438  // implicitly converted to type "lvalue reference to T2", subject to the
6439  // constraint that in the conversion the reference must bind directly to
6440  // an lvalue.
6441  // -- If E2 is an xvalue: E1 can be converted to match E2 if E1 can be
6442  // implicitly converted to the type "rvalue reference to R2", subject to
6443  // the constraint that the reference must bind directly.
6444  if (To->isGLValue()) {
6445  QualType T = Self.Context.getReferenceQualifiedType(To);
6446  InitializedEntity Entity = InitializedEntity::InitializeTemporary(T);
6447 
6448  InitializationSequence InitSeq(Self, Entity, Kind, From);
6449  if (InitSeq.isDirectReferenceBinding()) {
6450  ToType = T;
6451  HaveConversion = true;
6452  return false;
6453  }
6454 
6455  if (InitSeq.isAmbiguous())
6456  return InitSeq.Diagnose(Self, Entity, Kind, From);
6457  }
6458 
6459  // -- If E2 is an rvalue, or if the conversion above cannot be done:
6460  // -- if E1 and E2 have class type, and the underlying class types are
6461  // the same or one is a base class of the other:
6462  QualType FTy = From->getType();
6463  QualType TTy = To->getType();
6464  const RecordType *FRec = FTy->getAs<RecordType>();
6465  const RecordType *TRec = TTy->getAs<RecordType>();
6466  bool FDerivedFromT = FRec && TRec && FRec != TRec &&
6467  Self.IsDerivedFrom(QuestionLoc, FTy, TTy);
6468  if (FRec && TRec && (FRec == TRec || FDerivedFromT ||
6469  Self.IsDerivedFrom(QuestionLoc, TTy, FTy))) {
6470  // E1 can be converted to match E2 if the class of T2 is the
6471  // same type as, or a base class of, the class of T1, and
6472  // [cv2 > cv1].
6473  if (FRec == TRec || FDerivedFromT) {
6474  if (TTy.isAtLeastAsQualifiedAs(FTy)) {
6475  InitializedEntity Entity = InitializedEntity::InitializeTemporary(TTy);
6476  InitializationSequence InitSeq(Self, Entity, Kind, From);
6477  if (InitSeq) {
6478  HaveConversion = true;
6479  return false;
6480  }
6481 
6482  if (InitSeq.isAmbiguous())
6483  return InitSeq.Diagnose(Self, Entity, Kind, From);
6484  }
6485  }
6486 
6487  return false;
6488  }
6489 
6490  // -- Otherwise: E1 can be converted to match E2 if E1 can be
6491  // implicitly converted to the type that expression E2 would have
6492  // if E2 were converted to an rvalue (or the type it has, if E2 is
6493  // an rvalue).
6494  //
6495  // This actually refers very narrowly to the lvalue-to-rvalue conversion, not
6496  // to the array-to-pointer or function-to-pointer conversions.
6497  TTy = TTy.getNonLValueExprType(Self.Context);
6498 
6499  InitializedEntity Entity = InitializedEntity::InitializeTemporary(TTy);
6500  InitializationSequence InitSeq(Self, Entity, Kind, From);
6501  HaveConversion = !InitSeq.Failed();
6502  ToType = TTy;
6503  if (InitSeq.isAmbiguous())
6504  return InitSeq.Diagnose(Self, Entity, Kind, From);
6505 
6506  return false;
6507 }
6508 
6509 /// Try to find a common type for two according to C++0x 5.16p5.
6510 ///
6511 /// This is part of the parameter validation for the ? operator. If either
6512 /// value operand is a class type, overload resolution is used to find a
6513 /// conversion to a common type.
6514 static bool FindConditionalOverload(Sema &Self, ExprResult &LHS, ExprResult &RHS,
6515  SourceLocation QuestionLoc) {
6516  Expr *Args[2] = { LHS.get(), RHS.get() };
6517  OverloadCandidateSet CandidateSet(QuestionLoc,
6518  OverloadCandidateSet::CSK_Operator);
6519  Self.AddBuiltinOperatorCandidates(OO_Conditional, QuestionLoc, Args,
6520  CandidateSet);
6521 
6522  OverloadCandidateSet::iterator Best;
6523  switch (CandidateSet.BestViableFunction(Self, QuestionLoc, Best)) {
6524  case OR_Success: {
6525  // We found a match. Perform the conversions on the arguments and move on.
6526  ExprResult LHSRes = Self.PerformImplicitConversion(
6527  LHS.get(), Best->BuiltinParamTypes[0], Best->Conversions[0],
6528  Sema::AA_Converting);
6529  if (LHSRes.isInvalid())
6530  break;
6531  LHS = LHSRes;
6532 
6533  ExprResult RHSRes = Self.PerformImplicitConversion(
6534  RHS.get(), Best->BuiltinParamTypes[1], Best->Conversions[1],
6535  Sema::AA_Converting);
6536  if (RHSRes.isInvalid())
6537  break;
6538  RHS = RHSRes;
6539  if (Best->Function)
6540  Self.MarkFunctionReferenced(QuestionLoc, Best->Function);
6541  return false;
6542  }
6543 
6544  case OR_No_Viable_Function:
6545 
6546  // Emit a better diagnostic if one of the expressions is a null pointer
6547  // constant and the other is a pointer type. In this case, the user most
6548  // likely forgot to take the address of the other expression.
6549  if (Self.DiagnoseConditionalForNull(LHS.get(), RHS.get(), QuestionLoc))
6550  return true;
6551 
6552  Self.Diag(QuestionLoc, diag::err_typecheck_cond_incompatible_operands)
6553  << LHS.get()->getType() << RHS.get()->getType()
6554  << LHS.get()->getSourceRange() << RHS.get()->getSourceRange();
6555  return true;
6556 
6557  case OR_Ambiguous:
6558  Self.Diag(QuestionLoc, diag::err_conditional_ambiguous_ovl)
6559  << LHS.get()->getType() << RHS.get()->getType()
6560  << LHS.get()->getSourceRange() << RHS.get()->getSourceRange();
6561  // FIXME: Print the possible common types by printing the return types of
6562  // the viable candidates.
6563  break;
6564 
6565  case OR_Deleted:
6566  llvm_unreachable("Conditional operator has only built-in overloads");
6567  }
6568  return true;
6569 }
6570 
6571 /// Perform an "extended" implicit conversion as returned by
6572 /// TryClassUnification.
6573 static bool ConvertForConditional(Sema &Self, ExprResult &E, QualType T) {
6574  InitializedEntity Entity = InitializedEntity::InitializeTemporary(T);
6575  InitializationKind Kind =
6576  InitializationKind::CreateCopy(E.get()->getBeginLoc(), SourceLocation());
6577  Expr *Arg = E.get();
6578  InitializationSequence InitSeq(Self, Entity, Kind, Arg);
6579  ExprResult Result = InitSeq.Perform(Self, Entity, Kind, Arg);
6580  if (Result.isInvalid())
6581  return true;
6582 
6583  E = Result;
6584  return false;
6585 }
6586 
6587 // Check the condition operand of ?: to see if it is valid for the GCC
6588 // extension.
6589 static bool isValidVectorForConditionalCondition(ASTContext &Ctx,
6590  QualType CondTy) {
6591  if (!CondTy->isVectorType() && !CondTy->isExtVectorType())
6592  return false;
6593  const QualType EltTy =
6594  cast<VectorType>(CondTy.getCanonicalType())->getElementType();
6595  assert(!EltTy->isEnumeralType() && "Vectors cant be enum types");
6596  return EltTy->isIntegralType(Ctx);
6597 }
6598 
6599 static bool isValidSizelessVectorForConditionalCondition(ASTContext &Ctx,
6600  QualType CondTy) {
6601  if (!CondTy->isSveVLSBuiltinType())
6602  return false;
6603  const QualType EltTy =
6604  cast<BuiltinType>(CondTy.getCanonicalType())->getSveEltType(Ctx);
6605  assert(!EltTy->isEnumeralType() && "Vectors cant be enum types");
6606  return EltTy->isIntegralType(Ctx);
6607 }
6608 
6609 QualType Sema::CheckVectorConditionalTypes(ExprResult &Cond, ExprResult &LHS,
6610  ExprResult &RHS,
6611  SourceLocation QuestionLoc) {
6612  LHS = DefaultFunctionArrayLvalueConversion(LHS.get());
6613  RHS = DefaultFunctionArrayLvalueConversion(RHS.get());
6614 
6615  QualType CondType = Cond.get()->getType();
6616  const auto *CondVT = CondType->castAs<VectorType>();
6617  QualType CondElementTy = CondVT->getElementType();
6618  unsigned CondElementCount = CondVT->getNumElements();
6619  QualType LHSType = LHS.get()->getType();
6620  const auto *LHSVT = LHSType->getAs<VectorType>();
6621  QualType RHSType = RHS.get()->getType();
6622  const auto *RHSVT = RHSType->getAs<VectorType>();
6623 
6624  QualType ResultType;
6625 
6626 
6627  if (LHSVT && RHSVT) {
6628  if (isa<ExtVectorType>(CondVT) != isa<ExtVectorType>(LHSVT)) {
6629  Diag(QuestionLoc, diag::err_conditional_vector_cond_result_mismatch)
6630  << /*isExtVector*/ isa<ExtVectorType>(CondVT);
6631  return {};
6632  }
6633 
6634  // If both are vector types, they must be the same type.
6635  if (!Context.hasSameType(LHSType, RHSType)) {
6636  Diag(QuestionLoc, diag::err_conditional_vector_mismatched)
6637  << LHSType << RHSType;
6638  return {};
6639  }
6640  ResultType = Context.getCommonSugaredType(LHSType, RHSType);
6641  } else if (LHSVT || RHSVT) {
6642  ResultType = CheckVectorOperands(
6643  LHS, RHS, QuestionLoc, /*isCompAssign*/ false, /*AllowBothBool*/ true,
6644  /*AllowBoolConversions*/ false,
6645  /*AllowBoolOperation*/ true,
6646  /*ReportInvalid*/ true);
6647  if (ResultType.isNull())
6648  return {};
6649  } else {
6650  // Both are scalar.
6651  LHSType = LHSType.getUnqualifiedType();
6652  RHSType = RHSType.getUnqualifiedType();
6653  QualType ResultElementTy =
6654  Context.hasSameType(LHSType, RHSType)
6655  ? Context.getCommonSugaredType(LHSType, RHSType)
6656  : UsualArithmeticConversions(LHS, RHS, QuestionLoc,
6657  ACK_Conditional);
6658 
6659  if (ResultElementTy->isEnumeralType()) {
6660  Diag(QuestionLoc, diag::err_conditional_vector_operand_type)
6661  << ResultElementTy;
6662  return {};
6663  }
6664  if (CondType->isExtVectorType())
6665  ResultType =
6666  Context.getExtVectorType(ResultElementTy, CondVT->getNumElements());
6667  else
6668  ResultType = Context.getVectorType(
6669  ResultElementTy, CondVT->getNumElements(), VectorKind::Generic);
6670 
6671  LHS = ImpCastExprToType(LHS.get(), ResultType, CK_VectorSplat);
6672  RHS = ImpCastExprToType(RHS.get(), ResultType, CK_VectorSplat);
6673  }
6674 
6675  assert(!ResultType.isNull() && ResultType->isVectorType() &&
6676  (!CondType->isExtVectorType() || ResultType->isExtVectorType()) &&
6677  "Result should have been a vector type");
6678  auto *ResultVectorTy = ResultType->castAs<VectorType>();
6679  QualType ResultElementTy = ResultVectorTy->getElementType();
6680  unsigned ResultElementCount = ResultVectorTy->getNumElements();
6681 
6682  if (ResultElementCount != CondElementCount) {
6683  Diag(QuestionLoc, diag::err_conditional_vector_size) << CondType
6684  << ResultType;
6685  return {};
6686  }
6687 
6688  if (Context.getTypeSize(ResultElementTy) !=
6689  Context.getTypeSize(CondElementTy)) {
6690  Diag(QuestionLoc, diag::err_conditional_vector_element_size) << CondType
6691  << ResultType;
6692  return {};
6693  }
6694 
6695  return ResultType;
6696 }
6697 
6698 QualType Sema::CheckSizelessVectorConditionalTypes(ExprResult &Cond,
6699  ExprResult &LHS,
6700  ExprResult &RHS,
6701  SourceLocation QuestionLoc) {
6702  LHS = DefaultFunctionArrayLvalueConversion(LHS.get());
6703  RHS = DefaultFunctionArrayLvalueConversion(RHS.get());
6704 
6705  QualType CondType = Cond.get()->getType();
6706  const auto *CondBT = CondType->castAs<BuiltinType>();
6707  QualType CondElementTy = CondBT->getSveEltType(Context);
6708  llvm::ElementCount CondElementCount =
6709  Context.getBuiltinVectorTypeInfo(CondBT).EC;
6710 
6711  QualType LHSType = LHS.get()->getType();
6712  const auto *LHSBT =
6713  LHSType->isSveVLSBuiltinType() ? LHSType->getAs<BuiltinType>() : nullptr;
6714  QualType RHSType = RHS.get()->getType();
6715  const auto *RHSBT =
6716  RHSType->isSveVLSBuiltinType() ? RHSType->getAs<BuiltinType>() : nullptr;
6717 
6718  QualType ResultType;
6719 
6720  if (LHSBT && RHSBT) {
6721  // If both are sizeless vector types, they must be the same type.
6722  if (!Context.hasSameType(LHSType, RHSType)) {
6723  Diag(QuestionLoc, diag::err_conditional_vector_mismatched)
6724  << LHSType << RHSType;
6725  return QualType();
6726  }
6727  ResultType = LHSType;
6728  } else if (LHSBT || RHSBT) {
6729  ResultType = CheckSizelessVectorOperands(
6730  LHS, RHS, QuestionLoc, /*IsCompAssign*/ false, ACK_Conditional);
6731  if (ResultType.isNull())
6732  return QualType();
6733  } else {
6734  // Both are scalar so splat
6735  QualType ResultElementTy;
6736  LHSType = LHSType.getCanonicalType().getUnqualifiedType();
6737  RHSType = RHSType.getCanonicalType().getUnqualifiedType();
6738 
6739  if (Context.hasSameType(LHSType, RHSType))
6740  ResultElementTy = LHSType;
6741  else
6742  ResultElementTy =
6743  UsualArithmeticConversions(LHS, RHS, QuestionLoc, ACK_Conditional);
6744 
6745  if (ResultElementTy->isEnumeralType()) {
6746  Diag(QuestionLoc, diag::err_conditional_vector_operand_type)
6747  << ResultElementTy;
6748  return QualType();
6749  }
6750 
6751  ResultType = Context.getScalableVectorType(
6752  ResultElementTy, CondElementCount.getKnownMinValue());
6753 
6754  LHS = ImpCastExprToType(LHS.get(), ResultType, CK_VectorSplat);
6755  RHS = ImpCastExprToType(RHS.get(), ResultType, CK_VectorSplat);
6756  }
6757 
6758  assert(!ResultType.isNull() && ResultType->isSveVLSBuiltinType() &&
6759  "Result should have been a vector type");
6760  auto *ResultBuiltinTy = ResultType->castAs<BuiltinType>();
6761  QualType ResultElementTy = ResultBuiltinTy->getSveEltType(Context);
6762  llvm::ElementCount ResultElementCount =
6763  Context.getBuiltinVectorTypeInfo(ResultBuiltinTy).EC;
6764 
6765  if (ResultElementCount != CondElementCount) {
6766  Diag(QuestionLoc, diag::err_conditional_vector_size)
6767  << CondType << ResultType;
6768  return QualType();
6769  }
6770 
6771  if (Context.getTypeSize(ResultElementTy) !=
6772  Context.getTypeSize(CondElementTy)) {
6773  Diag(QuestionLoc, diag::err_conditional_vector_element_size)
6774  << CondType << ResultType;
6775  return QualType();
6776  }
6777 
6778  return ResultType;
6779 }
6780 
6781 /// Check the operands of ?: under C++ semantics.
6782 ///
6783 /// See C++ [expr.cond]. Note that LHS is never null, even for the GNU x ?: y
6784 /// extension. In this case, LHS == Cond. (But they're not aliases.)
6785 ///
6786 /// This function also implements GCC's vector extension and the
6787 /// OpenCL/ext_vector_type extension for conditionals. The vector extensions
6788 /// permit the use of a?b:c where the type of a is that of a integer vector with
6789 /// the same number of elements and size as the vectors of b and c. If one of
6790 /// either b or c is a scalar it is implicitly converted to match the type of
6791 /// the vector. Otherwise the expression is ill-formed. If both b and c are
6792 /// scalars, then b and c are checked and converted to the type of a if
6793 /// possible.
6794 ///
6795 /// The expressions are evaluated differently for GCC's and OpenCL's extensions.
6796 /// For the GCC extension, the ?: operator is evaluated as
6797 /// (a[0] != 0 ? b[0] : c[0], .. , a[n] != 0 ? b[n] : c[n]).
6798 /// For the OpenCL extensions, the ?: operator is evaluated as
6799 /// (most-significant-bit-set(a[0]) ? b[0] : c[0], .. ,
6800 /// most-significant-bit-set(a[n]) ? b[n] : c[n]).
6801 QualType Sema::CXXCheckConditionalOperands(ExprResult &Cond, ExprResult &LHS,
6802  ExprResult &RHS, ExprValueKind &VK,
6803  ExprObjectKind &OK,
6804  SourceLocation QuestionLoc) {
6805  // FIXME: Handle C99's complex types, block pointers and Obj-C++ interface
6806  // pointers.
6807 
6808  // Assume r-value.
6809  VK = VK_PRValue;
6810  OK = OK_Ordinary;
6811  bool IsVectorConditional =
6812  isValidVectorForConditionalCondition(Context, Cond.get()->getType());
6813 
6814  bool IsSizelessVectorConditional =
6815  isValidSizelessVectorForConditionalCondition(Context,
6816  Cond.get()->getType());
6817 
6818  // C++11 [expr.cond]p1
6819  // The first expression is contextually converted to bool.
6820  if (!Cond.get()->isTypeDependent()) {
6821  ExprResult CondRes = IsVectorConditional || IsSizelessVectorConditional
6822  ? DefaultFunctionArrayLvalueConversion(Cond.get())
6823  : CheckCXXBooleanCondition(Cond.get());
6824  if (CondRes.isInvalid())
6825  return QualType();
6826  Cond = CondRes;
6827  } else {
6828  // To implement C++, the first expression typically doesn't alter the result
6829  // type of the conditional, however the GCC compatible vector extension
6830  // changes the result type to be that of the conditional. Since we cannot
6831  // know if this is a vector extension here, delay the conversion of the
6832  // LHS/RHS below until later.
6833  return Context.DependentTy;
6834  }
6835 
6836 
6837  // Either of the arguments dependent?
6838  if (LHS.get()->isTypeDependent() || RHS.get()->isTypeDependent())
6839  return Context.DependentTy;
6840 
6841  // C++11 [expr.cond]p2
6842  // If either the second or the third operand has type (cv) void, ...
6843  QualType LTy = LHS.get()->getType();
6844  QualType RTy = RHS.get()->getType();
6845  bool LVoid = LTy->isVoidType();
6846  bool RVoid = RTy->isVoidType();
6847  if (LVoid || RVoid) {
6848  // ... one of the following shall hold:
6849  // -- The second or the third operand (but not both) is a (possibly
6850  // parenthesized) throw-expression; the result is of the type
6851  // and value category of the other.
6852  bool LThrow = isa<CXXThrowExpr>(LHS.get()->IgnoreParenImpCasts());
6853  bool RThrow = isa<CXXThrowExpr>(RHS.get()->IgnoreParenImpCasts());
6854 
6855  // Void expressions aren't legal in the vector-conditional expressions.
6856  if (IsVectorConditional) {
6857  SourceRange DiagLoc =
6858  LVoid ? LHS.get()->getSourceRange() : RHS.get()->getSourceRange();
6859  bool IsThrow = LVoid ? LThrow : RThrow;
6860  Diag(DiagLoc.getBegin(), diag::err_conditional_vector_has_void)
6861  << DiagLoc << IsThrow;
6862  return QualType();
6863  }
6864 
6865  if (LThrow != RThrow) {
6866  Expr *NonThrow = LThrow ? RHS.get() : LHS.get();
6867  VK = NonThrow->getValueKind();
6868  // DR (no number yet): the result is a bit-field if the
6869  // non-throw-expression operand is a bit-field.
6870  OK = NonThrow->getObjectKind();
6871  return NonThrow->getType();
6872  }
6873 
6874  // -- Both the second and third operands have type void; the result is of
6875  // type void and is a prvalue.
6876  if (LVoid && RVoid)
6877  return Context.getCommonSugaredType(LTy, RTy);
6878 
6879  // Neither holds, error.
6880  Diag(QuestionLoc, diag::err_conditional_void_nonvoid)
6881  << (LVoid ? RTy : LTy) << (LVoid ? 0 : 1)
6882  << LHS.get()->getSourceRange() << RHS.get()->getSourceRange();
6883  return QualType();
6884  }
6885 
6886  // Neither is void.
6887  if (IsVectorConditional)
6888  return CheckVectorConditionalTypes(Cond, LHS, RHS, QuestionLoc);
6889 
6890  if (IsSizelessVectorConditional)
6891  return CheckSizelessVectorConditionalTypes(Cond, LHS, RHS, QuestionLoc);
6892 
6893  // WebAssembly tables are not allowed as conditional LHS or RHS.
6894  if (LTy->isWebAssemblyTableType() || RTy->isWebAssemblyTableType()) {
6895  Diag(QuestionLoc, diag::err_wasm_table_conditional_expression)
6896  << LHS.get()->getSourceRange() << RHS.get()->getSourceRange();
6897  return QualType();
6898  }
6899 
6900  // C++11 [expr.cond]p3
6901  // Otherwise, if the second and third operand have different types, and
6902  // either has (cv) class type [...] an attempt is made to convert each of
6903  // those operands to the type of the other.
6904  if (!Context.hasSameType(LTy, RTy) &&
6905  (LTy->isRecordType() || RTy->isRecordType())) {
6906  // These return true if a single direction is already ambiguous.
6907  QualType L2RType, R2LType;
6908  bool HaveL2R, HaveR2L;
6909  if (TryClassUnification(*this, LHS.get(), RHS.get(), QuestionLoc, HaveL2R, L2RType))
6910  return QualType();
6911  if (TryClassUnification(*this, RHS.get(), LHS.get(), QuestionLoc, HaveR2L, R2LType))
6912  return QualType();
6913 
6914  // If both can be converted, [...] the program is ill-formed.
6915  if (HaveL2R && HaveR2L) {
6916  Diag(QuestionLoc, diag::err_conditional_ambiguous)
6917  << LTy << RTy << LHS.get()->getSourceRange() << RHS.get()->getSourceRange();
6918  return QualType();
6919  }
6920 
6921  // If exactly one conversion is possible, that conversion is applied to
6922  // the chosen operand and the converted operands are used in place of the
6923  // original operands for the remainder of this section.
6924  if (HaveL2R) {
6925  if (ConvertForConditional(*this, LHS, L2RType) || LHS.isInvalid())
6926  return QualType();
6927  LTy = LHS.get()->getType();
6928  } else if (HaveR2L) {
6929  if (ConvertForConditional(*this, RHS, R2LType) || RHS.isInvalid())
6930  return QualType();
6931  RTy = RHS.get()->getType();
6932  }
6933  }
6934 
6935  // C++11 [expr.cond]p3
6936  // if both are glvalues of the same value category and the same type except
6937  // for cv-qualification, an attempt is made to convert each of those
6938  // operands to the type of the other.
6939  // FIXME:
6940  // Resolving a defect in P0012R1: we extend this to cover all cases where
6941  // one of the operands is reference-compatible with the other, in order
6942  // to support conditionals between functions differing in noexcept. This
6943  // will similarly cover difference in array bounds after P0388R4.
6944  // FIXME: If LTy and RTy have a composite pointer type, should we convert to
6945  // that instead?
6946  ExprValueKind LVK = LHS.get()->getValueKind();
6947  ExprValueKind RVK = RHS.get()->getValueKind();
6948  if (!Context.hasSameType(LTy, RTy) && LVK == RVK && LVK != VK_PRValue) {
6949  // DerivedToBase was already handled by the class-specific case above.
6950  // FIXME: Should we allow ObjC conversions here?
6951  const ReferenceConversions AllowedConversions =
6952  ReferenceConversions::Qualification |
6953  ReferenceConversions::NestedQualification |
6954  ReferenceConversions::Function;
6955 
6956  ReferenceConversions RefConv;
6957  if (CompareReferenceRelationship(QuestionLoc, LTy, RTy, &RefConv) ==
6958  Ref_Compatible &&
6959  !(RefConv & ~AllowedConversions) &&
6960  // [...] subject to the constraint that the reference must bind
6961  // directly [...]
6962  !RHS.get()->refersToBitField() && !RHS.get()->refersToVectorElement()) {
6963  RHS = ImpCastExprToType(RHS.get(), LTy, CK_NoOp, RVK);
6964  RTy = RHS.get()->getType();
6965  } else if (CompareReferenceRelationship(QuestionLoc, RTy, LTy, &RefConv) ==
6966  Ref_Compatible &&
6967  !(RefConv & ~AllowedConversions) &&
6968  !LHS.get()->refersToBitField() &&
6969  !LHS.get()->refersToVectorElement()) {
6970  LHS = ImpCastExprToType(LHS.get(), RTy, CK_NoOp, LVK);
6971  LTy = LHS.get()->getType();
6972  }
6973  }
6974 
6975  // C++11 [expr.cond]p4
6976  // If the second and third operands are glvalues of the same value
6977  // category and have the same type, the result is of that type and
6978  // value category and it is a bit-field if the second or the third
6979  // operand is a bit-field, or if both are bit-fields.
6980  // We only extend this to bitfields, not to the crazy other kinds of
6981  // l-values.
6982  bool Same = Context.hasSameType(LTy, RTy);
6983  if (Same && LVK == RVK && LVK != VK_PRValue &&
6984  LHS.get()->isOrdinaryOrBitFieldObject() &&
6985  RHS.get()->isOrdinaryOrBitFieldObject()) {
6986  VK = LHS.get()->getValueKind();
6987  if (LHS.get()->getObjectKind() == OK_BitField ||
6988  RHS.get()->getObjectKind() == OK_BitField)
6989  OK = OK_BitField;
6990  return Context.getCommonSugaredType(LTy, RTy);
6991  }
6992 
6993  // C++11 [expr.cond]p5
6994  // Otherwise, the result is a prvalue. If the second and third operands
6995  // do not have the same type, and either has (cv) class type, ...
6996  if (!Same && (LTy->isRecordType() || RTy->isRecordType())) {
6997  // ... overload resolution is used to determine the conversions (if any)
6998  // to be applied to the operands. If the overload resolution fails, the
6999  // program is ill-formed.
7000  if (FindConditionalOverload(*this, LHS, RHS, QuestionLoc))
7001  return QualType();
7002  }
7003 
7004  // C++11 [expr.cond]p6
7005  // Lvalue-to-rvalue, array-to-pointer, and function-to-pointer standard
7006  // conversions are performed on the second and third operands.
7007  LHS = DefaultFunctionArrayLvalueConversion(LHS.get());
7008  RHS = DefaultFunctionArrayLvalueConversion(RHS.get());
7009  if (LHS.isInvalid() || RHS.isInvalid())
7010  return QualType();
7011  LTy = LHS.get()->getType();
7012  RTy = RHS.get()->getType();
7013 
7014  // After those conversions, one of the following shall hold:
7015  // -- The second and third operands have the same type; the result
7016  // is of that type. If the operands have class type, the result
7017  // is a prvalue temporary of the result type, which is
7018  // copy-initialized from either the second operand or the third
7019  // operand depending on the value of the first operand.
7020  if (Context.hasSameType(LTy, RTy)) {
7021  if (LTy->isRecordType()) {
7022  // The operands have class type. Make a temporary copy.
7023  ExprResult LHSCopy = PerformCopyInitialization(
7024  InitializedEntity::InitializeTemporary(LTy), SourceLocation(), LHS);
7025  if (LHSCopy.isInvalid())
7026  return QualType();
7027 
7028  ExprResult RHSCopy = PerformCopyInitialization(
7029  InitializedEntity::InitializeTemporary(RTy), SourceLocation(), RHS);
7030  if (RHSCopy.isInvalid())
7031  return QualType();
7032 
7033  LHS = LHSCopy;
7034  RHS = RHSCopy;
7035  }
7036  return Context.getCommonSugaredType(LTy, RTy);
7037  }
7038 
7039  // Extension: conditional operator involving vector types.
7040  if (LTy->isVectorType() || RTy->isVectorType())
7041  return CheckVectorOperands(LHS, RHS, QuestionLoc, /*isCompAssign*/ false,
7042  /*AllowBothBool*/ true,
7043  /*AllowBoolConversions*/ false,
7044  /*AllowBoolOperation*/ false,
7045  /*ReportInvalid*/ true);
7046 
7047  // -- The second and third operands have arithmetic or enumeration type;
7048  // the usual arithmetic conversions are performed to bring them to a
7049  // common type, and the result is of that type.
7050  if (LTy->isArithmeticType() && RTy->isArithmeticType()) {
7051  QualType ResTy =
7052  UsualArithmeticConversions(LHS, RHS, QuestionLoc, ACK_Conditional);
7053  if (LHS.isInvalid() || RHS.isInvalid())
7054  return QualType();
7055  if (ResTy.isNull()) {
7056  Diag(QuestionLoc,
7057  diag::err_typecheck_cond_incompatible_operands) << LTy << RTy
7058  << LHS.get()->getSourceRange() << RHS.get()->getSourceRange();
7059  return QualType();
7060  }
7061 
7062  LHS = ImpCastExprToType(LHS.get(), ResTy, PrepareScalarCast(LHS, ResTy));
7063  RHS = ImpCastExprToType(RHS.get(), ResTy, PrepareScalarCast(RHS, ResTy));
7064 
7065  return ResTy;
7066  }
7067 
7068  // -- The second and third operands have pointer type, or one has pointer
7069  // type and the other is a null pointer constant, or both are null
7070  // pointer constants, at least one of which is non-integral; pointer
7071  // conversions and qualification conversions are performed to bring them
7072  // to their composite pointer type. The result is of the composite
7073  // pointer type.
7074  // -- The second and third operands have pointer to member type, or one has
7075  // pointer to member type and the other is a null pointer constant;
7076  // pointer to member conversions and qualification conversions are
7077  // performed to bring them to a common type, whose cv-qualification
7078  // shall match the cv-qualification of either the second or the third
7079  // operand. The result is of the common type.
7080  QualType Composite = FindCompositePointerType(QuestionLoc, LHS, RHS);
7081  if (!Composite.isNull())
7082  return Composite;
7083 
7084  // Similarly, attempt to find composite type of two objective-c pointers.
7085  Composite = FindCompositeObjCPointerType(LHS, RHS, QuestionLoc);
7086  if (LHS.isInvalid() || RHS.isInvalid())
7087  return QualType();
7088  if (!Composite.isNull())
7089  return Composite;
7090 
7091  // Check if we are using a null with a non-pointer type.
7092  if (DiagnoseConditionalForNull(LHS.get(), RHS.get(), QuestionLoc))
7093  return QualType();
7094 
7095  Diag(QuestionLoc, diag::err_typecheck_cond_incompatible_operands)
7096  << LHS.get()->getType() << RHS.get()->getType()
7097  << LHS.get()->getSourceRange() << RHS.get()->getSourceRange();
7098  return QualType();
7099 }
7100 
7101 /// Find a merged pointer type and convert the two expressions to it.
7102 ///
7103 /// This finds the composite pointer type for \p E1 and \p E2 according to
7104 /// C++2a [expr.type]p3. It converts both expressions to this type and returns
7105 /// it. It does not emit diagnostics (FIXME: that's not true if \p ConvertArgs
7106 /// is \c true).
7107 ///
7108 /// \param Loc The location of the operator requiring these two expressions to
7109 /// be converted to the composite pointer type.
7110 ///
7111 /// \param ConvertArgs If \c false, do not convert E1 and E2 to the target type.
7112 QualType Sema::FindCompositePointerType(SourceLocation Loc,
7113  Expr *&E1, Expr *&E2,
7114  bool ConvertArgs) {
7115  assert(getLangOpts().CPlusPlus && "This function assumes C++");
7116 
7117  // C++1z [expr]p14:
7118  // The composite pointer type of two operands p1 and p2 having types T1
7119  // and T2
7120  QualType T1 = E1->getType(), T2 = E2->getType();
7121 
7122  // where at least one is a pointer or pointer to member type or
7123  // std::nullptr_t is:
7124  bool T1IsPointerLike = T1->isAnyPointerType() || T1->isMemberPointerType() ||
7125  T1->isNullPtrType();
7126  bool T2IsPointerLike = T2->isAnyPointerType() || T2->isMemberPointerType() ||
7127  T2->isNullPtrType();
7128  if (!T1IsPointerLike && !T2IsPointerLike)
7129  return QualType();
7130 
7131  // - if both p1 and p2 are null pointer constants, std::nullptr_t;
7132  // This can't actually happen, following the standard, but we also use this
7133  // to implement the end of [expr.conv], which hits this case.
7134  //
7135  // - if either p1 or p2 is a null pointer constant, T2 or T1, respectively;
7136  if (T1IsPointerLike &&
7137  E2->isNullPointerConstant(Context, Expr::NPC_ValueDependentIsNull)) {
7138  if (ConvertArgs)
7139  E2 = ImpCastExprToType(E2, T1, T1->isMemberPointerType()
7140  ? CK_NullToMemberPointer
7141  : CK_NullToPointer).get();
7142  return T1;
7143  }
7144  if (T2IsPointerLike &&
7145  E1->isNullPointerConstant(Context, Expr::NPC_ValueDependentIsNull)) {
7146  if (ConvertArgs)
7147  E1 = ImpCastExprToType(E1, T2, T2->isMemberPointerType()
7148  ? CK_NullToMemberPointer
7149  : CK_NullToPointer).get();
7150  return T2;
7151  }
7152 
7153  // Now both have to be pointers or member pointers.
7154  if (!T1IsPointerLike || !T2IsPointerLike)
7155  return QualType();
7156  assert(!T1->isNullPtrType() && !T2->isNullPtrType() &&
7157  "nullptr_t should be a null pointer constant");
7158 
7159  struct Step {
7160  enum Kind { Pointer, ObjCPointer, MemberPointer, Array } K;
7161  // Qualifiers to apply under the step kind.
7162  Qualifiers Quals;
7163  /// The class for a pointer-to-member; a constant array type with a bound
7164  /// (if any) for an array.
7165  const Type *ClassOrBound;
7166 
7167  Step(Kind K, const Type *ClassOrBound = nullptr)
7168  : K(K), ClassOrBound(ClassOrBound) {}
7169  QualType rebuild(ASTContext &Ctx, QualType T) const {
7170  T = Ctx.getQualifiedType(T, Quals);
7171  switch (K) {
7172  case Pointer:
7173  return Ctx.getPointerType(T);
7174  case MemberPointer:
7175  return Ctx.getMemberPointerType(T, ClassOrBound);
7176  case ObjCPointer:
7177  return Ctx.getObjCObjectPointerType(T);
7178  case Array:
7179  if (auto *CAT = cast_or_null<ConstantArrayType>(ClassOrBound))
7180  return Ctx.getConstantArrayType(T, CAT->getSize(), nullptr,
7181  ArraySizeModifier::Normal, 0);
7182  else
7183  return Ctx.getIncompleteArrayType(T, ArraySizeModifier::Normal, 0);
7184  }
7185  llvm_unreachable("unknown step kind");
7186  }
7187  };
7188 
7189  SmallVector<Step, 8> Steps;
7190 
7191  // - if T1 is "pointer to cv1 C1" and T2 is "pointer to cv2 C2", where C1
7192  // is reference-related to C2 or C2 is reference-related to C1 (8.6.3),
7193  // the cv-combined type of T1 and T2 or the cv-combined type of T2 and T1,
7194  // respectively;
7195  // - if T1 is "pointer to member of C1 of type cv1 U1" and T2 is "pointer
7196  // to member of C2 of type cv2 U2" for some non-function type U, where
7197  // C1 is reference-related to C2 or C2 is reference-related to C1, the
7198  // cv-combined type of T2 and T1 or the cv-combined type of T1 and T2,
7199  // respectively;
7200  // - if T1 and T2 are similar types (4.5), the cv-combined type of T1 and
7201  // T2;
7202  //
7203  // Dismantle T1 and T2 to simultaneously determine whether they are similar
7204  // and to prepare to form the cv-combined type if so.
7205  QualType Composite1 = T1;
7206  QualType Composite2 = T2;
7207  unsigned NeedConstBefore = 0;
7208  while (true) {
7209  assert(!Composite1.isNull() && !Composite2.isNull());
7210 
7211  Qualifiers Q1, Q2;
7212  Composite1 = Context.getUnqualifiedArrayType(Composite1, Q1);
7213  Composite2 = Context.getUnqualifiedArrayType(Composite2, Q2);
7214 
7215  // Top-level qualifiers are ignored. Merge at all lower levels.
7216  if (!Steps.empty()) {
7217  // Find the qualifier union: (approximately) the unique minimal set of
7218  // qualifiers that is compatible with both types.
7219  Qualifiers Quals = Qualifiers::fromCVRUMask(Q1.getCVRUQualifiers() |
7220  Q2.getCVRUQualifiers());
7221 
7222  // Under one level of pointer or pointer-to-member, we can change to an
7223  // unambiguous compatible address space.
7224  if (Q1.getAddressSpace() == Q2.getAddressSpace()) {
7225  Quals.setAddressSpace(Q1.getAddressSpace());
7226  } else if (Steps.size() == 1) {
7227  bool MaybeQ1 = Q1.isAddressSpaceSupersetOf(Q2);
7228  bool MaybeQ2 = Q2.isAddressSpaceSupersetOf(Q1);
7229  if (MaybeQ1 == MaybeQ2) {
7230  // Exception for ptr size address spaces. Should be able to choose
7231  // either address space during comparison.
7232  if (isPtrSizeAddressSpace(Q1.getAddressSpace()) ||
7233  isPtrSizeAddressSpace(Q2.getAddressSpace()))
7234  MaybeQ1 = true;
7235  else
7236  return QualType(); // No unique best address space.
7237  }
7238  Quals.setAddressSpace(MaybeQ1 ? Q1.getAddressSpace()
7239  : Q2.getAddressSpace());
7240  } else {
7241  return QualType();
7242  }
7243 
7244  // FIXME: In C, we merge __strong and none to __strong at the top level.
7245  if (Q1.getObjCGCAttr() == Q2.getObjCGCAttr())
7246  Quals.setObjCGCAttr(Q1.getObjCGCAttr());
7247  else if (T1->isVoidPointerType() || T2->isVoidPointerType())
7248  assert(Steps.size() == 1);
7249  else
7250  return QualType();
7251 
7252  // Mismatched lifetime qualifiers never compatibly include each other.
7253  if (Q1.getObjCLifetime() == Q2.getObjCLifetime())
7254  Quals.setObjCLifetime(Q1.getObjCLifetime());
7255  else if (T1->isVoidPointerType() || T2->isVoidPointerType())
7256  assert(Steps.size() == 1);
7257  else
7258  return QualType();
7259 
7260  Steps.back().Quals = Quals;
7261  if (Q1 != Quals || Q2 != Quals)
7262  NeedConstBefore = Steps.size() - 1;
7263  }
7264 
7265  // FIXME: Can we unify the following with UnwrapSimilarTypes?
7266 
7267  const ArrayType *Arr1, *Arr2;
7268  if ((Arr1 = Context.getAsArrayType(Composite1)) &&
7269  (Arr2 = Context.getAsArrayType(Composite2))) {
7270  auto *CAT1 = dyn_cast<ConstantArrayType>(Arr1);
7271  auto *CAT2 = dyn_cast<ConstantArrayType>(Arr2);
7272  if (CAT1 && CAT2 && CAT1->getSize() == CAT2->getSize()) {
7273  Composite1 = Arr1->getElementType();
7274  Composite2 = Arr2->getElementType();
7275  Steps.emplace_back(Step::Array, CAT1);
7276  continue;
7277  }
7278  bool IAT1 = isa<IncompleteArrayType>(Arr1);
7279  bool IAT2 = isa<IncompleteArrayType>(Arr2);
7280  if ((IAT1 && IAT2) ||
7281  (getLangOpts().CPlusPlus20 && (IAT1 != IAT2) &&
7282  ((bool)CAT1 != (bool)CAT2) &&
7283  (Steps.empty() || Steps.back().K != Step::Array))) {
7284  // In C++20 onwards, we can unify an array of N T with an array of
7285  // a different or unknown bound. But we can't form an array whose
7286  // element type is an array of unknown bound by doing so.
7287  Composite1 = Arr1->getElementType();
7288  Composite2 = Arr2->getElementType();
7289  Steps.emplace_back(Step::Array);
7290  if (CAT1 || CAT2)
7291  NeedConstBefore = Steps.size();
7292  continue;
7293  }
7294  }
7295 
7296  const PointerType *Ptr1, *Ptr2;
7297  if ((Ptr1 = Composite1->getAs<PointerType>()) &&
7298  (Ptr2 = Composite2->getAs<PointerType>())) {
7299  Composite1 = Ptr1->getPointeeType();
7300  Composite2 = Ptr2->getPointeeType();
7301  Steps.emplace_back(Step::Pointer);
7302  continue;
7303  }
7304 
7305  const ObjCObjectPointerType *ObjPtr1, *ObjPtr2;
7306  if ((ObjPtr1 = Composite1->getAs<ObjCObjectPointerType>()) &&
7307  (ObjPtr2 = Composite2->getAs<ObjCObjectPointerType>())) {
7308  Composite1 = ObjPtr1->getPointeeType();
7309  Composite2 = ObjPtr2->getPointeeType();
7310  Steps.emplace_back(Step::ObjCPointer);
7311  continue;
7312  }
7313 
7314  const MemberPointerType *MemPtr1, *MemPtr2;
7315  if ((MemPtr1 = Composite1->getAs<MemberPointerType>()) &&
7316  (MemPtr2 = Composite2->getAs<MemberPointerType>())) {
7317  Composite1 = MemPtr1->getPointeeType();
7318  Composite2 = MemPtr2->getPointeeType();
7319 
7320  // At the top level, we can perform a base-to-derived pointer-to-member
7321  // conversion:
7322  //
7323  // - [...] where C1 is reference-related to C2 or C2 is
7324  // reference-related to C1
7325  //
7326  // (Note that the only kinds of reference-relatedness in scope here are
7327  // "same type or derived from".) At any other level, the class must
7328  // exactly match.
7329  const Type *Class = nullptr;
7330  QualType Cls1(MemPtr1->getClass(), 0);
7331  QualType Cls2(MemPtr2->getClass(), 0);
7332  if (Context.hasSameType(Cls1, Cls2))
7333  Class = MemPtr1->getClass();
7334  else if (Steps.empty())
7335  Class = IsDerivedFrom(Loc, Cls1, Cls2) ? MemPtr1->getClass() :
7336  IsDerivedFrom(Loc, Cls2, Cls1) ? MemPtr2->getClass() : nullptr;
7337  if (!Class)
7338  return QualType();
7339 
7340  Steps.emplace_back(Step::MemberPointer, Class);
7341  continue;
7342  }
7343 
7344  // Special case: at the top level, we can decompose an Objective-C pointer
7345  // and a 'cv void *'. Unify the qualifiers.
7346  if (Steps.empty() && ((Composite1->isVoidPointerType() &&
7347  Composite2->isObjCObjectPointerType()) ||
7348  (Composite1->isObjCObjectPointerType() &&
7349  Composite2->isVoidPointerType()))) {
7350  Composite1 = Composite1->getPointeeType();
7351  Composite2 = Composite2->getPointeeType();
7352  Steps.emplace_back(Step::Pointer);
7353  continue;
7354  }
7355 
7356  // FIXME: block pointer types?
7357 
7358  // Cannot unwrap any more types.
7359  break;
7360  }
7361 
7362  // - if T1 or T2 is "pointer to noexcept function" and the other type is
7363  // "pointer to function", where the function types are otherwise the same,
7364  // "pointer to function";
7365  // - if T1 or T2 is "pointer to member of C1 of type function", the other
7366  // type is "pointer to member of C2 of type noexcept function", and C1
7367  // is reference-related to C2 or C2 is reference-related to C1, where
7368  // the function types are otherwise the same, "pointer to member of C2 of
7369  // type function" or "pointer to member of C1 of type function",
7370  // respectively;
7371  //
7372  // We also support 'noreturn' here, so as a Clang extension we generalize the
7373  // above to:
7374  //
7375  // - [Clang] If T1 and T2 are both of type "pointer to function" or
7376  // "pointer to member function" and the pointee types can be unified
7377  // by a function pointer conversion, that conversion is applied
7378  // before checking the following rules.
7379  //
7380  // We've already unwrapped down to the function types, and we want to merge
7381  // rather than just convert, so do this ourselves rather than calling
7382  // IsFunctionConversion.
7383  //
7384  // FIXME: In order to match the standard wording as closely as possible, we
7385  // currently only do this under a single level of pointers. Ideally, we would
7386  // allow this in general, and set NeedConstBefore to the relevant depth on
7387  // the side(s) where we changed anything. If we permit that, we should also
7388  // consider this conversion when determining type similarity and model it as
7389  // a qualification conversion.
7390  if (Steps.size() == 1) {
7391  if (auto *FPT1 = Composite1->getAs<FunctionProtoType>()) {
7392  if (auto *FPT2 = Composite2->getAs<FunctionProtoType>()) {
7393  FunctionProtoType::ExtProtoInfo EPI1 = FPT1->getExtProtoInfo();
7394  FunctionProtoType::ExtProtoInfo EPI2 = FPT2->getExtProtoInfo();
7395 
7396  // The result is noreturn if both operands are.
7397  bool Noreturn =
7398  EPI1.ExtInfo.getNoReturn() && EPI2.ExtInfo.getNoReturn();
7399  EPI1.ExtInfo = EPI1.ExtInfo.withNoReturn(Noreturn);
7400  EPI2.ExtInfo = EPI2.ExtInfo.withNoReturn(Noreturn);
7401 
7402  // The result is nothrow if both operands are.
7403  SmallVector<QualType, 8> ExceptionTypeStorage;
7404  EPI1.ExceptionSpec = EPI2.ExceptionSpec = Context.mergeExceptionSpecs(
7405  EPI1.ExceptionSpec, EPI2.ExceptionSpec, ExceptionTypeStorage,
7406  getLangOpts().CPlusPlus17);
7407 
7408  Composite1 = Context.getFunctionType(FPT1->getReturnType(),
7409  FPT1->getParamTypes(), EPI1);
7410  Composite2 = Context.getFunctionType(FPT2->getReturnType(),
7411  FPT2->getParamTypes(), EPI2);
7412  }
7413  }
7414  }
7415 
7416  // There are some more conversions we can perform under exactly one pointer.
7417  if (Steps.size() == 1 && Steps.front().K == Step::Pointer &&
7418  !Context.hasSameType(Composite1, Composite2)) {
7419  // - if T1 or T2 is "pointer to cv1 void" and the other type is
7420  // "pointer to cv2 T", where T is an object type or void,
7421  // "pointer to cv12 void", where cv12 is the union of cv1 and cv2;
7422  if (Composite1->isVoidType() && Composite2->isObjectType())
7423  Composite2 = Composite1;
7424  else if (Composite2->isVoidType() && Composite1->isObjectType())
7425  Composite1 = Composite2;
7426  // - if T1 is "pointer to cv1 C1" and T2 is "pointer to cv2 C2", where C1
7427  // is reference-related to C2 or C2 is reference-related to C1 (8.6.3),
7428  // the cv-combined type of T1 and T2 or the cv-combined type of T2 and
7429  // T1, respectively;
7430  //
7431  // The "similar type" handling covers all of this except for the "T1 is a
7432  // base class of T2" case in the definition of reference-related.
7433  else if (IsDerivedFrom(Loc, Composite1, Composite2))
7434  Composite1 = Composite2;
7435  else if (IsDerivedFrom(Loc, Composite2, Composite1))
7436  Composite2 = Composite1;
7437  }
7438 
7439  // At this point, either the inner types are the same or we have failed to
7440  // find a composite pointer type.
7441  if (!Context.hasSameType(Composite1, Composite2))
7442  return QualType();
7443 
7444  // Per C++ [conv.qual]p3, add 'const' to every level before the last
7445  // differing qualifier.
7446  for (unsigned I = 0; I != NeedConstBefore; ++I)
7447  Steps[I].Quals.addConst();
7448 
7449  // Rebuild the composite type.
7450  QualType Composite = Context.getCommonSugaredType(Composite1, Composite2);
7451  for (auto &S : llvm::reverse(Steps))
7452  Composite = S.rebuild(Context, Composite);
7453 
7454  if (ConvertArgs) {
7455  // Convert the expressions to the composite pointer type.
7456  InitializedEntity Entity =
7457  InitializedEntity::InitializeTemporary(Composite);
7458  InitializationKind Kind =
7459  InitializationKind::CreateCopy(Loc, SourceLocation());
7460 
7461  InitializationSequence E1ToC(*this, Entity, Kind, E1);
7462  if (!E1ToC)
7463  return QualType();
7464 
7465  InitializationSequence E2ToC(*this, Entity, Kind, E2);
7466  if (!E2ToC)
7467  return QualType();
7468 
7469  // FIXME: Let the caller know if these fail to avoid duplicate diagnostics.
7470  ExprResult E1Result = E1ToC.Perform(*this, Entity, Kind, E1);
7471  if (E1Result.isInvalid())
7472  return QualType();
7473  E1 = E1Result.get();
7474 
7475  ExprResult E2Result = E2ToC.Perform(*this, Entity, Kind, E2);
7476  if (E2Result.isInvalid())
7477  return QualType();
7478  E2 = E2Result.get();
7479  }
7480 
7481  return Composite;
7482 }
7483 
7484 ExprResult Sema::MaybeBindToTemporary(Expr *E) {
7485  if (!E)
7486  return ExprError();
7487 
7488  assert(!isa<CXXBindTemporaryExpr>(E) && "Double-bound temporary?");
7489 
7490  // If the result is a glvalue, we shouldn't bind it.
7491  if (E->isGLValue())
7492  return E;
7493 
7494  // In ARC, calls that return a retainable type can return retained,
7495  // in which case we have to insert a consuming cast.
7496  if (getLangOpts().ObjCAutoRefCount &&
7497  E->getType()->isObjCRetainableType()) {
7498 
7499  bool ReturnsRetained;
7500 
7501  // For actual calls, we compute this by examining the type of the
7502  // called value.
7503  if (CallExpr *Call = dyn_cast<CallExpr>(E)) {
7504  Expr *Callee = Call->getCallee()->IgnoreParens();
7505  QualType T = Callee->getType();
7506 
7507  if (T == Context.BoundMemberTy) {
7508  // Handle pointer-to-members.
7509  if (BinaryOperator *BinOp = dyn_cast<BinaryOperator>(Callee))
7510  T = BinOp->getRHS()->getType();
7511  else if (MemberExpr *Mem = dyn_cast<MemberExpr>(Callee))
7512  T = Mem->getMemberDecl()->getType();
7513  }
7514 
7515  if (const PointerType *Ptr = T->getAs<PointerType>())
7516  T = Ptr->getPointeeType();
7517  else if (const BlockPointerType *Ptr = T->getAs<BlockPointerType>())
7518  T = Ptr->getPointeeType();
7519  else if (const MemberPointerType *MemPtr = T->getAs<MemberPointerType>())
7520  T = MemPtr->getPointeeType();
7521 
7522  auto *FTy = T->castAs<FunctionType>();
7523  ReturnsRetained = FTy->getExtInfo().getProducesResult();
7524 
7525  // ActOnStmtExpr arranges things so that StmtExprs of retainable
7526  // type always produce a +1 object.
7527  } else if (isa<StmtExpr>(E)) {
7528  ReturnsRetained = true;
7529 
7530  // We hit this case with the lambda conversion-to-block optimization;
7531  // we don't want any extra casts here.
7532  } else if (isa<CastExpr>(E) &&
7533  isa<BlockExpr>(cast<CastExpr>(E)->getSubExpr())) {
7534  return E;
7535 
7536  // For message sends and property references, we try to find an
7537  // actual method. FIXME: we should infer retention by selector in
7538  // cases where we don't have an actual method.
7539  } else {
7540  ObjCMethodDecl *D = nullptr;
7541  if (ObjCMessageExpr *Send = dyn_cast<ObjCMessageExpr>(E)) {
7542  D = Send->getMethodDecl();
7543  } else if (ObjCBoxedExpr *BoxedExpr = dyn_cast<ObjCBoxedExpr>(E)) {
7544  D = BoxedExpr->getBoxingMethod();
7545  } else if (ObjCArrayLiteral *ArrayLit = dyn_cast<ObjCArrayLiteral>(E)) {
7546  // Don't do reclaims if we're using the zero-element array
7547  // constant.
7548  if (ArrayLit->getNumElements() == 0 &&
7549  Context.getLangOpts().ObjCRuntime.hasEmptyCollections())
7550  return E;
7551 
7552  D = ArrayLit->getArrayWithObjectsMethod();
7553  } else if (ObjCDictionaryLiteral *DictLit
7554  = dyn_cast<ObjCDictionaryLiteral>(E)) {
7555  // Don't do reclaims if we're using the zero-element dictionary
7556  // constant.
7557  if (DictLit->getNumElements() == 0 &&
7558  Context.getLangOpts().ObjCRuntime.hasEmptyCollections())
7559  return E;
7560 
7561  D = DictLit->getDictWithObjectsMethod();
7562  }
7563 
7564  ReturnsRetained = (D && D->hasAttr<NSReturnsRetainedAttr>());
7565 
7566  // Don't do reclaims on performSelector calls; despite their
7567  // return type, the invoked method doesn't necessarily actually
7568  // return an object.
7569  if (!ReturnsRetained &&
7570  D && D->getMethodFamily() == OMF_performSelector)
7571  return E;
7572  }
7573 
7574  // Don't reclaim an object of Class type.
7575  if (!ReturnsRetained && E->getType()->isObjCARCImplicitlyUnretainedType())
7576  return E;
7577 
7578  Cleanup.setExprNeedsCleanups(true);
7579 
7580  CastKind ck = (ReturnsRetained ? CK_ARCConsumeObject
7581  : CK_ARCReclaimReturnedObject);
7582  return ImplicitCastExpr::Create(Context, E->getType(), ck, E, nullptr,
7583  VK_PRValue, FPOptionsOverride());
7584  }
7585 
7586  if (E->getType().isDestructedType() == QualType::DK_nontrivial_c_struct)
7587  Cleanup.setExprNeedsCleanups(true);
7588 
7589  if (!getLangOpts().CPlusPlus)
7590  return E;
7591 
7592  // Search for the base element type (cf. ASTContext::getBaseElementType) with
7593  // a fast path for the common case that the type is directly a RecordType.
7594  const Type *T = Context.getCanonicalType(E->getType().getTypePtr());
7595  const RecordType *RT = nullptr;
7596  while (!RT) {
7597  switch (T->getTypeClass()) {
7598  case Type::Record:
7599  RT = cast<RecordType>(T);
7600  break;
7601  case Type::ConstantArray:
7602  case Type::IncompleteArray:
7603  case Type::VariableArray:
7604  case Type::DependentSizedArray:
7605  T = cast<ArrayType>(T)->getElementType().getTypePtr();
7606  break;
7607  default:
7608  return E;
7609  }
7610  }
7611 
7612  // That should be enough to guarantee that this type is complete, if we're
7613  // not processing a decltype expression.
7614  CXXRecordDecl *RD = cast<CXXRecordDecl>(RT->getDecl());
7615  if (RD->isInvalidDecl() || RD->isDependentContext())
7616  return E;
7617 
7618  bool IsDecltype = ExprEvalContexts.back().ExprContext ==
7619  ExpressionEvaluationContextRecord::EK_Decltype;
7620  CXXDestructorDecl *Destructor = IsDecltype ? nullptr : LookupDestructor(RD);
7621 
7622  if (Destructor) {
7623  MarkFunctionReferenced(E->getExprLoc(), Destructor);
7624  CheckDestructorAccess(E->getExprLoc(), Destructor,
7625  PDiag(diag::err_access_dtor_temp)
7626  << E->getType());
7627  if (DiagnoseUseOfDecl(Destructor, E->getExprLoc()))
7628  return ExprError();
7629 
7630  // If destructor is trivial, we can avoid the extra copy.
7631  if (Destructor->isTrivial())
7632  return E;
7633 
7634  // We need a cleanup, but we don't need to remember the temporary.
7635  Cleanup.setExprNeedsCleanups(true);
7636  }
7637 
7638  CXXTemporary *Temp = CXXTemporary::Create(Context, Destructor);
7639  CXXBindTemporaryExpr *Bind = CXXBindTemporaryExpr::Create(Context, Temp, E);
7640 
7641  if (IsDecltype)
7642  ExprEvalContexts.back().DelayedDecltypeBinds.push_back(Bind);
7643 
7644  return Bind;
7645 }
7646 
7647 ExprResult
7648 Sema::MaybeCreateExprWithCleanups(ExprResult SubExpr) {
7649  if (SubExpr.isInvalid())
7650  return ExprError();
7651 
7652  return MaybeCreateExprWithCleanups(SubExpr.get());
7653 }
7654 
7655 Expr *Sema::MaybeCreateExprWithCleanups(Expr *SubExpr) {
7656  assert(SubExpr && "subexpression can't be null!");
7657 
7658  CleanupVarDeclMarking();
7659 
7660  unsigned FirstCleanup = ExprEvalContexts.back().NumCleanupObjects;
7661  assert(ExprCleanupObjects.size() >= FirstCleanup);
7662  assert(Cleanup.exprNeedsCleanups() ||
7663  ExprCleanupObjects.size() == FirstCleanup);
7664  if (!Cleanup.exprNeedsCleanups())
7665  return SubExpr;
7666 
7667  auto Cleanups = llvm::ArrayRef(ExprCleanupObjects.begin() + FirstCleanup,
7668  ExprCleanupObjects.size() - FirstCleanup);
7669 
7670  auto *E = ExprWithCleanups::Create(
7671  Context, SubExpr, Cleanup.cleanupsHaveSideEffects(), Cleanups);
7672  DiscardCleanupsInEvaluationContext();
7673 
7674  return E;
7675 }
7676 
7677 Stmt *Sema::MaybeCreateStmtWithCleanups(Stmt *SubStmt) {
7678  assert(SubStmt && "sub-statement can't be null!");
7679 
7680  CleanupVarDeclMarking();
7681 
7682  if (!Cleanup.exprNeedsCleanups())
7683  return SubStmt;
7684 
7685  // FIXME: In order to attach the temporaries, wrap the statement into
7686  // a StmtExpr; currently this is only used for asm statements.
7687  // This is hacky, either create a new CXXStmtWithTemporaries statement or
7688  // a new AsmStmtWithTemporaries.
7689  CompoundStmt *CompStmt =
7690  CompoundStmt::Create(Context, SubStmt, FPOptionsOverride(),
7691  SourceLocation(), SourceLocation());
7692  Expr *E = new (Context)
7693  StmtExpr(CompStmt, Context.VoidTy, SourceLocation(), SourceLocation(),
7694  /*FIXME TemplateDepth=*/0);
7695  return MaybeCreateExprWithCleanups(E);
7696 }
7697 
7698 /// Process the expression contained within a decltype. For such expressions,
7699 /// certain semantic checks on temporaries are delayed until this point, and
7700 /// are omitted for the 'topmost' call in the decltype expression. If the
7701 /// topmost call bound a temporary, strip that temporary off the expression.
7702 ExprResult Sema::ActOnDecltypeExpression(Expr *E) {
7703  assert(ExprEvalContexts.back().ExprContext ==
7704  ExpressionEvaluationContextRecord::EK_Decltype &&
7705  "not in a decltype expression");
7706 
7707  ExprResult Result = CheckPlaceholderExpr(E);
7708  if (Result.isInvalid())
7709  return ExprError();
7710  E = Result.get();
7711 
7712  // C++11 [expr.call]p11:
7713  // If a function call is a prvalue of object type,
7714  // -- if the function call is either
7715  // -- the operand of a decltype-specifier, or
7716  // -- the right operand of a comma operator that is the operand of a
7717  // decltype-specifier,
7718  // a temporary object is not introduced for the prvalue.
7719 
7720  // Recursively rebuild ParenExprs and comma expressions to strip out the
7721  // outermost CXXBindTemporaryExpr, if any.
7722  if (ParenExpr *PE = dyn_cast<ParenExpr>(E)) {
7723  ExprResult SubExpr = ActOnDecltypeExpression(PE->getSubExpr());
7724  if (SubExpr.isInvalid())
7725  return ExprError();
7726  if (SubExpr.get() == PE->getSubExpr())
7727  return E;
7728  return ActOnParenExpr(PE->getLParen(), PE->getRParen(), SubExpr.get());
7729  }
7730  if (BinaryOperator *BO = dyn_cast<BinaryOperator>(E)) {
7731  if (BO->getOpcode() == BO_Comma) {
7732  ExprResult RHS = ActOnDecltypeExpression(BO->getRHS());
7733  if (RHS.isInvalid())
7734  return ExprError();
7735  if (RHS.get() == BO->getRHS())
7736  return E;
7737  return BinaryOperator::Create(Context, BO->getLHS(), RHS.get(), BO_Comma,
7738  BO->getType(), BO->getValueKind(),
7739  BO->getObjectKind(), BO->getOperatorLoc(),
7740  BO->getFPFeatures());
7741  }
7742  }
7743 
7744  CXXBindTemporaryExpr *TopBind = dyn_cast<CXXBindTemporaryExpr>(E);
7745  CallExpr *TopCall = TopBind ? dyn_cast<CallExpr>(TopBind->getSubExpr())
7746  : nullptr;
7747  if (TopCall)
7748  E = TopCall;
7749  else
7750  TopBind = nullptr;
7751 
7752  // Disable the special decltype handling now.
7753  ExprEvalContexts.back().ExprContext =
7754  ExpressionEvaluationContextRecord::EK_Other;
7755 
7756  Result = CheckUnevaluatedOperand(E);
7757  if (Result.isInvalid())
7758  return ExprError();
7759  E = Result.get();
7760 
7761  // In MS mode, don't perform any extra checking of call return types within a
7762  // decltype expression.
7763  if (getLangOpts().MSVCCompat)
7764  return E;
7765 
7766  // Perform the semantic checks we delayed until this point.
7767  for (unsigned I = 0, N = ExprEvalContexts.back().DelayedDecltypeCalls.size();
7768  I != N; ++I) {
7769  CallExpr *Call = ExprEvalContexts.back().DelayedDecltypeCalls[I];
7770  if (Call == TopCall)
7771  continue;
7772 
7773  if (CheckCallReturnType(Call->getCallReturnType(Context),
7774  Call->getBeginLoc(), Call, Call->getDirectCallee()))
7775  return ExprError();
7776  }
7777 
7778  // Now all relevant types are complete, check the destructors are accessible
7779  // and non-deleted, and annotate them on the temporaries.
7780  for (unsigned I = 0, N = ExprEvalContexts.back().DelayedDecltypeBinds.size();
7781  I != N; ++I) {
7782  CXXBindTemporaryExpr *Bind =
7783  ExprEvalContexts.back().DelayedDecltypeBinds[I];
7784  if (Bind == TopBind)
7785  continue;
7786 
7787  CXXTemporary *Temp = Bind->getTemporary();
7788 
7789  CXXRecordDecl *RD =
7790  Bind->getType()->getBaseElementTypeUnsafe()->getAsCXXRecordDecl();
7791  CXXDestructorDecl *Destructor = LookupDestructor(RD);
7792  Temp->setDestructor(Destructor);
7793 
7794  MarkFunctionReferenced(Bind->getExprLoc(), Destructor);
7795  CheckDestructorAccess(Bind->getExprLoc(), Destructor,
7796  PDiag(diag::err_access_dtor_temp)
7797  << Bind->getType());
7798  if (DiagnoseUseOfDecl(Destructor, Bind->getExprLoc()))
7799  return ExprError();
7800 
7801  // We need a cleanup, but we don't need to remember the temporary.
7802  Cleanup.setExprNeedsCleanups(true);
7803  }
7804 
7805  // Possibly strip off the top CXXBindTemporaryExpr.
7806  return E;
7807 }
7808 
7809 /// Note a set of 'operator->' functions that were used for a member access.
7810 static void noteOperatorArrows(Sema &S,
7811  ArrayRef<FunctionDecl *> OperatorArrows) {
7812  unsigned SkipStart = OperatorArrows.size(), SkipCount = 0;
7813  // FIXME: Make this configurable?
7814  unsigned Limit = 9;
7815  if (OperatorArrows.size() > Limit) {
7816  // Produce Limit-1 normal notes and one 'skipping' note.
7817  SkipStart = (Limit - 1) / 2 + (Limit - 1) % 2;
7818  SkipCount = OperatorArrows.size() - (Limit - 1);
7819  }
7820 
7821  for (unsigned I = 0; I < OperatorArrows.size(); /**/) {
7822  if (I == SkipStart) {
7823  S.Diag(OperatorArrows[I]->getLocation(),
7824  diag::note_operator_arrows_suppressed)
7825  << SkipCount;
7826  I += SkipCount;
7827  } else {
7828  S.Diag(OperatorArrows[I]->getLocation(), diag::note_operator_arrow_here)
7829  << OperatorArrows[I]->getCallResultType();
7830  ++I;
7831  }
7832  }
7833 }
7834 
7835 ExprResult Sema::ActOnStartCXXMemberReference(Scope *S, Expr *Base,
7836  SourceLocation OpLoc,
7837  tok::TokenKind OpKind,
7838  ParsedType &ObjectType,
7839  bool &MayBePseudoDestructor) {
7840  // Since this might be a postfix expression, get rid of ParenListExprs.
7841  ExprResult Result = MaybeConvertParenListExprToParenExpr(S, Base);
7842  if (Result.isInvalid()) return ExprError();
7843  Base = Result.get();
7844 
7845  Result = CheckPlaceholderExpr(Base);
7846  if (Result.isInvalid()) return ExprError();
7847  Base = Result.get();
7848 
7849  QualType BaseType = Base->getType();
7850  MayBePseudoDestructor = false;
7851  if (BaseType->isDependentType()) {
7852  // If we have a pointer to a dependent type and are using the -> operator,
7853  // the object type is the type that the pointer points to. We might still
7854  // have enough information about that type to do something useful.
7855  if (OpKind == tok::arrow)
7856  if (const PointerType *Ptr = BaseType->getAs<PointerType>())
7857  BaseType = Ptr->getPointeeType();
7858 
7859  ObjectType = ParsedType::make(BaseType);
7860  MayBePseudoDestructor = true;
7861  return Base;
7862  }
7863 
7864  // C++ [over.match.oper]p8:
7865  // [...] When operator->returns, the operator-> is applied to the value
7866  // returned, with the original second operand.
7867  if (OpKind == tok::arrow) {
7868  QualType StartingType = BaseType;
7869  bool NoArrowOperatorFound = false;
7870  bool FirstIteration = true;
7871  FunctionDecl *CurFD = dyn_cast<FunctionDecl>(CurContext);
7872  // The set of types we've considered so far.
7873  llvm::SmallPtrSet<CanQualType,8> CTypes;
7874  SmallVector<FunctionDecl*, 8> OperatorArrows;
7875  CTypes.insert(Context.getCanonicalType(BaseType));
7876 
7877  while (BaseType->isRecordType()) {
7878  if (OperatorArrows.size() >= getLangOpts().ArrowDepth) {
7879  Diag(OpLoc, diag::err_operator_arrow_depth_exceeded)
7880  << StartingType << getLangOpts().ArrowDepth << Base->getSourceRange();
7881  noteOperatorArrows(*this, OperatorArrows);
7882  Diag(OpLoc, diag::note_operator_arrow_depth)
7883  << getLangOpts().ArrowDepth;
7884  return ExprError();
7885  }
7886 
7887  Result = BuildOverloadedArrowExpr(
7888  S, Base, OpLoc,
7889  // When in a template specialization and on the first loop iteration,
7890  // potentially give the default diagnostic (with the fixit in a
7891  // separate note) instead of having the error reported back to here
7892  // and giving a diagnostic with a fixit attached to the error itself.
7893  (FirstIteration && CurFD && CurFD->isFunctionTemplateSpecialization())
7894  ? nullptr
7895  : &NoArrowOperatorFound);
7896  if (Result.isInvalid()) {
7897  if (NoArrowOperatorFound) {
7898  if (FirstIteration) {
7899  Diag(OpLoc, diag::err_typecheck_member_reference_suggestion)
7900  << BaseType << 1 << Base->getSourceRange()
7901  << FixItHint::CreateReplacement(OpLoc, ".");
7902  OpKind = tok::period;
7903  break;
7904  }
7905  Diag(OpLoc, diag::err_typecheck_member_reference_arrow)
7906  << BaseType << Base->getSourceRange();
7907  CallExpr *CE = dyn_cast<CallExpr>(Base);
7908  if (Decl *CD = (CE ? CE->getCalleeDecl() : nullptr)) {
7909  Diag(CD->getBeginLoc(),
7910  diag::note_member_reference_arrow_from_operator_arrow);
7911  }
7912  }
7913  return ExprError();
7914  }
7915  Base = Result.get();
7916  if (CXXOperatorCallExpr *OpCall = dyn_cast<CXXOperatorCallExpr>(Base))
7917  OperatorArrows.push_back(OpCall->getDirectCallee());
7918  BaseType = Base->getType();
7919  CanQualType CBaseType = Context.getCanonicalType(BaseType);
7920  if (!CTypes.insert(CBaseType).second) {
7921  Diag(OpLoc, diag::err_operator_arrow_circular) << StartingType;
7922  noteOperatorArrows(*this, OperatorArrows);
7923  return ExprError();
7924  }
7925  FirstIteration = false;
7926  }
7927 
7928  if (OpKind == tok::arrow) {
7929  if (BaseType->isPointerType())
7930  BaseType = BaseType->getPointeeType();
7931  else if (auto *AT = Context.getAsArrayType(BaseType))
7932  BaseType = AT->getElementType();
7933  }
7934  }
7935 
7936  // Objective-C properties allow "." access on Objective-C pointer types,
7937  // so adjust the base type to the object type itself.
7938  if (BaseType->isObjCObjectPointerType())
7939  BaseType = BaseType->getPointeeType();
7940 
7941  // C++ [basic.lookup.classref]p2:
7942  // [...] If the type of the object expression is of pointer to scalar
7943  // type, the unqualified-id is looked up in the context of the complete
7944  // postfix-expression.
7945  //
7946  // This also indicates that we could be parsing a pseudo-destructor-name.
7947  // Note that Objective-C class and object types can be pseudo-destructor
7948  // expressions or normal member (ivar or property) access expressions, and
7949  // it's legal for the type to be incomplete if this is a pseudo-destructor
7950  // call. We'll do more incomplete-type checks later in the lookup process,
7951  // so just skip this check for ObjC types.
7952  if (!BaseType->isRecordType()) {
7953  ObjectType = ParsedType::make(BaseType);
7954  MayBePseudoDestructor = true;
7955  return Base;
7956  }
7957 
7958  // The object type must be complete (or dependent), or
7959  // C++11 [expr.prim.general]p3:
7960  // Unlike the object expression in other contexts, *this is not required to
7961  // be of complete type for purposes of class member access (5.2.5) outside
7962  // the member function body.
7963  if (!BaseType->isDependentType() &&
7964  !isThisOutsideMemberFunctionBody(BaseType) &&
7965  RequireCompleteType(OpLoc, BaseType,
7966  diag::err_incomplete_member_access)) {
7967  return CreateRecoveryExpr(Base->getBeginLoc(), Base->getEndLoc(), {Base});
7968  }
7969 
7970  // C++ [basic.lookup.classref]p2:
7971  // If the id-expression in a class member access (5.2.5) is an
7972  // unqualified-id, and the type of the object expression is of a class
7973  // type C (or of pointer to a class type C), the unqualified-id is looked
7974  // up in the scope of class C. [...]
7975  ObjectType = ParsedType::make(BaseType);
7976  return Base;
7977 }
7978 
7979 static bool CheckArrow(Sema &S, QualType &ObjectType, Expr *&Base,
7980  tok::TokenKind &OpKind, SourceLocation OpLoc) {
7981  if (Base->hasPlaceholderType()) {
7982  ExprResult result = S.CheckPlaceholderExpr(Base);
7983  if (result.isInvalid()) return true;
7984  Base = result.get();
7985  }
7986  ObjectType = Base->getType();
7987 
7988  // C++ [expr.pseudo]p2:
7989  // The left-hand side of the dot operator shall be of scalar type. The
7990  // left-hand side of the arrow operator shall be of pointer to scalar type.
7991  // This scalar type is the object type.
7992  // Note that this is rather different from the normal handling for the
7993  // arrow operator.
7994  if (OpKind == tok::arrow) {
7995  // The operator requires a prvalue, so perform lvalue conversions.
7996  // Only do this if we might plausibly end with a pointer, as otherwise
7997  // this was likely to be intended to be a '.'.
7998  if (ObjectType->isPointerType() || ObjectType->isArrayType() ||
7999  ObjectType->isFunctionType()) {
