8000  ExprResult BaseResult = S.DefaultFunctionArrayLvalueConversion(Base);
8001  if (BaseResult.isInvalid())
8002  return true;
8003  Base = BaseResult.get();
8004  ObjectType = Base->getType();
8005  }
8006 
8007  if (const PointerType *Ptr = ObjectType->getAs<PointerType>()) {
8008  ObjectType = Ptr->getPointeeType();
8009  } else if (!Base->isTypeDependent()) {
8010  // The user wrote "p->" when they probably meant "p."; fix it.
8011  S.Diag(OpLoc, diag::err_typecheck_member_reference_suggestion)
8012  << ObjectType << true
8013  << FixItHint::CreateReplacement(OpLoc, ".");
8014  if (S.isSFINAEContext())
8015  return true;
8016 
8017  OpKind = tok::period;
8018  }
8019  }
8020 
8021  return false;
8022 }
8023 
8024 /// Check if it's ok to try and recover dot pseudo destructor calls on
8025 /// pointer objects.
8026 static bool
8027 canRecoverDotPseudoDestructorCallsOnPointerObjects(Sema &SemaRef,
8028  QualType DestructedType) {
8029  // If this is a record type, check if its destructor is callable.
8030  if (auto *RD = DestructedType->getAsCXXRecordDecl()) {
8031  if (RD->hasDefinition())
8032  if (CXXDestructorDecl *D = SemaRef.LookupDestructor(RD))
8033  return SemaRef.CanUseDecl(D, /*TreatUnavailableAsInvalid=*/false);
8034  return false;
8035  }
8036 
8037  // Otherwise, check if it's a type for which it's valid to use a pseudo-dtor.
8038  return DestructedType->isDependentType() || DestructedType->isScalarType() ||
8039  DestructedType->isVectorType();
8040 }
8041 
8042 ExprResult Sema::BuildPseudoDestructorExpr(Expr *Base,
8043  SourceLocation OpLoc,
8044  tok::TokenKind OpKind,
8045  const CXXScopeSpec &SS,
8046  TypeSourceInfo *ScopeTypeInfo,
8047  SourceLocation CCLoc,
8048  SourceLocation TildeLoc,
8049  PseudoDestructorTypeStorage Destructed) {
8050  TypeSourceInfo *DestructedTypeInfo = Destructed.getTypeSourceInfo();
8051 
8052  QualType ObjectType;
8053  if (CheckArrow(*this, ObjectType, Base, OpKind, OpLoc))
8054  return ExprError();
8055 
8056  if (!ObjectType->isDependentType() && !ObjectType->isScalarType() &&
8057  !ObjectType->isVectorType()) {
8058  if (getLangOpts().MSVCCompat && ObjectType->isVoidType())
8059  Diag(OpLoc, diag::ext_pseudo_dtor_on_void) << Base->getSourceRange();
8060  else {
8061  Diag(OpLoc, diag::err_pseudo_dtor_base_not_scalar)
8062  << ObjectType << Base->getSourceRange();
8063  return ExprError();
8064  }
8065  }
8066 
8067  // C++ [expr.pseudo]p2:
8068  // [...] The cv-unqualified versions of the object type and of the type
8069  // designated by the pseudo-destructor-name shall be the same type.
8070  if (DestructedTypeInfo) {
8071  QualType DestructedType = DestructedTypeInfo->getType();
8072  SourceLocation DestructedTypeStart =
8073  DestructedTypeInfo->getTypeLoc().getBeginLoc();
8074  if (!DestructedType->isDependentType() && !ObjectType->isDependentType()) {
8075  if (!Context.hasSameUnqualifiedType(DestructedType, ObjectType)) {
8076  // Detect dot pseudo destructor calls on pointer objects, e.g.:
8077  // Foo *foo;
8078  // foo.~Foo();
8079  if (OpKind == tok::period && ObjectType->isPointerType() &&
8080  Context.hasSameUnqualifiedType(DestructedType,
8081  ObjectType->getPointeeType())) {
8082  auto Diagnostic =
8083  Diag(OpLoc, diag::err_typecheck_member_reference_suggestion)
8084  << ObjectType << /*IsArrow=*/0 << Base->getSourceRange();
8085 
8086  // Issue a fixit only when the destructor is valid.
8087  if (canRecoverDotPseudoDestructorCallsOnPointerObjects(
8088  *this, DestructedType))
8089  Diagnostic << FixItHint::CreateReplacement(OpLoc, "->");
8090 
8091  // Recover by setting the object type to the destructed type and the
8092  // operator to '->'.
8093  ObjectType = DestructedType;
8094  OpKind = tok::arrow;
8095  } else {
8096  Diag(DestructedTypeStart, diag::err_pseudo_dtor_type_mismatch)
8097  << ObjectType << DestructedType << Base->getSourceRange()
8098  << DestructedTypeInfo->getTypeLoc().getSourceRange();
8099 
8100  // Recover by setting the destructed type to the object type.
8101  DestructedType = ObjectType;
8102  DestructedTypeInfo =
8103  Context.getTrivialTypeSourceInfo(ObjectType, DestructedTypeStart);
8104  Destructed = PseudoDestructorTypeStorage(DestructedTypeInfo);
8105  }
8106  } else if (DestructedType.getObjCLifetime() !=
8107  ObjectType.getObjCLifetime()) {
8108 
8109  if (DestructedType.getObjCLifetime() == Qualifiers::OCL_None) {
8110  // Okay: just pretend that the user provided the correctly-qualified
8111  // type.
8112  } else {
8113  Diag(DestructedTypeStart, diag::err_arc_pseudo_dtor_inconstant_quals)
8114  << ObjectType << DestructedType << Base->getSourceRange()
8115  << DestructedTypeInfo->getTypeLoc().getSourceRange();
8116  }
8117 
8118  // Recover by setting the destructed type to the object type.
8119  DestructedType = ObjectType;
8120  DestructedTypeInfo = Context.getTrivialTypeSourceInfo(ObjectType,
8121  DestructedTypeStart);
8122  Destructed = PseudoDestructorTypeStorage(DestructedTypeInfo);
8123  }
8124  }
8125  }
8126 
8127  // C++ [expr.pseudo]p2:
8128  // [...] Furthermore, the two type-names in a pseudo-destructor-name of the
8129  // form
8130  //
8131  // ::[opt] nested-name-specifier[opt] type-name :: ~ type-name
8132  //
8133  // shall designate the same scalar type.
8134  if (ScopeTypeInfo) {
8135  QualType ScopeType = ScopeTypeInfo->getType();
8136  if (!ScopeType->isDependentType() && !ObjectType->isDependentType() &&
8137  !Context.hasSameUnqualifiedType(ScopeType, ObjectType)) {
8138 
8139  Diag(ScopeTypeInfo->getTypeLoc().getSourceRange().getBegin(),
8140  diag::err_pseudo_dtor_type_mismatch)
8141  << ObjectType << ScopeType << Base->getSourceRange()
8142  << ScopeTypeInfo->getTypeLoc().getSourceRange();
8143 
8144  ScopeType = QualType();
8145  ScopeTypeInfo = nullptr;
8146  }
8147  }
8148 
8149  Expr *Result
8150  = new (Context) CXXPseudoDestructorExpr(Context, Base,
8151  OpKind == tok::arrow, OpLoc,
8152  SS.getWithLocInContext(Context),
8153  ScopeTypeInfo,
8154  CCLoc,
8155  TildeLoc,
8156  Destructed);
8157 
8158  return Result;
8159 }
8160 
8161 ExprResult Sema::ActOnPseudoDestructorExpr(Scope *S, Expr *Base,
8162  SourceLocation OpLoc,
8163  tok::TokenKind OpKind,
8164  CXXScopeSpec &SS,
8165  UnqualifiedId &FirstTypeName,
8166  SourceLocation CCLoc,
8167  SourceLocation TildeLoc,
8168  UnqualifiedId &SecondTypeName) {
8169  assert((FirstTypeName.getKind() == UnqualifiedIdKind::IK_TemplateId ||
8170  FirstTypeName.getKind() == UnqualifiedIdKind::IK_Identifier) &&
8171  "Invalid first type name in pseudo-destructor");
8172  assert((SecondTypeName.getKind() == UnqualifiedIdKind::IK_TemplateId ||
8173  SecondTypeName.getKind() == UnqualifiedIdKind::IK_Identifier) &&
8174  "Invalid second type name in pseudo-destructor");
8175 
8176  QualType ObjectType;
8177  if (CheckArrow(*this, ObjectType, Base, OpKind, OpLoc))
8178  return ExprError();
8179 
8180  // Compute the object type that we should use for name lookup purposes. Only
8181  // record types and dependent types matter.
8182  ParsedType ObjectTypePtrForLookup;
8183  if (!SS.isSet()) {
8184  if (ObjectType->isRecordType())
8185  ObjectTypePtrForLookup = ParsedType::make(ObjectType);
8186  else if (ObjectType->isDependentType())
8187  ObjectTypePtrForLookup = ParsedType::make(Context.DependentTy);
8188  }
8189 
8190  // Convert the name of the type being destructed (following the ~) into a
8191  // type (with source-location information).
8192  QualType DestructedType;
8193  TypeSourceInfo *DestructedTypeInfo = nullptr;
8194  PseudoDestructorTypeStorage Destructed;
8195  if (SecondTypeName.getKind() == UnqualifiedIdKind::IK_Identifier) {
8196  ParsedType T = getTypeName(*SecondTypeName.Identifier,
8197  SecondTypeName.StartLocation,
8198  S, &SS, true, false, ObjectTypePtrForLookup,
8199  /*IsCtorOrDtorName*/true);
8200  if (!T &&
8201  ((SS.isSet() && !computeDeclContext(SS, false)) ||
8202  (!SS.isSet() && ObjectType->isDependentType()))) {
8203  // The name of the type being destroyed is a dependent name, and we
8204  // couldn't find anything useful in scope. Just store the identifier and
8205  // it's location, and we'll perform (qualified) name lookup again at
8206  // template instantiation time.
8207  Destructed = PseudoDestructorTypeStorage(SecondTypeName.Identifier,
8208  SecondTypeName.StartLocation);
8209  } else if (!T) {
8210  Diag(SecondTypeName.StartLocation,
8211  diag::err_pseudo_dtor_destructor_non_type)
8212  << SecondTypeName.Identifier << ObjectType;
8213  if (isSFINAEContext())
8214  return ExprError();
8215 
8216  // Recover by assuming we had the right type all along.
8217  DestructedType = ObjectType;
8218  } else
8219  DestructedType = GetTypeFromParser(T, &DestructedTypeInfo);
8220  } else {
8221  // Resolve the template-id to a type.
8222  TemplateIdAnnotation *TemplateId = SecondTypeName.TemplateId;
8223  ASTTemplateArgsPtr TemplateArgsPtr(TemplateId->getTemplateArgs(),
8224  TemplateId->NumArgs);
8225  TypeResult T = ActOnTemplateIdType(S,
8226  SS,
8227  TemplateId->TemplateKWLoc,
8228  TemplateId->Template,
8229  TemplateId->Name,
8230  TemplateId->TemplateNameLoc,
8231  TemplateId->LAngleLoc,
8232  TemplateArgsPtr,
8233  TemplateId->RAngleLoc,
8234  /*IsCtorOrDtorName*/true);
8235  if (T.isInvalid() || !T.get()) {
8236  // Recover by assuming we had the right type all along.
8237  DestructedType = ObjectType;
8238  } else
8239  DestructedType = GetTypeFromParser(T.get(), &DestructedTypeInfo);
8240  }
8241 
8242  // If we've performed some kind of recovery, (re-)build the type source
8243  // information.
8244  if (!DestructedType.isNull()) {
8245  if (!DestructedTypeInfo)
8246  DestructedTypeInfo = Context.getTrivialTypeSourceInfo(DestructedType,
8247  SecondTypeName.StartLocation);
8248  Destructed = PseudoDestructorTypeStorage(DestructedTypeInfo);
8249  }
8250 
8251  // Convert the name of the scope type (the type prior to '::') into a type.
8252  TypeSourceInfo *ScopeTypeInfo = nullptr;
8253  QualType ScopeType;
8254  if (FirstTypeName.getKind() == UnqualifiedIdKind::IK_TemplateId ||
8255  FirstTypeName.Identifier) {
8256  if (FirstTypeName.getKind() == UnqualifiedIdKind::IK_Identifier) {
8257  ParsedType T = getTypeName(*FirstTypeName.Identifier,
8258  FirstTypeName.StartLocation,
8259  S, &SS, true, false, ObjectTypePtrForLookup,
8260  /*IsCtorOrDtorName*/true);
8261  if (!T) {
8262  Diag(FirstTypeName.StartLocation,
8263  diag::err_pseudo_dtor_destructor_non_type)
8264  << FirstTypeName.Identifier << ObjectType;
8265 
8266  if (isSFINAEContext())
8267  return ExprError();
8268 
8269  // Just drop this type. It's unnecessary anyway.
8270  ScopeType = QualType();
8271  } else
8272  ScopeType = GetTypeFromParser(T, &ScopeTypeInfo);
8273  } else {
8274  // Resolve the template-id to a type.
8275  TemplateIdAnnotation *TemplateId = FirstTypeName.TemplateId;
8276  ASTTemplateArgsPtr TemplateArgsPtr(TemplateId->getTemplateArgs(),
8277  TemplateId->NumArgs);
8278  TypeResult T = ActOnTemplateIdType(S,
8279  SS,
8280  TemplateId->TemplateKWLoc,
8281  TemplateId->Template,
8282  TemplateId->Name,
8283  TemplateId->TemplateNameLoc,
8284  TemplateId->LAngleLoc,
8285  TemplateArgsPtr,
8286  TemplateId->RAngleLoc,
8287  /*IsCtorOrDtorName*/true);
8288  if (T.isInvalid() || !T.get()) {
8289  // Recover by dropping this type.
8290  ScopeType = QualType();
8291  } else
8292  ScopeType = GetTypeFromParser(T.get(), &ScopeTypeInfo);
8293  }
8294  }
8295 
8296  if (!ScopeType.isNull() && !ScopeTypeInfo)
8297  ScopeTypeInfo = Context.getTrivialTypeSourceInfo(ScopeType,
8298  FirstTypeName.StartLocation);
8299 
8300 
8301  return BuildPseudoDestructorExpr(Base, OpLoc, OpKind, SS,
8302  ScopeTypeInfo, CCLoc, TildeLoc,
8303  Destructed);
8304 }
8305 
8306 ExprResult Sema::ActOnPseudoDestructorExpr(Scope *S, Expr *Base,
8307  SourceLocation OpLoc,
8308  tok::TokenKind OpKind,
8309  SourceLocation TildeLoc,
8310  const DeclSpec& DS) {
8311  QualType ObjectType;
8312  QualType T;
8313  TypeLocBuilder TLB;
8314  if (CheckArrow(*this, ObjectType, Base, OpKind, OpLoc))
8315  return ExprError();
8316 
8317  switch (DS.getTypeSpecType()) {
8318  case DeclSpec::TST_decltype_auto: {
8319  Diag(DS.getTypeSpecTypeLoc(), diag::err_decltype_auto_invalid);
8320  return true;
8321  }
8322  case DeclSpec::TST_decltype: {
8323  T = BuildDecltypeType(DS.getRepAsExpr(), /*AsUnevaluated=*/false);
8324  DecltypeTypeLoc DecltypeTL = TLB.push<DecltypeTypeLoc>(T);
8325  DecltypeTL.setDecltypeLoc(DS.getTypeSpecTypeLoc());
8326  DecltypeTL.setRParenLoc(DS.getTypeofParensRange().getEnd());
8327  break;
8328  }
8329  case DeclSpec::TST_typename_pack_indexing: {
8330  T = ActOnPackIndexingType(DS.getRepAsType().get(), DS.getPackIndexingExpr(),
8331  DS.getBeginLoc(), DS.getEllipsisLoc());
8332  TLB.pushTrivial(getASTContext(),
8333  cast<PackIndexingType>(T.getTypePtr())->getPattern(),
8334  DS.getBeginLoc());
8335  PackIndexingTypeLoc PITL = TLB.push<PackIndexingTypeLoc>(T);
8336  PITL.setEllipsisLoc(DS.getEllipsisLoc());
8337  break;
8338  }
8339  default:
8340  llvm_unreachable("Unsupported type in pseudo destructor");
8341  }
8342  TypeSourceInfo *DestructedTypeInfo = TLB.getTypeSourceInfo(Context, T);
8343  PseudoDestructorTypeStorage Destructed(DestructedTypeInfo);
8344 
8345  return BuildPseudoDestructorExpr(Base, OpLoc, OpKind, CXXScopeSpec(),
8346  nullptr, SourceLocation(), TildeLoc,
8347  Destructed);
8348 }
8349 
8350 ExprResult Sema::BuildCXXNoexceptExpr(SourceLocation KeyLoc, Expr *Operand,
8351  SourceLocation RParen) {
8352  // If the operand is an unresolved lookup expression, the expression is ill-
8353  // formed per [over.over]p1, because overloaded function names cannot be used
8354  // without arguments except in explicit contexts.
8355  ExprResult R = CheckPlaceholderExpr(Operand);
8356  if (R.isInvalid())
8357  return R;
8358 
8359  R = CheckUnevaluatedOperand(R.get());
8360  if (R.isInvalid())
8361  return ExprError();
8362 
8363  Operand = R.get();
8364 
8365  if (!inTemplateInstantiation() && !Operand->isInstantiationDependent() &&
8366  Operand->HasSideEffects(Context, false)) {
8367  // The expression operand for noexcept is in an unevaluated expression
8368  // context, so side effects could result in unintended consequences.
8369  Diag(Operand->getExprLoc(), diag::warn_side_effects_unevaluated_context);
8370  }
8371 
8372  CanThrowResult CanThrow = canThrow(Operand);
8373  return new (Context)
8374  CXXNoexceptExpr(Context.BoolTy, Operand, CanThrow, KeyLoc, RParen);
8375 }
8376 
8377 ExprResult Sema::ActOnNoexceptExpr(SourceLocation KeyLoc, SourceLocation,
8378  Expr *Operand, SourceLocation RParen) {
8379  return BuildCXXNoexceptExpr(KeyLoc, Operand, RParen);
8380 }
8381 
8382 static void MaybeDecrementCount(
8383  Expr *E, llvm::DenseMap<const VarDecl *, int> &RefsMinusAssignments) {
8384  DeclRefExpr *LHS = nullptr;
8385  bool IsCompoundAssign = false;
8386  bool isIncrementDecrementUnaryOp = false;
8387  if (BinaryOperator *BO = dyn_cast<BinaryOperator>(E)) {
8388  if (BO->getLHS()->getType()->isDependentType() ||
8389  BO->getRHS()->getType()->isDependentType()) {
8390  if (BO->getOpcode() != BO_Assign)
8391  return;
8392  } else if (!BO->isAssignmentOp())
8393  return;
8394  else
8395  IsCompoundAssign = BO->isCompoundAssignmentOp();
8396  LHS = dyn_cast<DeclRefExpr>(BO->getLHS());
8397  } else if (CXXOperatorCallExpr *COCE = dyn_cast<CXXOperatorCallExpr>(E)) {
8398  if (COCE->getOperator() != OO_Equal)
8399  return;
8400  LHS = dyn_cast<DeclRefExpr>(COCE->getArg(0));
8401  } else if (UnaryOperator *UO = dyn_cast<UnaryOperator>(E)) {
8402  if (!UO->isIncrementDecrementOp())
8403  return;
8404  isIncrementDecrementUnaryOp = true;
8405  LHS = dyn_cast<DeclRefExpr>(UO->getSubExpr());
8406  }
8407  if (!LHS)
8408  return;
8409  VarDecl *VD = dyn_cast<VarDecl>(LHS->getDecl());
8410  if (!VD)
8411  return;
8412  // Don't decrement RefsMinusAssignments if volatile variable with compound
8413  // assignment (+=, ...) or increment/decrement unary operator to avoid
8414  // potential unused-but-set-variable warning.
8415  if ((IsCompoundAssign || isIncrementDecrementUnaryOp) &&
8416  VD->getType().isVolatileQualified())
8417  return;
8418  auto iter = RefsMinusAssignments.find(VD);
8419  if (iter == RefsMinusAssignments.end())
8420  return;
8421  iter->getSecond()--;
8422 }
8423 
8424 /// Perform the conversions required for an expression used in a
8425 /// context that ignores the result.
8426 ExprResult Sema::IgnoredValueConversions(Expr *E) {
8427  MaybeDecrementCount(E, RefsMinusAssignments);
8428 
8429  if (E->hasPlaceholderType()) {
8430  ExprResult result = CheckPlaceholderExpr(E);
8431  if (result.isInvalid()) return E;
8432  E = result.get();
8433  }
8434 
8435  if (getLangOpts().CPlusPlus) {
8436  // The C++11 standard defines the notion of a discarded-value expression;
8437  // normally, we don't need to do anything to handle it, but if it is a
8438  // volatile lvalue with a special form, we perform an lvalue-to-rvalue
8439  // conversion.
8440  if (getLangOpts().CPlusPlus11 && E->isReadIfDiscardedInCPlusPlus11()) {
8441  ExprResult Res = DefaultLvalueConversion(E);
8442  if (Res.isInvalid())
8443  return E;
8444  E = Res.get();
8445  } else {
8446  // Per C++2a [expr.ass]p5, a volatile assignment is not deprecated if
8447  // it occurs as a discarded-value expression.
8448  CheckUnusedVolatileAssignment(E);
8449  }
8450 
8451  // C++1z:
8452  // If the expression is a prvalue after this optional conversion, the
8453  // temporary materialization conversion is applied.
8454  //
8455  // We do not materialize temporaries by default in order to avoid creating
8456  // unnecessary temporary objects. If we skip this step, IR generation is
8457  // able to synthesize the storage for itself in the aggregate case, and
8458  // adding the extra node to the AST is just clutter.
8459  if (isInLifetimeExtendingContext() && getLangOpts().CPlusPlus17 &&
8460  E->isPRValue() && !E->getType()->isVoidType()) {
8461  ExprResult Res = TemporaryMaterializationConversion(E);
8462  if (Res.isInvalid())
8463  return E;
8464  E = Res.get();
8465  }
8466  return E;
8467  }
8468 
8469  // C99 6.3.2.1:
8470  // [Except in specific positions,] an lvalue that does not have
8471  // array type is converted to the value stored in the
8472  // designated object (and is no longer an lvalue).
8473  if (E->isPRValue()) {
8474  // In C, function designators (i.e. expressions of function type)
8475  // are r-values, but we still want to do function-to-pointer decay
8476  // on them. This is both technically correct and convenient for
8477  // some clients.
8478  if (!getLangOpts().CPlusPlus && E->getType()->isFunctionType())
8479  return DefaultFunctionArrayConversion(E);
8480 
8481  return E;
8482  }
8483 
8484  // GCC seems to also exclude expressions of incomplete enum type.
8485  if (const EnumType *T = E->getType()->getAs<EnumType>()) {
8486  if (!T->getDecl()->isComplete()) {
8487  // FIXME: stupid workaround for a codegen bug!
8488  E = ImpCastExprToType(E, Context.VoidTy, CK_ToVoid).get();
8489  return E;
8490  }
8491  }
8492 
8493  ExprResult Res = DefaultFunctionArrayLvalueConversion(E);
8494  if (Res.isInvalid())
8495  return E;
8496  E = Res.get();
8497 
8498  if (!E->getType()->isVoidType())
8499  RequireCompleteType(E->getExprLoc(), E->getType(),
8500  diag::err_incomplete_type);
8501  return E;
8502 }
8503 
8504 ExprResult Sema::CheckUnevaluatedOperand(Expr *E) {
8505  // Per C++2a [expr.ass]p5, a volatile assignment is not deprecated if
8506  // it occurs as an unevaluated operand.
8507  CheckUnusedVolatileAssignment(E);
8508 
8509  return E;
8510 }
8511 
8512 // If we can unambiguously determine whether Var can never be used
8513 // in a constant expression, return true.
8514 // - if the variable and its initializer are non-dependent, then
8515 // we can unambiguously check if the variable is a constant expression.
8516 // - if the initializer is not value dependent - we can determine whether
8517 // it can be used to initialize a constant expression. If Init can not
8518 // be used to initialize a constant expression we conclude that Var can
8519 // never be a constant expression.
8520 // - FXIME: if the initializer is dependent, we can still do some analysis and
8521 // identify certain cases unambiguously as non-const by using a Visitor:
8522 // - such as those that involve odr-use of a ParmVarDecl, involve a new
8523 // delete, lambda-expr, dynamic-cast, reinterpret-cast etc...
8524 static inline bool VariableCanNeverBeAConstantExpression(VarDecl *Var,
8525  ASTContext &Context) {
8526  if (isa<ParmVarDecl>(Var)) return true;
8527  const VarDecl *DefVD = nullptr;
8528 
8529  // If there is no initializer - this can not be a constant expression.
8530  const Expr *Init = Var->getAnyInitializer(DefVD);
8531  if (!Init)
8532  return true;
8533  assert(DefVD);
8534  if (DefVD->isWeak())
8535  return false;
8536 
8537  if (Var->getType()->isDependentType() || Init->isValueDependent()) {
8538  // FIXME: Teach the constant evaluator to deal with the non-dependent parts
8539  // of value-dependent expressions, and use it here to determine whether the
8540  // initializer is a potential constant expression.
8541  return false;
8542  }
8543 
8544  return !Var->isUsableInConstantExpressions(Context);
8545 }
8546 
8547 /// Check if the current lambda has any potential captures
8548 /// that must be captured by any of its enclosing lambdas that are ready to
8549 /// capture. If there is a lambda that can capture a nested
8550 /// potential-capture, go ahead and do so. Also, check to see if any
8551 /// variables are uncaptureable or do not involve an odr-use so do not
8552 /// need to be captured.
8553 
8554 static void CheckIfAnyEnclosingLambdasMustCaptureAnyPotentialCaptures(
8555  Expr *const FE, LambdaScopeInfo *const CurrentLSI, Sema &S) {
8556 
8557  assert(!S.isUnevaluatedContext());
8558  assert(S.CurContext->isDependentContext());
8559 #ifndef NDEBUG
8560  DeclContext *DC = S.CurContext;
8561  while (DC && isa<CapturedDecl>(DC))
8562  DC = DC->getParent();
8563  assert(
8564  CurrentLSI->CallOperator == DC &&
8565  "The current call operator must be synchronized with Sema's CurContext");
8566 #endif // NDEBUG
8567 
8568  const bool IsFullExprInstantiationDependent = FE->isInstantiationDependent();
8569 
8570  // All the potentially captureable variables in the current nested
8571  // lambda (within a generic outer lambda), must be captured by an
8572  // outer lambda that is enclosed within a non-dependent context.
8573  CurrentLSI->visitPotentialCaptures([&](ValueDecl *Var, Expr *VarExpr) {
8574  // If the variable is clearly identified as non-odr-used and the full
8575  // expression is not instantiation dependent, only then do we not
8576  // need to check enclosing lambda's for speculative captures.
8577  // For e.g.:
8578  // Even though 'x' is not odr-used, it should be captured.
8579  // int test() {
8580  // const int x = 10;
8581  // auto L = [=](auto a) {
8582  // (void) +x + a;
8583  // };
8584  // }
8585  if (CurrentLSI->isVariableExprMarkedAsNonODRUsed(VarExpr) &&
8586  !IsFullExprInstantiationDependent)
8587  return;
8588 
8589  VarDecl *UnderlyingVar = Var->getPotentiallyDecomposedVarDecl();
8590  if (!UnderlyingVar)
8591  return;
8592 
8593  // If we have a capture-capable lambda for the variable, go ahead and
8594  // capture the variable in that lambda (and all its enclosing lambdas).
8595  if (const std::optional<unsigned> Index =
8596  getStackIndexOfNearestEnclosingCaptureCapableLambda(
8597  S.FunctionScopes, Var, S))
8598  S.MarkCaptureUsedInEnclosingContext(Var, VarExpr->getExprLoc(), *Index);
8599  const bool IsVarNeverAConstantExpression =
8600  VariableCanNeverBeAConstantExpression(UnderlyingVar, S.Context);
8601  if (!IsFullExprInstantiationDependent || IsVarNeverAConstantExpression) {
8602  // This full expression is not instantiation dependent or the variable
8603  // can not be used in a constant expression - which means
8604  // this variable must be odr-used here, so diagnose a
8605  // capture violation early, if the variable is un-captureable.
8606  // This is purely for diagnosing errors early. Otherwise, this
8607  // error would get diagnosed when the lambda becomes capture ready.
8608  QualType CaptureType, DeclRefType;
8609  SourceLocation ExprLoc = VarExpr->getExprLoc();
8610  if (S.tryCaptureVariable(Var, ExprLoc, S.TryCapture_Implicit,
8611  /*EllipsisLoc*/ SourceLocation(),
8612  /*BuildAndDiagnose*/false, CaptureType,
8613  DeclRefType, nullptr)) {
8614  // We will never be able to capture this variable, and we need
8615  // to be able to in any and all instantiations, so diagnose it.
8616  S.tryCaptureVariable(Var, ExprLoc, S.TryCapture_Implicit,
8617  /*EllipsisLoc*/ SourceLocation(),
8618  /*BuildAndDiagnose*/true, CaptureType,
8619  DeclRefType, nullptr);
8620  }
8621  }
8622  });
8623 
8624  // Check if 'this' needs to be captured.
8625  if (CurrentLSI->hasPotentialThisCapture()) {
8626  // If we have a capture-capable lambda for 'this', go ahead and capture
8627  // 'this' in that lambda (and all its enclosing lambdas).
8628  if (const std::optional<unsigned> Index =
8629  getStackIndexOfNearestEnclosingCaptureCapableLambda(
8630  S.FunctionScopes, /*0 is 'this'*/ nullptr, S)) {
8631  const unsigned FunctionScopeIndexOfCapturableLambda = *Index;
8632  S.CheckCXXThisCapture(CurrentLSI->PotentialThisCaptureLocation,
8633  /*Explicit*/ false, /*BuildAndDiagnose*/ true,
8634  &FunctionScopeIndexOfCapturableLambda);
8635  }
8636  }
8637 
8638  // Reset all the potential captures at the end of each full-expression.
8639  CurrentLSI->clearPotentialCaptures();
8640 }
8641 
8642 static ExprResult attemptRecovery(Sema &SemaRef,
8643  const TypoCorrectionConsumer &Consumer,
8644  const TypoCorrection &TC) {
8645  LookupResult R(SemaRef, Consumer.getLookupResult().getLookupNameInfo(),
8646  Consumer.getLookupResult().getLookupKind());
8647  const CXXScopeSpec *SS = Consumer.getSS();
8648  CXXScopeSpec NewSS;
8649 
8650  // Use an approprate CXXScopeSpec for building the expr.
8651  if (auto *NNS = TC.getCorrectionSpecifier())
8652  NewSS.MakeTrivial(SemaRef.Context, NNS, TC.getCorrectionRange());
8653  else if (SS && !TC.WillReplaceSpecifier())
8654  NewSS = *SS;
8655 
8656  if (auto *ND = TC.getFoundDecl()) {
8657  R.setLookupName(ND->getDeclName());
8658  R.addDecl(ND);
8659  if (ND->isCXXClassMember()) {
8660  // Figure out the correct naming class to add to the LookupResult.
8661  CXXRecordDecl *Record = nullptr;
8662  if (auto *NNS = TC.getCorrectionSpecifier())
8663  Record = NNS->getAsType()->getAsCXXRecordDecl();
8664  if (!Record)
8665  Record =
8666  dyn_cast<CXXRecordDecl>(ND->getDeclContext()->getRedeclContext());
8667  if (Record)
8668  R.setNamingClass(Record);
8669 
8670  // Detect and handle the case where the decl might be an implicit
8671  // member.
8672  if (SemaRef.isPotentialImplicitMemberAccess(
8673  NewSS, R, Consumer.isAddressOfOperand()))
8674  return SemaRef.BuildPossibleImplicitMemberExpr(
8675  NewSS, /*TemplateKWLoc*/ SourceLocation(), R,
8676  /*TemplateArgs*/ nullptr, /*S*/ nullptr);
8677  } else if (auto *Ivar = dyn_cast<ObjCIvarDecl>(ND)) {
8678  return SemaRef.LookupInObjCMethod(R, Consumer.getScope(),
8679  Ivar->getIdentifier());
8680  }
8681  }
8682 
8683  return SemaRef.BuildDeclarationNameExpr(NewSS, R, /*NeedsADL*/ false,
8684  /*AcceptInvalidDecl*/ true);
8685 }
8686 
8687 namespace {
8688 class FindTypoExprs : public RecursiveASTVisitor<FindTypoExprs> {
8689  llvm::SmallSetVector<TypoExpr *, 2> &TypoExprs;
8690 
8691 public:
8692  explicit FindTypoExprs(llvm::SmallSetVector<TypoExpr *, 2> &TypoExprs)
8693  : TypoExprs(TypoExprs) {}
8694  bool VisitTypoExpr(TypoExpr *TE) {
8695  TypoExprs.insert(TE);
8696  return true;
8697  }
8698 };
8699 
8700 class TransformTypos : public TreeTransform<TransformTypos> {
8701  typedef TreeTransform<TransformTypos> BaseTransform;
8702 
8703  VarDecl *InitDecl; // A decl to avoid as a correction because it is in the
8704  // process of being initialized.
8705  llvm::function_ref<ExprResult(Expr *)> ExprFilter;
8706  llvm::SmallSetVector<TypoExpr *, 2> TypoExprs, AmbiguousTypoExprs;
8707  llvm::SmallDenseMap<TypoExpr *, ExprResult, 2> TransformCache;
8708  llvm::SmallDenseMap<OverloadExpr *, Expr *, 4> OverloadResolution;
8709 
8710  /// Emit diagnostics for all of the TypoExprs encountered.
8711  ///
8712  /// If the TypoExprs were successfully corrected, then the diagnostics should
8713  /// suggest the corrections. Otherwise the diagnostics will not suggest
8714  /// anything (having been passed an empty TypoCorrection).
8715  ///
8716  /// If we've failed to correct due to ambiguous corrections, we need to
8717  /// be sure to pass empty corrections and replacements. Otherwise it's
8718  /// possible that the Consumer has a TypoCorrection that failed to ambiguity
8719  /// and we don't want to report those diagnostics.
8720  void EmitAllDiagnostics(bool IsAmbiguous) {
8721  for (TypoExpr *TE : TypoExprs) {
8722  auto &State = SemaRef.getTypoExprState(TE);
8723  if (State.DiagHandler) {
8724  TypoCorrection TC = IsAmbiguous
8725  ? TypoCorrection() : State.Consumer->getCurrentCorrection();
8726  ExprResult Replacement = IsAmbiguous ? ExprError() : TransformCache[TE];
8727 
8728  // Extract the NamedDecl from the transformed TypoExpr and add it to the
8729  // TypoCorrection, replacing the existing decls. This ensures the right
8730  // NamedDecl is used in diagnostics e.g. in the case where overload
8731  // resolution was used to select one from several possible decls that
8732  // had been stored in the TypoCorrection.
8733  if (auto *ND = getDeclFromExpr(
8734  Replacement.isInvalid() ? nullptr : Replacement.get()))
8735  TC.setCorrectionDecl(ND);
8736 
8737  State.DiagHandler(TC);
8738  }
8739  SemaRef.clearDelayedTypo(TE);
8740  }
8741  }
8742 
8743  /// Try to advance the typo correction state of the first unfinished TypoExpr.
8744  /// We allow advancement of the correction stream by removing it from the
8745  /// TransformCache which allows `TransformTypoExpr` to advance during the
8746  /// next transformation attempt.
8747  ///
8748  /// Any substitution attempts for the previous TypoExprs (which must have been
8749  /// finished) will need to be retried since it's possible that they will now
8750  /// be invalid given the latest advancement.
8751  ///
8752  /// We need to be sure that we're making progress - it's possible that the
8753  /// tree is so malformed that the transform never makes it to the
8754  /// `TransformTypoExpr`.
8755  ///
8756  /// Returns true if there are any untried correction combinations.
8757  bool CheckAndAdvanceTypoExprCorrectionStreams() {
8758  for (auto *TE : TypoExprs) {
8759  auto &State = SemaRef.getTypoExprState(TE);
8760  TransformCache.erase(TE);
8761  if (!State.Consumer->hasMadeAnyCorrectionProgress())
8762  return false;
8763  if (!State.Consumer->finished())
8764  return true;
8765  State.Consumer->resetCorrectionStream();
8766  }
8767  return false;
8768  }
8769 
8770  NamedDecl *getDeclFromExpr(Expr *E) {
8771  if (auto *OE = dyn_cast_or_null<OverloadExpr>(E))
8772  E = OverloadResolution[OE];
8773 
8774  if (!E)
8775  return nullptr;
8776  if (auto *DRE = dyn_cast<DeclRefExpr>(E))
8777  return DRE->getFoundDecl();
8778  if (auto *ME = dyn_cast<MemberExpr>(E))
8779  return ME->getFoundDecl();
8780  // FIXME: Add any other expr types that could be seen by the delayed typo
8781  // correction TreeTransform for which the corresponding TypoCorrection could
8782  // contain multiple decls.
8783  return nullptr;
8784  }
8785 
8786  ExprResult TryTransform(Expr *E) {
8787  Sema::SFINAETrap Trap(SemaRef);
8788  ExprResult Res = TransformExpr(E);
8789  if (Trap.hasErrorOccurred() || Res.isInvalid())
8790  return ExprError();
8791 
8792  return ExprFilter(Res.get());
8793  }
8794 
8795  // Since correcting typos may intoduce new TypoExprs, this function
8796  // checks for new TypoExprs and recurses if it finds any. Note that it will
8797  // only succeed if it is able to correct all typos in the given expression.
8798  ExprResult CheckForRecursiveTypos(ExprResult Res, bool &IsAmbiguous) {
8799  if (Res.isInvalid()) {
8800  return Res;
8801  }
8802  // Check to see if any new TypoExprs were created. If so, we need to recurse
8803  // to check their validity.
8804  Expr *FixedExpr = Res.get();
8805 
8806  auto SavedTypoExprs = std::move(TypoExprs);
8807  auto SavedAmbiguousTypoExprs = std::move(AmbiguousTypoExprs);
8808  TypoExprs.clear();
8809  AmbiguousTypoExprs.clear();
8810 
8811  FindTypoExprs(TypoExprs).TraverseStmt(FixedExpr);
8812  if (!TypoExprs.empty()) {
8813  // Recurse to handle newly created TypoExprs. If we're not able to
8814  // handle them, discard these TypoExprs.
8815  ExprResult RecurResult =
8816  RecursiveTransformLoop(FixedExpr, IsAmbiguous);
8817  if (RecurResult.isInvalid()) {
8818  Res = ExprError();
8819  // Recursive corrections didn't work, wipe them away and don't add
8820  // them to the TypoExprs set. Remove them from Sema's TypoExpr list
8821  // since we don't want to clear them twice. Note: it's possible the
8822  // TypoExprs were created recursively and thus won't be in our
8823  // Sema's TypoExprs - they were created in our `RecursiveTransformLoop`.
8824  auto &SemaTypoExprs = SemaRef.TypoExprs;
8825  for (auto *TE : TypoExprs) {
8826  TransformCache.erase(TE);
8827  SemaRef.clearDelayedTypo(TE);
8828 
8829  auto SI = find(SemaTypoExprs, TE);
8830  if (SI != SemaTypoExprs.end()) {
8831  SemaTypoExprs.erase(SI);
8832  }
8833  }
8834  } else {
8835  // TypoExpr is valid: add newly created TypoExprs since we were
8836  // able to correct them.
8837  Res = RecurResult;
8838  SavedTypoExprs.set_union(TypoExprs);
8839  }
8840  }
8841 
8842  TypoExprs = std::move(SavedTypoExprs);
8843  AmbiguousTypoExprs = std::move(SavedAmbiguousTypoExprs);
8844 
8845  return Res;
8846  }
8847 
8848  // Try to transform the given expression, looping through the correction
8849  // candidates with `CheckAndAdvanceTypoExprCorrectionStreams`.
8850  //
8851  // If valid ambiguous typo corrections are seen, `IsAmbiguous` is set to
8852  // true and this method immediately will return an `ExprError`.
8853  ExprResult RecursiveTransformLoop(Expr *E, bool &IsAmbiguous) {
8854  ExprResult Res;
8855  auto SavedTypoExprs = std::move(SemaRef.TypoExprs);
8856  SemaRef.TypoExprs.clear();
8857 
8858  while (true) {
8859  Res = CheckForRecursiveTypos(TryTransform(E), IsAmbiguous);
8860 
8861  // Recursion encountered an ambiguous correction. This means that our
8862  // correction itself is ambiguous, so stop now.
8863  if (IsAmbiguous)
8864  break;
8865 
8866  // If the transform is still valid after checking for any new typos,
8867  // it's good to go.
8868  if (!Res.isInvalid())
8869  break;
8870 
8871  // The transform was invalid, see if we have any TypoExprs with untried
8872  // correction candidates.
8873  if (!CheckAndAdvanceTypoExprCorrectionStreams())
8874  break;
8875  }
8876 
8877  // If we found a valid result, double check to make sure it's not ambiguous.
8878  if (!IsAmbiguous && !Res.isInvalid() && !AmbiguousTypoExprs.empty()) {
8879  auto SavedTransformCache =
8880  llvm::SmallDenseMap<TypoExpr *, ExprResult, 2>(TransformCache);
8881 
8882  // Ensure none of the TypoExprs have multiple typo correction candidates
8883  // with the same edit length that pass all the checks and filters.
8884  while (!AmbiguousTypoExprs.empty()) {
8885  auto TE = AmbiguousTypoExprs.back();
8886 
8887  // TryTransform itself can create new Typos, adding them to the TypoExpr map
8888  // and invalidating our TypoExprState, so always fetch it instead of storing.
8889  SemaRef.getTypoExprState(TE).Consumer->saveCurrentPosition();
8890 
8891  TypoCorrection TC = SemaRef.getTypoExprState(TE).Consumer->peekNextCorrection();
8892  TypoCorrection Next;
8893  do {
8894  // Fetch the next correction by erasing the typo from the cache and calling
8895  // `TryTransform` which will iterate through corrections in
8896  // `TransformTypoExpr`.
8897  TransformCache.erase(TE);
8898  ExprResult AmbigRes = CheckForRecursiveTypos(TryTransform(E), IsAmbiguous);
8899 
8900  if (!AmbigRes.isInvalid() || IsAmbiguous) {
8901  SemaRef.getTypoExprState(TE).Consumer->resetCorrectionStream();
8902  SavedTransformCache.erase(TE);
8903  Res = ExprError();
8904  IsAmbiguous = true;
8905  break;
8906  }
8907  } while ((Next = SemaRef.getTypoExprState(TE).Consumer->peekNextCorrection()) &&
8908  Next.getEditDistance(false) == TC.getEditDistance(false));
8909 
8910  if (IsAmbiguous)
8911  break;
8912 
8913  AmbiguousTypoExprs.remove(TE);
8914  SemaRef.getTypoExprState(TE).Consumer->restoreSavedPosition();
8915  TransformCache[TE] = SavedTransformCache[TE];
8916  }
8917  TransformCache = std::move(SavedTransformCache);
8918  }
8919 
8920  // Wipe away any newly created TypoExprs that we don't know about. Since we
8921  // clear any invalid TypoExprs in `CheckForRecursiveTypos`, this is only
8922  // possible if a `TypoExpr` is created during a transformation but then
8923  // fails before we can discover it.
8924  auto &SemaTypoExprs = SemaRef.TypoExprs;
8925  for (auto Iterator = SemaTypoExprs.begin(); Iterator != SemaTypoExprs.end();) {
8926  auto TE = *Iterator;
8927  auto FI = find(TypoExprs, TE);
8928  if (FI != TypoExprs.end()) {
8929  Iterator++;
8930  continue;
8931  }
8932  SemaRef.clearDelayedTypo(TE);
8933  Iterator = SemaTypoExprs.erase(Iterator);
8934  }
8935  SemaRef.TypoExprs = std::move(SavedTypoExprs);
8936 
8937  return Res;
8938  }
8939 
8940 public:
8941  TransformTypos(Sema &SemaRef, VarDecl *InitDecl, llvm::function_ref<ExprResult(Expr *)> Filter)
8942  : BaseTransform(SemaRef), InitDecl(InitDecl), ExprFilter(Filter) {}
8943 
8944  ExprResult RebuildCallExpr(Expr *Callee, SourceLocation LParenLoc,
8945  MultiExprArg Args,
8946  SourceLocation RParenLoc,
8947  Expr *ExecConfig = nullptr) {
8948  auto Result = BaseTransform::RebuildCallExpr(Callee, LParenLoc, Args,
8949  RParenLoc, ExecConfig);
8950  if (auto *OE = dyn_cast<OverloadExpr>(Callee)) {
8951  if (Result.isUsable()) {
8952  Expr *ResultCall = Result.get();
8953  if (auto *BE = dyn_cast<CXXBindTemporaryExpr>(ResultCall))
8954  ResultCall = BE->getSubExpr();
8955  if (auto *CE = dyn_cast<CallExpr>(ResultCall))
8956  OverloadResolution[OE] = CE->getCallee();
8957  }
8958  }
8959  return Result;
8960  }
8961 
8962  ExprResult TransformLambdaExpr(LambdaExpr *E) { return Owned(E); }
8963 
8964  ExprResult TransformBlockExpr(BlockExpr *E) { return Owned(E); }
8965 
8966  ExprResult Transform(Expr *E) {
8967  bool IsAmbiguous = false;
8968  ExprResult Res = RecursiveTransformLoop(E, IsAmbiguous);
8969 
8970  if (!Res.isUsable())
8971  FindTypoExprs(TypoExprs).TraverseStmt(E);
8972 
8973  EmitAllDiagnostics(IsAmbiguous);
8974 
8975  return Res;
8976  }
8977 
8978  ExprResult TransformTypoExpr(TypoExpr *E) {
8979  // If the TypoExpr hasn't been seen before, record it. Otherwise, return the
8980  // cached transformation result if there is one and the TypoExpr isn't the
8981  // first one that was encountered.
8982  auto &CacheEntry = TransformCache[E];
8983  if (!TypoExprs.insert(E) && !CacheEntry.isUnset()) {
8984  return CacheEntry;
8985  }
8986 
8987  auto &State = SemaRef.getTypoExprState(E);
8988  assert(State.Consumer && "Cannot transform a cleared TypoExpr");
8989 
8990  // For the first TypoExpr and an uncached TypoExpr, find the next likely
8991  // typo correction and return it.
8992  while (TypoCorrection TC = State.Consumer->getNextCorrection()) {
8993  if (InitDecl && TC.getFoundDecl() == InitDecl)
8994  continue;
8995  // FIXME: If we would typo-correct to an invalid declaration, it's
8996  // probably best to just suppress all errors from this typo correction.
8997  ExprResult NE = State.RecoveryHandler ?
8998  State.RecoveryHandler(SemaRef, E, TC) :
8999  attemptRecovery(SemaRef, *State.Consumer, TC);
9000  if (!NE.isInvalid()) {
9001  // Check whether there may be a second viable correction with the same
9002  // edit distance; if so, remember this TypoExpr may have an ambiguous
9003  // correction so it can be more thoroughly vetted later.
9004  TypoCorrection Next;
9005  if ((Next = State.Consumer->peekNextCorrection()) &&
9006  Next.getEditDistance(false) == TC.getEditDistance(false)) {
9007  AmbiguousTypoExprs.insert(E);
9008  } else {
9009  AmbiguousTypoExprs.remove(E);
9010  }
9011  assert(!NE.isUnset() &&
9012  "Typo was transformed into a valid-but-null ExprResult");
9013  return CacheEntry = NE;
9014  }
9015  }
9016  return CacheEntry = ExprError();
9017  }
9018 };
9019 }
9020 
9021 ExprResult
9022 Sema::CorrectDelayedTyposInExpr(Expr *E, VarDecl *InitDecl,
9023  bool RecoverUncorrectedTypos,
9024  llvm::function_ref<ExprResult(Expr *)> Filter) {
9025  // If the current evaluation context indicates there are uncorrected typos
9026  // and the current expression isn't guaranteed to not have typos, try to
9027  // resolve any TypoExpr nodes that might be in the expression.
9028  if (E && !ExprEvalContexts.empty() && ExprEvalContexts.back().NumTypos &&
9029  (E->isTypeDependent() || E->isValueDependent() ||
9030  E->isInstantiationDependent())) {
9031  auto TyposResolved = DelayedTypos.size();
9032  auto Result = TransformTypos(*this, InitDecl, Filter).Transform(E);
9033  TyposResolved -= DelayedTypos.size();
9034  if (Result.isInvalid() || Result.get() != E) {
9035  ExprEvalContexts.back().NumTypos -= TyposResolved;
9036  if (Result.isInvalid() && RecoverUncorrectedTypos) {
9037  struct TyposReplace : TreeTransform<TyposReplace> {
9038  TyposReplace(Sema &SemaRef) : TreeTransform(SemaRef) {}
9039  ExprResult TransformTypoExpr(clang::TypoExpr *E) {
9040  return this->SemaRef.CreateRecoveryExpr(E->getBeginLoc(),
9041  E->getEndLoc(), {});
9042  }
9043  } TT(*this);
9044  return TT.TransformExpr(E);
9045  }
9046  return Result;
9047  }
9048  assert(TyposResolved == 0 && "Corrected typo but got same Expr back?");
9049  }
9050  return E;
9051 }
9052 
9053 ExprResult Sema::ActOnFinishFullExpr(Expr *FE, SourceLocation CC,
9054  bool DiscardedValue, bool IsConstexpr,
9055  bool IsTemplateArgument) {
9056  ExprResult FullExpr = FE;
9057 
9058  if (!FullExpr.get())
9059  return ExprError();
9060 
9061  if (!IsTemplateArgument && DiagnoseUnexpandedParameterPack(FullExpr.get()))
9062  return ExprError();
9063 
9064  if (DiscardedValue) {
9065  // Top-level expressions default to 'id' when we're in a debugger.
9066  if (getLangOpts().DebuggerCastResultToId &&
9067  FullExpr.get()->getType() == Context.UnknownAnyTy) {
9068  FullExpr = forceUnknownAnyToType(FullExpr.get(), Context.getObjCIdType());
9069  if (FullExpr.isInvalid())
9070  return ExprError();
9071  }
9072 
9073  FullExpr = CheckPlaceholderExpr(FullExpr.get());
9074  if (FullExpr.isInvalid())
9075  return ExprError();
9076 
9077  FullExpr = IgnoredValueConversions(FullExpr.get());
9078  if (FullExpr.isInvalid())
9079  return ExprError();
9080 
9081  DiagnoseUnusedExprResult(FullExpr.get(), diag::warn_unused_expr);
9082  }
9083 
9084  FullExpr = CorrectDelayedTyposInExpr(FullExpr.get(), /*InitDecl=*/nullptr,
9085  /*RecoverUncorrectedTypos=*/true);
9086  if (FullExpr.isInvalid())
9087  return ExprError();
9088 
9089  CheckCompletedExpr(FullExpr.get(), CC, IsConstexpr);
9090 
9091  // At the end of this full expression (which could be a deeply nested
9092  // lambda), if there is a potential capture within the nested lambda,
9093  // have the outer capture-able lambda try and capture it.
9094  // Consider the following code:
9095  // void f(int, int);
9096  // void f(const int&, double);
9097  // void foo() {
9098  // const int x = 10, y = 20;
9099  // auto L = [=](auto a) {
9100  // auto M = [=](auto b) {
9101  // f(x, b); <-- requires x to be captured by L and M
9102  // f(y, a); <-- requires y to be captured by L, but not all Ms
9103  // };
9104  // };
9105  // }
9106 
9107  // FIXME: Also consider what happens for something like this that involves
9108  // the gnu-extension statement-expressions or even lambda-init-captures:
9109  // void f() {
9110  // const int n = 0;
9111  // auto L = [&](auto a) {
9112  // +n + ({ 0; a; });
9113  // };
9114  // }
9115  //
9116  // Here, we see +n, and then the full-expression 0; ends, so we don't
9117  // capture n (and instead remove it from our list of potential captures),
9118  // and then the full-expression +n + ({ 0; }); ends, but it's too late
9119  // for us to see that we need to capture n after all.
9120 
9121  LambdaScopeInfo *const CurrentLSI =
9122  getCurLambda(/*IgnoreCapturedRegions=*/true);
9123  // FIXME: PR 17877 showed that getCurLambda() can return a valid pointer
9124  // even if CurContext is not a lambda call operator. Refer to that Bug Report
9125  // for an example of the code that might cause this asynchrony.
9126  // By ensuring we are in the context of a lambda's call operator
9127  // we can fix the bug (we only need to check whether we need to capture
9128  // if we are within a lambda's body); but per the comments in that
9129  // PR, a proper fix would entail :
9130  // "Alternative suggestion:
9131  // - Add to Sema an integer holding the smallest (outermost) scope
9132  // index that we are *lexically* within, and save/restore/set to
9133  // FunctionScopes.size() in InstantiatingTemplate's
9134  // constructor/destructor.
9135  // - Teach the handful of places that iterate over FunctionScopes to
9136  // stop at the outermost enclosing lexical scope."
9137  DeclContext *DC = CurContext;
9138  while (DC && isa<CapturedDecl>(DC))
9139  DC = DC->getParent();
9140  const bool IsInLambdaDeclContext = isLambdaCallOperator(DC);
9141  if (IsInLambdaDeclContext && CurrentLSI &&
9142  CurrentLSI->hasPotentialCaptures() && !FullExpr.isInvalid())
9143  CheckIfAnyEnclosingLambdasMustCaptureAnyPotentialCaptures(FE, CurrentLSI,
9144  *this);
9145  return MaybeCreateExprWithCleanups(FullExpr);
9146 }
9147 
9148 StmtResult Sema::ActOnFinishFullStmt(Stmt *FullStmt) {
9149  if (!FullStmt) return StmtError();
9150 
9151  return MaybeCreateStmtWithCleanups(FullStmt);
9152 }

9154 Sema::IfExistsResult
9155 Sema::CheckMicrosoftIfExistsSymbol(Scope *S,
9156  CXXScopeSpec &SS,
9157  const DeclarationNameInfo &TargetNameInfo) {
9158  DeclarationName TargetName = TargetNameInfo.getName();
9159  if (!TargetName)
9160  return IER_DoesNotExist;
9161 
9162  // If the name itself is dependent, then the result is dependent.
9163  if (TargetName.isDependentName())
9164  return IER_Dependent;
9165 
9166  // Do the redeclaration lookup in the current scope.
9167  LookupResult R(*this, TargetNameInfo, Sema::LookupAnyName,
9168  RedeclarationKind::NotForRedeclaration);
9169  LookupParsedName(R, S, &SS);
9170  R.suppressDiagnostics();
9171 
9172  switch (R.getResultKind()) {
9173  case LookupResult::Found:
9174  case LookupResult::FoundOverloaded:
9175  case LookupResult::FoundUnresolvedValue:
9176  case LookupResult::Ambiguous:
9177  return IER_Exists;
9178 
9179  case LookupResult::NotFound:
9180  return IER_DoesNotExist;
9181 
9182  case LookupResult::NotFoundInCurrentInstantiation:
9183  return IER_Dependent;
9184  }
9185 
9186  llvm_unreachable("Invalid LookupResult Kind!");
9187 }
9188 
9189 Sema::IfExistsResult
9190 Sema::CheckMicrosoftIfExistsSymbol(Scope *S, SourceLocation KeywordLoc,
9191  bool IsIfExists, CXXScopeSpec &SS,
9192  UnqualifiedId &Name) {
9193  DeclarationNameInfo TargetNameInfo = GetNameFromUnqualifiedId(Name);
9194 
9195  // Check for an unexpanded parameter pack.
9196  auto UPPC = IsIfExists ? UPPC_IfExists : UPPC_IfNotExists;
9197  if (DiagnoseUnexpandedParameterPack(SS, UPPC) ||
9198  DiagnoseUnexpandedParameterPack(TargetNameInfo, UPPC))
9199  return IER_Error;
9200 
9201  return CheckMicrosoftIfExistsSymbol(S, SS, TargetNameInfo);
9202 }

9210 concepts::Requirement *Sema::ActOnTypeRequirement(
9211  SourceLocation TypenameKWLoc, CXXScopeSpec &SS, SourceLocation NameLoc,
9212  const IdentifierInfo *TypeName, TemplateIdAnnotation *TemplateId) {
9213  assert(((!TypeName && TemplateId) || (TypeName && !TemplateId)) &&
9214  "Exactly one of TypeName and TemplateId must be specified.");
9215  TypeSourceInfo *TSI = nullptr;
9216  if (TypeName) {
9217  QualType T =
9218  CheckTypenameType(ElaboratedTypeKeyword::Typename, TypenameKWLoc,
9219  SS.getWithLocInContext(Context), *TypeName, NameLoc,
9220  &TSI, /*DeducedTSTContext=*/false);
9221  if (T.isNull())
9222  return nullptr;
9223  } else {
9224  ASTTemplateArgsPtr ArgsPtr(TemplateId->getTemplateArgs(),
9225  TemplateId->NumArgs);
9226  TypeResult T = ActOnTypenameType(CurScope, TypenameKWLoc, SS,
9227  TemplateId->TemplateKWLoc,

9229  TemplateId->TemplateNameLoc,
9230  TemplateId->LAngleLoc, ArgsPtr,
9231  TemplateId->RAngleLoc);
9232  if (T.isInvalid())
9233  return nullptr;

9235  return nullptr;
9236  }
9237  return BuildTypeRequirement(TSI);

9245 
9246 concepts::Requirement *
9247 Sema::ActOnCompoundRequirement(
9248  Expr *E, SourceLocation NoexceptLoc, CXXScopeSpec &SS,
9249  TemplateIdAnnotation *TypeConstraint, unsigned Depth) {
9250  // C++2a [expr.prim.req.compound] p1.3.3
9251  // [..] the expression is deduced against an invented function template
9252  // F [...] F is a void function template with a single type template
9253  // parameter T declared with the constrained-parameter. Form a new
9254  // cv-qualifier-seq cv by taking the union of const and volatile specifiers
9255  // around the constrained-parameter. F has a single parameter whose
9256  // type-specifier is cv T followed by the abstract-declarator. [...]
9257  //
9258  // The cv part is done in the calling function - we get the concept with
9259  // arguments and the abstract declarator with the correct CV qualification and
9260  // have to synthesize T and the single parameter of F.
9261  auto &II = Context.Idents.get("expr-type");
9262  auto *TParam = TemplateTypeParmDecl::Create(Context, CurContext,
9263  SourceLocation(),
9264  SourceLocation(), Depth,
9265  /*Index=*/0, &II,
9266  /*Typename=*/true,
9267  /*ParameterPack=*/false,
9268  /*HasTypeConstraint=*/true);
9269 
9270  if (BuildTypeConstraint(SS, TypeConstraint, TParam,
9271  /*EllipsisLoc=*/SourceLocation(),
9272  /*AllowUnexpandedPack=*/true))
9273  // Just produce a requirement with no type requirements.
9274  return BuildExprRequirement(E, /*IsSimple=*/false, NoexceptLoc, {});
9275 
9276  auto *TPL = TemplateParameterList::Create(Context, SourceLocation(),
9277  SourceLocation(),
9278  ArrayRef<NamedDecl *>(TParam),
9279  SourceLocation(),
9280  /*RequiresClause=*/nullptr);
9281  return BuildExprRequirement(
9282  E, /*IsSimple=*/false, NoexceptLoc,
9283  concepts::ExprRequirement::ReturnTypeRequirement(TPL));
9284 }
9285 
9286 concepts::ExprRequirement *
9287 Sema::BuildExprRequirement(
9288  Expr *E, bool IsSimple, SourceLocation NoexceptLoc,
9289  concepts::ExprRequirement::ReturnTypeRequirement ReturnTypeRequirement) {
9290  auto Status = concepts::ExprRequirement::SS_Satisfied;
9291  ConceptSpecializationExpr *SubstitutedConstraintExpr = nullptr;
9292  if (E->isInstantiationDependent() || E->getType()->isPlaceholderType() ||
9293  ReturnTypeRequirement.isDependent())
9294  Status = concepts::ExprRequirement::SS_Dependent;
9295  else if (NoexceptLoc.isValid() && canThrow(E) == CanThrowResult::CT_Can)
9296  Status = concepts::ExprRequirement::SS_NoexceptNotMet;
9297  else if (ReturnTypeRequirement.isSubstitutionFailure())
9298  Status = concepts::ExprRequirement::SS_TypeRequirementSubstitutionFailure;
9299  else if (ReturnTypeRequirement.isTypeConstraint()) {
9300  // C++2a [expr.prim.req]p1.3.3
9301  // The immediately-declared constraint ([temp]) of decltype((E)) shall
9302  // be satisfied.
9303  TemplateParameterList *TPL =
9304  ReturnTypeRequirement.getTypeConstraintTemplateParameterList();
9305  QualType MatchedType =
9306  Context.getReferenceQualifiedType(E).getCanonicalType();
9307  llvm::SmallVector<TemplateArgument, 1> Args;
9308  Args.push_back(TemplateArgument(MatchedType));
9309 
9310  auto *Param = cast<TemplateTypeParmDecl>(TPL->getParam(0));
9311 
9312  MultiLevelTemplateArgumentList MLTAL(Param, Args, /*Final=*/false);
9313  MLTAL.addOuterRetainedLevels(TPL->getDepth());
9314  const TypeConstraint *TC = Param->getTypeConstraint();
9315  assert(TC && "Type Constraint cannot be null here");
9316  auto *IDC = TC->getImmediatelyDeclaredConstraint();
9317  assert(IDC && "ImmediatelyDeclaredConstraint can't be null here.");
9318  ExprResult Constraint = SubstExpr(IDC, MLTAL);
9319  if (Constraint.isInvalid()) {
9320  return new (Context) concepts::ExprRequirement(
9321  concepts::createSubstDiagAt(*this, IDC->getExprLoc(),
9322  [&](llvm::raw_ostream &OS) {
9323  IDC->printPretty(OS, /*Helper=*/nullptr,
9324  getPrintingPolicy());
9325  }),
9326  IsSimple, NoexceptLoc, ReturnTypeRequirement);
9327  }
9328  SubstitutedConstraintExpr =
9329  cast<ConceptSpecializationExpr>(Constraint.get());
9330  if (!SubstitutedConstraintExpr->isSatisfied())
9331  Status = concepts::ExprRequirement::SS_ConstraintsNotSatisfied;
9332  }
9333  return new (Context) concepts::ExprRequirement(E, IsSimple, NoexceptLoc,
9334  ReturnTypeRequirement, Status,
9335  SubstitutedConstraintExpr);
9336 }

9382 RequiresExprBodyDecl *
9383 Sema::ActOnStartRequiresExpr(SourceLocation RequiresKWLoc,
9384  ArrayRef<ParmVarDecl *> LocalParameters,
9385  Scope *BodyScope) {
9386  assert(BodyScope);
9387 
9388  RequiresExprBodyDecl *Body = RequiresExprBodyDecl::Create(Context, CurContext,
9389  RequiresKWLoc);
9390 
9391  PushDeclContext(BodyScope, Body);
9392 
9393  for (ParmVarDecl *Param : LocalParameters) {
9394  if (Param->hasDefaultArg())
9395  // C++2a [expr.prim.req] p4
9396  // [...] A local parameter of a requires-expression shall not have a
9397  // default argument. [...]
9398  Diag(Param->getDefaultArgRange().getBegin(),
9399  diag::err_requires_expr_local_parameter_default_argument);
9400  // Ignore default argument and move on
9401 
9402  Param->setDeclContext(Body);
9403  // If this has an identifier, add it to the scope stack.
9404  if (Param->getIdentifier()) {
9405  CheckShadow(BodyScope, Param);
9406  PushOnScopeChains(Param, BodyScope);
9407  }
9408  }
9409  return Body;
9410 }
